oman&quot;;\tmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\tmso-ansi-language:DE;\tmso-fareast-language:DE;\tfont-weight:bold;\tfont-style:italic;\tmso-bidi-font-style:normal;}@page Section1\t{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\tmargin:70.85pt 70.85pt 2.0cm 70.85pt;\tmso-header-margin:36.0pt;\tmso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\tmso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1\t{page:Section1;}--&gt;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;!--[if gte mso 10]&gt;&lt;style&gt;/* Style Definitions */table.MsoNormalTable{mso-style-name:&quot;Normale Tabelle&quot;;mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;mso-style-noshow:yes;mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;;mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;mso-para-margin:0cm;mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-pagination:widow-orphan;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-ansi-language:#0400;mso-fareast-language:#0400;mso-bidi-language:#0400;}&lt;/style&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;DE&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;DE&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser Architektur, F&amp;uuml;r ein natur- und menschengerechteres Bauen, K&amp;ouml;ln: Taschen, 2006, S. 212&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'courtesy Taschen', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-15 9:46:54.2088###object###text###1.3.2.13###ONION DOMES
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.3.2.13&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Rich and powerful and tasteful people always had towers.&lt;br&gt;But for a modern average person to have towers, even golden ones, that is new.&lt;br&gt;Architecture should elevate man, not humiliate, oppress and enslave him. &lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-114&quot;&gt; 114&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;A golden onion tower on your own house elevates the resident to the status of a king. &lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-114&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;114 &lt;/span&gt;The grey mass misery is over. The Golden Age das dawned.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', txt-'1.3.2.13', text_type-'1.3.2.13', text_category-'', text_title_en-'ONION DOMES', text_title_ge-'ZWIEBELT&Uuml;RME', text_contents_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Reiche und M&amp;auml;chtige hatten immer schon T&amp;uuml;rme. &lt;br /&gt;Da&amp;szlig; aber der moderne Durchschnittsmensch auch T&amp;uuml;rme, sogar vergoldet, haben kann, ist neu.&lt;br /&gt;Architektur soll den Menschen erh&amp;ouml;hen, nicht erniedrigen, unterdr&amp;uuml;cken und versklaven. &lt;br /&gt;Ein goldener Zwiebelturm am eigenen Haus erhebt den Bewohner in den Status eines K&amp;ouml;nigs. &lt;br /&gt;Die graue Massenmisere ist zu Ende. &lt;br /&gt;Das Goldene Zeitalter bricht an.&lt;br /&gt;Das Reich der Zwiebelt&amp;uuml;rme erstreckt sich seit der T&amp;uuml;rkenbelagerung Wiens von Bayern &amp;uuml;ber Ru&amp;szlig;land, Byzanz nach Indien.&lt;br /&gt;Nicht dazu geh&amp;ouml;ren die romanischen, skandinavischen, anglophonen L&amp;auml;nder und Amerika, genausowenig wie Japan, China, Afrika und Ozeanien.&lt;br /&gt;Wien geh&amp;ouml;rt zum gro&amp;szlig;en Reich der Zwiebelt&amp;uuml;rme. Der Goldgehalt der vergoldeten Zwiebelt&amp;uuml;rme entspricht dem eines Golddukaten.&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_keywords-'Architektur, architecture, Zwiebelturm, Zwiebelt&uuml;rme', text_date-'1985-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_occasion_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;Content-Type&quot; content=&quot;text/html; charset=utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;ProgId&quot; content=&quot;Word.Document&quot;&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;Generator&quot; content=&quot;Microsoft Word 11&quot;&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;Originator&quot; content=&quot;Microsoft Word 11&quot;&gt;&lt;link rel=&quot;File-List&quot; href=&quot;file:///C:\\\\DOKUME~1\\\\Andrea\\\\LOKALE~1\\\\Temp\\\\msohtml1\\\\12\\\\clip_filelist.xml&quot; /&gt;&lt;!--[if gte mso 9]&gt;&lt;xml&gt;&lt;w:WordDocument&gt;&lt;w:View&gt;Normal&lt;/w:View&gt;&lt;w:Zoom&gt;0&lt;/w:Zoom&gt;&lt;w:HyphenationZone&gt;21&lt;/w:HyphenationZone&gt;&lt;w:PunctuationKerning /&gt;&lt;w:ValidateAgainstSchemas /&gt;&lt;w:SaveIfXMLInvalid&gt;false&lt;/w:SaveIfXMLInvalid&gt;&lt;w:IgnoreMixedContent&gt;false&lt;/w:IgnoreMixedContent&gt;&lt;w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText&gt;false&lt;/w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText&gt;&lt;w:Compatibility&gt;&lt;w:BreakWrappedTables /&gt;&lt;w:SnapToGridInCell /&gt;&lt;w:WrapTextWithPunct /&gt;&lt;w:UseAsianBreakRules /&gt;&lt;w:DontGrowAutofit /&gt;&lt;/w:Compatibility&gt;&lt;w:BrowserLevel&gt;MicrosoftInternetExplorer4&lt;/w:BrowserLevel&gt;&lt;/w:WordDocument&gt;&lt;/xml&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;!--[if gte mso 9]&gt;&lt;xml&gt;&lt;w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=&quot;false&quot; LatentStyleCount=&quot;156&quot;&gt;&lt;/w:LatentStyles&gt;&lt;/xml&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&lt;!-- /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\\t{mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;;\\tmargin:0cm;\\tmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\\tmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\\tfont-size:12.0pt;\\tfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\tmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\tmso-ansi-language:DE;\\tmso-fareast-language:DE;}@page Section1\\t{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\\tmargin:70.85pt 70.85pt 2.0cm 70.85pt;\\tmso-header-margin:36.0pt;\\tmso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\\tmso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1\\t{page:Section1;}--&gt;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;!--[if gte mso 10]&gt;&lt;style&gt;/* Style Definitions */table.MsoNormalTable{mso-style-name:&quot;Normale Tabelle&quot;;mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;mso-style-noshow:yes;mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;;mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;mso-para-margin:0cm;mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-pagination:widow-orphan;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-ansi-language:#0400;mso-fareast-language:#0400;mso-bidi-language:#0400;}&lt;/style&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;DE&quot;&gt;written as an explanation of the architectural characteristics of the Residential Building of the City of Vienna, the so-called Hundertwasser House&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;DE&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;DE&quot;&gt;, 1985&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;DE&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;DE&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;DE&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/meta&gt;&lt;/meta&gt;&lt;/meta&gt;&lt;/meta&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;div&gt;verfa&amp;szlig;t als Erkl&amp;auml;rung zu den architektonischen Eigenschaften der Wohnhausanlage der Gemeinde Wien, genannt das &amp;bdquo;Hundertwasser-Haus&amp;ldquo;, 1985&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus, Vienna: &amp;Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag and Compress Verlag, 1985, pp. 232-233 (German)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser Architecture, For a More Human Architecture in Harmony with Nature. Cologne: Taschen, 2007&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;, p. 192&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus, Wien: &amp;Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag und Compress Verlag, 1985, S.&amp;nbsp; 232f. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-GB&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser Architektur, F&amp;uuml;r eine natur- und menschengerechtere Architektur, K&amp;ouml;ln: Taschen, 2006, S. 192&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'courtesy Taschen', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-15 10:6:41.0297###object###text###1.3.2.14###THE SKYLINE
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.3.2.14&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-115&quot;&gt; 115&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;The absolutely straight, dead skyline is an ignominious heirloom of the Bauhaus. If the boundary between the earth and the sky, as it were the transition from man to God, is murdered by the ruler, all the bridges are broken down between man and a higher order.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-115&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;115 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;The skyline made straight by the ruler weighs on us with &lt;br&gt;a levelling, despotic egalitarianism. Woe to the chimney, the ledge or cupola, to the gable, dormer, turret or statue that dares to break through the skyline.&lt;br&gt;Man is beaten from above by the straight-edged ruler. Man is squashed between the straight skyline and the flat floor.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', txt-'1.3.2.14', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'THE SKYLINE', text_title_ge-'DIE SKYLINE', text_contents_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Die schnurgerade, tote Skyline ist ein unr&amp;uuml;hmliches Erbe des Bauhauses.&lt;br /&gt;Wenn die Grenze zwischen Erde und Himmel, quasi der &amp;Uuml;bergang von Mensch zu Gott, ermordet ist durchs Lineal, so sind auch alle Br&amp;uuml;cken abgebrochen zwischen den Menschen und H&amp;ouml;herem.&lt;br /&gt;Die linealgerade Skyline lastet auf uns mit nivellierender despotischer Gleichmacherei.&lt;br /&gt;Wehe dem Schornstein, dem Gesims oder der Kuppel, die es wagen, die Skyline zu durchbrechen.&lt;br /&gt;Der Mensch wird von oben mit dem Lineal erschlagen.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_keywords-'Architektur, architecture, skyline, Bauhaus, Lineal, ruler', text_date-'1985-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_occasion_en-'&lt;div&gt;written as an explanation of the architectural characteristics of the residential building of the city of Vienna, the so-called Hundertwasser-House, 1985&lt;/div&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;div&gt;von Hundertwasser verfa&amp;szlig;t als Erkl&amp;auml;rung zu den architektonischen Eigenschaften der Wohnhausanlage der Gemeinde Wien, genannt das &amp;bdquo;Hundertwasser-Haus&amp;ldquo;, 1985&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;div&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus, Vienna: &amp;Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag and Compress Verlag, 1985, p. 236 (German)&lt;br /&gt;Hundertwasser Architecture, For a More Human Architecture in Harmony with Nature. Cologne: Taschen, 2007, p. 192&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus, Wien: &amp;Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag und Compress Verlag, 1985, S. 236 &lt;br /&gt;Hundertwasser Architektur, F&amp;uuml;r ein natur- und menschengerechteres Bauen, K&amp;ouml;ln: Taschen, 2006, S. 192&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'Hundertwasser', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-15 10:30:15.9312###object###text###1.3.2.15###THE COLUMNS
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.3.2.15&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Against the disease of modern architecture of far overhanging canopies, balconies and building portions, we have only one remedy: columns.&lt;br&gt;The overhanging building portions with no support are probably intended to demonstrate the daring of the architect and statical engineer, but they only produce uneasiness in anybody standing under them. Sometimes the &ldquo;floating architecture&rdquo; collapses as at the Berlin Congress Hall.&lt;br&gt;The column is an important element of Western architecture.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-116&quot;&gt; 116&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Next to a column one feels as under a tree.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-116&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;116 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;A column must be beautiful and colourful and shine in the rain and in the moonlight of its own accord. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', txt-'1.3.2.15', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'THE COLUMNS', text_title_ge-'DIE S&Auml;ULEN', text_contents_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Gegen die Krankheit der weit auskragenden Vord&amp;auml;cher, Balkone und Geb&amp;auml;udeteile gibt es nur ein Heilmittel: S&amp;auml;ulen.&lt;br /&gt;Die st&amp;uuml;tzenlosen, vorspringenden Geb&amp;auml;udeteile sollen wohl den Wagemut des Architekten und Statikers veranschaulichen, erzeugen aber nur Unbehagen f&amp;uuml;r den, der darunter ist. Manchmal f&amp;auml;llt die Schwebe-Architektur herunter, wie bei der Berliner Kongre&amp;szlig;halle.&lt;br /&gt;Die S&amp;auml;ule ist ein wesentliches Element abendl&amp;auml;ndischer Architektur.&lt;br /&gt;Bei einer S&amp;auml;ule f&amp;uuml;hlt man sich wie unter einem Baum. &lt;br /&gt;Eine S&amp;auml;ule mu&amp;szlig; sch&amp;ouml;n und vielfarbig sein und auch im Regen und im Mondlicht aus eigener Kraft leuchten.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_keywords-'Architektur, architecture, column, S&auml;ule', text_date-'', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_occasion_en-'&lt;div&gt;written as an explanation for the architectural characteristics of the Residential Building of the City of Vienna, the so-called &amp;quot;Hundertwasser-House&amp;quot;, 1985&lt;/div&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;div&gt;verfasst als Erkl&amp;auml;rung zu den architektonischen Eigenschaften der Wohnhausanlage der Gemeinde Wien, genannt das &amp;bdquo;Hundertwasser-Haus&amp;ldquo;, 1985&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;div&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus, Vienna: &amp;Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag and Compress Verlag, 1985, p. 238 (German)&lt;br /&gt;Hundertwasser Architecture, For a More Human Architecture in Harmony with Nature. Cologne: Taschen, 2007, p. 209&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus, Wien: &amp;Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag und Compress Verlag, 1985, S. 238&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hundertwasser Architektur, F&amp;uuml;r ein natur- und menschengerechteres Bauen, K&amp;ouml;ln: Taschen, 2006, S. 209&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'courtesy Taschen, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-15 11:48:23.1387###object###text###1.4.0.0.3###BEING A PAINTER IS WONDERFUL&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;

[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.0.0.3&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-117&quot;&gt; 117&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Being a painter is good&lt;br&gt;A painter is free and unbound&lt;br&gt;And independent&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-117&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;117 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;A painter has no boss&lt;br&gt;A painter has a lot of time to contemplate everything&lt;br&gt;A painter also feels the impulses that come from somewhere else&lt;br&gt;From a different world. From where he does not know.&lt;br&gt;Thus I became a vegetative painter&lt;br&gt;I painted in layers one next to another just like annual rings emerge or deposits&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;Just like plants grow and like the water flows in meanders&lt;br&gt;Only later did I know that vegetation is our model&lt;br&gt;That we live in this earth we owe to vegetation&lt;br&gt;We squander the wealth that vegetation prepared for us and gave us as a gift&lt;br&gt;The trees look quite the same&lt;br&gt;On this side and the other side of the border&lt;br&gt;The trees survives all religions&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; all wars&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; all political systems&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Modern architecture is a crime&lt;br&gt;Modern architecture is against human rights&lt;br&gt;The straight line is Godless.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', txt-'1.4.0.0.3', text_type-'Speech', text_category-'HW on his work', text_title_en-'BEING A PAINTER IS WONDERFUL&lt;br /&gt;', text_title_ge-'MALER SEIN IST SCH&Ouml;N&lt;br /&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Maler sein ist sch&amp;ouml;n&lt;br /&gt;Ein Maler ist frei und ungebunden &lt;br /&gt;und selbst&amp;auml;ndig&lt;br /&gt;Ein Maler hat keinen Chef&lt;br /&gt;Ein Maler hat viel Zeit, &amp;uuml;ber alles nachzudenken&lt;br /&gt;Ein Maler sp&amp;uuml;rt auch die Impulse, die von woanders &lt;br /&gt;her kommen&lt;br /&gt;Von einer anderen Welt. &lt;br /&gt;Von woher wei&amp;szlig; er nicht&lt;br /&gt;So wurde ich ein vegetativer Maler&lt;br /&gt;Ich malte in Schichten nebeneinander so wie &lt;br /&gt;Jahresringe entstehen oder Ablagerungen&lt;br /&gt;So wie Pflanzen wachsen und so wie das &lt;br /&gt;Wasser in M&amp;auml;andern rinnt&lt;br /&gt;Erst sp&amp;auml;ter wu&amp;szlig;te ich, da&amp;szlig; die Vegetation unser &lt;br /&gt;Vorbild ist&lt;br /&gt;Da&amp;szlig; wir auf dieser Erde leben, verdanken wir &lt;br /&gt;der Vegetation&lt;br /&gt;Wir verschwenden den Reichtum, den die Vegetation &lt;br /&gt;f&amp;uuml;r uns vorbereitet und uns geschenkt hat&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Die B&amp;auml;ume sehen diesseits und jenseits der &lt;br /&gt;Grenze ganz gleich aus&lt;br /&gt;Der Baum &amp;uuml;bersteht alle Religionen&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; alle Kriege&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; alle politischen Systeme&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Die moderne Architektur ist ein Verbrechen&lt;br /&gt;Die moderne Architektur ist gegen die Menschenrechte&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Die gerade Linie ist gottlos.&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_keywords-'Maler, painter, unabh&auml;ngig, independant, vegetative, Malerei, vegetative, painting, Vegetation', text_date-'1976-04-26', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_occasion_en-'&lt;div&gt;Gesprochen mit &amp;Uuml;bersetzer vor der Presse zur Er&amp;ouml;ffnung der Ausstellung &amp;bdquo;&amp;Ouml;sterreich zeigt den Kontinenten Hundertwasser&amp;ldquo; im Muzeum Naradowe in Warschau, 26. April 1976&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Spoken with an interpreter to the press in Warsaw, at the opening of the exhibition Austria Presents Hundertwasser to the Continents on 26 April, 1976, in Norodowe Muzeum, Warsaw&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;div&gt;Hundertwasser, New York: Parkstone Press International, 2008, p. 77&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Hundertwasser, New York: Parkstone Press International, 2008, S. 77&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'courtesy Sirrocco, 2008', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-15 12:52:5.87897###object###text###1.4.0.0.4###I AM A KING
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.0.0.4&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-118&quot;&gt; 118&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;I am a King,&lt;br&gt;I have crowned myself.&lt;br&gt;I am rich.&lt;br&gt;Wealth is pursuing me.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-118&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;118 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;And it is sad that not everyone is a rich King.&lt;br&gt;You have only to set a crown on your head, and recognise the wealth around you.&lt;br&gt;But you are too weak and too cowardly to do this.&lt;br&gt;I would rather live in a valley with rich kings than in a valley of tears.&lt;br&gt;Then I would not need to be a king myself.&lt;br&gt;When everyone is quite naturally and simply creative, a paradise, a kingdom is right there where he is.&lt;br&gt;There one has no need to go far to reach the next paradise, the next kingdom, because paradise starts round the corner at the neighbour&rsquo;s place.&lt;br&gt;There is no energy crisis.&lt;br&gt;There is only an insane waste of energy.&lt;br&gt;Does nature know such a thing as an energy crisis?&lt;br&gt;Do the birds, the trees, the beetles have an energy crisis?&lt;br&gt;Only man imagines he has an energy crisis, because he has gone mad.&lt;br&gt;Perfect ecology must be that man places himself back into his environmental barriers so that the earth can regenerate.&lt;br&gt;The insane an unjustified consumption of energy should correspond with the equal amount of responsible intelligence.&lt;br&gt;But this is not so.&lt;br&gt;Man remained a stupid animal that all of a sudden has crazy amounts of energy, of poison and deadly weapons at his disposal. And he wastes this all blindly destroying his environment and killing his own brothers.&lt;br&gt;And greedily this man, this stupid animal is asking for more energy, more poison and more deadly weapons.&lt;br&gt;Men, especially the so-called experts, have lost control over the levers of energy. They do not know anymore what they do.&lt;br&gt;The consumer society does not bring us the salvation.&lt;br&gt;We produce without sense.&lt;br&gt;We consume like mad.&lt;br&gt;We waste blindly.&lt;br&gt;Man degraded himself to a manipulated consumer item, nuclear energy consolidates this most dangerous of all forms of slavery.&lt;br&gt;He who advocates nuclear energy is either excessively short-sighted, tendentiously misinformed, or consciously criminal.&lt;br&gt;We live in paradise, but we destroy it.&lt;br&gt;Everything is here to be happy on earth.&lt;br&gt;We have snow, and every day a new morning&lt;br&gt;We have trees and rain, hope and tears&lt;br&gt;We have humus and oxygen, animals and all the colours, distant lands and bicycles,&lt;br&gt;We have sun and shadow, we are rich.&lt;br&gt;But what is the avant-garde fool doing with art?&lt;br&gt;He helps to destroy our existence.&lt;br&gt;Modern art has become a panopticon of horrors.&lt;br&gt;The most absurd activities are perfected and worshipped, the art-makers want to stand in the front rank of the destroyers.&lt;br&gt;Since long-time the artists ceased to be the creators of art. It is a small international mafia of frustrated intellectuals who wants to dictate to the people what they consider as art.&lt;br&gt;They sit, unapproachable and unnoticed by the people on their thrones and speak to the people in foreign words and complicated phrases, just as doctors do in Latin procuring respect for themselves by using the fear of the incomprehensible. &lt;br&gt;Pop Art, Body Art, Concept Art, Land Art, Happening, Dripping, Action Painting, Tachism, Op Art, Kinetism, to name only a few expressions out of the avant-garde Latin. First the Latin was French, now it is English.&lt;br&gt;Modern Art became intellectual masturbation, enforced as a short-lived status symbol, ugly, cold, Godless, without heart. An art which creates unhappiness.&lt;br&gt;The artist, deprived of power, is in reality an executor of mental rubbish. &lt;br&gt;All he does now is to illustrate basically wrong intellectual theories, completely estranged from the laws of nature, and from what mankind is longing for.&lt;br&gt;Modern Art as avant-garde has missed the target and hit the emptiness. This is stupid self-destruction.&lt;br&gt;Culture is committing suicide.&lt;br&gt;New &ndash; newer &ndash; newest at any price is the slogan of avant-gardism &ldquo;new&rdquo; stands for most effective destruction.&lt;br&gt;This mafia which I have attacked condemns everything which does not fit her, and assumes educational functions with a hitherto unknown intolerance.&lt;br&gt;Everything that is not propagated by this mafia has no right to exist. Everything that it does not consider as art, is not art. This is an intolerance without compare.&lt;br&gt;This negative avant-garde&rsquo;s claim to politico-cultural power is similar to that of the Nazis during the Third Reich. Only the trend is reversed.&lt;br&gt;The museums of modern art are the hospitals of our exhausted society in which the diseases of civilisation are cultivated and preserved, instead of being healed. On exhibit are the products of a masochistic therapy, the purulent discharge of our impotence to&amp;nbsp;create.&lt;br&gt;Our enemy is really the stupidity of not being able to distinguish the genuine from the false. A museum director must be made liable for his deeds and must be put in gaol if he buys rubbish with public money. This panopticon of horrors of contemporary art is like the emperor&rsquo;s new clothes in Andersen&rsquo;s famous story. And the emperor&rsquo;s new clothes will long be admired, although he has no clothes on, although he is naked.&lt;br&gt;A structure of lies collapses.&lt;br&gt;One only has to make light, and the nightmare disappears like as if you open your eyes, and one is no longer in the&amp;nbsp;dark.&lt;br&gt;There are painters, thank God, who go their own way, imperturbable, strong and&amp;nbsp;free.&lt;br&gt;They spread the good and the beautiful.&lt;br&gt;They have an aura like dark glowing.&lt;br&gt;They are our hope.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', txt-'1.4.0.0.4', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'I AM A KING', text_title_ge-'ICH BIN EIN K&Ouml;NIG', text_contents_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Ich bin ein K&amp;ouml;nig. &lt;br /&gt;Ich habe mich selbst gekr&amp;ouml;nt.&lt;br /&gt;Ich bin reich. &lt;br /&gt;Der Reichtum flie&amp;szlig;t mir hinterher. &lt;br /&gt;Und es ist traurig, da&amp;szlig; nicht jeder ein reicher K&amp;ouml;nig ist.&lt;br /&gt;Man braucht sich nur eine Krone aufzusetzen und den Reichtum wahrzunehmen. &lt;br /&gt;Jedoch dazu ist man zu feige.&lt;br /&gt;Mir w&amp;auml;re lieber, in einem Tal mit reichen K&amp;ouml;nigen zu leben statt in einem Jammertal. &lt;br /&gt;Dann brauchte ich selbst kein K&amp;ouml;nig zu sein.&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;Wenn jeder ganz nat&amp;uuml;rlich, ganz einfach sch&amp;ouml;pferisch ist, ist da, wo er ist, ein Paradies, ein K&amp;ouml;nigreich.&lt;br /&gt;Dann braucht man nicht lange zu gehen, um ins n&amp;auml;chste Paradies, ins n&amp;auml;chste K&amp;ouml;nigreich zu kommen, denn das Paradies ist beim Nachbarn um die Ecke.&lt;br /&gt;Es gibt keine Energiekrise. &lt;br /&gt;Es gibt nur eine ma&amp;szlig;lose Energieverschwendung. &lt;br /&gt;Hat die Natur eine Energiekrise?&lt;br /&gt;Haben die V&amp;ouml;gel, die B&amp;auml;ume, die K&amp;auml;fer eine Energiekrise? &lt;br /&gt;Nur der Mensch bildet sich ein, eine Energiekrise zu haben, weil er wahnsinnig geworden ist.&lt;br /&gt;Der heutige Mensch ist der gef&amp;auml;hrlichste Sch&amp;auml;dling, der je die Erde bev&amp;ouml;lkert hat. &lt;br /&gt;Der Mensch mu&amp;szlig; wieder in seine &amp;ouml;kologischen Schranken verwiesen werden, damit sich die Erde regenerieren kann.&lt;br /&gt;Unmengen von Energie, Zeit und Geld werden verwendet, um Menschen einzureden, da&amp;szlig; sie unn&amp;ouml;tige Dinge haben wollen. Das schafft Frustration, Mord und Totschlag, denn es ist nicht m&amp;ouml;glich, da&amp;szlig; alle alles haben k&amp;ouml;nnen.&lt;br /&gt;Wir leben scheinbar im materiellen Gl&amp;uuml;ck, tats&amp;auml;chlich jedoch im seelischen Ungl&amp;uuml;ck.&lt;br /&gt;Um gl&amp;uuml;cklich zu sein, braucht der Mensch keinen &amp;auml;u&amp;szlig;eren Reichtum, sondern einen inneren Reichtum der Seele.&lt;br /&gt;Um gl&amp;uuml;cklich zu sein, braucht der Mensch keine mechanische Energie, sondern eine innere sch&amp;ouml;pferische Energie.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Der wahnsinnige, unbegr&amp;uuml;ndete Energieverbrauch des Menschen m&amp;uuml;sste einer dementsprechenden verantwortungsbewussten, sch&amp;ouml;pferischen Intelligenz entsprechen.&lt;br /&gt;Dem ist aber nicht so.&lt;br /&gt;Der Mensch ist ein dummes Herdentier geblieben, das pl&amp;ouml;tzlich irrsinnige Mengen von Energie, von Giften und anderen Mordmitteln zur Verf&amp;uuml;gung hat, die es wild verpulvert oder r&amp;uuml;cksichtslos zur Vernichtung der Umwelt und der eigenen Br&amp;uuml;der einsetzt. &lt;br /&gt;Und gierig verlangt dieser Mensch, dieses dumme Herdentier, nach noch mehr Energie, noch mehr Giften und noch mehr Mordmitteln.&lt;br /&gt;Konsum ist kein Allheilmittel.&lt;br /&gt;Es wird kopflos produziert, &lt;br /&gt;wie wahnsinnig konsumiert, &lt;br /&gt;blind verschwendet, &lt;br /&gt;und der Mensch wird zur KONSUMMASCHINE degradiert.&lt;br /&gt;Kernenergie soll wohl diese gef&amp;auml;hrlichste aller Versklavungen verfestigen.&lt;br /&gt;Wer Kernenergie propagiert, ist entweder ma&amp;szlig;los kurzsichtig, tendenzi&amp;ouml;s informiert oder bewu&amp;szlig;t kriminell.&lt;br /&gt;Wir leben im Paradies. Wir machen es nur kaputt.&lt;br /&gt;Es ist alles da, um gl&amp;uuml;cklich auf Erden zu sein. &lt;br /&gt;Wir haben Schnee und jeden Tag einen neuen Morgen, &lt;br /&gt;wir haben B&amp;auml;ume und Regen, Hoffnung und Tr&amp;auml;nen, &lt;br /&gt;Wir haben Humus und Sauerstoff, Tiere und alle Farben, &lt;br /&gt;ferne L&amp;auml;nder und Fahrr&amp;auml;der, &lt;br /&gt;wir haben Sonne und Schatten, wir sind reich.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Doch was macht der avantgardistische Narr mit der Kunst? &lt;br /&gt;Er hilft den Zerst&amp;ouml;rern unserer Existenz nach Kr&amp;auml;ften. &lt;br /&gt;Die moderne Kunst ist ein Horrorpanoptikum geworden.&lt;br /&gt;Die absurdesten T&amp;auml;tigkeiten werden perfektioniert und angebetet. &lt;br /&gt;Die Kunstmacher wollen in der vordersten Reihe der Zerst&amp;ouml;rer stehen.&lt;br /&gt;Die Kunstmacher und Kunstbetreiber sind lange schon nicht mehr die K&amp;uuml;nstler selbst, sondern eine kleine internationale Mafia von frustrierten Intellektuellen. &lt;br /&gt;Diese Mafia, bla&amp;szlig; und weltfremd und lichtscheu und wahr&amp;shy;heitsscheu, will dem Volk diktieren, was Kunst ist.&lt;br /&gt;Sie sitzt abseits unnahbar und vom Volk unbeachtet auf Thronen, spricht zum dummen Volk mit Fremdw&amp;ouml;rtern und Verklausulierungen, so wie die &amp;Auml;rzte auf lateinisch, um sich mit der Angst vor Unverst&amp;auml;ndlichem Respekt zu verschaffen.&lt;br /&gt;Pop art, body art, concept art, land art, happening, dripping, action painting, Tachismus, op art, Kinetismus, um nur einen Teil des avantgardistischen Lateins zu nennen. &lt;br /&gt;Zuerst war das Latein franz&amp;ouml;sisch, jetzt ist es englisch.&lt;br /&gt;Die zeitgen&amp;ouml;ssische Kunst ist eine intellektuelle Onanie geworden, &lt;br /&gt;erzwungen als kurzlebiges Statussymbol. Eine Kunst, die ungl&amp;uuml;cklich macht.&lt;br /&gt;In Wahrheit ist der entmachtete K&amp;uuml;nstler ein Nachvollzieher von Hirngespinsten. &lt;br /&gt;Er liefert nur mehr Belege f&amp;uuml;r intellektuelle Theorien, v&amp;ouml;llig entfremdet von den Gesetzen der Natur und dem, wonach der Mensch sich sehnt.&lt;br /&gt;Die moderne Kunst ist als Avantgarde am Ziel vorbeigeschossen, ins Leere, in den stupiden Selbstmord. Die Kultur begeht Selbstmord.&lt;br /&gt;NEU NEUER NEUEST um jeden Preis ist das Gebot des Avantgardismus.&lt;br /&gt;Und unter neu versteht der negative Theoretiker das, was SCHNELL und TOLL zerst&amp;ouml;rt.&lt;br /&gt;Die von mir attackierte Mafia verurteilt pauschal das, was ihr nicht genehm ist. Und ma&amp;szlig;t sich sogar erzieherische Funktionen an mit einer nie dagewesenen Intoleranz. Alles, was von ihr nicht propagiert wird, hat in ihren Augen keine Existenzberechtigung. &lt;br /&gt;Alles, was sie nicht f&amp;uuml;r Kunst h&amp;auml;lt, ist keine Kunst. &lt;br /&gt;Eine Intoleranz ohnegleichen.&lt;br /&gt;Der kulturpolitische Machtanspruch dieser negativen Avantgarde ist &amp;auml;hnlich dem kulturpolitischen Machtanspruch der Nazis im Dritten Reich, nur mit umgekehrten Vorzeichen.&lt;br /&gt;Die Museen der zeitgen&amp;ouml;ssischen Kunst sind Krankenh&amp;auml;user unserer kaputten Gesellschaft, worin unsere Zivilisationskrankheiten kultiviert und konserviert werden, statt sie zu heilen.&lt;br /&gt;Und zur Schau gestellt werden die Produkte einer masochistischen Therapie, zur Schau gestellt werden die eiternden Ausfl&amp;uuml;sse unserer sch&amp;ouml;pferischen Impotenz. &lt;br /&gt;Unser Feind ist eigentlich die Dummheit, nicht echt von falsch unterscheiden zu k&amp;ouml;nnen.&lt;br /&gt;Ein Museumsdirektor mu&amp;szlig; haftbar sein f&amp;uuml;r seine Handlungen, und mu&amp;szlig; ins Gef&amp;auml;ngnis kommen k&amp;ouml;nnen, wenn er mit &amp;ouml;ffentlichen Geldern Plunder kauft.&lt;br /&gt;Dieses Horrorpanoptikum der zeitgen&amp;ouml;ssischen Kunst ist wie des Kaisers neue Kleider. Und des Kaisers neue Kleider werden noch lange bestaunt und angebetet, obwohl er gar keine anhat.&lt;br /&gt;Ein L&amp;uuml;gengeb&amp;auml;ude bricht zusammen.&lt;br /&gt;Man braucht nur Licht zu machen, und der Spuk f&amp;auml;llt wie Schuppen von den Augen, und man ist nicht mehr blind.&lt;br /&gt;Es gibt Maler, Gott sei Dank, die unersch&amp;uuml;tterlich und stark und frei ihren Weg gehen. Sie verbreiten Gutes und Sch&amp;ouml;nes mit &amp;uuml;berirdischer Kraft. Sie haben eine Aura, wie ein dunkles Leuchten. Sie sind unsere Hoffnung.&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_keywords-'K&ouml;nig, king, K&ouml;nigreich, kingdom, art, Kunst, energy, Energie, Reichtum, Kernenergie, nuclear energy, artist, K&uuml;nstler', text_date-'1981-10-12', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_occasion_en-'&lt;div&gt;Written in Vienna, 12 October, 1981, for the magazine &amp;quot;Austria today&amp;quot;, using his speech &amp;quot;Die Welt hat sich nicht gebessert&amp;quot; on occasion of being awarded the Grand Austrian State Prize on May 14, 1981&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Verfa&amp;szlig;t in Wien f&amp;uuml;r die Zeitschrift &amp;bdquo;Austria Today&amp;ldquo;, 12. Oktober 1981 unter Verwendung der Rede &amp;quot;Die Welt hat sich nicht gebessert&amp;quot; anl&amp;auml;&amp;szlig;lich der Verleihung des GROSSEN &amp;Ouml;STERREICHISCHEN STAATSPREISES F&amp;Uuml;R KUNST am 14. Mai 1981 &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;div&gt;Magazine &amp;quot;Austria Today&amp;quot;, Vienna, October 1981&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hundertwasser, New York: Parkstone Press International, 2008, pp. 86-89&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Zeitschrift &amp;quot;Austria Today&amp;quot;, Wien, Oktober 1981&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Hundertwasser, New York: Parkstone Press International, 2008, S. 86ff.&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'Sirrocco, 2007', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-15 15:25:0.219162###object###text###1.4.0.0.5###BETWEEN HITLER YOUTH AND STAR OF DAVID
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.0.0.5&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;My father died when I was one year old; probably as a result of appendicitis. In my mind, he is only a photograph. My mother never talked much about him and when she did, not really in a positive sense. She seemed to be his superior in every way, and therefore everything had rested on her shoulders even while he was alive. My father was one of hundreds of thousands jobless people in the late 1920s, while my mother earned our money as an employee of the Creditanstalt bank, from which we could barely live.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; At first in a municipal flat in the Johnstra&szlig;e in the district F&uuml;nfhaus in Vienna, not far from Sch&ouml;nbrunn. But there were worlds between the imperial glory of the castle and our small flat. We were poor, there was only a kitchenette, which made my mother very angry. Our second flat in the Brunhildengasse nearby wasn&rsquo;t much better.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Who could guess that these lodgings were luxurious compared with those awaiting us in the years to follow? After we had heard the words of Chancellor Kurt Schuschnigg &ndash; &ldquo;God protect Austria&rdquo; &ndash; in the radio on 11 March 1938, my mother told me that we had to expect hard times from then on. I was to understand the reason for these words very much later. My mother was a Jewess. We stayed at home when Hitler&rsquo;s troops marched into the country. When we ventured out into the street again, we, too, wore swastikas, for anybody who didn&rsquo;t was suspect and bound to be abused.&amp;nbsp; It was a simple, primitive protection: a small pin on the shirt or blouse, and we went unmolested. Neither of us was a hero. There were only two alternatives: to get jostled, fist on eye, bloody nose &ndash; or a swastika on the lapel. We decided in favor of the latter.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Which didn&rsquo;t alter the fact that we had to leave our flat after a few months. The district Leopoldstadt had been declared Jewish ghetto, and this was where a flat was allocated to us. But there we stayed only a few hours. For, while my mother was unpacking furniture, dishes and clothes, some anti-Semite painted &ldquo;Gr&uuml;nspan&rdquo; on our door. Herschel Gr&uuml;nspan, a Polish Jew whose parents had been deported by the Nazis, had just assassinated Ernst von Rath, the German envoy accredited to Paris, which the Germans avenged in the so-called Pogrom Night, the Night of the Broken Glass against the Jews. Now they called us &ldquo;Gr&uuml;nspan&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; When the janitor of the house in Leopoldstadt requested my mother to remove the &ldquo;Gr&uuml;nspan&rdquo;-lettering at her own cost, she got so angry that she decided to leave the flat immediately. I had just returned from a trip with my scooter and was rather surprised by the news of the imminent move. This time it was to a flat in the Obere Donaustra&szlig;e, where my grandmother and my aunt Ida lived. We spent the whole war in a small room of this apartment.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I was half-Jewish and a member of the Hitler Youth. And this wasn&rsquo;t so paradoxical as it may sound today. It was a necessity to survive. When the harassment began to become unbearable in 1942 &ndash; we heard of the first deportations to the camps; Jews had to be called Sara and Israel -, my relatives had the idea that I ought to join the Hitler Youth as a protection for the family, which I did. Whenever necessary I wore the swastika, an armband and the HY cap.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; In fact, members of the SS in uniform turned up at our house several times, around 2 in the morning. They leant on the bell, insisted that all Jews leave the apartment; we should be picked up in an hour. Always when the bell rang by night, I put on swastika, armband and cap at lightning speed and opened the door for the frightening SS-people. I showed them a box with my father&rsquo;s medals for bravery and my uncle&rsquo;s Iron Cross from World War I. Surprisingly, this somehow impressed them and they left us alone for a while. Some months later, the procedure was repeated: leaning on the bell, men in SS uniforms, father&rsquo;s World War medals, men leaving. This way I could delay my grandmother&rsquo;s and aunt&rsquo;s deportation by a year.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; At the third occasion, it weren&rsquo;t the SS people, but Jewish collaborators, who &ndash; in order to survive themselves &ndash; picked up other Jews for deportation. Both my aunt as well as my grandmother were abducted. They died in the concentration camp. Same as more than eighty other relatives, uncles, aunts, nieces, nephews, cousins &ndash; my mother once made a list &ndash; who became victims of the Nazi regime. My aunt Gisela in Berlin and her daughter, my mother and I were the only survivors of a once huge family. Our survival was due to the fact that chiefly full Jews were deported. I was protected by being half Jewish, and my full Jewish mother was protected because she had a half Jewish son. The half Jew was able to protect the full Jew.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; It was much later that I realized the perversion of the situation. While my mother went shopping wearing the Star of David, I walked around with the swastika. But when the normal situation becomes perverted, perversion is normal. I knew Jews who believed that if they would fight for Hitler and work hard for him, he wouldn&rsquo;t hurt them. Many a &ldquo;non-Aryan&rdquo; said: Hitler is a good man, he just wants us to work for him. I remember our neighbors, the Jewish family Blau, in the Obere Donaustra&szlig;e. Their opinion was: Hitler doesn&rsquo;t wish to do us any harm, he just wants us to be upright and honest. They felt themselves to be good Germans and could not understand that they were disapproved of for religious, racist or any other reasons. There even were Jews who agreed with the Nazi watchword that the Jews were to blame for everything. Even my mother thought that the Polish Jews were responsible for the anti-Semitism. &lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We also thought that, when my grandmother and aunt were picked up, that they were brought &ldquo;only&rdquo; to a labor camp. There were rumors which whispered worse things, but nobody could believe that any regime would kill the inhabitants of its own country. One clung to the hope that the rumor would turn out to be untrue. Right to the end, we never believed the worst.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The Hitler Youth (Hitlerjugend &ndash; HJ) never found out that in my case, this abbreviation didn&rsquo;t mean just that, but also Half Jew. It was a miracle that this organization never realized this fact, but certainly my father&rsquo;s Aryan name Stowasser helped a great deal. We of the Hitler Youth used to meet regularly, sang Hitler songs, marched to the Prater, where once a military attack was simulated.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; When we had to choose a branch of arms in the last days of the War, my decision was the radio operations, because this seemed to me least dangerous. After I had passed the radio operator&rsquo;s exam, our bell rang and some colleagues from the Hitler Youth wanted me to join them to go to war.&amp;nbsp; The Russians meanwhile had reached Burgenland. In an attack of madness, which later turned out to be cleverness, I declared: I cannot go with you, I am half Jewish. The colleagues from the Hitler Youth went away shocked, but didn&rsquo;t report the affair in the general chaos of war. My &ldquo;confession&rdquo; to be half Jewish saved my life. When the shooting started in Vienna, I saw a detachment of my friends of the Hitler Youth, fifteen, sixteen years old like myself, marching in the direction of the St. Stephen&rsquo;s cathedral with bazookas over their shoulders. And none of them returned alive.&lt;br&gt;----------------&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I attended the first grade of elementary school in 1935, at the Montessori school, which had been founded a short time before. This school was well known for its liberal teaching methods. Every child was allowed to do whatever it wished to do, so I immediately started to paint, and my report confirmed &ldquo;exceptional sense of colors and shapes&rdquo;. On the other hand I was unable to add up three and three after a year. This as well as the fact that the Montessori school was too expensive induced my mother to send me to a public elementary school. I had to drop out of the secondary school &ldquo;for racist reasons&rdquo; after five years, then attended a commercial school and finally graduated after the war.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Already in the Schuschnigg era, my mother had me baptized &ldquo;for safety&rsquo;s sake&rdquo;. &lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-119&quot;&gt; 119&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;And it was in a Catholic church in the 15th district that I saw a picture of the Madonna which let me wish to become a painter. This resolution was also influenced by the flowers which I picked in the Vienna Woods in order to press them between the pages of a book. We used to discuss about how to avoid that the colors should fade. That&rsquo;s when I said to myself, if you paint them instead of pressing them, the colors will remain unchanged. Another impulse was my stamp collection; I wanted to be able to paint such pretty little pictures myself one day. In 1943, I consciously made my first drawings.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-119&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;119 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I often used to stand for hours in front of the window display of a frame shop in the Wallensteinstra&szlig;e, where they showed watercolors which delighted me. Every dot, every line fascinated me. Naturally, these pictures were conventional, upright and honest, just as these times required. I, too, painted my first watercolors, exactly in this style reminding of Hitler&rsquo;s picture postcards, and I was always very happy when I succeeded to draw something that could be identified. Flowers, landscapes, houses and still lives were my favorite subjects.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; In a small suitcase, which I carried around everywhere, I had a carefully rolled watercolor painted by me in order to be able to prove that I was a painter &ndash; just in case.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;[&hellip;]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Doubtless the road I chose as an artist is causally connected with the situation in which I grew up. My youth as a double outsider &ndash; without a father and being half Jewish &ndash; has naturally contributed to my reflecting a lot and becoming aware. I became a lone wolf, a fighter for certain matters which seemed important to me. During my childhood I didn&rsquo;t have the chance to feel part of a group and thus remained a solo combatant.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;[&hellip;]&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', txt-'1.4.0.0.5', text_type-'Prose', text_category-'', text_title_en-'BETWEEN HITLER YOUTH AND STAR OF DAVID', text_title_ge-'ZWISCHEN &quot;HJ&quot; UND JUDENSTERN', text_contents_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Mein Vater starb, als ich ein Jahr alt war, vermutlich an den Folgen einer Blinddarmentz&amp;uuml;ndung. Er ist mir nur als Fotografie pr&amp;auml;sent. Meine Mutter hat nie besonders viel und wenn, dann nicht besonders gut von ihm gesprochen. Sie war ihm wohl in allem &amp;uuml;berlegen, und daher lastete, auch als er noch da war, alles auf ihren Schultern. Mein Vater war in den sp&amp;auml;ten zwanziger Jahren einer von Hunderttausenden Arbeitslosen, meine Mutter hat als Angestellte der Creditanstalt das Geld beschafft, von dem wir recht und schlecht leben konnten.&lt;br /&gt;Zun&amp;auml;chst in einer Gemeindewohnung in der Johnstra&amp;szlig;e in Wien-F&amp;uuml;nfhaus, nicht weit von Sch&amp;ouml;nbrunn. Doch zwischen der imperialen Pracht des Schlosses und unserer kleinen Wohnung lagen Welten. Wir waren arm, es gab nur eine Kochnische, was meine Mutter sehr ge&amp;auml;rgert hat. Auch unsere zweite Wohnung in der nahen Brunhildengasse bot nicht viel mehr.&lt;br /&gt;Wer h&amp;auml;tte gedacht, da&amp;szlig; diese Unterk&amp;uuml;nfte luxuri&amp;ouml;s waren gegen das, was uns in den folgenden Jahren erwartete? Nachdem wir die Worte des Bundeskanzlers Kurt Schuschnigg - &amp;bdquo;Gott sch&amp;uuml;tze &amp;Ouml;sterreich&amp;ldquo; - am 11. M&amp;auml;rz 1938 im Radio geh&amp;ouml;rt hatten, sagte meine Mutter zu mir, es k&amp;auml;men jetzt schlechte Zeiten auf uns zu. Den Grund daf&amp;uuml;r sollte ich erst viel sp&amp;auml;ter verstehen. Meine Mutter war J&amp;uuml;din. W&amp;auml;hrend des Einmarsches der Hitler-Truppen blieben wir zu Hause. Als wir uns wieder auf die Stra&amp;szlig;e wagten, hatten auch wir Hakenkreuze angesteckt, denn jeder, der dies nicht tat, war suspekt und lief Gefahr, angep&amp;ouml;belt zu werden. Es war ein ganz einfacher, primitiver Schutz: Eine kleine Stecknadel am Hemd oder an der Bluse, und schon wurde man in Ruhe gelassen. Keiner von uns war ein Held. Es gab nur zwei M&amp;ouml;glichkeiten: angerempelt werden, Faust aufs Aug&amp;rsquo;, blutige Nase - oder ein Hakenkreuz am Revers. Wir entschieden uns f&amp;uuml;r letzteres.&lt;br /&gt;Was nichts daran &amp;auml;nderte, da&amp;szlig; wir nach einigen Monaten unsere Wohnung verlassen mu&amp;szlig;ten. Der Bezirk Leopoldstadt war zum j&amp;uuml;dischen Ghetto erkl&amp;auml;rt worden, und hier wies man uns eine Wohnung zu. Doch da blieben wir nur ein paar Stunden. Denn w&amp;auml;hrend meine Mutter damit besch&amp;auml;ftigt war, M&amp;ouml;bel, Geschirr und W&amp;auml;sche auszupacken, malte ein Antisemit die Buchstaben &amp;bdquo;Gr&amp;uuml;nspan&amp;ldquo; an unsere Eingangst&amp;uuml;r. Herschel Gr&amp;uuml;nspan, ein polnischer Jude, dessen Eltern von den Nazis deportiert worden waren, hatte kurz zuvor ein Attentat auf den in Paris akkreditierten deutschen Gesandtschaftsrat Ernst vom Rath ver&amp;uuml;bt, worauf sich die Nazis mit der sogenannten Reichskristallnacht an den Juden revanchierten. Jetzt nannte man uns &amp;bdquo;Gr&amp;uuml;nspan&amp;ldquo;.&lt;br /&gt;Als nun unser Hausmeister in der Leopoldstadt von meiner Mutter verlangte, sie m&amp;uuml;sse die &amp;bdquo;Gr&amp;uuml;nspan&amp;ldquo;-Bemalung auf eigene Kosten entfernen lassen, regte sie sich so auf, da&amp;szlig; sie beschlo&amp;szlig;, die Wohnung sofort wieder zu verlassen. Ich kam gerade von einer Ausfahrt mit meinem Tretroller nach Hause und wurde von der Nachricht des neuerlich bevorstehenden Umzugs &amp;uuml;berrascht. Diesmal ging&amp;rsquo;s in eine Wohnung in der Oberen Donaustra&amp;szlig;e, in der meine Gro&amp;szlig;mutter und meine Tante Ida lebten. In einem kleinen Zimmer dieser Wohnung verbrachten wir den ganzen Krieg.&lt;br /&gt;Ich war Halbjude und Mitglied der Hitler-Jugend. Und das ist nicht so paradox gewesen, wie es heute klingen mag. Es war eine &amp;Uuml;berlebensnotwendigkeit. Als die Schikanen 1942 unertr&amp;auml;glich zu werden begannen - man h&amp;ouml;rte von den ersten Lagerverschickungen, Juden mu&amp;szlig;ten sich Sara und Israel nennen -, kam meiner Verwandtschaft die Idee, ich sollte zum Schutz der Familie der HJ beitreten, was ich auch tat. Ich trug, wenn es n&amp;ouml;tig war, das Hakenkreuzzeichen, eine Binde und die HJ-Kappe.&lt;br /&gt;Tats&amp;auml;chlich kamen mehrmals uniformierte SS-Leute, gegen zwei Uhr fr&amp;uuml;h, zu uns nach Hause. Sie l&amp;auml;uteten Sturm, verlangten, da&amp;szlig; alle Juden die Wohnung r&amp;auml;umen mu&amp;szlig;ten, in einer Stunde w&amp;uuml;rden wir geholt. Immer wenn es nachts l&amp;auml;utete, legte ich in Blitzeseile Hakenkreuz, Binde und Kapperl an und &amp;ouml;ffnete den furchterregenden SS-M&amp;auml;nnern die T&amp;uuml;r. Dabei hielt ich ihnen eine Schachtel mit den Tapferkeitsmedaillen meines Vaters und dem Eisernen Kreuz meines Onkels aus dem Ersten Weltkrieg entgegen. &amp;Uuml;berraschenderweise beeindruckte sie das irgendwie, und man lie&amp;szlig; uns wieder f&amp;uuml;r einige Zeit in Ruhe. Monate sp&amp;auml;ter wiederholte sich die Prozedur: Sturml&amp;auml;uten, uniformierte SS, Vaters Weltkriegsorden, die M&amp;auml;nner gehen wieder weg. Auf diese Weise konnte ich die Deportation meiner Gro&amp;szlig;mutter und meiner Tante um ein Jahr verz&amp;ouml;gern.&lt;br /&gt;Beim drittenmal kamen keine SS-Leute, sondern j&amp;uuml;dische Vertrauensleute, die - um selbst zu &amp;uuml;berleben - andere Juden zum Abtransport holten. Nun wurden sowohl meine Tante als auch meine Gro&amp;szlig;mutter verschleppt. Beide starben im Konzentrationslager. Wie &amp;uuml;brigens mehr als achtzig weitere Verwandte, Onkel, Tanten, Nichten, Neffen, Cousins und Cousinen - meine Mutter hat dar&amp;uuml;ber einmal eine Liste angefertigt - Opfer der Naziherrschaft wurden. Meine Tante Gisela aus Berlin und ihre Tochter, meine Mutter und ich waren die einzigen &amp;Uuml;berlebenden der einst riesigen Familie. Wir verdankten das &amp;Uuml;berleben dem Umstand, da&amp;szlig; in erster Linie Volljuden verschickt wurden. Ich war gesch&amp;uuml;tzt, weil ich Halbjude war, und meine vollj&amp;uuml;dische Mutter war gesch&amp;uuml;tzt, weil sie einen halbj&amp;uuml;dischen Sohn hatte. Der Halbjude konnte die Ganzj&amp;uuml;din sch&amp;uuml;tzen.&lt;br /&gt;Die Perversion des Ganzen wurde mir erst viel sp&amp;auml;ter bewu&amp;szlig;t. W&amp;auml;hrend meine Mutter mit dem Judenstern einkaufen ging, lief ich mit dem Hakenkreuz durch die Gegend. Aber wenn der Normalzustand zur Perversion wird, ist das Perverse normal. Ich kannte Juden, die der Meinung waren, wenn sie f&amp;uuml;r Hitler k&amp;auml;mpfen, brav f&amp;uuml;r ihn arbeiten, w&amp;uuml;rde er ihnen nichts tun. So mancher &amp;bdquo;Nichtarier&amp;ldquo; sagte: Der Hitler ist ein braver Mensch, er will nur, da&amp;szlig; wir f&amp;uuml;r ihn arbeiten. Ich erinnere mich an die uns benachbarte j&amp;uuml;dische Familie Blau in der Oberen Donaustra&amp;szlig;e. Da hie&amp;szlig; es: Der Hitler will uns nichts tun, er will nur, da&amp;szlig; wir aufrecht und ehrlich sind. Sie f&amp;uuml;hlten sich als gute Deutsche und konnten nicht verstehen, da&amp;szlig; sie aus religi&amp;ouml;sen, rassischen oder irgendwelchen anderen Gr&amp;uuml;nden abgelehnt w&amp;uuml;rden. Es gab auch Juden, die der Naziparole recht gaben, die Juden seien an allem schuld. Selbst meine Mutter war der Meinung, da&amp;szlig; die polnischen Juden am Antisemitismus schuld seien.&lt;br /&gt;Wir dachten auch, da&amp;szlig; meine Gro&amp;szlig;mutter und meine Tante, als man sie abholte, &amp;bdquo;nur&amp;ldquo; in ein Arbeitslager k&amp;auml;men. Es gab zwar Ger&amp;uuml;chte, die Schlimmeres besagten, aber keiner konnte glauben, da&amp;szlig; ein Regime die Bewohner des eigenen Landes umbringt. Man klammerte sich an die Hoffnung, da&amp;szlig; an dem Ger&amp;uuml;cht nichts dran sei. Bis zum Schlu&amp;szlig; haben wir nicht an das Schlimmste geglaubt.&lt;br /&gt;Bei der HJ wu&amp;szlig;ten sie nicht, da&amp;szlig; dieses K&amp;uuml;rzel f&amp;uuml;r mich nicht nur Hitler-Jugend, sondern auch Halbjude bedeutete. Wie durch ein Wunder kam das bei dieser Organisation nie heraus, wobei mir nat&amp;uuml;rlich der arische Name Stowasser meines Vaters half. Wir von der HJ trafen uns regelm&amp;auml;&amp;szlig;ig, sangen Hitler-Lieder, marschierten in den Prater, wo auch einmal ein milit&amp;auml;rischer Angriff simuliert wurde.&lt;br /&gt;Als es in den letzten Kriegstagen hie&amp;szlig;, wir sollten uns zu einer Waffengattung melden, entschied ich mich f&amp;uuml;r den Funkdienst, der mir am wenigsten gef&amp;auml;hrlich schien. Nachdem ich die Funkerpr&amp;uuml;fung abgelegt hatte, l&amp;auml;utete es an unserer T&amp;uuml;r, ein paar Kollegen von der HJ wollten mich abholen, um mit mir in den Krieg zu ziehen. Die Russen waren zu diesem Zeitpunkt bereits bis ins Burgenland vorgedrungen. In einem Anflug von Wahnsinn, der sich aber als Gescheitheit erweisen sollte, erkl&amp;auml;rte ich: Ich kann nicht kommen, ich bin ein Halbjude. Die HJ-Kollegen gingen erschrocken weg, ohne die Aff&amp;auml;re im allgemeinen Kriegschaos weiterzuleiten. Mir hat das &amp;bdquo; Gest&amp;auml;ndnis&amp;ldquo;, Halbjude zu sein, das Leben gerettet. Ich sah, als in Wien schon geschossen wurde, vor unserer Haust&amp;uuml;r einen Trupp meiner HJ-Freunde, die wie ich f&amp;uuml;nfzehn, sechzehn Jahre alt waren, mit Panzerf&amp;auml;usten &amp;uuml;ber der Schulter Richtung Stephansdom marschieren. Und keiner von ihnen ist lebend zur&amp;uuml;ckgekehrt.&lt;br /&gt;Die erste Volksschulklasse hatte ich 1935 in der kurz zuvor gegr&amp;uuml;ndeten Montessori-Schule besucht, die f&amp;uuml;r ihre liberalen Lehrmethoden bekannt war. Jedes Kind durfte tun und lassen, was es wollte, ich habe sofort gemalt, wof&amp;uuml;r in meinem Zeugnis &amp;bdquo;au&amp;szlig;ergew&amp;ouml;hnliches Farben- und Formengef&amp;uuml;hl&amp;ldquo; attestiert wurde. Daf&amp;uuml;r konnte ich nach einem Jahr noch immer nicht drei und drei zusammenz&amp;auml;hlen. Das und die Tatsache, da&amp;szlig; die Montessori-Schule zu teuer war, bewog meine Mutter, mich in eine &amp;ouml;ffentliche Volksschule zu schicken. Die anschlie&amp;szlig;end besuchte Realschule mu&amp;szlig;te ich nach f&amp;uuml;nf Jahren &amp;bdquo;aus rassischen Gr&amp;uuml;nden&amp;ldquo; verlassen, worauf ich eine Handelsschule besuchte und die Matura nach dem Krieg nachholte.&lt;br /&gt;Noch in der Schuschnigg-Zeit hatte mich meine Mutter &amp;bdquo;sicherheitshalber&amp;ldquo; taufen lassen. Und in einer katholischen Kirche im 15. Bezirk sah ich dann auch ein Madonnenbild, das in mir den Wunsch weckte, Maler zu werden. Wichtig f&amp;uuml;r diesen Entschlu&amp;szlig; waren auch die Blumen, die ich im Wienerwald pfl&amp;uuml;ckte, um sie dann zwischen die Seiten eines Buches zu pressen. Wir haben dar&amp;uuml;ber diskutiert, wie man verhindern k&amp;ouml;nne, da&amp;szlig; die Farben verblassen. Da sagte ich mir, wenn du das malst, statt es zu pressen, bleiben die Farben erhalten. Einen weiteren Ansto&amp;szlig; bot mir meine Briefmarkensammlung, ich wollte selbst einmal so sch&amp;ouml;ne kleine Bilder malen k&amp;ouml;nnen. 1943 habe ich meine ersten Zeichnungen bewu&amp;szlig;t angefertigt.&lt;br /&gt;Ich stand oft stundenlang vor der Auslage einer Rahmenhandlung in der Wallensteinstra&amp;szlig;e, wo Aquarelle zu sehen waren, die mich begeisterten. Jeder Tupfen, jeder Strich faszinierte mich. Nat&amp;uuml;rlich waren die Bilder brav, bieder und anst&amp;auml;ndig, ganz wie es die Zeit verlangte. Auch ich malte meine ersten Aquarelle ganz in diesem Stil, der dem der Hitler-Postkarten &amp;auml;hnelte, und war immer sehr gl&amp;uuml;cklich, wenn es mir gelang, etwas so zu zeichnen, da&amp;szlig; man es erkennen konnte. Blumen, Landschaften, H&amp;auml;user und Stilleben waren meine liebsten Motive.&lt;br /&gt;In einem kleinen Koffer, den ich immer bei mir trug, hatte ich ein sorgsam eingerolltes, von mir gemaltes Aquarell mit, um - im Fall des Falles - beweisen zu k&amp;ouml;nnen, da&amp;szlig; ich Maler bin.&lt;br /&gt;Auch den Donaukanal habe ich mehrmals gemalt, und nicht nur das, ich habe ihn immer wieder schwimmend &amp;uuml;berquert, um mich vor mir selbst zu beweisen. Infolge meiner Schwimmtouren erkrankte ich kurz nach Kriegsende, vermutlich durch eine kleine Hautverletzung, an Paratyphus. Bald war ich so schwach, da&amp;szlig; ich nicht mehr gehen konnte, und ich sehe heute noch vor mir, wie mich zwei M&amp;auml;nner auf einem Brett durch das zerbombte Wien trugen, bis wir im Krankenhaus der Barmherzigen Br&amp;uuml;der in der Praterstra&amp;szlig;e ankamen. Bald gesellte sich zum Paratyphus ein Herzklappenfehler. Auf 48 Kilo abgemagert, sah ich aus wie die von Auschwitz Heimgekehrten, und ich f&amp;uuml;hlte mich dem Tode nahe. Ich hatte den Krieg &amp;uuml;berlebt - und jetzt, da alles vorbei war, sollte ich sterben. Aber ich &amp;uuml;berstand die Krankheit. Und kaum ging es mir etwas besser, zeichnete ich auch schon wieder. Eine Blumenvase in meinem Krankenzimmer, einen Teekessel auf dem Tisch und den Blick aus dem Fenster. Und ich portr&amp;auml;tierte meine Mutter, die mich t&amp;auml;glich besuchte.&lt;br /&gt;Ein Jahr sp&amp;auml;ter war ich, weil ganz Wien hungerte, in Wulfing bei Schwanenstadt bei Bauern zum Erntedienst eingeteilt. Ich bekam zu essen und arbeitete hart. Aber ich f&amp;uuml;hlte mich wie im Paradies und erlebte auf den Feldern zum erstenmal in meinem Leben bewu&amp;szlig;t die Farben der Natur. Hier entwickelte sich in mir der Wandel vom realistischen zum freien Malen. Viel sp&amp;auml;ter erst lernte ich die Modernen - Picasso, Klee, Schiele, Klimt - kennen. Wer in der Nazizeit aufgewachsen ist, hatte von ihrer Existenz nie erfahren.&lt;br /&gt;Ab 1949 war ich st&amp;auml;ndig unterwegs. Es trieb mich hinaus, in die Toskana, nach Paris - alles per Autostopp. Auf so einer Fahrt versuchte mich im Jahre 1953 ein Russe, der mich in seinem Dienstwagen mitnahm, als Agent f&amp;uuml;r den KGB anzuwerben. Er gab mir 150 Schilling, mit denen ich Stadtpl&amp;auml;ne von Wien und Paris besorgen sollte. Ich sagte ihm, bei &amp;bdquo;Freytag und Berndt&amp;ldquo; am Kohlmarkt k&amp;ouml;nnte jeder Mensch all diese Stadtpl&amp;auml;ne kaufen. Er wollte mit diesem &amp;bdquo;Auftrag&amp;ldquo; offensichtlich testen, ob ich als Spion geeignet war. Ich erwies mich als ungeeignet. Die 150 Schilling, die er mir gegeben hatte, behielt ich allerdings.&lt;br /&gt;Wie seinerzeit die Nazis, kamen jetzt die Russen einmal in der Woche, wieder zwischen zwei und drei Uhr nachts, und l&amp;auml;uteten Sturm. Meine arme Mutter stand wieder die schlimmsten &amp;Auml;ngste aus. Ich wagte mich erst wieder nach 1955, als der Staatsvertrag unterzeichnet war und die Russen Wien verlassen hatten, nach Hause.&lt;br /&gt;Sicher steht der Weg, den ich als K&amp;uuml;nstler ging, in urs&amp;auml;chlichem Zusammenhang mit der Situation, in der ich aufgewachsen bin. Meine Jugend als doppelter Au&amp;szlig;enseiter - ohne Vater und als Halbjude - hat nat&amp;uuml;rlich dazu beigetragen, da&amp;szlig; ich viel nachgedacht und mich besonnen habe. Ich wurde zum Einzelg&amp;auml;nger, zum K&amp;auml;mpfer f&amp;uuml;r bestimmte Anliegen, die mir wichtig erschienen. In meiner Kindheit hatte ich keine Gelegenheit, mich einer Gruppe zugeh&amp;ouml;rig zu f&amp;uuml;hlen, und so blieb ich Einzelk&amp;auml;mpfer.&lt;br /&gt;Meine Mutter starb 1972, sie hat noch einige meiner Erfolge miterlebt, zuletzt den Film &amp;bdquo;Hundertwassers Regentag&amp;ldquo;, den Peter Schamoni &amp;uuml;ber mich drehte, worauf sie sehr stolz war. Sie hat sich vor der Urania als normale Kinobesucherin angestellt, um sich eine Karte zu kaufen, was ich sehr r&amp;uuml;hrend fand.&lt;br /&gt;F&amp;uuml;r meine Generation, die damals jung war, gab es nichts anderes als Krieg, wir kannten keinen Frieden. Der allt&amp;auml;gliche Schrecken war eine Selbstverst&amp;auml;ndlichkeit, anders konnte der Alltag in unseren Augen gar nicht sein, so war das Leben. T&amp;auml;gliches Sterben war v&amp;ouml;llig normal. In meinem Hirn als Zehn- bis Vierzehnj&amp;auml;hriger war das ganze Kriegsgeschehen so selbstverst&amp;auml;ndlich wie f&amp;uuml;r einen heutigen Jugendlichen das Auto und die Stra&amp;szlig;enbahn.&lt;br /&gt;Jeder wei&amp;szlig; mittlerweile, da&amp;szlig; Hitler ein wahnsinniger Teufel war, doch ich glaube nicht, da&amp;szlig; ich damals die F&amp;auml;higkeit hatte, Recht von Unrecht zu unterscheiden. Ich empfand den Krieg zwar als etwas Au&amp;szlig;erordentliches, aber nicht als etwas Unrechtes. Viele Leute meines Alters dichten heute in ihre Kriegserlebnisse Dinge hinein, die nicht sein k&amp;ouml;nnen. Wer damals zehn, zw&amp;ouml;lf Jahre alt war und heute sagt, er h&amp;auml;tte erkannt, da&amp;szlig; der Hitler und sein Regime unmenschlich waren, der l&amp;uuml;gt.&lt;br /&gt;Mir hat genauso wie den anderen jungen Burschen die deutsche Wehrmacht imponiert. Mich interessierten die Grenzverschiebungen, die ich mit bunten Nadeln in beide Richtungen - zuerst den Vormarsch, dann den R&amp;uuml;ckzug - absteckte. Was da passierte, das war f&amp;uuml;r einen jungen Menschen ein gro&amp;szlig;es Abenteuer, ein R&amp;auml;uber-und-Gendarm-Spiel.&lt;br /&gt;Aber irgendwie f&amp;uuml;hlte ich doch, da&amp;szlig; einmal andere Zeiten kommen w&amp;uuml;rden. Denn als ein Freund von mir, er hie&amp;szlig; Leopold und wohnte bei uns im Haus in der Oberen Donaustra&amp;szlig;e, zu mir sagte, der einzelne Mensch sei nur ein Spielball der M&amp;auml;chtigen, da habe ich ihm widersprochen. Ich werde dir beweisen, sagte ich, da&amp;szlig; sich auch der einzelne Mensch zur Wehr setzen kann.&lt;br /&gt;Ich war damals, mit meinen dreizehn Jahren, felsenfest davon &amp;uuml;berzeugt, da&amp;szlig; ich eines Tages etwas tun, da&amp;szlig; ich etwas bewegen werde k&amp;ouml;nnen.&lt;/div&gt;', text_keywords-'Autobiographisches, autobiographical, childhood, Kindheit, Jugend, youth, Hitlerjugend, Hitler youth, Halbjude, half jew, Jude, jew, Mutter, mother, family, Familie', text_date-'1990-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_occasion_en-'&lt;div&gt;Text based on Georg Markus&#039;&amp;nbsp; interview with Hundertwasser Hundertwasser, 1990 (Excerpt)&lt;/div&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Text basierend auf einem Interview, das Georg Markus mit Hundertwasser im Jahr 1990 f&amp;uuml;hrte.&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;div&gt;Georg Markus (Ed.), Mein Elternhaus - Ein &amp;ouml;sterreichisches Familienalbum, &lt;br /&gt;Dusseldorf, Vienna, New York: Econ Verlag, 1990 (German)&lt;br /&gt;Schurian, Walter (Ed.): Hundertwasser &amp;ndash; sch&amp;ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &amp;uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. [Hundertwasser - Beautiful Paths, Thoughts on Art and Life], Munich: Langen M&amp;uuml;ller, 2004, pp. 49 - 55&amp;nbsp; (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Georg Markus (Hg.), Mein Elternhaus - Ein &amp;ouml;sterreichisches Familienalbum, &lt;br /&gt;D&amp;uuml;sseldorf, Wien, New York: Econ Verlag, 1990&lt;br /&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &amp;ndash; sch&amp;ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &amp;uuml;ber Kunst und Leben.&lt;br /&gt;M&amp;uuml;nchen: Langen M&amp;uuml;ller, 2004, S. 49-55&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-15 15:25:49.1716###object###text###1.4.0.0.5###BETWEEN HITLER YOUTH AND STAR OF DAVID
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.0.0.5&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;My father died when I was one year old; probably as a result of appendicitis. In my mind, he is only a photograph. My mother never talked much about him and when she did, not really in a positive sense. She seemed to be his superior in every way, and therefore everything had rested on her shoulders even while he was alive. My father was one of hundreds of thousands jobless people in the late 1920s, while my mother earned our money as an employee of the Creditanstalt bank, from which we could barely live.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; At first in a municipal flat in the Johnstra&szlig;e in the district F&uuml;nfhaus in Vienna, not far from Sch&ouml;nbrunn. But there were worlds between the imperial glory of the castle and our small flat. We were poor, there was only a kitchenette, which made my mother very angry. Our second flat in the Brunhildengasse nearby wasn&rsquo;t much better.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Who could guess that these lodgings were luxurious compared with those awaiting us in the years to follow? After we had heard the words of Chancellor Kurt Schuschnigg &ndash; &ldquo;God protect Austria&rdquo; &ndash; in the radio on 11 March 1938, my mother told me that we had to expect hard times from then on. I was to understand the reason for these words very much later. My mother was a Jewess. We stayed at home when Hitler&rsquo;s troops marched into the country. When we ventured out into the street again, we, too, wore swastikas, for anybody who didn&rsquo;t was suspect and bound to be abused.&amp;nbsp; It was a simple, primitive protection: a small pin on the shirt or blouse, and we went unmolested. Neither of us was a hero. There were only two alternatives: to get jostled, fist on eye, bloody nose &ndash; or a swastika on the lapel. We decided in favor of the latter.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Which didn&rsquo;t alter the fact that we had to leave our flat after a few months. The district Leopoldstadt had been declared Jewish ghetto, and this was where a flat was allocated to us. But there we stayed only a few hours. For, while my mother was unpacking furniture, dishes and clothes, some anti-Semite painted &ldquo;Gr&uuml;nspan&rdquo; on our door. Herschel Gr&uuml;nspan, a Polish Jew whose parents had been deported by the Nazis, had just assassinated Ernst von Rath, the German envoy accredited to Paris, which the Germans avenged in the so-called Pogrom Night, the Night of the Broken Glass against the Jews. Now they called us &ldquo;Gr&uuml;nspan&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; When the janitor of the house in Leopoldstadt requested my mother to remove the &ldquo;Gr&uuml;nspan&rdquo;-lettering at her own cost, she got so angry that she decided to leave the flat immediately. I had just returned from a trip with my scooter and was rather surprised by the news of the imminent move. This time it was to a flat in the Obere Donaustra&szlig;e, where my grandmother and my aunt Ida lived. We spent the whole war in a small room of this apartment.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I was half-Jewish and a member of the Hitler Youth. And this wasn&rsquo;t so paradoxical as it may sound today. It was a necessity to survive. When the harassment began to become unbearable in 1942 &ndash; we heard of the first deportations to the camps; Jews had to be called Sara and Israel -, my relatives had the idea that I ought to join the Hitler Youth as a protection for the family, which I did. Whenever necessary I wore the swastika, an armband and the HY cap.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; In fact, members of the SS in uniform turned up at our house several times, around 2 in the morning. They leant on the bell, insisted that all Jews leave the apartment; we should be picked up in an hour. Always when the bell rang by night, I put on swastika, armband and cap at lightning speed and opened the door for the frightening SS-people. I showed them a box with my father&rsquo;s medals for bravery and my uncle&rsquo;s Iron Cross from World War I. Surprisingly, this somehow impressed them and they left us alone for a while. Some months later, the procedure was repeated: leaning on the bell, men in SS uniforms, father&rsquo;s World War medals, men leaving. This way I could delay my grandmother&rsquo;s and aunt&rsquo;s deportation by a year.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; At the third occasion, it weren&rsquo;t the SS people, but Jewish collaborators, who &ndash; in order to survive themselves &ndash; picked up other Jews for deportation. Both my aunt as well as my grandmother were abducted. They died in the concentration camp. Same as more than eighty other relatives, uncles, aunts, nieces, nephews, cousins &ndash; my mother once made a list &ndash; who became victims of the Nazi regime. My aunt Gisela in Berlin and her daughter, my mother and I were the only survivors of a once huge family. Our survival was due to the fact that chiefly full Jews were deported. I was protected by being half Jewish, and my full Jewish mother was protected because she had a half Jewish son. The half Jew was able to protect the full Jew.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; It was much later that I realized the perversion of the situation. While my mother went shopping wearing the Star of David, I walked around with the swastika. But when the normal situation becomes perverted, perversion is normal. I knew Jews who believed that if they would fight for Hitler and work hard for him, he wouldn&rsquo;t hurt them. Many a &ldquo;non-Aryan&rdquo; said: Hitler is a good man, he just wants us to work for him. I remember our neighbors, the Jewish family Blau, in the Obere Donaustra&szlig;e. Their opinion was: Hitler doesn&rsquo;t wish to do us any harm, he just wants us to be upright and honest. They felt themselves to be good Germans and could not understand that they were disapproved of for religious, racist or any other reasons. There even were Jews who agreed with the Nazi watchword that the Jews were to blame for everything. Even my mother thought that the Polish Jews were responsible for the anti-Semitism. &lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We also thought that, when my grandmother and aunt were picked up, that they were brought &ldquo;only&rdquo; to a labor camp. There were rumors which whispered worse things, but nobody could believe that any regime would kill the inhabitants of its own country. One clung to the hope that the rumor would turn out to be untrue. Right to the end, we never believed the worst.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The Hitler Youth (Hitlerjugend &ndash; HJ) never found out that in my case, this abbreviation didn&rsquo;t mean just that, but also Half Jew. It was a miracle that this organization never realized this fact, but certainly my father&rsquo;s Aryan name Stowasser helped a great deal. We of the Hitler Youth used to meet regularly, sang Hitler songs, marched to the Prater, where once a military attack was simulated.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; When we had to choose a branch of arms in the last days of the War, my decision was the radio operations, because this seemed to me least dangerous. After I had passed the radio operator&rsquo;s exam, our bell rang and some colleagues from the Hitler Youth wanted me to join them to go to war.&amp;nbsp; The Russians meanwhile had reached Burgenland. In an attack of madness, which later turned out to be cleverness, I declared: I cannot go with you, I am half Jewish. The colleagues from the Hitler Youth went away shocked, but didn&rsquo;t report the affair in the general chaos of war. My &ldquo;confession&rdquo; to be half Jewish saved my life. When the shooting started in Vienna, I saw a detachment of my friends of the Hitler Youth, fifteen, sixteen years old like myself, marching in the direction of the St. Stephen&rsquo;s cathedral with bazookas over their shoulders. And none of them returned alive.&lt;br&gt;----------------&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I attended the first grade of elementary school in 1935, at the Montessori school, which had been founded a short time before. This school was well known for its liberal teaching methods. Every child was allowed to do whatever it wished to do, so I immediately started to paint, and my report confirmed &ldquo;exceptional sense of colors and shapes&rdquo;. On the other hand I was unable to add up three and three after a year. This as well as the fact that the Montessori school was too expensive induced my mother to send me to a public elementary school. I had to drop out of the secondary school &ldquo;for racist reasons&rdquo; after five years, then attended a commercial school and finally graduated after the war.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Already in the Schuschnigg era, my mother had me baptized &ldquo;for safety&rsquo;s sake&rdquo;. &lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-119&quot;&gt; 119&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;And it was in a Catholic church in the 15th district that I saw a picture of the Madonna which let me wish to become a painter. This resolution was also influenced by the flowers which I picked in the Vienna Woods in order to press them between the pages of a book. We used to discuss about how to avoid that the colors should fade. That&rsquo;s when I said to myself, if you paint them instead of pressing them, the colors will remain unchanged. Another impulse was my stamp collection; I wanted to be able to paint such pretty little pictures myself one day. In 1943, I consciously made my first drawings.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-119&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;119 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I often used to stand for hours in front of the window display of a frame shop in the Wallensteinstra&szlig;e, where they showed watercolors which delighted me. Every dot, every line fascinated me. Naturally, these pictures were conventional, upright and honest, just as these times required. I, too, painted my first watercolors, exactly in this style reminding of Hitler&rsquo;s picture postcards, and I was always very happy when I succeeded to draw something that could be identified. Flowers, landscapes, houses and still lives were my favorite subjects.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; In a small suitcase, which I carried around everywhere, I had a carefully rolled watercolor painted by me in order to be able to prove that I was a painter &ndash; just in case.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;[&hellip;]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-120&quot;&gt; 120&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Doubtless the road I chose as an artist is causally connected with the situation in which I grew up. My youth as a double outsider &ndash; without a father and being half Jewish &ndash; has naturally contributed to my reflecting a lot and becoming aware. I became a lone wolf, a fighter for certain matters which seemed important to me. During my childhood I didn&rsquo;t have the chance to feel part of a group and thus remained a solo combatant.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-120&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;120 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;[&hellip;]&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', txt-'1.4.0.0.5', text_type-'Prose', text_category-'', text_title_en-'BETWEEN HITLER YOUTH AND STAR OF DAVID', text_title_ge-'ZWISCHEN &quot;HJ&quot; UND JUDENSTERN', text_contents_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Mein Vater starb, als ich ein Jahr alt war, vermutlich an den Folgen einer Blinddarmentz&amp;uuml;ndung. Er ist mir nur als Fotografie pr&amp;auml;sent. Meine Mutter hat nie besonders viel und wenn, dann nicht besonders gut von ihm gesprochen. Sie war ihm wohl in allem &amp;uuml;berlegen, und daher lastete, auch als er noch da war, alles auf ihren Schultern. Mein Vater war in den sp&amp;auml;ten zwanziger Jahren einer von Hunderttausenden Arbeitslosen, meine Mutter hat als Angestellte der Creditanstalt das Geld beschafft, von dem wir recht und schlecht leben konnten.&lt;br /&gt;Zun&amp;auml;chst in einer Gemeindewohnung in der Johnstra&amp;szlig;e in Wien-F&amp;uuml;nfhaus, nicht weit von Sch&amp;ouml;nbrunn. Doch zwischen der imperialen Pracht des Schlosses und unserer kleinen Wohnung lagen Welten. Wir waren arm, es gab nur eine Kochnische, was meine Mutter sehr ge&amp;auml;rgert hat. Auch unsere zweite Wohnung in der nahen Brunhildengasse bot nicht viel mehr.&lt;br /&gt;Wer h&amp;auml;tte gedacht, da&amp;szlig; diese Unterk&amp;uuml;nfte luxuri&amp;ouml;s waren gegen das, was uns in den folgenden Jahren erwartete? Nachdem wir die Worte des Bundeskanzlers Kurt Schuschnigg - &amp;bdquo;Gott sch&amp;uuml;tze &amp;Ouml;sterreich&amp;ldquo; - am 11. M&amp;auml;rz 1938 im Radio geh&amp;ouml;rt hatten, sagte meine Mutter zu mir, es k&amp;auml;men jetzt schlechte Zeiten auf uns zu. Den Grund daf&amp;uuml;r sollte ich erst viel sp&amp;auml;ter verstehen. Meine Mutter war J&amp;uuml;din. W&amp;auml;hrend des Einmarsches der Hitler-Truppen blieben wir zu Hause. Als wir uns wieder auf die Stra&amp;szlig;e wagten, hatten auch wir Hakenkreuze angesteckt, denn jeder, der dies nicht tat, war suspekt und lief Gefahr, angep&amp;ouml;belt zu werden. Es war ein ganz einfacher, primitiver Schutz: Eine kleine Stecknadel am Hemd oder an der Bluse, und schon wurde man in Ruhe gelassen. Keiner von uns war ein Held. Es gab nur zwei M&amp;ouml;glichkeiten: angerempelt werden, Faust aufs Aug&amp;rsquo;, blutige Nase - oder ein Hakenkreuz am Revers. Wir entschieden uns f&amp;uuml;r letzteres.&lt;br /&gt;Was nichts daran &amp;auml;nderte, da&amp;szlig; wir nach einigen Monaten unsere Wohnung verlassen mu&amp;szlig;ten. Der Bezirk Leopoldstadt war zum j&amp;uuml;dischen Ghetto erkl&amp;auml;rt worden, und hier wies man uns eine Wohnung zu. Doch da blieben wir nur ein paar Stunden. Denn w&amp;auml;hrend meine Mutter damit besch&amp;auml;ftigt war, M&amp;ouml;bel, Geschirr und W&amp;auml;sche auszupacken, malte ein Antisemit die Buchstaben &amp;bdquo;Gr&amp;uuml;nspan&amp;ldquo; an unsere Eingangst&amp;uuml;r. Herschel Gr&amp;uuml;nspan, ein polnischer Jude, dessen Eltern von den Nazis deportiert worden waren, hatte kurz zuvor ein Attentat auf den in Paris akkreditierten deutschen Gesandtschaftsrat Ernst vom Rath ver&amp;uuml;bt, worauf sich die Nazis mit der sogenannten Reichskristallnacht an den Juden revanchierten. Jetzt nannte man uns &amp;bdquo;Gr&amp;uuml;nspan&amp;ldquo;.&lt;br /&gt;Als nun unser Hausmeister in der Leopoldstadt von meiner Mutter verlangte, sie m&amp;uuml;sse die &amp;bdquo;Gr&amp;uuml;nspan&amp;ldquo;-Bemalung auf eigene Kosten entfernen lassen, regte sie sich so auf, da&amp;szlig; sie beschlo&amp;szlig;, die Wohnung sofort wieder zu verlassen. Ich kam gerade von einer Ausfahrt mit meinem Tretroller nach Hause und wurde von der Nachricht des neuerlich bevorstehenden Umzugs &amp;uuml;berrascht. Diesmal ging&amp;rsquo;s in eine Wohnung in der Oberen Donaustra&amp;szlig;e, in der meine Gro&amp;szlig;mutter und meine Tante Ida lebten. In einem kleinen Zimmer dieser Wohnung verbrachten wir den ganzen Krieg.&lt;br /&gt;Ich war Halbjude und Mitglied der Hitler-Jugend. Und das ist nicht so paradox gewesen, wie es heute klingen mag. Es war eine &amp;Uuml;berlebensnotwendigkeit. Als die Schikanen 1942 unertr&amp;auml;glich zu werden begannen - man h&amp;ouml;rte von den ersten Lagerverschickungen, Juden mu&amp;szlig;ten sich Sara und Israel nennen -, kam meiner Verwandtschaft die Idee, ich sollte zum Schutz der Familie der HJ beitreten, was ich auch tat. Ich trug, wenn es n&amp;ouml;tig war, das Hakenkreuzzeichen, eine Binde und die HJ-Kappe.&lt;br /&gt;Tats&amp;auml;chlich kamen mehrmals uniformierte SS-Leute, gegen zwei Uhr fr&amp;uuml;h, zu uns nach Hause. Sie l&amp;auml;uteten Sturm, verlangten, da&amp;szlig; alle Juden die Wohnung r&amp;auml;umen mu&amp;szlig;ten, in einer Stunde w&amp;uuml;rden wir geholt. Immer wenn es nachts l&amp;auml;utete, legte ich in Blitzeseile Hakenkreuz, Binde und Kapperl an und &amp;ouml;ffnete den furchterregenden SS-M&amp;auml;nnern die T&amp;uuml;r. Dabei hielt ich ihnen eine Schachtel mit den Tapferkeitsmedaillen meines Vaters und dem Eisernen Kreuz meines Onkels aus dem Ersten Weltkrieg entgegen. &amp;Uuml;berraschenderweise beeindruckte sie das irgendwie, und man lie&amp;szlig; uns wieder f&amp;uuml;r einige Zeit in Ruhe. Monate sp&amp;auml;ter wiederholte sich die Prozedur: Sturml&amp;auml;uten, uniformierte SS, Vaters Weltkriegsorden, die M&amp;auml;nner gehen wieder weg. Auf diese Weise konnte ich die Deportation meiner Gro&amp;szlig;mutter und meiner Tante um ein Jahr verz&amp;ouml;gern.&lt;br /&gt;Beim drittenmal kamen keine SS-Leute, sondern j&amp;uuml;dische Vertrauensleute, die - um selbst zu &amp;uuml;berleben - andere Juden zum Abtransport holten. Nun wurden sowohl meine Tante als auch meine Gro&amp;szlig;mutter verschleppt. Beide starben im Konzentrationslager. Wie &amp;uuml;brigens mehr als achtzig weitere Verwandte, Onkel, Tanten, Nichten, Neffen, Cousins und Cousinen - meine Mutter hat dar&amp;uuml;ber einmal eine Liste angefertigt - Opfer der Naziherrschaft wurden. Meine Tante Gisela aus Berlin und ihre Tochter, meine Mutter und ich waren die einzigen &amp;Uuml;berlebenden der einst riesigen Familie. Wir verdankten das &amp;Uuml;berleben dem Umstand, da&amp;szlig; in erster Linie Volljuden verschickt wurden. Ich war gesch&amp;uuml;tzt, weil ich Halbjude war, und meine vollj&amp;uuml;dische Mutter war gesch&amp;uuml;tzt, weil sie einen halbj&amp;uuml;dischen Sohn hatte. Der Halbjude konnte die Ganzj&amp;uuml;din sch&amp;uuml;tzen.&lt;br /&gt;Die Perversion des Ganzen wurde mir erst viel sp&amp;auml;ter bewu&amp;szlig;t. W&amp;auml;hrend meine Mutter mit dem Judenstern einkaufen ging, lief ich mit dem Hakenkreuz durch die Gegend. Aber wenn der Normalzustand zur Perversion wird, ist das Perverse normal. Ich kannte Juden, die der Meinung waren, wenn sie f&amp;uuml;r Hitler k&amp;auml;mpfen, brav f&amp;uuml;r ihn arbeiten, w&amp;uuml;rde er ihnen nichts tun. So mancher &amp;bdquo;Nichtarier&amp;ldquo; sagte: Der Hitler ist ein braver Mensch, er will nur, da&amp;szlig; wir f&amp;uuml;r ihn arbeiten. Ich erinnere mich an die uns benachbarte j&amp;uuml;dische Familie Blau in der Oberen Donaustra&amp;szlig;e. Da hie&amp;szlig; es: Der Hitler will uns nichts tun, er will nur, da&amp;szlig; wir aufrecht und ehrlich sind. Sie f&amp;uuml;hlten sich als gute Deutsche und konnten nicht verstehen, da&amp;szlig; sie aus religi&amp;ouml;sen, rassischen oder irgendwelchen anderen Gr&amp;uuml;nden abgelehnt w&amp;uuml;rden. Es gab auch Juden, die der Naziparole recht gaben, die Juden seien an allem schuld. Selbst meine Mutter war der Meinung, da&amp;szlig; die polnischen Juden am Antisemitismus schuld seien.&lt;br /&gt;Wir dachten auch, da&amp;szlig; meine Gro&amp;szlig;mutter und meine Tante, als man sie abholte, &amp;bdquo;nur&amp;ldquo; in ein Arbeitslager k&amp;auml;men. Es gab zwar Ger&amp;uuml;chte, die Schlimmeres besagten, aber keiner konnte glauben, da&amp;szlig; ein Regime die Bewohner des eigenen Landes umbringt. Man klammerte sich an die Hoffnung, da&amp;szlig; an dem Ger&amp;uuml;cht nichts dran sei. Bis zum Schlu&amp;szlig; haben wir nicht an das Schlimmste geglaubt.&lt;br /&gt;Bei der HJ wu&amp;szlig;ten sie nicht, da&amp;szlig; dieses K&amp;uuml;rzel f&amp;uuml;r mich nicht nur Hitler-Jugend, sondern auch Halbjude bedeutete. Wie durch ein Wunder kam das bei dieser Organisation nie heraus, wobei mir nat&amp;uuml;rlich der arische Name Stowasser meines Vaters half. Wir von der HJ trafen uns regelm&amp;auml;&amp;szlig;ig, sangen Hitler-Lieder, marschierten in den Prater, wo auch einmal ein milit&amp;auml;rischer Angriff simuliert wurde.&lt;br /&gt;Als es in den letzten Kriegstagen hie&amp;szlig;, wir sollten uns zu einer Waffengattung melden, entschied ich mich f&amp;uuml;r den Funkdienst, der mir am wenigsten gef&amp;auml;hrlich schien. Nachdem ich die Funkerpr&amp;uuml;fung abgelegt hatte, l&amp;auml;utete es an unserer T&amp;uuml;r, ein paar Kollegen von der HJ wollten mich abholen, um mit mir in den Krieg zu ziehen. Die Russen waren zu diesem Zeitpunkt bereits bis ins Burgenland vorgedrungen. In einem Anflug von Wahnsinn, der sich aber als Gescheitheit erweisen sollte, erkl&amp;auml;rte ich: Ich kann nicht kommen, ich bin ein Halbjude. Die HJ-Kollegen gingen erschrocken weg, ohne die Aff&amp;auml;re im allgemeinen Kriegschaos weiterzuleiten. Mir hat das &amp;bdquo; Gest&amp;auml;ndnis&amp;ldquo;, Halbjude zu sein, das Leben gerettet. Ich sah, als in Wien schon geschossen wurde, vor unserer Haust&amp;uuml;r einen Trupp meiner HJ-Freunde, die wie ich f&amp;uuml;nfzehn, sechzehn Jahre alt waren, mit Panzerf&amp;auml;usten &amp;uuml;ber der Schulter Richtung Stephansdom marschieren. Und keiner von ihnen ist lebend zur&amp;uuml;ckgekehrt.&lt;br /&gt;Die erste Volksschulklasse hatte ich 1935 in der kurz zuvor gegr&amp;uuml;ndeten Montessori-Schule besucht, die f&amp;uuml;r ihre liberalen Lehrmethoden bekannt war. Jedes Kind durfte tun und lassen, was es wollte, ich habe sofort gemalt, wof&amp;uuml;r in meinem Zeugnis &amp;bdquo;au&amp;szlig;ergew&amp;ouml;hnliches Farben- und Formengef&amp;uuml;hl&amp;ldquo; attestiert wurde. Daf&amp;uuml;r konnte ich nach einem Jahr noch immer nicht drei und drei zusammenz&amp;auml;hlen. Das und die Tatsache, da&amp;szlig; die Montessori-Schule zu teuer war, bewog meine Mutter, mich in eine &amp;ouml;ffentliche Volksschule zu schicken. Die anschlie&amp;szlig;end besuchte Realschule mu&amp;szlig;te ich nach f&amp;uuml;nf Jahren &amp;bdquo;aus rassischen Gr&amp;uuml;nden&amp;ldquo; verlassen, worauf ich eine Handelsschule besuchte und die Matura nach dem Krieg nachholte.&lt;br /&gt;Noch in der Schuschnigg-Zeit hatte mich meine Mutter &amp;bdquo;sicherheitshalber&amp;ldquo; taufen lassen. Und in einer katholischen Kirche im 15. Bezirk sah ich dann auch ein Madonnenbild, das in mir den Wunsch weckte, Maler zu werden. Wichtig f&amp;uuml;r diesen Entschlu&amp;szlig; waren auch die Blumen, die ich im Wienerwald pfl&amp;uuml;ckte, um sie dann zwischen die Seiten eines Buches zu pressen. Wir haben dar&amp;uuml;ber diskutiert, wie man verhindern k&amp;ouml;nne, da&amp;szlig; die Farben verblassen. Da sagte ich mir, wenn du das malst, statt es zu pressen, bleiben die Farben erhalten. Einen weiteren Ansto&amp;szlig; bot mir meine Briefmarkensammlung, ich wollte selbst einmal so sch&amp;ouml;ne kleine Bilder malen k&amp;ouml;nnen. 1943 habe ich meine ersten Zeichnungen bewu&amp;szlig;t angefertigt.&lt;br /&gt;Ich stand oft stundenlang vor der Auslage einer Rahmenhandlung in der Wallensteinstra&amp;szlig;e, wo Aquarelle zu sehen waren, die mich begeisterten. Jeder Tupfen, jeder Strich faszinierte mich. Nat&amp;uuml;rlich waren die Bilder brav, bieder und anst&amp;auml;ndig, ganz wie es die Zeit verlangte. Auch ich malte meine ersten Aquarelle ganz in diesem Stil, der dem der Hitler-Postkarten &amp;auml;hnelte, und war immer sehr gl&amp;uuml;cklich, wenn es mir gelang, etwas so zu zeichnen, da&amp;szlig; man es erkennen konnte. Blumen, Landschaften, H&amp;auml;user und Stilleben waren meine liebsten Motive.&lt;br /&gt;In einem kleinen Koffer, den ich immer bei mir trug, hatte ich ein sorgsam eingerolltes, von mir gemaltes Aquarell mit, um - im Fall des Falles - beweisen zu k&amp;ouml;nnen, da&amp;szlig; ich Maler bin.&lt;br /&gt;Auch den Donaukanal habe ich mehrmals gemalt, und nicht nur das, ich habe ihn immer wieder schwimmend &amp;uuml;berquert, um mich vor mir selbst zu beweisen. Infolge meiner Schwimmtouren erkrankte ich kurz nach Kriegsende, vermutlich durch eine kleine Hautverletzung, an Paratyphus. Bald war ich so schwach, da&amp;szlig; ich nicht mehr gehen konnte, und ich sehe heute noch vor mir, wie mich zwei M&amp;auml;nner auf einem Brett durch das zerbombte Wien trugen, bis wir im Krankenhaus der Barmherzigen Br&amp;uuml;der in der Praterstra&amp;szlig;e ankamen. Bald gesellte sich zum Paratyphus ein Herzklappenfehler. Auf 48 Kilo abgemagert, sah ich aus wie die von Auschwitz Heimgekehrten, und ich f&amp;uuml;hlte mich dem Tode nahe. Ich hatte den Krieg &amp;uuml;berlebt - und jetzt, da alles vorbei war, sollte ich sterben. Aber ich &amp;uuml;berstand die Krankheit. Und kaum ging es mir etwas besser, zeichnete ich auch schon wieder. Eine Blumenvase in meinem Krankenzimmer, einen Teekessel auf dem Tisch und den Blick aus dem Fenster. Und ich portr&amp;auml;tierte meine Mutter, die mich t&amp;auml;glich besuchte.&lt;br /&gt;Ein Jahr sp&amp;auml;ter war ich, weil ganz Wien hungerte, in Wulfing bei Schwanenstadt bei Bauern zum Erntedienst eingeteilt. Ich bekam zu essen und arbeitete hart. Aber ich f&amp;uuml;hlte mich wie im Paradies und erlebte auf den Feldern zum erstenmal in meinem Leben bewu&amp;szlig;t die Farben der Natur. Hier entwickelte sich in mir der Wandel vom realistischen zum freien Malen. Viel sp&amp;auml;ter erst lernte ich die Modernen - Picasso, Klee, Schiele, Klimt - kennen. Wer in der Nazizeit aufgewachsen ist, hatte von ihrer Existenz nie erfahren.&lt;br /&gt;Ab 1949 war ich st&amp;auml;ndig unterwegs. Es trieb mich hinaus, in die Toskana, nach Paris - alles per Autostopp. Auf so einer Fahrt versuchte mich im Jahre 1953 ein Russe, der mich in seinem Dienstwagen mitnahm, als Agent f&amp;uuml;r den KGB anzuwerben. Er gab mir 150 Schilling, mit denen ich Stadtpl&amp;auml;ne von Wien und Paris besorgen sollte. Ich sagte ihm, bei &amp;bdquo;Freytag und Berndt&amp;ldquo; am Kohlmarkt k&amp;ouml;nnte jeder Mensch all diese Stadtpl&amp;auml;ne kaufen. Er wollte mit diesem &amp;bdquo;Auftrag&amp;ldquo; offensichtlich testen, ob ich als Spion geeignet war. Ich erwies mich als ungeeignet. Die 150 Schilling, die er mir gegeben hatte, behielt ich allerdings.&lt;br /&gt;Wie seinerzeit die Nazis, kamen jetzt die Russen einmal in der Woche, wieder zwischen zwei und drei Uhr nachts, und l&amp;auml;uteten Sturm. Meine arme Mutter stand wieder die schlimmsten &amp;Auml;ngste aus. Ich wagte mich erst wieder nach 1955, als der Staatsvertrag unterzeichnet war und die Russen Wien verlassen hatten, nach Hause.&lt;br /&gt;Sicher steht der Weg, den ich als K&amp;uuml;nstler ging, in urs&amp;auml;chlichem Zusammenhang mit der Situation, in der ich aufgewachsen bin. Meine Jugend als doppelter Au&amp;szlig;enseiter - ohne Vater und als Halbjude - hat nat&amp;uuml;rlich dazu beigetragen, da&amp;szlig; ich viel nachgedacht und mich besonnen habe. Ich wurde zum Einzelg&amp;auml;nger, zum K&amp;auml;mpfer f&amp;uuml;r bestimmte Anliegen, die mir wichtig erschienen. In meiner Kindheit hatte ich keine Gelegenheit, mich einer Gruppe zugeh&amp;ouml;rig zu f&amp;uuml;hlen, und so blieb ich Einzelk&amp;auml;mpfer.&lt;br /&gt;Meine Mutter starb 1972, sie hat noch einige meiner Erfolge miterlebt, zuletzt den Film &amp;bdquo;Hundertwassers Regentag&amp;ldquo;, den Peter Schamoni &amp;uuml;ber mich drehte, worauf sie sehr stolz war. Sie hat sich vor der Urania als normale Kinobesucherin angestellt, um sich eine Karte zu kaufen, was ich sehr r&amp;uuml;hrend fand.&lt;br /&gt;F&amp;uuml;r meine Generation, die damals jung war, gab es nichts anderes als Krieg, wir kannten keinen Frieden. Der allt&amp;auml;gliche Schrecken war eine Selbstverst&amp;auml;ndlichkeit, anders konnte der Alltag in unseren Augen gar nicht sein, so war das Leben. T&amp;auml;gliches Sterben war v&amp;ouml;llig normal. In meinem Hirn als Zehn- bis Vierzehnj&amp;auml;hriger war das ganze Kriegsgeschehen so selbstverst&amp;auml;ndlich wie f&amp;uuml;r einen heutigen Jugendlichen das Auto und die Stra&amp;szlig;enbahn.&lt;br /&gt;Jeder wei&amp;szlig; mittlerweile, da&amp;szlig; Hitler ein wahnsinniger Teufel war, doch ich glaube nicht, da&amp;szlig; ich damals die F&amp;auml;higkeit hatte, Recht von Unrecht zu unterscheiden. Ich empfand den Krieg zwar als etwas Au&amp;szlig;erordentliches, aber nicht als etwas Unrechtes. Viele Leute meines Alters dichten heute in ihre Kriegserlebnisse Dinge hinein, die nicht sein k&amp;ouml;nnen. Wer damals zehn, zw&amp;ouml;lf Jahre alt war und heute sagt, er h&amp;auml;tte erkannt, da&amp;szlig; der Hitler und sein Regime unmenschlich waren, der l&amp;uuml;gt.&lt;br /&gt;Mir hat genauso wie den anderen jungen Burschen die deutsche Wehrmacht imponiert. Mich interessierten die Grenzverschiebungen, die ich mit bunten Nadeln in beide Richtungen - zuerst den Vormarsch, dann den R&amp;uuml;ckzug - absteckte. Was da passierte, das war f&amp;uuml;r einen jungen Menschen ein gro&amp;szlig;es Abenteuer, ein R&amp;auml;uber-und-Gendarm-Spiel.&lt;br /&gt;Aber irgendwie f&amp;uuml;hlte ich doch, da&amp;szlig; einmal andere Zeiten kommen w&amp;uuml;rden. Denn als ein Freund von mir, er hie&amp;szlig; Leopold und wohnte bei uns im Haus in der Oberen Donaustra&amp;szlig;e, zu mir sagte, der einzelne Mensch sei nur ein Spielball der M&amp;auml;chtigen, da habe ich ihm widersprochen. Ich werde dir beweisen, sagte ich, da&amp;szlig; sich auch der einzelne Mensch zur Wehr setzen kann.&lt;br /&gt;Ich war damals, mit meinen dreizehn Jahren, felsenfest davon &amp;uuml;berzeugt, da&amp;szlig; ich eines Tages etwas tun, da&amp;szlig; ich etwas bewegen werde k&amp;ouml;nnen.&lt;/div&gt;', text_keywords-'Autobiographisches, autobiographical, childhood, Kindheit, Jugend, youth, Hitlerjugend, Hitler youth, Halbjude, half jew, Jude, jew, Mutter, mother, family, Familie', text_date-'1990-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_occasion_en-'&lt;div&gt;Text based on Georg Markus&#039;&amp;nbsp; interview with Hundertwasser Hundertwasser, 1990 (Excerpt)&lt;/div&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Text basierend auf einem Interview, das Georg Markus mit Hundertwasser im Jahr 1990 f&amp;uuml;hrte.&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;div&gt;Georg Markus (Ed.), Mein Elternhaus - Ein &amp;ouml;sterreichisches Familienalbum, &lt;br /&gt;Dusseldorf, Vienna, New York: Econ Verlag, 1990 (German)&lt;br /&gt;Schurian, Walter (Ed.): Hundertwasser &amp;ndash; sch&amp;ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &amp;uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. [Hundertwasser - Beautiful Paths, Thoughts on Art and Life], Munich: Langen M&amp;uuml;ller, 2004, pp. 49 - 55&amp;nbsp; (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Georg Markus (Hg.), Mein Elternhaus - Ein &amp;ouml;sterreichisches Familienalbum, &lt;br /&gt;D&amp;uuml;sseldorf, Wien, New York: Econ Verlag, 1990&lt;br /&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &amp;ndash; sch&amp;ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &amp;uuml;ber Kunst und Leben.&lt;br /&gt;M&amp;uuml;nchen: Langen M&amp;uuml;ller, 2004, S. 49-55&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-22 12:36:38.2533###object###text###1.4.2.1###LIKE ENTRANCE MONEY INTO PARADISE

[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.2.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.2.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Copper, silver and gold are at least as noble as lapislazuli, ultramarine, linen, linseed-oil, polivinyl acetate, paper, eggs and grinded bricks. I designed the coins in the size of a soup plate; then the modeller forms it into plaster, and I continue to shape it until it is ready to be reduced to coin size. So the coins are not copies of my paintings. &lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-80&quot;&gt; 80&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;When I was first asked to make coins, I was very, very sceptical and almost against it. But this is always so when I am offered to work with a new material, if it is lithography, engraving, tapestry, silkscreen or glass.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-80&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;80 &lt;/span&gt; But afterwards, when I had my first results in hand, at first soup plate size in plaster, then coin size, I got more and more enthusiastic. Now, I carry the first coins always with me in my pocket as small works of art which I show to everybody. They are not money-coins in the usual sense because they are no legal currency. Maybe one could pay with my coins? That would be wonderful. My coins have no face and revers as usual but only a front side. On the revers there are embossed seals, stamps representing the hall-mark, the modeller&rsquo;s sign, the seal of the Austrian Mint, the editor&rsquo;s sign and the copyright sign, the year, the title and number of the work, the running edition number and my signature in gothic letters and in Japanese. Furthermore, the coins are not round but have irregular edges. The metal will be denaturated. The silver will be blackened with sulphur and will not look like new silver anymore. The copper will be darkened or greened by means of acid to get a verdigris aspect like the old Roman coins. The result is extraordinary. It is like things hundred or thousand years old, mysterious like ancient engravings, like very old rediscovered treasures. &lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-121&quot;&gt; 121&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;If you hold such a heavy peace of metal in your hand with all its light and shadow effects and the black and verdigris in the depths, you feel as if you walked into a wonderland. The plastic forms create a new dimension. The unreal of my shapes and forms becomes real to touch and feel even for the blind. Therefore, it becomes twice unreal because such shapes and forms must not be and can not be real. Otherwise we would already be in paradise.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-121&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;121 &lt;/span&gt; It is really incredible to be able to carry such a picture in the pocket of your trousers without it getting worn out or ugly. On the contrary. It becomes always better and more beautiful. From time to time, you touch it with your fingers, you take it out of your pocket and look at it all wet in the pouring rain or in the bath under the water or in a glass of water or in the sun or it shines at candle light when you turn and turn it about. And when night comes you feel the forms with your hands. At night, under the blanket when you are lonely or when you lie sick in a hospital bed between sterile walls, or when you die alone, I think it is beautiful to have something like this in your hand. You can warm yourself with it like with a hot stone. Or cool yourself like with a snow crystal or with a piece of blue ice. You can put the coins into fire or into water. Here, all my worlds are concentrated and represented like a beautiful d&eacute;j&agrave;-vu of Eden. It is like a renaissance, like a resurrection in a new dimension. It is like entrance money into paradise. ', id-126, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-126, txt-'1.4.2.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'LIKE ENTRANCE MONEY INTO PARADISE', text_title_ge-'', text_keywords-'', text_date-'1978-10-01', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_language-en, text_contents-'Copper, silver and gold are at least as noble as lapislazuli, ultramarine, linen, linseed-oil, polivinyl acetate, paper, eggs and grinded bricks. I designed the coins in the size of a soup plate; then the modeller forms it into plaster, and I continue to shape it until it is ready to be reduced to coin size. So the coins are not copies of my paintings. When I was first asked to make coins, I was very, very sceptical and almost against it. But this is always so when I am offered to work with a new material, if it is lithography, engraving, tapestry, silkscreen or glass. But afterwards, when I had my first results in hand, at first soup plate size in plaster, then coin size, I got more and more enthusiastic. Now, I carry the first coins always with me in my pocket as small works of art which I show to everybody. They are not money-coins in the usual sense because they are no legal currency. Maybe one could pay with my coins? That would be wonderful. My coins have no face and revers as usual but only a front side. On the revers there are embossed seals, stamps representing the hall-mark, the modeller&rsquo;s sign, the seal of the Austrian Mint, the editor&rsquo;s sign and the copyright sign, the year, the title and number of the work, the running edition number and my signature in gothic letters and in Japanese. Furthermore, the coins are not round but have irregular edges. The metal will be denaturated. The silver will be blackened with sulphur and will not look like new silver anymore. The copper will be darkened or greened by means of acid to get a verdigris aspect like the old Roman coins. The result is extraordinary. It is like things hundred or thousand years old, mysterious like ancient engravings, like very old rediscovered treasures. If you hold such a heavy peace of metal in your hand with all its light and shadow effects and the black and verdigris in the depths, you feel as if you walked into a wonderland. The plastic forms create a new dimension. The unreal of my shapes and forms becomes real to touch and feel even for the blind. Therefore, it becomes twice unreal because such shapes and forms must not be and can not be real. Otherwise we would already be in paradise. It is really incredible to be able to carry such a picture in the pocket of your trousers without it getting worn out or ugly. On the contrary. It becomes always better and more beautiful. From time to time, you touch it with your fingers, you take it out of your pocket and look at it all wet in the pouring rain or in the bath under the water or in a glass of water or in the sun or it shines at candle light when you turn and turn it about. And when night comes you feel the forms with your hands. At night, under the blanket when you are lonely or when you lie sick in a hospital bed between sterile walls, or when you die alone, I think it is beautiful to have something like this in your hand. You can warm yourself with it like with a hot stone. Or cool yourself like with a snow crystal or with a piece of blue ice. You can put the coins into fire or into water. Here, all my worlds are concentrated and represented like a beautiful d&eacute;j&agrave;-vu of Eden. It is like a renaissance, like a resurrection in a new dimension. It is like entrance money into paradise. ', text_contents_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Kupfer, Silber, Gold sind zumindest genauso edel wie Ultramarin, Leinen, Polivinylacetat-Leim, Lein&ouml;l, Eier und zerriebene Ziegel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Die M&uuml;nzen entwerfe ich pers&ouml;nlich und arbeite eigenh&auml;ndig an der Gipsform weiter, nachdem der Modelleur die Form in Tellergr&ouml;&szlig;e vorgestaltet hat. Es sind also keine Kopien von Bildern.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Als ich gebeten wurde, M&uuml;nzen zu entwerfen, war ich sehr, sehr skeptisch und fast dagegen. Das ist aber immer so, wenn man mir ein neues Material zum Arbeiten anbietet, sei es Kupferstich, Litho, Gobelin, Seidensieb oder Glas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Dann jedoch, als ich die ersten Resultate in Tellergr&ouml;&szlig;e in Gips, dann in M&uuml;nzgr&ouml;&szlig;e in der Hand hatte, war ich mehr und mehr begeistert. Jetzt trage ich die ersten M&uuml;nzen st&auml;ndig bei mir im Sack herum als kleine Kunstwerke, die ich allen zeige.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Es sind keine M&uuml;nzen im &uuml;blichen Sinn, denn es ist kein Zahlungsmittel. Aber vielleicht kann man doch mit meinen M&uuml;nzen zahlen? Das w&auml;re wunderbar.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Die M&uuml;nzen haben keinen Kopf und Adler, also nur eine Vorderseite. Hinten sind nur Stempel des Feingehaltes, Zeichen des Modelleurs, Jahr, Zeichen des &Ouml;sterreichischen M&uuml;nzamtes, des Herausgebers, das Copyrightzeichen, Titel und Oeuvrenummer, fortlaufende Auflagennummer und meine Signatur in Kurrentschrift und in Japanisch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Au&szlig;erdem sind die M&uuml;nzen nicht rund, sondern haben einen unregelm&auml;&szlig;igen Rand. Und das Metall wird denaturiert. Silber wird schwarz und schaut nicht wie Silber aus. Kupfer wird dunkel oder gr&uuml;nspangr&uuml;n und wird wie alte r&ouml;mische M&uuml;nzen aussehen. &Uuml;berhaupt ist das Resultat verbl&uuml;ffend, so wie Werke aus dem vorigen Jahrhundert oder Jahrtausend, und so geheimnisvoll wie alte Stiche, wie alte, wiedergefundene Sch&auml;tze.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Wenn man so ein St&uuml;ck Metall so schwer in der Hand hat mit seinen Licht- und Schattenwirkungen und den Schw&auml;rzungen und Gr&uuml;nungen in den Tiefen, glaubt man, in ein Wunderland zu schreiten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;&quot;&gt;Die Plastizit&auml;t erzeugt eine neue Dimension. Das Irreale meiner Formenwelt wird real, abtastbar, f&uuml;hlbar, auch f&uuml;r Blinde, und daher doppelt irreal, weil es solche Formen real nicht geben darf, nicht geben kann auf Erden, oder wir w&auml;ren schon im Paradies. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Es ist wirklich unglaublich, so ein Bild im Hosensack zu tragen, ohne da&szlig; es sich abnutzt, und dabei immer besser wird. Ab und zu f&uuml;hlt man danach, zieht es aus der Tasche oder dem Portemonnaie und betrachtet es, na&szlig; in str&ouml;mendem Regen oder im Bad unter Wasser, im Wasserglas oder in der Sonne, oder es blitzt, wenn man es im Kerzenlicht hin- und herdreht.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Und wenn es Nacht ist, ertastet man die Formen mit den Fingern. Im Bett nachts unter der Decke, wenn man einsam ist oder wenn man krank im Spitalbett zwischen sterilen W&auml;nden liegt, oder wenn man alleine stirbt, glaube ich, ist es sch&ouml;n, so etwas in H&auml;nden zu haben. Man kann sich daran w&auml;rmen wie an einem hei&szlig;en Stein. Oder k&uuml;hlen wie an einem Schneekristall oder einem St&uuml;ck aus blauem Eis. Man kann es ins Feuer legen oder ins Wasser.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Alle meine Welten sind hier konzentriert und schemenhaft zugleich vertreten, so wie eine Wiedergeburt, eine Wiederauferstehung in einer neuen Dimension. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Es ist so etwas wie Eintrittsgeld ins Paradies.&lt;/p&gt;  ', text_occasion_en-'&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: &#039;Times New Roman&#039;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: &#039;Times New Roman&#039;&quot;&gt;Written in Kaurinui on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: &#039;Times New Roman&#039;&quot;&gt;1 October 1978 &lt;/span&gt;on occasion of his designs for coins.&lt;/span&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Anl&auml;sslich der Entw&uuml;rfe f&uuml;r M&uuml;nzen 1978.&lt;/p&gt;  ', text_published_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser Coin catalogue, Gruener Janura AG: Glarus/Switzerland, 1978, pp. 3-6&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Deutscher Taschenbuch Verlag (dtv): Munich, 1983, pp. 80-82 and ed. 2004 (Langen M&uuml;ller Verlag, Munich), pp. 97-98 (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 1022-1023 (German and English)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_published_ge-'  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Katalog zu den Hundertwasser M&uuml;nzen, Gruener Janura AG: Glarus/Schweiz, 1978, S. 10-15&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Deutscher Taschenbuch Verlag (dtv): M&uuml;nchen 1983, S. 80-82 und Ausgabe 2004 (Langen M&uuml;ller Verlag, M&uuml;nchen), S. 97-98&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 1022-1023 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  ', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'', text_translator-'', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-22 13:17:31.7022###object###text###1.4.5.1###TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.5.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-124&quot;&gt; 124&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-124&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;124 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', id-130, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-130, txt-'1.4.5.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?', text_title_ge-'', text_keywords-'', text_date-'1994-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_language-en, text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In Sache &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird die &ouml;sterreichische &Ouml;ffentlichkeit von den staatlichen Medien einer dogmatischen Gehirnw&auml;sche ohnegleichen ausgesetzt. Es herrscht im Fernsehen, im Radio und fast in der gesamten Presse eine infame verschleierte Zensur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich w&uuml;rde das auch nicht in einer Demokratie f&uuml;r m&ouml;glich halten, h&auml;tte ich diese Art von Zensur nicht selbst erlebt. Unter allerlei Pr&auml;texten und Vorw&auml;nden wurde ich mehrmals behindert und verhindert,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; &ouml;ffentlich&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; eine Anti-&lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Meinung zu vertreten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Vorw&auml;nde waren: es passe nicht in die Sendung, ich d&uuml;rfe nichts vorlesen, ich w&auml;re daf&uuml;r nicht zust&auml;ndig, ich w&auml;re verr&uuml;ckt oder aber man versucht mit gezielter Diffamation mich unglaubw&uuml;rdig zu machen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dabei sind meine Bedenken und &Auml;ngste in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten selbst l&auml;ngst best&auml;tigt. Warum h&ouml;rt man nicht auf Leopold Kohr (Das Ende der Gro&szlig;en), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (Small is beautiful), Jimmy Goldsmith (Le pi&egrave;ge - et si nous avions suivi la mauvaise route?), Henry Coston (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe des banquiers), Jean Pierre Chevenement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe Seguin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (Cacciamo i mercanti dal tempio dell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europa), Gerard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht-Partei), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (Ex-EU-Kommissar: &quot;k&uuml;nstliche Superkonstruktion nicht lebensf&auml;hig&quot;), Denis de Rougemont (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe doit se faire pour la diversit&eacute;) und unz&auml;hlige andere Warner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich ist von der Geschichte auserw&auml;hlt, Beispiel und Zentrum und Halt in Mitteleuropa zu sein. &Ouml;sterreich ist eine Br&uuml;cke der Hoffnung zum Osten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wir haben seit dem Krieg in m&uuml;hevoller Arbeit ein riesiges Kapital an Wohlstand, innerem Frieden, internationalem Respekt und Glaubw&uuml;rdigkeit aufgebaut als unabh&auml;ngige, liebenswerte, friedliebende Kulturnation im Herzen Europas. Das kann nicht kurzsichtig und verantwortungslos aufs Spiel gesetzt werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt nach dem Zerfall der kommunistischen Diktatur und der &Ouml;ffnung der Grenzen muss sich &Ouml;sterreich seiner Verantwortung in Europa bewusst werden und darf sich nicht selbst eliminieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mit einer uns suggerierten Torschlusspanik wird eine Anschlussneurose erzeugt. Angst vor was oder wem? Welche Feinde hat &Ouml;sterreich? Wer sollte und warum &Ouml;sterreichs Sicherheit gef&auml;hrden? Gerade durch den Anschluss an einen Milit&auml;rblock w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich als &quot;Randgebiet Ostmark&quot; erst zum Aufmarschgebiet und zum Feindbild und Angriffsziel werden (Warnung von Erwin Lanc). Gegen atomare Bedrohung ist kein Kraut gewachsen und bei Regionalkriegen - siehe Bosnien - gibt es keinen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Schutz, nicht einmal in Nordirland, innerhalb der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;t ist gerade jetzt n&ouml;tiger als je zuvor. Man muss die Neutralit&auml;t beim Namen nennen und zu ihr stehen. Neutralit&auml;t ist ein wahrer Wert. Die immerw&auml;hrende Neutralit&auml;t ist das Fundament unseres Staates und darf nicht verraten und ausgeh&ouml;hlt werden. Wenn wir dieses Fundament unterminieren, zerst&ouml;ren wir diesen unseren Staat &Ouml;sterreich, der darauf errichtet ist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ab jetzt bedeutet die Neutralit&auml;t &Ouml;sterreichs Selbst&auml;ndigkeit, Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit, Verantwortung tragen, Beispiel geben, eine aktive Neutralit&auml;t. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch hier ist die Schweiz ein Beispiel und wird auch im Staatsvertrag als Beispiel genannt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es besteht kein Anlass, gerade jetzt einen Graben quer durch Europa zu ziehen. Es ist so als ob &ouml;stlich von Wien Feindesland w&auml;re.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Die Grenzposten werden von Deutschland an den eben beseitigten Eisernen Vorhang verlegt!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp; Diese neue Grenzziehung ist nicht nur quer durch Europa, sondern quer durch &Ouml;sterreich, wo die Donaumonarchie war. Es w&auml;re verantwortungslos und gef&auml;hrlich, durch den Anschluss an eine wirtschaftliche und politische &Uuml;bermacht das Gef&auml;lle zu und die Bedrohung f&uuml;r die L&auml;nder &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; zu vergr&ouml;&szlig;ern. &Ouml;sterreichs kulturelle, wirtschaftliche und geschichtliche Bestimmung, &Ouml;sterreichs Verantwortung und Ausstrahlung liegt im Osten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;(Das besagt auch der Name &Ouml;sterreich.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Fronten haben sich gewandelt. Es sind nicht mehr die politischen Grenzen, sondern die Front verl&auml;uft zwischen der brutalen, nur wirtschaftsinteressierten Wegwerfgesellschaft und der ausgebeuteten Natur und der zerst&ouml;rten Seele des Menschen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt einen neuen Widerstand und schon wieder feige Kollaborateure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die jetzt verantwortlichen Politiker sind Hampelm&auml;nner der Wirtschaftsinteressen und heucheln Umweltbewusstsein und Kulturbewusstsein mit Lippenbekenntnissen. Sie beschlie&szlig;en umweltzerst&ouml;rende und kulturzerst&ouml;rende Ma&szlig;nahmen, die unsere Zukunft in Frage stellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die sogenannte &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; betreibt die brutale Vernichtung unserer Lebensbasis, unserer uralten Kulturen, unserer kleinen, gewachsenen Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten, unseres Artenreichtums und unserer Selbstachtung.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Handelsvertretung des Gro&szlig;unternehmertums, der Gewerkschaften, Genossenschaften, der Gro&szlig;banken, der Giftkonzerne, der Monokultur-Monopolisten und der Atom-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;obby, die uns wie brave Schafe gemeinsam wie das Schlachtvieh in einen Zug in die falsche Richtung verladen will.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dieser riesigen Wirtschaftsmafia geht es nur um Macht und Geld und nicht um das Wohl der Natur und des Menschen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine von verantwortungslosen Schreibtischstrategen ferngesteuerte gigantische Fehlplanung zerst&ouml;rt die Fundamente unseres &uuml;ber uralte Zeiten gewachsenen Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa erlebt die gr&ouml;&szlig;te Vergewaltigung seiner Geschichte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus Br&uuml;ssel kommt keine geistige und kulturelle Erneuerung Europas. Von dort kommen keine Antworten auf die Fragen, die das Gewissen der V&ouml;lker Europas beunruhigen (Alberto Miele). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus dieser neuen Hegemonie kommen keine Botschaften, die die Identit&auml;t, unsere uralten Werte, die Inhalte unserer Zivilisation und die Sehns&uuml;chte der Menschen Europas betreffen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wo sind die Kulturen, die Religionen, die Philosophien, die ein neues europ&auml;isches Zeitalter aus der Taufe heben?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt, wo unsere Gesellschaft die Grenzen des Wachstums erreicht, ist Dezentralisierung unsere einzige &Uuml;berlebenschance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein Anschluss an diese &uuml;berm&auml;chtige Zentralgewalt, die noch immer Wirtschaftswachstum als Zentraldogma gegen alle Evidenz durchziehen will, hat f&uuml;r alle Beteiligten katastrophale Folgen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wohin diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; uns mithineinziehen will, ist ein gnadenloser Konkurrenzkampf, ein Amoklauf in eine gro&szlig;e, gef&auml;hrliche Illusion, in die Sackgasse des Wirtschaftswachstums. Es w&auml;re Wahnsinn, diesem exklusiven Klub der Wegwerfgesellschaft beizutreten, der sich selbst in den M&uuml;ll wirft und ad absurdum f&uuml;hrt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das Produkt &quot;EU&quot; so gut ist, warum muss man derart intensiv daf&uuml;r werben? Und dieser verd&auml;chtige Zeitdruck: Wir m&uuml;ssen uns sofort enteignen, sonst ist es zu sp&auml;t! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Alle guten Dinge geschehen langsam in einem organischen Ablauf von selbst. Einen Baum kann man auch nicht mit Drohungen &uuml;berzeugen und &uuml;berreden, da&szlig; er im tiefen Winter zu bl&uuml;hen hat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe nicht, warum man uns mit Gewalt &uuml;berreden will, die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;, dieses sinkende Schiff zu besteigen, und zwar sofort.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Titanic. Die Analogien zum Untergang der Titanic sind erschreckend. Hier wie dort: Konzeptlosigkeit, Gr&ouml;&szlig;enwahn, Ma&szlig;losigkeit, blinde Technologiegl&auml;ubigkeit und Geschwindigkeitswahn um jeden Preis. Dort das Rennen um das &quot;blaue Band&quot; in die t&ouml;dlichen Eisberge, hier das m&ouml;rderische Wettrennen an die Grenzen des Wachstums der Wegwerfgesellschaft, die unsere Umwelt und uns selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;So einen &quot;europ&auml;ischen Ungl&uuml;cksdampfer&quot; besteigt man nicht und vertraut man unser Leben und unsere Zukunft nicht an. Da ist es besser, man bleibt in einem kleinen, aber man&ouml;vrierbaren Boot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In praktisch der ganzen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; geht es wild zu: Nordirland, Baskenland, Korsika, Mafia, Comorra, Ausl&auml;nderverfolgungen, Rassenhass und Pogrome, Diskriminierung von Gr&ouml;nl&auml;ndern, Macedoniern und Bretonen, brutale Streiks, blutige Ausschreitungen, Studentenrevolten, Drogenkriminalit&auml;t, nukleare St&ouml;rf&auml;lle, verw&uuml;stete Landstriche, Apathie und Katastrophenstimmung, Jugendkriminalit&auml;t, bald 20 Millionen Arbeitslose und eine Staatsspaltung in Flamen und Wallonen, ausgerechnet in Br&uuml;ssel, dem Sitz der &quot;Europ&auml;ischen Union&quot;. Im Vergleich dazu haben das &quot;isolierte &Ouml;sterreich&quot; und die skandinavischen L&auml;nder, die man unbedingt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; treiben will, es &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; noch gut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; mit Menschenschicksalen jongliert als w&auml;ren es Bauern auf dem Schachbrett. Man kann doch freie Bauern nicht mit Geld abspeisen und ins Ausgedinge schicken, das ist erniedrigend, oder sie nur noch als Folklore- und Alibibauern ben&uuml;tzen, zum Herzeigen f&uuml;r den Tourismus. Das geht gegen Ehre und Selbstachtung, das ist &auml;rger als Mord.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man bezahlt die Bauern f&uuml;r ihren Selbstmord. Die EU verlangt von den Bauern, sie sollen ihre eigene uralte Kultur zerst&ouml;ren. Daf&uuml;r bekommen sie Geld. Anders als bei der Katastrophenhilfe wird die Katastrophe erst mutwillig in Gang gesetzt. Umgebrachte gewachsene Strukturen kann man auch mit sehr viel Geld nicht wiedergutmachen. Tote kann man mit Geld nicht zum Leben erwecken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Wunsch einiger m&auml;chtiger und konkurrenzf&auml;higer Gro&szlig;industrieller nach Eintritt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist, noch mehr wirtschaftliche Vorteile zu erlangen. Das geht jedoch auf Kosten der sowieso schon gef&auml;hrdeten Kleinbetriebe und Kleinbauern.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich wei&szlig; aus eigener Erfahrung, dass in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten z.B. in Frankreich nur Agrargenossenschaften &uuml;ber 100 ha eine &Uuml;berlebenschance haben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das schaut dann so aus: entweder brachliegende, ver&ouml;dete Felder, verlassene D&ouml;rfer oder Nivellierung von Terrain, Beseitigung von f&uuml;r Gro&szlig;maschinen st&ouml;rende W&auml;ldchen, B&auml;umen und Felsen, Nivellierung von uralten Geh&ouml;ften, Begradigung von B&auml;chen. Eine perfide Zerst&ouml;rung, die in ihren gigantischen Auswirkungen jeden Krieg &uuml;bersteigt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Vermehrte Verwendung von Kunstd&uuml;nger, Pestiziden, genetischen Manipulationen, Bestrahlungen und Umweltgiften aller Art, nat&uuml;rlich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; erzeugt. Eine sadistische, technokratische Zerst&ouml;rung jeglicher Romantik mit dem Schlagwort: unrentabel. Monokultur, so weit das Auge reicht. Dem Bauern wird befohlen, unsere &Uuml;berlebensgrundlage systematisch zu vergewaltigen, den ihm zu treuen H&auml;nden anvertrauten Grund und Boden, Wald und Fluren zu vergiften und zu zerst&ouml;ren. Die Landwirtschaft wird zur gigantischen Agro-Business-Industrie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Abh&auml;ngigkeit der Bauern und von uns allen von Industrie, Chemie und Monopolwirtschaft, diese neue Leibeigenschaft, wird durch einen Anschluss an die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ins Unertr&auml;gliche gesteigert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ausl&auml;ndische, m&auml;chtigere, brutalere Befehlshaber treten an die Stelle der einheimischen kleineren Firmen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ebenso ergeht es den Kleineren, d. h. allen menschlichen Betrieben, sie werden vernichtet, daf&uuml;r gibt es noch mehr Gro&szlig;kaufh&auml;user, Gro&szlig;banken und Gro&szlig;industrialisierung. Kurzum alles, was unser aller Leben romantisch, liebens- und lebenswert macht, hat kaum mehr &Uuml;berlebensm&ouml;glichkeit. Die stupiden Brutalit&auml;ten siegen, die delikaten Werte kommen um, weil sie sich nicht wehren k&ouml;nnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Agro-Business-Industrie in der EU betreibt fast analog dem &bdquo;Dritten Reich&quot; eine brutale Auslese von reinrassigen gleichgeschalteten &quot;Elite&quot;-Produkten und eine Eliminierung von &quot;minderwertigem&quot; Erbgut oder Saatgut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es beginnt mit den sch&ouml;nen gro&szlig;en &Auml;pfeln, die alle gleich sein m&uuml;ssen, die in Monokultur gez&uuml;chtet sind, in gleicher Rasse, mit gleichem Geschmack, und setzt sich fort in der genetischen &quot;Nutztierveredelung&quot; und den Legehennenbatterien. Alles nicht produktive Leben wird eliminiert. Alle nicht profitable Vielfalt, alle Andersartigkeit, alle Kleinteiligkeit, aller nutzloser Artenreichtum, alle unrentable Sch&ouml;nheit wird vernichtet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dadurch sterben auch das Kleinbauerntum, die Familienbetriebe, die Romantik, kurzum unsere Lebensqualit&auml;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Durch das Sterben der Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen),&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Bauern, der Familien- und Kleinbetriebe, durch das Sterben der kleinen Identit&auml;ten entsteht eine Gleichschaltung und eine Anonymisierung unserer Gesellschaft. Man raubt dem Menschen seine W&uuml;rde. Dies bringt eine neue Abh&auml;ngigkeit, eine neue Versklavung, eine neue Leibeigenschaft noch nie dagewesenen Ausma&szlig;es hervor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das ist das Ende des humanistischen Europas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was dann &uuml;brigbleibt ist keine menschengerechte, sondern eine maschinengerechte und computergerechte Welt. Es ist eine Zerst&ouml;rung von h&ouml;heren Werten, die in ihrer Vielfalt Europa ausmachen. Es ist die Zerst&ouml;rung Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kleinbauern m&uuml;ssen Haus und Hof und Land verkaufen, werden entweder arbeitslos oder Stadtproletariat oder m&uuml;ssen sich Agro-Business-Genossenschaften anschlie&szlig;en, wo sie nur mehr Befehlsempf&auml;nger ohne Entscheidungsfreiheit sind, auf einem Land, das einmal ihnen geh&ouml;rte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; leidet unter einem wachsenden Arbeitslosenheer, das schon jetzt der arbeitenden Bev&ouml;lkerung eines Landes 7- bis 10-mal so gro&szlig; wie &Ouml;sterreich entspricht!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man kann sich vorstellen, welches verheerende Beispiel die &lt;strong&gt;EU &lt;/strong&gt;damit der Welt gibt, wenn die 3 Milliarden Menschen, die in der Dritten Welt auf dem Lande ihr Auskommen finden, diesem &lt;strong&gt;EU B&lt;/strong&gt;eispiel zu folgen gezwungen werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine gigantische Fl&uuml;chtlingswelle von 2 Milliarden Landbev&ouml;lkerung - diesen &quot;exode rural mondial&quot;, wie Jimmy Goldsmith warnt, k&ouml;nne die Welt nicht mehr ertragen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Grenzen sind so wie unsere Haut. Sie sch&uuml;tzen den gewachsenen Organismus, unsere individuelle Andersartigkeit vor Gefahr von Au&szlig;en wie Hitze und K&auml;lte. Wenn man die Haut entfernt, stirbt der Organismus, weil er schutzlos wird.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Daher haben wir Schutzz&ouml;lle zum Schutz einer gef&auml;hrdeten Gemeinschaft. &auml;hnlich wie wir Sonnenbrillen und Zeckenimpfungen etc. zu unserem Schutz einsetzen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was Gott getrennt hat, sollen wir nicht mit Gewalt einen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt nat&uuml;rliche Grenzen wie zum Beispiel die Sahara, das Mittelmeer und die Alpen, in deren Schutz sich uralte Kulturen gebildet haben wie die afrikanischen, die mediterranen und die nordeurop&auml;ischen Kulturen. Die Alpen haben eine Schutzfunktion sowohl f&uuml;r den Norden als auch f&uuml;r den S&uuml;den.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein schrankenloser, sinnloser Transitverkehr ist gleichbedeutend mit einem Niederrei&szlig;en und Nivellieren der Alpen, auch wenn der Verkehr untertunnelt wird. &Ouml;sterreich hat genauso wie die Schweiz eine Alpine Schutzw&auml;chterfunktion f&uuml;r Europa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die fieberhafte, unnat&uuml;rliche, konzeptlose Hin- und Herraserei ist Wahnsinn und wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; zum &quot;grenzenlosen Wahnsinn&quot;. An dem Ort, wo wir sind, machen wir alles hin, dann fl&uuml;chten wir vor unserer eigenen Zerst&ouml;rung, um anderswo alles hin zu machen, und auf dem Weg dahin wird auch alles hin. Dieser falsche Trend wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; forciert und unterst&uuml;tzt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou dr&uuml;ckt das so aus: Eine Wirtschaft, die nur auf Kurzzeit-Rentabilit&auml;t ausgerichtet ist, ohne Plan, ohne Vision, ohne Sinn, die arbeitsstellen-fressende Maschinen produziert, die mehr und mehr von der Transport- und Kommunikationsgeschwindigkeit abh&auml;ngig ist und die unter Au&szlig;erachtlassung des &ouml;kologischen Gleichgewichtes die Menschen zu einer ebenso forcierten Beweglichkeit zwingt wie die Waren, die Kapitalien, die Technologien und Informationen unter Missachtung der Menschenw&uuml;rde und des Schutzes der gewohnten Lebensweisen, eine &ouml;konomische Diktatur, die &uuml;ber alle anderen menschlichen T&auml;tigkeiten triumphiert...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn man das, was man zu sch&uuml;tzen hat, vorher umbringt, braucht man keinen Schutz mehr. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen die Bauern und die Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; weg und die Kleinbetriebe und der &quot;nutzlose&quot; Artenreichtum, die &quot;unrentable&quot; Vielfalt. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir uns angleichen an internationales Mittelma&szlig;, an vergiftetes Essen, genmanipulierte und bestrahlte Lebensmittel. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir in vorauseilendem Gehorsam uns selbst nivellieren und uns vernichten, dann kann die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; widerstandslos einmarschieren und durchmarschieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich als ganzes wird ein Vasallenstaat, eine neue Ostmark. Selbstverst&auml;ndlich ist dann &Ouml;sterreichs Position als neutrale, kernkraftfreie, umweltbewusste Nation kaum mehr haltbar. &Ouml;sterreich kann dann nicht mehr selbst entscheiden, was es tut, was und wieviel es produziert und in welche L&auml;nder es exportiert und aus welchen es importiert. &Ouml;sterreichs Geschicke werden von fremden Leuten in Br&uuml;ssel oder anderswo in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; bestimmt, von Schreibtischstrategen, die sich einen Dreck um &Ouml;sterreichs Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit scheren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;tswillen, &uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Umweltbewusstsein wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Kommandozentrale nur gelacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Slogan &quot;einsam oder gemeinsam&quot; ist eine angstmachende, demagogische Aufforderung zur Verunsicherung, zur Unfreiheit und zur Abh&auml;ngigkeit. Es mag paradox klingen, aber allein ist jeder am st&auml;rksten. Aus pers&ouml;nlicher Erfahrung wei&szlig; ich, dass ein Aussenstehender genauso stark ist wie die Gruppe und nicht schw&auml;cher. Der Au&szlig;enstehende ist beweglicher, effektiver in seinem Handeln und im Reagieren als eine schwerf&auml;llige, b&uuml;rokratische, chaotische Organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa ist nur stark dank der Vielfalt seiner Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. Diese kleinteilige Vielfalt muss verst&auml;rkt und gesch&uuml;tzt werden. Diese Vielfalt ist Europa. Schon de Gaulle erkannte, dass Europa nur eine Chance als Europa der selbst&auml;ndigen, freien Vaterl&auml;nder hat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unverst&auml;ndlich, wie verantwortungslos unsere Politiker jetzt unser wertvollstes Gut, unsere Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit und Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit aufgeben und &Ouml;sterreich entm&uuml;ndigen wollen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein Verrat an &Ouml;sterreich. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim letzten Anschluss gab es auch jede Menge Seyss-Inquarts, Guislings, Petains, die in der damaligen Situation wahrscheinlich auch aus &Uuml;berzeugung und Patriotismus glaubten, das Richtige zu tun und ihre Pflicht erf&uuml;llen zu m&uuml;ssen, indem sie ihr Land einer fremden Hegemonie anvertrauten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Heute lehrt uns die Geschichte, dass ihr Tun falsch und sch&auml;dlich war, und sie sind l&auml;ngst als Verr&auml;ter und Kollaborateure gebrandmarkt, bestraft und hingerichtet worden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mitgefangen - mitgehangen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Unter der Dunstglocke der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird von allen unbemerkt der Anschluss an Deutschland vollzogen. Wenn dann diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Schiffbruch erleidet, haben wir noch ein St&uuml;ck mehr unserer Unabh&auml;ngigkeit verloren und bleiben am gro&szlig;en deutschen Bruder kleben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Bei Wahrung aller Unterschiede hat &Ouml;sterreich &Auml;hnliches bereits erlebt, als auch aus wirtschaftlichen Gr&uuml;nden 1937-1938 ein Anschluss an das &quot;Altreich&quot; propagiert wurde. &quot;Heim ins Reich&quot; hie&szlig; damals die Parole. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim Umtausch des Schilling in den Gro&szlig;macht-Euro muss man fatalerweise Analogien mit dem Umtausch des Schilling 1938 in die Reichsmark feststellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man darf nicht vergessen, dass das Versprechen einer finanziellen und wirtschaftlichen Besserstellung der k&uuml;nftigen Ostm&auml;rker Haupttriebfeder vieler &Ouml;sterreicher war, um f&uuml;r den Anschluss zu stimmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auf die bejubelte Einverleibung mit Gro&szlig;deutschland erfolgte die Ern&uuml;chterung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Jetzt ist es &auml;hnlich. Genau das, was man uns in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; vorgaukeln will, verlieren wir in der&lt;strong&gt; EU&lt;/strong&gt;: sozialen Wohlstand, Vollbesch&auml;ftigung, eine intakte Umwelt, unsere hohe Lebensqualit&auml;t, unsere Heimat, unsere Selbstachtung, unsere Natur und unsere uralten Kulturen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europ&auml;er ist man nur dann, wenn man sein unabh&auml;ngiges, eigenst&auml;ndiges Europ&auml;ertum bewahrt und hochh&auml;lt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Schweiz, wohlhabend und demokratisch, auch im Herzen Europas gelegen, soll uns ein leuchtendes Beispiel sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe auch nicht, wieso unser Bundespr&auml;sident uns zur Aufgabe unserer Souver&auml;nit&auml;t auffordert. Er m&uuml;sste doch als oberster Patriot warnen und die Verfassung sch&uuml;tzen. Ist denn Landesverrat kein Vergehen, wenn man &Ouml;sterreich einer ausl&auml;ndischen Zentralgewalt unterwerfen will? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Staatsvertrag brachte &Ouml;sterreich die Befreiung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Vertrag ist eine Kapitulation &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Entm&uuml;ndigung &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Unterwerfung unter eine neue anachronistische Hegemonie - und ein Bruch des Staatsvertrages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unglaublich: Die Politiker bereiten den zweiten Anschluss vor und wollen das &ouml;sterreichische Volk vor vollendete Tatsachen stellen. Sind unsere Politiker von allen guten Geistern verlassen, so dass erst&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; die Geschichte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; sie zurechtweisen muss? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich bin kein Jurist, aber ich bin der festen &Uuml;berzeugung, dass wir von m&auml;chtigen Interessensgruppen au&szlig;erhalb jeder ethischen, geschichtlichen, moralischen, kulturellen und &ouml;kologischen Legalit&auml;t mit einer miesen Demagogie manipuliert werden, so wie seinerzeit bei Zwentendorf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Inbetriebnahme des Atommeilers wurde durch Volksabstimmung verhindert)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten werden nivelliert und anonymisiert und ihrer Identit&auml;t beraubt. In diese Richtung geht es und nicht in die Richtung der Dezentralisation und&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Vertiefung&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Zum Beweis gen&uuml;gt die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne mit den jetzt 12 genau gleichen 5-zackigen Sternchen. Welches dieser Sternchen w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich symbolisieren, etwa das dritte rechts von unten oder das zweite, das genauso aussieht?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der F&uuml;nfstern ist kein Symbol aus der europ&auml;ischen und schon gar nicht aus der &ouml;sterreichischen Geschichte. Er kommt in der Entwicklung der Staaten des Okzidents nicht vor. Das Pentagramm, ein okkultistisches Zeichen der Druden und Freimaurer ist ein Fremdk&ouml;rper in der abendl&auml;ndischen Heraldik. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die 5-zackigen Sterne dienen eher als Merkmal der Unterwerfung, Inbesitznahme und Kolonisierung wie auf der austral-neuseel&auml;ndischen, amerikanischen und auf Kolonialfahnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne ist noch dazu ein Plagiat aus dem Sternenbanner. Auch die Vereinigten Staaten Amerikas waren als 5-zackige Sternchen, wei&szlig; auf blau, zuerst im Kreis angeordnet, genauso wie jetzt die M&ouml;chtegern-&quot;Vereinigten Staaten Europas&quot;. Sp&auml;ter, als sie sich vermehrten, wurden sie in Reih und Glied gebracht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese 5-zackigen Sternchen sind dieselben wie der Sowjetstern, der Stern der jugoslawischen, chinesischen, kubanischen und sonstigen Volksrepubliken. Wahrlich, dieses Symbol ist ein Armutszeugnis f&uuml;r die gewachsenen Identit&auml;ten Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein b&ouml;ses Omen, wenn schon das Zeichen falsch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Sternchenfahne symbolisiert die Selbstaufgabe Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist die Kultur weniger als Nebensache. Die sch&ouml;pferischen Kr&auml;fte werden zu n&uuml;tzlichen Idioten getrimmt. Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung und Verbr&auml;mung und Legitimierung eines merkantilen und industriellen Wachstums, das sich selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kultur ist in Br&uuml;ssel nicht pr&auml;sent. Sie ist in der nur merkantilen und industriellen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; kein Thema. In Br&uuml;ssel kennt man den Preis von allem und den Wert von nichts. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es geht in dieser kulturlosen, sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; nur um Zahlen: Produktionszahlen, Termine und Laufzeiten, &Uuml;bergangsfristen, Einwohner- und Viehzahlen. Bruttosozialprodukte, Anbau-, Wald- und Weidegebiete in Quadratkilometern, Lohnkosten, Sozialleistungen, Nebenkosten. Exportziffern, Tonnenzahlen f&uuml;r Schwertransporte, Milchpreise, Preisanpassungen, Finanzierungszahlen, Ausgleichszahlen, Prozente, Preissenkungen, Zucker-, Milch&shy;- und Fischquoten, Transitbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen, Kontingente, Mitfinanzierungen, Tabellen, Statistiken, Marktzugangsbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen. Laufzeiten, Ecu Umtauschkurse, hohe Arbeitslosenzahlen, niedrige Besch&auml;ftigungszahlen, F&ouml;rderungs- und Subventionszahlen, die Anzahl von &Ouml;kopunkten, Geldzahlungen aller Art, irreale Wirtschaftswachstumszahlen, Umfrageergebnisse in Zahlen und Prozenten, Stimmenanzahlen des Ministerrates und der Sperrminorit&auml;t, Mehrheiten, Minderheiten, Abstimmungsergebnisse, EU-Werbeausgaben. Ja sogar H&ouml;henzahlen f&uuml;r Bergbauern in Metern und Breitegradzahlen f&uuml;r die Landwirtschaft in Finnland. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das nicht symptomatisch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch der Umweltschutz ist in der Br&uuml;sseler Hegemonie abwesend. Nur 0,3 Prozent (30 von 10.000) der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Beamten sind f&uuml;r die &Ouml;kologie t&auml;tig. Vom Grenzen &uuml;berbr&uuml;ckenden Umweltschutz ist nur die Rede. &Ouml;sterreich muss die Kernkraft mitfinanzieren und z. B. Plastikflaschen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-Produkte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und idiotisch-gef&auml;hrliche Richtlinien f&uuml;r Apfelgr&ouml;&szlig;en und Monokultur-Obstsorten &uuml;bernehmen. Das habe ich selbst gesehen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Von Kultur und den Werten des Abendlandes ist in Br&uuml;ssel keine Rede. Um Ausgaben f&uuml;r Kultur muss man erst Br&uuml;ssel bitten. Das Kulturstudium und auch der gesamte Studienbereich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird ausgerichtet auf die N&uuml;tzlichkeit f&uuml;r die Industrie und auf das forcierte Wachstum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Kreativit&auml;t und organisches Wachstum lehren. Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Achtung lehren vor dem Artenreichtum und der unglaublichen Vielfalt, deren Teil wir selbst sind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; aber gehen die Bestrebungen in die genau umgekehrte Richtung: Vernichtung der kleinteiligen sch&ouml;pferischen Werte zugunsten einer v&ouml;llig falschen und &uuml;berholten Automatisierung, Zentralisierung und Rationalisierung, die uns &uuml;ber kurz oder lang zum Untergang bringt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das Gewissen unserer Zivilisation, unsere uralte Bestimmung, h&ouml;here Werte anzustreben, bleibt auf der Strecke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_occasion_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Written in Vienna &ndash; Paris &ndash; Kaurinui, 1988&ndash;1994. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Passages in italics: La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Geschrieben in Wien - Paris - Kaurinui, 1988 - 1994,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; erg&auml;nzt in kursiv in La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1993, p. 65-68 (Text Anschlu&szlig;psychose, 1988) (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;protokolle&lt;/em&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. edited by Otto Breicha. Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Vienna, 1997, pp. 185-193 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1998, p. 83-99 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 1151-1162 (German and English)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Langen M&uuml;ller: Munich, 2004, pp. 55-64 (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1993, S. 65-68 (Text &lt;span style=&quot;background: yellow 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial&quot;&gt;Anschlu&szlig;psychose&lt;/span&gt;, 1988)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;protokolle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. hrsg. von Otto Breicha. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Wien 1997, S. 185-193&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1998, S. 83-99&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. II: F&uuml;r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;st, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 1151-1162 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Langen M&uuml;ller: M&uuml;nchen 2004, S. 55-64&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'', text_translator-'Courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-22 13:18:24.3268###object###text###1.4.5.1###TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.5.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-124&quot;&gt; 124&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-124&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;124 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-125&quot;&gt; 125&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-125&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;125 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', id-130, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-130, txt-'1.4.5.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?', text_title_ge-'', text_keywords-'', text_date-'1994-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_language-en, text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In Sache &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird die &ouml;sterreichische &Ouml;ffentlichkeit von den staatlichen Medien einer dogmatischen Gehirnw&auml;sche ohnegleichen ausgesetzt. Es herrscht im Fernsehen, im Radio und fast in der gesamten Presse eine infame verschleierte Zensur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich w&uuml;rde das auch nicht in einer Demokratie f&uuml;r m&ouml;glich halten, h&auml;tte ich diese Art von Zensur nicht selbst erlebt. Unter allerlei Pr&auml;texten und Vorw&auml;nden wurde ich mehrmals behindert und verhindert,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; &ouml;ffentlich&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; eine Anti-&lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Meinung zu vertreten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Vorw&auml;nde waren: es passe nicht in die Sendung, ich d&uuml;rfe nichts vorlesen, ich w&auml;re daf&uuml;r nicht zust&auml;ndig, ich w&auml;re verr&uuml;ckt oder aber man versucht mit gezielter Diffamation mich unglaubw&uuml;rdig zu machen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dabei sind meine Bedenken und &Auml;ngste in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten selbst l&auml;ngst best&auml;tigt. Warum h&ouml;rt man nicht auf Leopold Kohr (Das Ende der Gro&szlig;en), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (Small is beautiful), Jimmy Goldsmith (Le pi&egrave;ge - et si nous avions suivi la mauvaise route?), Henry Coston (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe des banquiers), Jean Pierre Chevenement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe Seguin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (Cacciamo i mercanti dal tempio dell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europa), Gerard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht-Partei), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (Ex-EU-Kommissar: &quot;k&uuml;nstliche Superkonstruktion nicht lebensf&auml;hig&quot;), Denis de Rougemont (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe doit se faire pour la diversit&eacute;) und unz&auml;hlige andere Warner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich ist von der Geschichte auserw&auml;hlt, Beispiel und Zentrum und Halt in Mitteleuropa zu sein. &Ouml;sterreich ist eine Br&uuml;cke der Hoffnung zum Osten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wir haben seit dem Krieg in m&uuml;hevoller Arbeit ein riesiges Kapital an Wohlstand, innerem Frieden, internationalem Respekt und Glaubw&uuml;rdigkeit aufgebaut als unabh&auml;ngige, liebenswerte, friedliebende Kulturnation im Herzen Europas. Das kann nicht kurzsichtig und verantwortungslos aufs Spiel gesetzt werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt nach dem Zerfall der kommunistischen Diktatur und der &Ouml;ffnung der Grenzen muss sich &Ouml;sterreich seiner Verantwortung in Europa bewusst werden und darf sich nicht selbst eliminieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mit einer uns suggerierten Torschlusspanik wird eine Anschlussneurose erzeugt. Angst vor was oder wem? Welche Feinde hat &Ouml;sterreich? Wer sollte und warum &Ouml;sterreichs Sicherheit gef&auml;hrden? Gerade durch den Anschluss an einen Milit&auml;rblock w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich als &quot;Randgebiet Ostmark&quot; erst zum Aufmarschgebiet und zum Feindbild und Angriffsziel werden (Warnung von Erwin Lanc). Gegen atomare Bedrohung ist kein Kraut gewachsen und bei Regionalkriegen - siehe Bosnien - gibt es keinen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Schutz, nicht einmal in Nordirland, innerhalb der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;t ist gerade jetzt n&ouml;tiger als je zuvor. Man muss die Neutralit&auml;t beim Namen nennen und zu ihr stehen. Neutralit&auml;t ist ein wahrer Wert. Die immerw&auml;hrende Neutralit&auml;t ist das Fundament unseres Staates und darf nicht verraten und ausgeh&ouml;hlt werden. Wenn wir dieses Fundament unterminieren, zerst&ouml;ren wir diesen unseren Staat &Ouml;sterreich, der darauf errichtet ist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ab jetzt bedeutet die Neutralit&auml;t &Ouml;sterreichs Selbst&auml;ndigkeit, Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit, Verantwortung tragen, Beispiel geben, eine aktive Neutralit&auml;t. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch hier ist die Schweiz ein Beispiel und wird auch im Staatsvertrag als Beispiel genannt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es besteht kein Anlass, gerade jetzt einen Graben quer durch Europa zu ziehen. Es ist so als ob &ouml;stlich von Wien Feindesland w&auml;re.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Die Grenzposten werden von Deutschland an den eben beseitigten Eisernen Vorhang verlegt!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp; Diese neue Grenzziehung ist nicht nur quer durch Europa, sondern quer durch &Ouml;sterreich, wo die Donaumonarchie war. Es w&auml;re verantwortungslos und gef&auml;hrlich, durch den Anschluss an eine wirtschaftliche und politische &Uuml;bermacht das Gef&auml;lle zu und die Bedrohung f&uuml;r die L&auml;nder &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; zu vergr&ouml;&szlig;ern. &Ouml;sterreichs kulturelle, wirtschaftliche und geschichtliche Bestimmung, &Ouml;sterreichs Verantwortung und Ausstrahlung liegt im Osten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;(Das besagt auch der Name &Ouml;sterreich.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Fronten haben sich gewandelt. Es sind nicht mehr die politischen Grenzen, sondern die Front verl&auml;uft zwischen der brutalen, nur wirtschaftsinteressierten Wegwerfgesellschaft und der ausgebeuteten Natur und der zerst&ouml;rten Seele des Menschen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt einen neuen Widerstand und schon wieder feige Kollaborateure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die jetzt verantwortlichen Politiker sind Hampelm&auml;nner der Wirtschaftsinteressen und heucheln Umweltbewusstsein und Kulturbewusstsein mit Lippenbekenntnissen. Sie beschlie&szlig;en umweltzerst&ouml;rende und kulturzerst&ouml;rende Ma&szlig;nahmen, die unsere Zukunft in Frage stellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die sogenannte &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; betreibt die brutale Vernichtung unserer Lebensbasis, unserer uralten Kulturen, unserer kleinen, gewachsenen Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten, unseres Artenreichtums und unserer Selbstachtung.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Handelsvertretung des Gro&szlig;unternehmertums, der Gewerkschaften, Genossenschaften, der Gro&szlig;banken, der Giftkonzerne, der Monokultur-Monopolisten und der Atom-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;obby, die uns wie brave Schafe gemeinsam wie das Schlachtvieh in einen Zug in die falsche Richtung verladen will.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dieser riesigen Wirtschaftsmafia geht es nur um Macht und Geld und nicht um das Wohl der Natur und des Menschen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine von verantwortungslosen Schreibtischstrategen ferngesteuerte gigantische Fehlplanung zerst&ouml;rt die Fundamente unseres &uuml;ber uralte Zeiten gewachsenen Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa erlebt die gr&ouml;&szlig;te Vergewaltigung seiner Geschichte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus Br&uuml;ssel kommt keine geistige und kulturelle Erneuerung Europas. Von dort kommen keine Antworten auf die Fragen, die das Gewissen der V&ouml;lker Europas beunruhigen (Alberto Miele). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus dieser neuen Hegemonie kommen keine Botschaften, die die Identit&auml;t, unsere uralten Werte, die Inhalte unserer Zivilisation und die Sehns&uuml;chte der Menschen Europas betreffen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wo sind die Kulturen, die Religionen, die Philosophien, die ein neues europ&auml;isches Zeitalter aus der Taufe heben?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt, wo unsere Gesellschaft die Grenzen des Wachstums erreicht, ist Dezentralisierung unsere einzige &Uuml;berlebenschance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein Anschluss an diese &uuml;berm&auml;chtige Zentralgewalt, die noch immer Wirtschaftswachstum als Zentraldogma gegen alle Evidenz durchziehen will, hat f&uuml;r alle Beteiligten katastrophale Folgen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wohin diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; uns mithineinziehen will, ist ein gnadenloser Konkurrenzkampf, ein Amoklauf in eine gro&szlig;e, gef&auml;hrliche Illusion, in die Sackgasse des Wirtschaftswachstums. Es w&auml;re Wahnsinn, diesem exklusiven Klub der Wegwerfgesellschaft beizutreten, der sich selbst in den M&uuml;ll wirft und ad absurdum f&uuml;hrt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das Produkt &quot;EU&quot; so gut ist, warum muss man derart intensiv daf&uuml;r werben? Und dieser verd&auml;chtige Zeitdruck: Wir m&uuml;ssen uns sofort enteignen, sonst ist es zu sp&auml;t! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Alle guten Dinge geschehen langsam in einem organischen Ablauf von selbst. Einen Baum kann man auch nicht mit Drohungen &uuml;berzeugen und &uuml;berreden, da&szlig; er im tiefen Winter zu bl&uuml;hen hat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe nicht, warum man uns mit Gewalt &uuml;berreden will, die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;, dieses sinkende Schiff zu besteigen, und zwar sofort.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Titanic. Die Analogien zum Untergang der Titanic sind erschreckend. Hier wie dort: Konzeptlosigkeit, Gr&ouml;&szlig;enwahn, Ma&szlig;losigkeit, blinde Technologiegl&auml;ubigkeit und Geschwindigkeitswahn um jeden Preis. Dort das Rennen um das &quot;blaue Band&quot; in die t&ouml;dlichen Eisberge, hier das m&ouml;rderische Wettrennen an die Grenzen des Wachstums der Wegwerfgesellschaft, die unsere Umwelt und uns selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;So einen &quot;europ&auml;ischen Ungl&uuml;cksdampfer&quot; besteigt man nicht und vertraut man unser Leben und unsere Zukunft nicht an. Da ist es besser, man bleibt in einem kleinen, aber man&ouml;vrierbaren Boot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In praktisch der ganzen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; geht es wild zu: Nordirland, Baskenland, Korsika, Mafia, Comorra, Ausl&auml;nderverfolgungen, Rassenhass und Pogrome, Diskriminierung von Gr&ouml;nl&auml;ndern, Macedoniern und Bretonen, brutale Streiks, blutige Ausschreitungen, Studentenrevolten, Drogenkriminalit&auml;t, nukleare St&ouml;rf&auml;lle, verw&uuml;stete Landstriche, Apathie und Katastrophenstimmung, Jugendkriminalit&auml;t, bald 20 Millionen Arbeitslose und eine Staatsspaltung in Flamen und Wallonen, ausgerechnet in Br&uuml;ssel, dem Sitz der &quot;Europ&auml;ischen Union&quot;. Im Vergleich dazu haben das &quot;isolierte &Ouml;sterreich&quot; und die skandinavischen L&auml;nder, die man unbedingt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; treiben will, es &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; noch gut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; mit Menschenschicksalen jongliert als w&auml;ren es Bauern auf dem Schachbrett. Man kann doch freie Bauern nicht mit Geld abspeisen und ins Ausgedinge schicken, das ist erniedrigend, oder sie nur noch als Folklore- und Alibibauern ben&uuml;tzen, zum Herzeigen f&uuml;r den Tourismus. Das geht gegen Ehre und Selbstachtung, das ist &auml;rger als Mord.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man bezahlt die Bauern f&uuml;r ihren Selbstmord. Die EU verlangt von den Bauern, sie sollen ihre eigene uralte Kultur zerst&ouml;ren. Daf&uuml;r bekommen sie Geld. Anders als bei der Katastrophenhilfe wird die Katastrophe erst mutwillig in Gang gesetzt. Umgebrachte gewachsene Strukturen kann man auch mit sehr viel Geld nicht wiedergutmachen. Tote kann man mit Geld nicht zum Leben erwecken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Wunsch einiger m&auml;chtiger und konkurrenzf&auml;higer Gro&szlig;industrieller nach Eintritt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist, noch mehr wirtschaftliche Vorteile zu erlangen. Das geht jedoch auf Kosten der sowieso schon gef&auml;hrdeten Kleinbetriebe und Kleinbauern.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich wei&szlig; aus eigener Erfahrung, dass in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten z.B. in Frankreich nur Agrargenossenschaften &uuml;ber 100 ha eine &Uuml;berlebenschance haben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das schaut dann so aus: entweder brachliegende, ver&ouml;dete Felder, verlassene D&ouml;rfer oder Nivellierung von Terrain, Beseitigung von f&uuml;r Gro&szlig;maschinen st&ouml;rende W&auml;ldchen, B&auml;umen und Felsen, Nivellierung von uralten Geh&ouml;ften, Begradigung von B&auml;chen. Eine perfide Zerst&ouml;rung, die in ihren gigantischen Auswirkungen jeden Krieg &uuml;bersteigt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Vermehrte Verwendung von Kunstd&uuml;nger, Pestiziden, genetischen Manipulationen, Bestrahlungen und Umweltgiften aller Art, nat&uuml;rlich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; erzeugt. Eine sadistische, technokratische Zerst&ouml;rung jeglicher Romantik mit dem Schlagwort: unrentabel. Monokultur, so weit das Auge reicht. Dem Bauern wird befohlen, unsere &Uuml;berlebensgrundlage systematisch zu vergewaltigen, den ihm zu treuen H&auml;nden anvertrauten Grund und Boden, Wald und Fluren zu vergiften und zu zerst&ouml;ren. Die Landwirtschaft wird zur gigantischen Agro-Business-Industrie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Abh&auml;ngigkeit der Bauern und von uns allen von Industrie, Chemie und Monopolwirtschaft, diese neue Leibeigenschaft, wird durch einen Anschluss an die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ins Unertr&auml;gliche gesteigert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ausl&auml;ndische, m&auml;chtigere, brutalere Befehlshaber treten an die Stelle der einheimischen kleineren Firmen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ebenso ergeht es den Kleineren, d. h. allen menschlichen Betrieben, sie werden vernichtet, daf&uuml;r gibt es noch mehr Gro&szlig;kaufh&auml;user, Gro&szlig;banken und Gro&szlig;industrialisierung. Kurzum alles, was unser aller Leben romantisch, liebens- und lebenswert macht, hat kaum mehr &Uuml;berlebensm&ouml;glichkeit. Die stupiden Brutalit&auml;ten siegen, die delikaten Werte kommen um, weil sie sich nicht wehren k&ouml;nnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Agro-Business-Industrie in der EU betreibt fast analog dem &bdquo;Dritten Reich&quot; eine brutale Auslese von reinrassigen gleichgeschalteten &quot;Elite&quot;-Produkten und eine Eliminierung von &quot;minderwertigem&quot; Erbgut oder Saatgut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es beginnt mit den sch&ouml;nen gro&szlig;en &Auml;pfeln, die alle gleich sein m&uuml;ssen, die in Monokultur gez&uuml;chtet sind, in gleicher Rasse, mit gleichem Geschmack, und setzt sich fort in der genetischen &quot;Nutztierveredelung&quot; und den Legehennenbatterien. Alles nicht produktive Leben wird eliminiert. Alle nicht profitable Vielfalt, alle Andersartigkeit, alle Kleinteiligkeit, aller nutzloser Artenreichtum, alle unrentable Sch&ouml;nheit wird vernichtet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dadurch sterben auch das Kleinbauerntum, die Familienbetriebe, die Romantik, kurzum unsere Lebensqualit&auml;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Durch das Sterben der Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen),&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Bauern, der Familien- und Kleinbetriebe, durch das Sterben der kleinen Identit&auml;ten entsteht eine Gleichschaltung und eine Anonymisierung unserer Gesellschaft. Man raubt dem Menschen seine W&uuml;rde. Dies bringt eine neue Abh&auml;ngigkeit, eine neue Versklavung, eine neue Leibeigenschaft noch nie dagewesenen Ausma&szlig;es hervor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das ist das Ende des humanistischen Europas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was dann &uuml;brigbleibt ist keine menschengerechte, sondern eine maschinengerechte und computergerechte Welt. Es ist eine Zerst&ouml;rung von h&ouml;heren Werten, die in ihrer Vielfalt Europa ausmachen. Es ist die Zerst&ouml;rung Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kleinbauern m&uuml;ssen Haus und Hof und Land verkaufen, werden entweder arbeitslos oder Stadtproletariat oder m&uuml;ssen sich Agro-Business-Genossenschaften anschlie&szlig;en, wo sie nur mehr Befehlsempf&auml;nger ohne Entscheidungsfreiheit sind, auf einem Land, das einmal ihnen geh&ouml;rte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; leidet unter einem wachsenden Arbeitslosenheer, das schon jetzt der arbeitenden Bev&ouml;lkerung eines Landes 7- bis 10-mal so gro&szlig; wie &Ouml;sterreich entspricht!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man kann sich vorstellen, welches verheerende Beispiel die &lt;strong&gt;EU &lt;/strong&gt;damit der Welt gibt, wenn die 3 Milliarden Menschen, die in der Dritten Welt auf dem Lande ihr Auskommen finden, diesem &lt;strong&gt;EU B&lt;/strong&gt;eispiel zu folgen gezwungen werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine gigantische Fl&uuml;chtlingswelle von 2 Milliarden Landbev&ouml;lkerung - diesen &quot;exode rural mondial&quot;, wie Jimmy Goldsmith warnt, k&ouml;nne die Welt nicht mehr ertragen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Grenzen sind so wie unsere Haut. Sie sch&uuml;tzen den gewachsenen Organismus, unsere individuelle Andersartigkeit vor Gefahr von Au&szlig;en wie Hitze und K&auml;lte. Wenn man die Haut entfernt, stirbt der Organismus, weil er schutzlos wird.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Daher haben wir Schutzz&ouml;lle zum Schutz einer gef&auml;hrdeten Gemeinschaft. &auml;hnlich wie wir Sonnenbrillen und Zeckenimpfungen etc. zu unserem Schutz einsetzen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was Gott getrennt hat, sollen wir nicht mit Gewalt einen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt nat&uuml;rliche Grenzen wie zum Beispiel die Sahara, das Mittelmeer und die Alpen, in deren Schutz sich uralte Kulturen gebildet haben wie die afrikanischen, die mediterranen und die nordeurop&auml;ischen Kulturen. Die Alpen haben eine Schutzfunktion sowohl f&uuml;r den Norden als auch f&uuml;r den S&uuml;den.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein schrankenloser, sinnloser Transitverkehr ist gleichbedeutend mit einem Niederrei&szlig;en und Nivellieren der Alpen, auch wenn der Verkehr untertunnelt wird. &Ouml;sterreich hat genauso wie die Schweiz eine Alpine Schutzw&auml;chterfunktion f&uuml;r Europa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die fieberhafte, unnat&uuml;rliche, konzeptlose Hin- und Herraserei ist Wahnsinn und wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; zum &quot;grenzenlosen Wahnsinn&quot;. An dem Ort, wo wir sind, machen wir alles hin, dann fl&uuml;chten wir vor unserer eigenen Zerst&ouml;rung, um anderswo alles hin zu machen, und auf dem Weg dahin wird auch alles hin. Dieser falsche Trend wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; forciert und unterst&uuml;tzt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou dr&uuml;ckt das so aus: Eine Wirtschaft, die nur auf Kurzzeit-Rentabilit&auml;t ausgerichtet ist, ohne Plan, ohne Vision, ohne Sinn, die arbeitsstellen-fressende Maschinen produziert, die mehr und mehr von der Transport- und Kommunikationsgeschwindigkeit abh&auml;ngig ist und die unter Au&szlig;erachtlassung des &ouml;kologischen Gleichgewichtes die Menschen zu einer ebenso forcierten Beweglichkeit zwingt wie die Waren, die Kapitalien, die Technologien und Informationen unter Missachtung der Menschenw&uuml;rde und des Schutzes der gewohnten Lebensweisen, eine &ouml;konomische Diktatur, die &uuml;ber alle anderen menschlichen T&auml;tigkeiten triumphiert...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn man das, was man zu sch&uuml;tzen hat, vorher umbringt, braucht man keinen Schutz mehr. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen die Bauern und die Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; weg und die Kleinbetriebe und der &quot;nutzlose&quot; Artenreichtum, die &quot;unrentable&quot; Vielfalt. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir uns angleichen an internationales Mittelma&szlig;, an vergiftetes Essen, genmanipulierte und bestrahlte Lebensmittel. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir in vorauseilendem Gehorsam uns selbst nivellieren und uns vernichten, dann kann die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; widerstandslos einmarschieren und durchmarschieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich als ganzes wird ein Vasallenstaat, eine neue Ostmark. Selbstverst&auml;ndlich ist dann &Ouml;sterreichs Position als neutrale, kernkraftfreie, umweltbewusste Nation kaum mehr haltbar. &Ouml;sterreich kann dann nicht mehr selbst entscheiden, was es tut, was und wieviel es produziert und in welche L&auml;nder es exportiert und aus welchen es importiert. &Ouml;sterreichs Geschicke werden von fremden Leuten in Br&uuml;ssel oder anderswo in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; bestimmt, von Schreibtischstrategen, die sich einen Dreck um &Ouml;sterreichs Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit scheren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;tswillen, &uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Umweltbewusstsein wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Kommandozentrale nur gelacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Slogan &quot;einsam oder gemeinsam&quot; ist eine angstmachende, demagogische Aufforderung zur Verunsicherung, zur Unfreiheit und zur Abh&auml;ngigkeit. Es mag paradox klingen, aber allein ist jeder am st&auml;rksten. Aus pers&ouml;nlicher Erfahrung wei&szlig; ich, dass ein Aussenstehender genauso stark ist wie die Gruppe und nicht schw&auml;cher. Der Au&szlig;enstehende ist beweglicher, effektiver in seinem Handeln und im Reagieren als eine schwerf&auml;llige, b&uuml;rokratische, chaotische Organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa ist nur stark dank der Vielfalt seiner Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. Diese kleinteilige Vielfalt muss verst&auml;rkt und gesch&uuml;tzt werden. Diese Vielfalt ist Europa. Schon de Gaulle erkannte, dass Europa nur eine Chance als Europa der selbst&auml;ndigen, freien Vaterl&auml;nder hat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unverst&auml;ndlich, wie verantwortungslos unsere Politiker jetzt unser wertvollstes Gut, unsere Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit und Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit aufgeben und &Ouml;sterreich entm&uuml;ndigen wollen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein Verrat an &Ouml;sterreich. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim letzten Anschluss gab es auch jede Menge Seyss-Inquarts, Guislings, Petains, die in der damaligen Situation wahrscheinlich auch aus &Uuml;berzeugung und Patriotismus glaubten, das Richtige zu tun und ihre Pflicht erf&uuml;llen zu m&uuml;ssen, indem sie ihr Land einer fremden Hegemonie anvertrauten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Heute lehrt uns die Geschichte, dass ihr Tun falsch und sch&auml;dlich war, und sie sind l&auml;ngst als Verr&auml;ter und Kollaborateure gebrandmarkt, bestraft und hingerichtet worden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mitgefangen - mitgehangen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Unter der Dunstglocke der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird von allen unbemerkt der Anschluss an Deutschland vollzogen. Wenn dann diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Schiffbruch erleidet, haben wir noch ein St&uuml;ck mehr unserer Unabh&auml;ngigkeit verloren und bleiben am gro&szlig;en deutschen Bruder kleben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Bei Wahrung aller Unterschiede hat &Ouml;sterreich &Auml;hnliches bereits erlebt, als auch aus wirtschaftlichen Gr&uuml;nden 1937-1938 ein Anschluss an das &quot;Altreich&quot; propagiert wurde. &quot;Heim ins Reich&quot; hie&szlig; damals die Parole. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim Umtausch des Schilling in den Gro&szlig;macht-Euro muss man fatalerweise Analogien mit dem Umtausch des Schilling 1938 in die Reichsmark feststellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man darf nicht vergessen, dass das Versprechen einer finanziellen und wirtschaftlichen Besserstellung der k&uuml;nftigen Ostm&auml;rker Haupttriebfeder vieler &Ouml;sterreicher war, um f&uuml;r den Anschluss zu stimmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auf die bejubelte Einverleibung mit Gro&szlig;deutschland erfolgte die Ern&uuml;chterung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Jetzt ist es &auml;hnlich. Genau das, was man uns in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; vorgaukeln will, verlieren wir in der&lt;strong&gt; EU&lt;/strong&gt;: sozialen Wohlstand, Vollbesch&auml;ftigung, eine intakte Umwelt, unsere hohe Lebensqualit&auml;t, unsere Heimat, unsere Selbstachtung, unsere Natur und unsere uralten Kulturen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europ&auml;er ist man nur dann, wenn man sein unabh&auml;ngiges, eigenst&auml;ndiges Europ&auml;ertum bewahrt und hochh&auml;lt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Schweiz, wohlhabend und demokratisch, auch im Herzen Europas gelegen, soll uns ein leuchtendes Beispiel sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe auch nicht, wieso unser Bundespr&auml;sident uns zur Aufgabe unserer Souver&auml;nit&auml;t auffordert. Er m&uuml;sste doch als oberster Patriot warnen und die Verfassung sch&uuml;tzen. Ist denn Landesverrat kein Vergehen, wenn man &Ouml;sterreich einer ausl&auml;ndischen Zentralgewalt unterwerfen will? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Staatsvertrag brachte &Ouml;sterreich die Befreiung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Vertrag ist eine Kapitulation &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Entm&uuml;ndigung &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Unterwerfung unter eine neue anachronistische Hegemonie - und ein Bruch des Staatsvertrages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unglaublich: Die Politiker bereiten den zweiten Anschluss vor und wollen das &ouml;sterreichische Volk vor vollendete Tatsachen stellen. Sind unsere Politiker von allen guten Geistern verlassen, so dass erst&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; die Geschichte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; sie zurechtweisen muss? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich bin kein Jurist, aber ich bin der festen &Uuml;berzeugung, dass wir von m&auml;chtigen Interessensgruppen au&szlig;erhalb jeder ethischen, geschichtlichen, moralischen, kulturellen und &ouml;kologischen Legalit&auml;t mit einer miesen Demagogie manipuliert werden, so wie seinerzeit bei Zwentendorf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Inbetriebnahme des Atommeilers wurde durch Volksabstimmung verhindert)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten werden nivelliert und anonymisiert und ihrer Identit&auml;t beraubt. In diese Richtung geht es und nicht in die Richtung der Dezentralisation und&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Vertiefung&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Zum Beweis gen&uuml;gt die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne mit den jetzt 12 genau gleichen 5-zackigen Sternchen. Welches dieser Sternchen w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich symbolisieren, etwa das dritte rechts von unten oder das zweite, das genauso aussieht?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der F&uuml;nfstern ist kein Symbol aus der europ&auml;ischen und schon gar nicht aus der &ouml;sterreichischen Geschichte. Er kommt in der Entwicklung der Staaten des Okzidents nicht vor. Das Pentagramm, ein okkultistisches Zeichen der Druden und Freimaurer ist ein Fremdk&ouml;rper in der abendl&auml;ndischen Heraldik. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die 5-zackigen Sterne dienen eher als Merkmal der Unterwerfung, Inbesitznahme und Kolonisierung wie auf der austral-neuseel&auml;ndischen, amerikanischen und auf Kolonialfahnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne ist noch dazu ein Plagiat aus dem Sternenbanner. Auch die Vereinigten Staaten Amerikas waren als 5-zackige Sternchen, wei&szlig; auf blau, zuerst im Kreis angeordnet, genauso wie jetzt die M&ouml;chtegern-&quot;Vereinigten Staaten Europas&quot;. Sp&auml;ter, als sie sich vermehrten, wurden sie in Reih und Glied gebracht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese 5-zackigen Sternchen sind dieselben wie der Sowjetstern, der Stern der jugoslawischen, chinesischen, kubanischen und sonstigen Volksrepubliken. Wahrlich, dieses Symbol ist ein Armutszeugnis f&uuml;r die gewachsenen Identit&auml;ten Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein b&ouml;ses Omen, wenn schon das Zeichen falsch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Sternchenfahne symbolisiert die Selbstaufgabe Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist die Kultur weniger als Nebensache. Die sch&ouml;pferischen Kr&auml;fte werden zu n&uuml;tzlichen Idioten getrimmt. Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung und Verbr&auml;mung und Legitimierung eines merkantilen und industriellen Wachstums, das sich selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kultur ist in Br&uuml;ssel nicht pr&auml;sent. Sie ist in der nur merkantilen und industriellen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; kein Thema. In Br&uuml;ssel kennt man den Preis von allem und den Wert von nichts. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es geht in dieser kulturlosen, sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; nur um Zahlen: Produktionszahlen, Termine und Laufzeiten, &Uuml;bergangsfristen, Einwohner- und Viehzahlen. Bruttosozialprodukte, Anbau-, Wald- und Weidegebiete in Quadratkilometern, Lohnkosten, Sozialleistungen, Nebenkosten. Exportziffern, Tonnenzahlen f&uuml;r Schwertransporte, Milchpreise, Preisanpassungen, Finanzierungszahlen, Ausgleichszahlen, Prozente, Preissenkungen, Zucker-, Milch&shy;- und Fischquoten, Transitbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen, Kontingente, Mitfinanzierungen, Tabellen, Statistiken, Marktzugangsbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen. Laufzeiten, Ecu Umtauschkurse, hohe Arbeitslosenzahlen, niedrige Besch&auml;ftigungszahlen, F&ouml;rderungs- und Subventionszahlen, die Anzahl von &Ouml;kopunkten, Geldzahlungen aller Art, irreale Wirtschaftswachstumszahlen, Umfrageergebnisse in Zahlen und Prozenten, Stimmenanzahlen des Ministerrates und der Sperrminorit&auml;t, Mehrheiten, Minderheiten, Abstimmungsergebnisse, EU-Werbeausgaben. Ja sogar H&ouml;henzahlen f&uuml;r Bergbauern in Metern und Breitegradzahlen f&uuml;r die Landwirtschaft in Finnland. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das nicht symptomatisch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch der Umweltschutz ist in der Br&uuml;sseler Hegemonie abwesend. Nur 0,3 Prozent (30 von 10.000) der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Beamten sind f&uuml;r die &Ouml;kologie t&auml;tig. Vom Grenzen &uuml;berbr&uuml;ckenden Umweltschutz ist nur die Rede. &Ouml;sterreich muss die Kernkraft mitfinanzieren und z. B. Plastikflaschen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-Produkte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und idiotisch-gef&auml;hrliche Richtlinien f&uuml;r Apfelgr&ouml;&szlig;en und Monokultur-Obstsorten &uuml;bernehmen. Das habe ich selbst gesehen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Von Kultur und den Werten des Abendlandes ist in Br&uuml;ssel keine Rede. Um Ausgaben f&uuml;r Kultur muss man erst Br&uuml;ssel bitten. Das Kulturstudium und auch der gesamte Studienbereich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird ausgerichtet auf die N&uuml;tzlichkeit f&uuml;r die Industrie und auf das forcierte Wachstum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Kreativit&auml;t und organisches Wachstum lehren. Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Achtung lehren vor dem Artenreichtum und der unglaublichen Vielfalt, deren Teil wir selbst sind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; aber gehen die Bestrebungen in die genau umgekehrte Richtung: Vernichtung der kleinteiligen sch&ouml;pferischen Werte zugunsten einer v&ouml;llig falschen und &uuml;berholten Automatisierung, Zentralisierung und Rationalisierung, die uns &uuml;ber kurz oder lang zum Untergang bringt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das Gewissen unserer Zivilisation, unsere uralte Bestimmung, h&ouml;here Werte anzustreben, bleibt auf der Strecke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_occasion_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Written in Vienna &ndash; Paris &ndash; Kaurinui, 1988&ndash;1994. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Passages in italics: La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Geschrieben in Wien - Paris - Kaurinui, 1988 - 1994,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; erg&auml;nzt in kursiv in La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1993, p. 65-68 (Text Anschlu&szlig;psychose, 1988) (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;protokolle&lt;/em&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. edited by Otto Breicha. Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Vienna, 1997, pp. 185-193 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1998, p. 83-99 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 1151-1162 (German and English)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Langen M&uuml;ller: Munich, 2004, pp. 55-64 (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1993, S. 65-68 (Text &lt;span style=&quot;background: yellow 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial&quot;&gt;Anschlu&szlig;psychose&lt;/span&gt;, 1988)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;protokolle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. hrsg. von Otto Breicha. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Wien 1997, S. 185-193&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1998, S. 83-99&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. II: F&uuml;r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;st, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 1151-1162 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Langen M&uuml;ller: M&uuml;nchen 2004, S. 55-64&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'', text_translator-'Courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-22 13:38:17.9903###object###text###1.4.5.1###TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.5.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-124&quot;&gt; 124&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-124&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;124 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-125&quot;&gt; 125&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-125&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;125 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-126&quot;&gt; 126&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-126&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;126 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', id-130, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-130, txt-'1.4.5.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?', text_title_ge-'', text_keywords-'', text_date-'1994-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_language-en, text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In Sache &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird die &ouml;sterreichische &Ouml;ffentlichkeit von den staatlichen Medien einer dogmatischen Gehirnw&auml;sche ohnegleichen ausgesetzt. Es herrscht im Fernsehen, im Radio und fast in der gesamten Presse eine infame verschleierte Zensur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich w&uuml;rde das auch nicht in einer Demokratie f&uuml;r m&ouml;glich halten, h&auml;tte ich diese Art von Zensur nicht selbst erlebt. Unter allerlei Pr&auml;texten und Vorw&auml;nden wurde ich mehrmals behindert und verhindert,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; &ouml;ffentlich&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; eine Anti-&lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Meinung zu vertreten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Vorw&auml;nde waren: es passe nicht in die Sendung, ich d&uuml;rfe nichts vorlesen, ich w&auml;re daf&uuml;r nicht zust&auml;ndig, ich w&auml;re verr&uuml;ckt oder aber man versucht mit gezielter Diffamation mich unglaubw&uuml;rdig zu machen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dabei sind meine Bedenken und &Auml;ngste in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten selbst l&auml;ngst best&auml;tigt. Warum h&ouml;rt man nicht auf Leopold Kohr (Das Ende der Gro&szlig;en), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (Small is beautiful), Jimmy Goldsmith (Le pi&egrave;ge - et si nous avions suivi la mauvaise route?), Henry Coston (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe des banquiers), Jean Pierre Chevenement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe Seguin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (Cacciamo i mercanti dal tempio dell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europa), Gerard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht-Partei), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (Ex-EU-Kommissar: &quot;k&uuml;nstliche Superkonstruktion nicht lebensf&auml;hig&quot;), Denis de Rougemont (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe doit se faire pour la diversit&eacute;) und unz&auml;hlige andere Warner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich ist von der Geschichte auserw&auml;hlt, Beispiel und Zentrum und Halt in Mitteleuropa zu sein. &Ouml;sterreich ist eine Br&uuml;cke der Hoffnung zum Osten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wir haben seit dem Krieg in m&uuml;hevoller Arbeit ein riesiges Kapital an Wohlstand, innerem Frieden, internationalem Respekt und Glaubw&uuml;rdigkeit aufgebaut als unabh&auml;ngige, liebenswerte, friedliebende Kulturnation im Herzen Europas. Das kann nicht kurzsichtig und verantwortungslos aufs Spiel gesetzt werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt nach dem Zerfall der kommunistischen Diktatur und der &Ouml;ffnung der Grenzen muss sich &Ouml;sterreich seiner Verantwortung in Europa bewusst werden und darf sich nicht selbst eliminieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mit einer uns suggerierten Torschlusspanik wird eine Anschlussneurose erzeugt. Angst vor was oder wem? Welche Feinde hat &Ouml;sterreich? Wer sollte und warum &Ouml;sterreichs Sicherheit gef&auml;hrden? Gerade durch den Anschluss an einen Milit&auml;rblock w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich als &quot;Randgebiet Ostmark&quot; erst zum Aufmarschgebiet und zum Feindbild und Angriffsziel werden (Warnung von Erwin Lanc). Gegen atomare Bedrohung ist kein Kraut gewachsen und bei Regionalkriegen - siehe Bosnien - gibt es keinen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Schutz, nicht einmal in Nordirland, innerhalb der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;t ist gerade jetzt n&ouml;tiger als je zuvor. Man muss die Neutralit&auml;t beim Namen nennen und zu ihr stehen. Neutralit&auml;t ist ein wahrer Wert. Die immerw&auml;hrende Neutralit&auml;t ist das Fundament unseres Staates und darf nicht verraten und ausgeh&ouml;hlt werden. Wenn wir dieses Fundament unterminieren, zerst&ouml;ren wir diesen unseren Staat &Ouml;sterreich, der darauf errichtet ist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ab jetzt bedeutet die Neutralit&auml;t &Ouml;sterreichs Selbst&auml;ndigkeit, Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit, Verantwortung tragen, Beispiel geben, eine aktive Neutralit&auml;t. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch hier ist die Schweiz ein Beispiel und wird auch im Staatsvertrag als Beispiel genannt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es besteht kein Anlass, gerade jetzt einen Graben quer durch Europa zu ziehen. Es ist so als ob &ouml;stlich von Wien Feindesland w&auml;re.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Die Grenzposten werden von Deutschland an den eben beseitigten Eisernen Vorhang verlegt!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp; Diese neue Grenzziehung ist nicht nur quer durch Europa, sondern quer durch &Ouml;sterreich, wo die Donaumonarchie war. Es w&auml;re verantwortungslos und gef&auml;hrlich, durch den Anschluss an eine wirtschaftliche und politische &Uuml;bermacht das Gef&auml;lle zu und die Bedrohung f&uuml;r die L&auml;nder &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; zu vergr&ouml;&szlig;ern. &Ouml;sterreichs kulturelle, wirtschaftliche und geschichtliche Bestimmung, &Ouml;sterreichs Verantwortung und Ausstrahlung liegt im Osten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;(Das besagt auch der Name &Ouml;sterreich.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Fronten haben sich gewandelt. Es sind nicht mehr die politischen Grenzen, sondern die Front verl&auml;uft zwischen der brutalen, nur wirtschaftsinteressierten Wegwerfgesellschaft und der ausgebeuteten Natur und der zerst&ouml;rten Seele des Menschen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt einen neuen Widerstand und schon wieder feige Kollaborateure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die jetzt verantwortlichen Politiker sind Hampelm&auml;nner der Wirtschaftsinteressen und heucheln Umweltbewusstsein und Kulturbewusstsein mit Lippenbekenntnissen. Sie beschlie&szlig;en umweltzerst&ouml;rende und kulturzerst&ouml;rende Ma&szlig;nahmen, die unsere Zukunft in Frage stellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die sogenannte &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; betreibt die brutale Vernichtung unserer Lebensbasis, unserer uralten Kulturen, unserer kleinen, gewachsenen Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten, unseres Artenreichtums und unserer Selbstachtung.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Handelsvertretung des Gro&szlig;unternehmertums, der Gewerkschaften, Genossenschaften, der Gro&szlig;banken, der Giftkonzerne, der Monokultur-Monopolisten und der Atom-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;obby, die uns wie brave Schafe gemeinsam wie das Schlachtvieh in einen Zug in die falsche Richtung verladen will.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dieser riesigen Wirtschaftsmafia geht es nur um Macht und Geld und nicht um das Wohl der Natur und des Menschen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine von verantwortungslosen Schreibtischstrategen ferngesteuerte gigantische Fehlplanung zerst&ouml;rt die Fundamente unseres &uuml;ber uralte Zeiten gewachsenen Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa erlebt die gr&ouml;&szlig;te Vergewaltigung seiner Geschichte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus Br&uuml;ssel kommt keine geistige und kulturelle Erneuerung Europas. Von dort kommen keine Antworten auf die Fragen, die das Gewissen der V&ouml;lker Europas beunruhigen (Alberto Miele). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus dieser neuen Hegemonie kommen keine Botschaften, die die Identit&auml;t, unsere uralten Werte, die Inhalte unserer Zivilisation und die Sehns&uuml;chte der Menschen Europas betreffen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wo sind die Kulturen, die Religionen, die Philosophien, die ein neues europ&auml;isches Zeitalter aus der Taufe heben?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt, wo unsere Gesellschaft die Grenzen des Wachstums erreicht, ist Dezentralisierung unsere einzige &Uuml;berlebenschance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein Anschluss an diese &uuml;berm&auml;chtige Zentralgewalt, die noch immer Wirtschaftswachstum als Zentraldogma gegen alle Evidenz durchziehen will, hat f&uuml;r alle Beteiligten katastrophale Folgen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wohin diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; uns mithineinziehen will, ist ein gnadenloser Konkurrenzkampf, ein Amoklauf in eine gro&szlig;e, gef&auml;hrliche Illusion, in die Sackgasse des Wirtschaftswachstums. Es w&auml;re Wahnsinn, diesem exklusiven Klub der Wegwerfgesellschaft beizutreten, der sich selbst in den M&uuml;ll wirft und ad absurdum f&uuml;hrt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das Produkt &quot;EU&quot; so gut ist, warum muss man derart intensiv daf&uuml;r werben? Und dieser verd&auml;chtige Zeitdruck: Wir m&uuml;ssen uns sofort enteignen, sonst ist es zu sp&auml;t! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Alle guten Dinge geschehen langsam in einem organischen Ablauf von selbst. Einen Baum kann man auch nicht mit Drohungen &uuml;berzeugen und &uuml;berreden, da&szlig; er im tiefen Winter zu bl&uuml;hen hat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe nicht, warum man uns mit Gewalt &uuml;berreden will, die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;, dieses sinkende Schiff zu besteigen, und zwar sofort.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Titanic. Die Analogien zum Untergang der Titanic sind erschreckend. Hier wie dort: Konzeptlosigkeit, Gr&ouml;&szlig;enwahn, Ma&szlig;losigkeit, blinde Technologiegl&auml;ubigkeit und Geschwindigkeitswahn um jeden Preis. Dort das Rennen um das &quot;blaue Band&quot; in die t&ouml;dlichen Eisberge, hier das m&ouml;rderische Wettrennen an die Grenzen des Wachstums der Wegwerfgesellschaft, die unsere Umwelt und uns selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;So einen &quot;europ&auml;ischen Ungl&uuml;cksdampfer&quot; besteigt man nicht und vertraut man unser Leben und unsere Zukunft nicht an. Da ist es besser, man bleibt in einem kleinen, aber man&ouml;vrierbaren Boot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In praktisch der ganzen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; geht es wild zu: Nordirland, Baskenland, Korsika, Mafia, Comorra, Ausl&auml;nderverfolgungen, Rassenhass und Pogrome, Diskriminierung von Gr&ouml;nl&auml;ndern, Macedoniern und Bretonen, brutale Streiks, blutige Ausschreitungen, Studentenrevolten, Drogenkriminalit&auml;t, nukleare St&ouml;rf&auml;lle, verw&uuml;stete Landstriche, Apathie und Katastrophenstimmung, Jugendkriminalit&auml;t, bald 20 Millionen Arbeitslose und eine Staatsspaltung in Flamen und Wallonen, ausgerechnet in Br&uuml;ssel, dem Sitz der &quot;Europ&auml;ischen Union&quot;. Im Vergleich dazu haben das &quot;isolierte &Ouml;sterreich&quot; und die skandinavischen L&auml;nder, die man unbedingt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; treiben will, es &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; noch gut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; mit Menschenschicksalen jongliert als w&auml;ren es Bauern auf dem Schachbrett. Man kann doch freie Bauern nicht mit Geld abspeisen und ins Ausgedinge schicken, das ist erniedrigend, oder sie nur noch als Folklore- und Alibibauern ben&uuml;tzen, zum Herzeigen f&uuml;r den Tourismus. Das geht gegen Ehre und Selbstachtung, das ist &auml;rger als Mord.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man bezahlt die Bauern f&uuml;r ihren Selbstmord. Die EU verlangt von den Bauern, sie sollen ihre eigene uralte Kultur zerst&ouml;ren. Daf&uuml;r bekommen sie Geld. Anders als bei der Katastrophenhilfe wird die Katastrophe erst mutwillig in Gang gesetzt. Umgebrachte gewachsene Strukturen kann man auch mit sehr viel Geld nicht wiedergutmachen. Tote kann man mit Geld nicht zum Leben erwecken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Wunsch einiger m&auml;chtiger und konkurrenzf&auml;higer Gro&szlig;industrieller nach Eintritt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist, noch mehr wirtschaftliche Vorteile zu erlangen. Das geht jedoch auf Kosten der sowieso schon gef&auml;hrdeten Kleinbetriebe und Kleinbauern.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich wei&szlig; aus eigener Erfahrung, dass in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten z.B. in Frankreich nur Agrargenossenschaften &uuml;ber 100 ha eine &Uuml;berlebenschance haben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das schaut dann so aus: entweder brachliegende, ver&ouml;dete Felder, verlassene D&ouml;rfer oder Nivellierung von Terrain, Beseitigung von f&uuml;r Gro&szlig;maschinen st&ouml;rende W&auml;ldchen, B&auml;umen und Felsen, Nivellierung von uralten Geh&ouml;ften, Begradigung von B&auml;chen. Eine perfide Zerst&ouml;rung, die in ihren gigantischen Auswirkungen jeden Krieg &uuml;bersteigt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Vermehrte Verwendung von Kunstd&uuml;nger, Pestiziden, genetischen Manipulationen, Bestrahlungen und Umweltgiften aller Art, nat&uuml;rlich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; erzeugt. Eine sadistische, technokratische Zerst&ouml;rung jeglicher Romantik mit dem Schlagwort: unrentabel. Monokultur, so weit das Auge reicht. Dem Bauern wird befohlen, unsere &Uuml;berlebensgrundlage systematisch zu vergewaltigen, den ihm zu treuen H&auml;nden anvertrauten Grund und Boden, Wald und Fluren zu vergiften und zu zerst&ouml;ren. Die Landwirtschaft wird zur gigantischen Agro-Business-Industrie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Abh&auml;ngigkeit der Bauern und von uns allen von Industrie, Chemie und Monopolwirtschaft, diese neue Leibeigenschaft, wird durch einen Anschluss an die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ins Unertr&auml;gliche gesteigert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ausl&auml;ndische, m&auml;chtigere, brutalere Befehlshaber treten an die Stelle der einheimischen kleineren Firmen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ebenso ergeht es den Kleineren, d. h. allen menschlichen Betrieben, sie werden vernichtet, daf&uuml;r gibt es noch mehr Gro&szlig;kaufh&auml;user, Gro&szlig;banken und Gro&szlig;industrialisierung. Kurzum alles, was unser aller Leben romantisch, liebens- und lebenswert macht, hat kaum mehr &Uuml;berlebensm&ouml;glichkeit. Die stupiden Brutalit&auml;ten siegen, die delikaten Werte kommen um, weil sie sich nicht wehren k&ouml;nnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Agro-Business-Industrie in der EU betreibt fast analog dem &bdquo;Dritten Reich&quot; eine brutale Auslese von reinrassigen gleichgeschalteten &quot;Elite&quot;-Produkten und eine Eliminierung von &quot;minderwertigem&quot; Erbgut oder Saatgut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es beginnt mit den sch&ouml;nen gro&szlig;en &Auml;pfeln, die alle gleich sein m&uuml;ssen, die in Monokultur gez&uuml;chtet sind, in gleicher Rasse, mit gleichem Geschmack, und setzt sich fort in der genetischen &quot;Nutztierveredelung&quot; und den Legehennenbatterien. Alles nicht produktive Leben wird eliminiert. Alle nicht profitable Vielfalt, alle Andersartigkeit, alle Kleinteiligkeit, aller nutzloser Artenreichtum, alle unrentable Sch&ouml;nheit wird vernichtet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dadurch sterben auch das Kleinbauerntum, die Familienbetriebe, die Romantik, kurzum unsere Lebensqualit&auml;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Durch das Sterben der Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen),&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Bauern, der Familien- und Kleinbetriebe, durch das Sterben der kleinen Identit&auml;ten entsteht eine Gleichschaltung und eine Anonymisierung unserer Gesellschaft. Man raubt dem Menschen seine W&uuml;rde. Dies bringt eine neue Abh&auml;ngigkeit, eine neue Versklavung, eine neue Leibeigenschaft noch nie dagewesenen Ausma&szlig;es hervor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das ist das Ende des humanistischen Europas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was dann &uuml;brigbleibt ist keine menschengerechte, sondern eine maschinengerechte und computergerechte Welt. Es ist eine Zerst&ouml;rung von h&ouml;heren Werten, die in ihrer Vielfalt Europa ausmachen. Es ist die Zerst&ouml;rung Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kleinbauern m&uuml;ssen Haus und Hof und Land verkaufen, werden entweder arbeitslos oder Stadtproletariat oder m&uuml;ssen sich Agro-Business-Genossenschaften anschlie&szlig;en, wo sie nur mehr Befehlsempf&auml;nger ohne Entscheidungsfreiheit sind, auf einem Land, das einmal ihnen geh&ouml;rte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; leidet unter einem wachsenden Arbeitslosenheer, das schon jetzt der arbeitenden Bev&ouml;lkerung eines Landes 7- bis 10-mal so gro&szlig; wie &Ouml;sterreich entspricht!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man kann sich vorstellen, welches verheerende Beispiel die &lt;strong&gt;EU &lt;/strong&gt;damit der Welt gibt, wenn die 3 Milliarden Menschen, die in der Dritten Welt auf dem Lande ihr Auskommen finden, diesem &lt;strong&gt;EU B&lt;/strong&gt;eispiel zu folgen gezwungen werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine gigantische Fl&uuml;chtlingswelle von 2 Milliarden Landbev&ouml;lkerung - diesen &quot;exode rural mondial&quot;, wie Jimmy Goldsmith warnt, k&ouml;nne die Welt nicht mehr ertragen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Grenzen sind so wie unsere Haut. Sie sch&uuml;tzen den gewachsenen Organismus, unsere individuelle Andersartigkeit vor Gefahr von Au&szlig;en wie Hitze und K&auml;lte. Wenn man die Haut entfernt, stirbt der Organismus, weil er schutzlos wird.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Daher haben wir Schutzz&ouml;lle zum Schutz einer gef&auml;hrdeten Gemeinschaft. &auml;hnlich wie wir Sonnenbrillen und Zeckenimpfungen etc. zu unserem Schutz einsetzen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was Gott getrennt hat, sollen wir nicht mit Gewalt einen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt nat&uuml;rliche Grenzen wie zum Beispiel die Sahara, das Mittelmeer und die Alpen, in deren Schutz sich uralte Kulturen gebildet haben wie die afrikanischen, die mediterranen und die nordeurop&auml;ischen Kulturen. Die Alpen haben eine Schutzfunktion sowohl f&uuml;r den Norden als auch f&uuml;r den S&uuml;den.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein schrankenloser, sinnloser Transitverkehr ist gleichbedeutend mit einem Niederrei&szlig;en und Nivellieren der Alpen, auch wenn der Verkehr untertunnelt wird. &Ouml;sterreich hat genauso wie die Schweiz eine Alpine Schutzw&auml;chterfunktion f&uuml;r Europa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die fieberhafte, unnat&uuml;rliche, konzeptlose Hin- und Herraserei ist Wahnsinn und wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; zum &quot;grenzenlosen Wahnsinn&quot;. An dem Ort, wo wir sind, machen wir alles hin, dann fl&uuml;chten wir vor unserer eigenen Zerst&ouml;rung, um anderswo alles hin zu machen, und auf dem Weg dahin wird auch alles hin. Dieser falsche Trend wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; forciert und unterst&uuml;tzt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou dr&uuml;ckt das so aus: Eine Wirtschaft, die nur auf Kurzzeit-Rentabilit&auml;t ausgerichtet ist, ohne Plan, ohne Vision, ohne Sinn, die arbeitsstellen-fressende Maschinen produziert, die mehr und mehr von der Transport- und Kommunikationsgeschwindigkeit abh&auml;ngig ist und die unter Au&szlig;erachtlassung des &ouml;kologischen Gleichgewichtes die Menschen zu einer ebenso forcierten Beweglichkeit zwingt wie die Waren, die Kapitalien, die Technologien und Informationen unter Missachtung der Menschenw&uuml;rde und des Schutzes der gewohnten Lebensweisen, eine &ouml;konomische Diktatur, die &uuml;ber alle anderen menschlichen T&auml;tigkeiten triumphiert...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn man das, was man zu sch&uuml;tzen hat, vorher umbringt, braucht man keinen Schutz mehr. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen die Bauern und die Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; weg und die Kleinbetriebe und der &quot;nutzlose&quot; Artenreichtum, die &quot;unrentable&quot; Vielfalt. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir uns angleichen an internationales Mittelma&szlig;, an vergiftetes Essen, genmanipulierte und bestrahlte Lebensmittel. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir in vorauseilendem Gehorsam uns selbst nivellieren und uns vernichten, dann kann die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; widerstandslos einmarschieren und durchmarschieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich als ganzes wird ein Vasallenstaat, eine neue Ostmark. Selbstverst&auml;ndlich ist dann &Ouml;sterreichs Position als neutrale, kernkraftfreie, umweltbewusste Nation kaum mehr haltbar. &Ouml;sterreich kann dann nicht mehr selbst entscheiden, was es tut, was und wieviel es produziert und in welche L&auml;nder es exportiert und aus welchen es importiert. &Ouml;sterreichs Geschicke werden von fremden Leuten in Br&uuml;ssel oder anderswo in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; bestimmt, von Schreibtischstrategen, die sich einen Dreck um &Ouml;sterreichs Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit scheren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;tswillen, &uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Umweltbewusstsein wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Kommandozentrale nur gelacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Slogan &quot;einsam oder gemeinsam&quot; ist eine angstmachende, demagogische Aufforderung zur Verunsicherung, zur Unfreiheit und zur Abh&auml;ngigkeit. Es mag paradox klingen, aber allein ist jeder am st&auml;rksten. Aus pers&ouml;nlicher Erfahrung wei&szlig; ich, dass ein Aussenstehender genauso stark ist wie die Gruppe und nicht schw&auml;cher. Der Au&szlig;enstehende ist beweglicher, effektiver in seinem Handeln und im Reagieren als eine schwerf&auml;llige, b&uuml;rokratische, chaotische Organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa ist nur stark dank der Vielfalt seiner Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. Diese kleinteilige Vielfalt muss verst&auml;rkt und gesch&uuml;tzt werden. Diese Vielfalt ist Europa. Schon de Gaulle erkannte, dass Europa nur eine Chance als Europa der selbst&auml;ndigen, freien Vaterl&auml;nder hat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unverst&auml;ndlich, wie verantwortungslos unsere Politiker jetzt unser wertvollstes Gut, unsere Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit und Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit aufgeben und &Ouml;sterreich entm&uuml;ndigen wollen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein Verrat an &Ouml;sterreich. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim letzten Anschluss gab es auch jede Menge Seyss-Inquarts, Guislings, Petains, die in der damaligen Situation wahrscheinlich auch aus &Uuml;berzeugung und Patriotismus glaubten, das Richtige zu tun und ihre Pflicht erf&uuml;llen zu m&uuml;ssen, indem sie ihr Land einer fremden Hegemonie anvertrauten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Heute lehrt uns die Geschichte, dass ihr Tun falsch und sch&auml;dlich war, und sie sind l&auml;ngst als Verr&auml;ter und Kollaborateure gebrandmarkt, bestraft und hingerichtet worden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mitgefangen - mitgehangen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Unter der Dunstglocke der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird von allen unbemerkt der Anschluss an Deutschland vollzogen. Wenn dann diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Schiffbruch erleidet, haben wir noch ein St&uuml;ck mehr unserer Unabh&auml;ngigkeit verloren und bleiben am gro&szlig;en deutschen Bruder kleben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Bei Wahrung aller Unterschiede hat &Ouml;sterreich &Auml;hnliches bereits erlebt, als auch aus wirtschaftlichen Gr&uuml;nden 1937-1938 ein Anschluss an das &quot;Altreich&quot; propagiert wurde. &quot;Heim ins Reich&quot; hie&szlig; damals die Parole. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim Umtausch des Schilling in den Gro&szlig;macht-Euro muss man fatalerweise Analogien mit dem Umtausch des Schilling 1938 in die Reichsmark feststellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man darf nicht vergessen, dass das Versprechen einer finanziellen und wirtschaftlichen Besserstellung der k&uuml;nftigen Ostm&auml;rker Haupttriebfeder vieler &Ouml;sterreicher war, um f&uuml;r den Anschluss zu stimmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auf die bejubelte Einverleibung mit Gro&szlig;deutschland erfolgte die Ern&uuml;chterung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Jetzt ist es &auml;hnlich. Genau das, was man uns in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; vorgaukeln will, verlieren wir in der&lt;strong&gt; EU&lt;/strong&gt;: sozialen Wohlstand, Vollbesch&auml;ftigung, eine intakte Umwelt, unsere hohe Lebensqualit&auml;t, unsere Heimat, unsere Selbstachtung, unsere Natur und unsere uralten Kulturen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europ&auml;er ist man nur dann, wenn man sein unabh&auml;ngiges, eigenst&auml;ndiges Europ&auml;ertum bewahrt und hochh&auml;lt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Schweiz, wohlhabend und demokratisch, auch im Herzen Europas gelegen, soll uns ein leuchtendes Beispiel sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe auch nicht, wieso unser Bundespr&auml;sident uns zur Aufgabe unserer Souver&auml;nit&auml;t auffordert. Er m&uuml;sste doch als oberster Patriot warnen und die Verfassung sch&uuml;tzen. Ist denn Landesverrat kein Vergehen, wenn man &Ouml;sterreich einer ausl&auml;ndischen Zentralgewalt unterwerfen will? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Staatsvertrag brachte &Ouml;sterreich die Befreiung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Vertrag ist eine Kapitulation &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Entm&uuml;ndigung &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Unterwerfung unter eine neue anachronistische Hegemonie - und ein Bruch des Staatsvertrages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unglaublich: Die Politiker bereiten den zweiten Anschluss vor und wollen das &ouml;sterreichische Volk vor vollendete Tatsachen stellen. Sind unsere Politiker von allen guten Geistern verlassen, so dass erst&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; die Geschichte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; sie zurechtweisen muss? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich bin kein Jurist, aber ich bin der festen &Uuml;berzeugung, dass wir von m&auml;chtigen Interessensgruppen au&szlig;erhalb jeder ethischen, geschichtlichen, moralischen, kulturellen und &ouml;kologischen Legalit&auml;t mit einer miesen Demagogie manipuliert werden, so wie seinerzeit bei Zwentendorf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Inbetriebnahme des Atommeilers wurde durch Volksabstimmung verhindert)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten werden nivelliert und anonymisiert und ihrer Identit&auml;t beraubt. In diese Richtung geht es und nicht in die Richtung der Dezentralisation und&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Vertiefung&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Zum Beweis gen&uuml;gt die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne mit den jetzt 12 genau gleichen 5-zackigen Sternchen. Welches dieser Sternchen w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich symbolisieren, etwa das dritte rechts von unten oder das zweite, das genauso aussieht?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der F&uuml;nfstern ist kein Symbol aus der europ&auml;ischen und schon gar nicht aus der &ouml;sterreichischen Geschichte. Er kommt in der Entwicklung der Staaten des Okzidents nicht vor. Das Pentagramm, ein okkultistisches Zeichen der Druden und Freimaurer ist ein Fremdk&ouml;rper in der abendl&auml;ndischen Heraldik. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die 5-zackigen Sterne dienen eher als Merkmal der Unterwerfung, Inbesitznahme und Kolonisierung wie auf der austral-neuseel&auml;ndischen, amerikanischen und auf Kolonialfahnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne ist noch dazu ein Plagiat aus dem Sternenbanner. Auch die Vereinigten Staaten Amerikas waren als 5-zackige Sternchen, wei&szlig; auf blau, zuerst im Kreis angeordnet, genauso wie jetzt die M&ouml;chtegern-&quot;Vereinigten Staaten Europas&quot;. Sp&auml;ter, als sie sich vermehrten, wurden sie in Reih und Glied gebracht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese 5-zackigen Sternchen sind dieselben wie der Sowjetstern, der Stern der jugoslawischen, chinesischen, kubanischen und sonstigen Volksrepubliken. Wahrlich, dieses Symbol ist ein Armutszeugnis f&uuml;r die gewachsenen Identit&auml;ten Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein b&ouml;ses Omen, wenn schon das Zeichen falsch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Sternchenfahne symbolisiert die Selbstaufgabe Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist die Kultur weniger als Nebensache. Die sch&ouml;pferischen Kr&auml;fte werden zu n&uuml;tzlichen Idioten getrimmt. Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung und Verbr&auml;mung und Legitimierung eines merkantilen und industriellen Wachstums, das sich selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kultur ist in Br&uuml;ssel nicht pr&auml;sent. Sie ist in der nur merkantilen und industriellen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; kein Thema. In Br&uuml;ssel kennt man den Preis von allem und den Wert von nichts. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es geht in dieser kulturlosen, sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; nur um Zahlen: Produktionszahlen, Termine und Laufzeiten, &Uuml;bergangsfristen, Einwohner- und Viehzahlen. Bruttosozialprodukte, Anbau-, Wald- und Weidegebiete in Quadratkilometern, Lohnkosten, Sozialleistungen, Nebenkosten. Exportziffern, Tonnenzahlen f&uuml;r Schwertransporte, Milchpreise, Preisanpassungen, Finanzierungszahlen, Ausgleichszahlen, Prozente, Preissenkungen, Zucker-, Milch&shy;- und Fischquoten, Transitbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen, Kontingente, Mitfinanzierungen, Tabellen, Statistiken, Marktzugangsbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen. Laufzeiten, Ecu Umtauschkurse, hohe Arbeitslosenzahlen, niedrige Besch&auml;ftigungszahlen, F&ouml;rderungs- und Subventionszahlen, die Anzahl von &Ouml;kopunkten, Geldzahlungen aller Art, irreale Wirtschaftswachstumszahlen, Umfrageergebnisse in Zahlen und Prozenten, Stimmenanzahlen des Ministerrates und der Sperrminorit&auml;t, Mehrheiten, Minderheiten, Abstimmungsergebnisse, EU-Werbeausgaben. Ja sogar H&ouml;henzahlen f&uuml;r Bergbauern in Metern und Breitegradzahlen f&uuml;r die Landwirtschaft in Finnland. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das nicht symptomatisch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch der Umweltschutz ist in der Br&uuml;sseler Hegemonie abwesend. Nur 0,3 Prozent (30 von 10.000) der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Beamten sind f&uuml;r die &Ouml;kologie t&auml;tig. Vom Grenzen &uuml;berbr&uuml;ckenden Umweltschutz ist nur die Rede. &Ouml;sterreich muss die Kernkraft mitfinanzieren und z. B. Plastikflaschen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-Produkte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und idiotisch-gef&auml;hrliche Richtlinien f&uuml;r Apfelgr&ouml;&szlig;en und Monokultur-Obstsorten &uuml;bernehmen. Das habe ich selbst gesehen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Von Kultur und den Werten des Abendlandes ist in Br&uuml;ssel keine Rede. Um Ausgaben f&uuml;r Kultur muss man erst Br&uuml;ssel bitten. Das Kulturstudium und auch der gesamte Studienbereich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird ausgerichtet auf die N&uuml;tzlichkeit f&uuml;r die Industrie und auf das forcierte Wachstum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Kreativit&auml;t und organisches Wachstum lehren. Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Achtung lehren vor dem Artenreichtum und der unglaublichen Vielfalt, deren Teil wir selbst sind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; aber gehen die Bestrebungen in die genau umgekehrte Richtung: Vernichtung der kleinteiligen sch&ouml;pferischen Werte zugunsten einer v&ouml;llig falschen und &uuml;berholten Automatisierung, Zentralisierung und Rationalisierung, die uns &uuml;ber kurz oder lang zum Untergang bringt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das Gewissen unserer Zivilisation, unsere uralte Bestimmung, h&ouml;here Werte anzustreben, bleibt auf der Strecke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_occasion_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Written in Vienna &ndash; Paris &ndash; Kaurinui, 1988&ndash;1994. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Passages in italics: La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Geschrieben in Wien - Paris - Kaurinui, 1988 - 1994,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; erg&auml;nzt in kursiv in La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1993, p. 65-68 (Text Anschlu&szlig;psychose, 1988) (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;protokolle&lt;/em&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. edited by Otto Breicha. Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Vienna, 1997, pp. 185-193 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1998, p. 83-99 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 1151-1162 (German and English)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Langen M&uuml;ller: Munich, 2004, pp. 55-64 (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1993, S. 65-68 (Text &lt;span style=&quot;background: yellow 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial&quot;&gt;Anschlu&szlig;psychose&lt;/span&gt;, 1988)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;protokolle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. hrsg. von Otto Breicha. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Wien 1997, S. 185-193&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1998, S. 83-99&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. II: F&uuml;r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;st, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 1151-1162 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Langen M&uuml;ller: M&uuml;nchen 2004, S. 55-64&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'', text_translator-'Courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-22 13:38:47.54###object###text###1.4.5.1###TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.5.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-124&quot;&gt; 124&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-124&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;124 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-125&quot;&gt; 125&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-125&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;125 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-126&quot;&gt; 126&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-126&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;126 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-127&quot;&gt; 127&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-127&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;127 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', id-130, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-130, txt-'1.4.5.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?', text_title_ge-'', text_keywords-'', text_date-'1994-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_language-en, text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In Sache &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird die &ouml;sterreichische &Ouml;ffentlichkeit von den staatlichen Medien einer dogmatischen Gehirnw&auml;sche ohnegleichen ausgesetzt. Es herrscht im Fernsehen, im Radio und fast in der gesamten Presse eine infame verschleierte Zensur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich w&uuml;rde das auch nicht in einer Demokratie f&uuml;r m&ouml;glich halten, h&auml;tte ich diese Art von Zensur nicht selbst erlebt. Unter allerlei Pr&auml;texten und Vorw&auml;nden wurde ich mehrmals behindert und verhindert,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; &ouml;ffentlich&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; eine Anti-&lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Meinung zu vertreten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Vorw&auml;nde waren: es passe nicht in die Sendung, ich d&uuml;rfe nichts vorlesen, ich w&auml;re daf&uuml;r nicht zust&auml;ndig, ich w&auml;re verr&uuml;ckt oder aber man versucht mit gezielter Diffamation mich unglaubw&uuml;rdig zu machen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dabei sind meine Bedenken und &Auml;ngste in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten selbst l&auml;ngst best&auml;tigt. Warum h&ouml;rt man nicht auf Leopold Kohr (Das Ende der Gro&szlig;en), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (Small is beautiful), Jimmy Goldsmith (Le pi&egrave;ge - et si nous avions suivi la mauvaise route?), Henry Coston (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe des banquiers), Jean Pierre Chevenement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe Seguin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (Cacciamo i mercanti dal tempio dell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europa), Gerard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht-Partei), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (Ex-EU-Kommissar: &quot;k&uuml;nstliche Superkonstruktion nicht lebensf&auml;hig&quot;), Denis de Rougemont (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe doit se faire pour la diversit&eacute;) und unz&auml;hlige andere Warner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich ist von der Geschichte auserw&auml;hlt, Beispiel und Zentrum und Halt in Mitteleuropa zu sein. &Ouml;sterreich ist eine Br&uuml;cke der Hoffnung zum Osten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wir haben seit dem Krieg in m&uuml;hevoller Arbeit ein riesiges Kapital an Wohlstand, innerem Frieden, internationalem Respekt und Glaubw&uuml;rdigkeit aufgebaut als unabh&auml;ngige, liebenswerte, friedliebende Kulturnation im Herzen Europas. Das kann nicht kurzsichtig und verantwortungslos aufs Spiel gesetzt werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt nach dem Zerfall der kommunistischen Diktatur und der &Ouml;ffnung der Grenzen muss sich &Ouml;sterreich seiner Verantwortung in Europa bewusst werden und darf sich nicht selbst eliminieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mit einer uns suggerierten Torschlusspanik wird eine Anschlussneurose erzeugt. Angst vor was oder wem? Welche Feinde hat &Ouml;sterreich? Wer sollte und warum &Ouml;sterreichs Sicherheit gef&auml;hrden? Gerade durch den Anschluss an einen Milit&auml;rblock w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich als &quot;Randgebiet Ostmark&quot; erst zum Aufmarschgebiet und zum Feindbild und Angriffsziel werden (Warnung von Erwin Lanc). Gegen atomare Bedrohung ist kein Kraut gewachsen und bei Regionalkriegen - siehe Bosnien - gibt es keinen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Schutz, nicht einmal in Nordirland, innerhalb der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;t ist gerade jetzt n&ouml;tiger als je zuvor. Man muss die Neutralit&auml;t beim Namen nennen und zu ihr stehen. Neutralit&auml;t ist ein wahrer Wert. Die immerw&auml;hrende Neutralit&auml;t ist das Fundament unseres Staates und darf nicht verraten und ausgeh&ouml;hlt werden. Wenn wir dieses Fundament unterminieren, zerst&ouml;ren wir diesen unseren Staat &Ouml;sterreich, der darauf errichtet ist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ab jetzt bedeutet die Neutralit&auml;t &Ouml;sterreichs Selbst&auml;ndigkeit, Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit, Verantwortung tragen, Beispiel geben, eine aktive Neutralit&auml;t. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch hier ist die Schweiz ein Beispiel und wird auch im Staatsvertrag als Beispiel genannt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es besteht kein Anlass, gerade jetzt einen Graben quer durch Europa zu ziehen. Es ist so als ob &ouml;stlich von Wien Feindesland w&auml;re.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Die Grenzposten werden von Deutschland an den eben beseitigten Eisernen Vorhang verlegt!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp; Diese neue Grenzziehung ist nicht nur quer durch Europa, sondern quer durch &Ouml;sterreich, wo die Donaumonarchie war. Es w&auml;re verantwortungslos und gef&auml;hrlich, durch den Anschluss an eine wirtschaftliche und politische &Uuml;bermacht das Gef&auml;lle zu und die Bedrohung f&uuml;r die L&auml;nder &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; zu vergr&ouml;&szlig;ern. &Ouml;sterreichs kulturelle, wirtschaftliche und geschichtliche Bestimmung, &Ouml;sterreichs Verantwortung und Ausstrahlung liegt im Osten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;(Das besagt auch der Name &Ouml;sterreich.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Fronten haben sich gewandelt. Es sind nicht mehr die politischen Grenzen, sondern die Front verl&auml;uft zwischen der brutalen, nur wirtschaftsinteressierten Wegwerfgesellschaft und der ausgebeuteten Natur und der zerst&ouml;rten Seele des Menschen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt einen neuen Widerstand und schon wieder feige Kollaborateure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die jetzt verantwortlichen Politiker sind Hampelm&auml;nner der Wirtschaftsinteressen und heucheln Umweltbewusstsein und Kulturbewusstsein mit Lippenbekenntnissen. Sie beschlie&szlig;en umweltzerst&ouml;rende und kulturzerst&ouml;rende Ma&szlig;nahmen, die unsere Zukunft in Frage stellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die sogenannte &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; betreibt die brutale Vernichtung unserer Lebensbasis, unserer uralten Kulturen, unserer kleinen, gewachsenen Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten, unseres Artenreichtums und unserer Selbstachtung.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Handelsvertretung des Gro&szlig;unternehmertums, der Gewerkschaften, Genossenschaften, der Gro&szlig;banken, der Giftkonzerne, der Monokultur-Monopolisten und der Atom-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;obby, die uns wie brave Schafe gemeinsam wie das Schlachtvieh in einen Zug in die falsche Richtung verladen will.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dieser riesigen Wirtschaftsmafia geht es nur um Macht und Geld und nicht um das Wohl der Natur und des Menschen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine von verantwortungslosen Schreibtischstrategen ferngesteuerte gigantische Fehlplanung zerst&ouml;rt die Fundamente unseres &uuml;ber uralte Zeiten gewachsenen Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa erlebt die gr&ouml;&szlig;te Vergewaltigung seiner Geschichte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus Br&uuml;ssel kommt keine geistige und kulturelle Erneuerung Europas. Von dort kommen keine Antworten auf die Fragen, die das Gewissen der V&ouml;lker Europas beunruhigen (Alberto Miele). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus dieser neuen Hegemonie kommen keine Botschaften, die die Identit&auml;t, unsere uralten Werte, die Inhalte unserer Zivilisation und die Sehns&uuml;chte der Menschen Europas betreffen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wo sind die Kulturen, die Religionen, die Philosophien, die ein neues europ&auml;isches Zeitalter aus der Taufe heben?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt, wo unsere Gesellschaft die Grenzen des Wachstums erreicht, ist Dezentralisierung unsere einzige &Uuml;berlebenschance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein Anschluss an diese &uuml;berm&auml;chtige Zentralgewalt, die noch immer Wirtschaftswachstum als Zentraldogma gegen alle Evidenz durchziehen will, hat f&uuml;r alle Beteiligten katastrophale Folgen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wohin diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; uns mithineinziehen will, ist ein gnadenloser Konkurrenzkampf, ein Amoklauf in eine gro&szlig;e, gef&auml;hrliche Illusion, in die Sackgasse des Wirtschaftswachstums. Es w&auml;re Wahnsinn, diesem exklusiven Klub der Wegwerfgesellschaft beizutreten, der sich selbst in den M&uuml;ll wirft und ad absurdum f&uuml;hrt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das Produkt &quot;EU&quot; so gut ist, warum muss man derart intensiv daf&uuml;r werben? Und dieser verd&auml;chtige Zeitdruck: Wir m&uuml;ssen uns sofort enteignen, sonst ist es zu sp&auml;t! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Alle guten Dinge geschehen langsam in einem organischen Ablauf von selbst. Einen Baum kann man auch nicht mit Drohungen &uuml;berzeugen und &uuml;berreden, da&szlig; er im tiefen Winter zu bl&uuml;hen hat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe nicht, warum man uns mit Gewalt &uuml;berreden will, die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;, dieses sinkende Schiff zu besteigen, und zwar sofort.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Titanic. Die Analogien zum Untergang der Titanic sind erschreckend. Hier wie dort: Konzeptlosigkeit, Gr&ouml;&szlig;enwahn, Ma&szlig;losigkeit, blinde Technologiegl&auml;ubigkeit und Geschwindigkeitswahn um jeden Preis. Dort das Rennen um das &quot;blaue Band&quot; in die t&ouml;dlichen Eisberge, hier das m&ouml;rderische Wettrennen an die Grenzen des Wachstums der Wegwerfgesellschaft, die unsere Umwelt und uns selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;So einen &quot;europ&auml;ischen Ungl&uuml;cksdampfer&quot; besteigt man nicht und vertraut man unser Leben und unsere Zukunft nicht an. Da ist es besser, man bleibt in einem kleinen, aber man&ouml;vrierbaren Boot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In praktisch der ganzen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; geht es wild zu: Nordirland, Baskenland, Korsika, Mafia, Comorra, Ausl&auml;nderverfolgungen, Rassenhass und Pogrome, Diskriminierung von Gr&ouml;nl&auml;ndern, Macedoniern und Bretonen, brutale Streiks, blutige Ausschreitungen, Studentenrevolten, Drogenkriminalit&auml;t, nukleare St&ouml;rf&auml;lle, verw&uuml;stete Landstriche, Apathie und Katastrophenstimmung, Jugendkriminalit&auml;t, bald 20 Millionen Arbeitslose und eine Staatsspaltung in Flamen und Wallonen, ausgerechnet in Br&uuml;ssel, dem Sitz der &quot;Europ&auml;ischen Union&quot;. Im Vergleich dazu haben das &quot;isolierte &Ouml;sterreich&quot; und die skandinavischen L&auml;nder, die man unbedingt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; treiben will, es &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; noch gut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; mit Menschenschicksalen jongliert als w&auml;ren es Bauern auf dem Schachbrett. Man kann doch freie Bauern nicht mit Geld abspeisen und ins Ausgedinge schicken, das ist erniedrigend, oder sie nur noch als Folklore- und Alibibauern ben&uuml;tzen, zum Herzeigen f&uuml;r den Tourismus. Das geht gegen Ehre und Selbstachtung, das ist &auml;rger als Mord.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man bezahlt die Bauern f&uuml;r ihren Selbstmord. Die EU verlangt von den Bauern, sie sollen ihre eigene uralte Kultur zerst&ouml;ren. Daf&uuml;r bekommen sie Geld. Anders als bei der Katastrophenhilfe wird die Katastrophe erst mutwillig in Gang gesetzt. Umgebrachte gewachsene Strukturen kann man auch mit sehr viel Geld nicht wiedergutmachen. Tote kann man mit Geld nicht zum Leben erwecken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Wunsch einiger m&auml;chtiger und konkurrenzf&auml;higer Gro&szlig;industrieller nach Eintritt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist, noch mehr wirtschaftliche Vorteile zu erlangen. Das geht jedoch auf Kosten der sowieso schon gef&auml;hrdeten Kleinbetriebe und Kleinbauern.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich wei&szlig; aus eigener Erfahrung, dass in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten z.B. in Frankreich nur Agrargenossenschaften &uuml;ber 100 ha eine &Uuml;berlebenschance haben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das schaut dann so aus: entweder brachliegende, ver&ouml;dete Felder, verlassene D&ouml;rfer oder Nivellierung von Terrain, Beseitigung von f&uuml;r Gro&szlig;maschinen st&ouml;rende W&auml;ldchen, B&auml;umen und Felsen, Nivellierung von uralten Geh&ouml;ften, Begradigung von B&auml;chen. Eine perfide Zerst&ouml;rung, die in ihren gigantischen Auswirkungen jeden Krieg &uuml;bersteigt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Vermehrte Verwendung von Kunstd&uuml;nger, Pestiziden, genetischen Manipulationen, Bestrahlungen und Umweltgiften aller Art, nat&uuml;rlich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; erzeugt. Eine sadistische, technokratische Zerst&ouml;rung jeglicher Romantik mit dem Schlagwort: unrentabel. Monokultur, so weit das Auge reicht. Dem Bauern wird befohlen, unsere &Uuml;berlebensgrundlage systematisch zu vergewaltigen, den ihm zu treuen H&auml;nden anvertrauten Grund und Boden, Wald und Fluren zu vergiften und zu zerst&ouml;ren. Die Landwirtschaft wird zur gigantischen Agro-Business-Industrie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Abh&auml;ngigkeit der Bauern und von uns allen von Industrie, Chemie und Monopolwirtschaft, diese neue Leibeigenschaft, wird durch einen Anschluss an die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ins Unertr&auml;gliche gesteigert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ausl&auml;ndische, m&auml;chtigere, brutalere Befehlshaber treten an die Stelle der einheimischen kleineren Firmen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ebenso ergeht es den Kleineren, d. h. allen menschlichen Betrieben, sie werden vernichtet, daf&uuml;r gibt es noch mehr Gro&szlig;kaufh&auml;user, Gro&szlig;banken und Gro&szlig;industrialisierung. Kurzum alles, was unser aller Leben romantisch, liebens- und lebenswert macht, hat kaum mehr &Uuml;berlebensm&ouml;glichkeit. Die stupiden Brutalit&auml;ten siegen, die delikaten Werte kommen um, weil sie sich nicht wehren k&ouml;nnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Agro-Business-Industrie in der EU betreibt fast analog dem &bdquo;Dritten Reich&quot; eine brutale Auslese von reinrassigen gleichgeschalteten &quot;Elite&quot;-Produkten und eine Eliminierung von &quot;minderwertigem&quot; Erbgut oder Saatgut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es beginnt mit den sch&ouml;nen gro&szlig;en &Auml;pfeln, die alle gleich sein m&uuml;ssen, die in Monokultur gez&uuml;chtet sind, in gleicher Rasse, mit gleichem Geschmack, und setzt sich fort in der genetischen &quot;Nutztierveredelung&quot; und den Legehennenbatterien. Alles nicht produktive Leben wird eliminiert. Alle nicht profitable Vielfalt, alle Andersartigkeit, alle Kleinteiligkeit, aller nutzloser Artenreichtum, alle unrentable Sch&ouml;nheit wird vernichtet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dadurch sterben auch das Kleinbauerntum, die Familienbetriebe, die Romantik, kurzum unsere Lebensqualit&auml;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Durch das Sterben der Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen),&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Bauern, der Familien- und Kleinbetriebe, durch das Sterben der kleinen Identit&auml;ten entsteht eine Gleichschaltung und eine Anonymisierung unserer Gesellschaft. Man raubt dem Menschen seine W&uuml;rde. Dies bringt eine neue Abh&auml;ngigkeit, eine neue Versklavung, eine neue Leibeigenschaft noch nie dagewesenen Ausma&szlig;es hervor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das ist das Ende des humanistischen Europas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was dann &uuml;brigbleibt ist keine menschengerechte, sondern eine maschinengerechte und computergerechte Welt. Es ist eine Zerst&ouml;rung von h&ouml;heren Werten, die in ihrer Vielfalt Europa ausmachen. Es ist die Zerst&ouml;rung Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kleinbauern m&uuml;ssen Haus und Hof und Land verkaufen, werden entweder arbeitslos oder Stadtproletariat oder m&uuml;ssen sich Agro-Business-Genossenschaften anschlie&szlig;en, wo sie nur mehr Befehlsempf&auml;nger ohne Entscheidungsfreiheit sind, auf einem Land, das einmal ihnen geh&ouml;rte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; leidet unter einem wachsenden Arbeitslosenheer, das schon jetzt der arbeitenden Bev&ouml;lkerung eines Landes 7- bis 10-mal so gro&szlig; wie &Ouml;sterreich entspricht!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man kann sich vorstellen, welches verheerende Beispiel die &lt;strong&gt;EU &lt;/strong&gt;damit der Welt gibt, wenn die 3 Milliarden Menschen, die in der Dritten Welt auf dem Lande ihr Auskommen finden, diesem &lt;strong&gt;EU B&lt;/strong&gt;eispiel zu folgen gezwungen werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine gigantische Fl&uuml;chtlingswelle von 2 Milliarden Landbev&ouml;lkerung - diesen &quot;exode rural mondial&quot;, wie Jimmy Goldsmith warnt, k&ouml;nne die Welt nicht mehr ertragen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Grenzen sind so wie unsere Haut. Sie sch&uuml;tzen den gewachsenen Organismus, unsere individuelle Andersartigkeit vor Gefahr von Au&szlig;en wie Hitze und K&auml;lte. Wenn man die Haut entfernt, stirbt der Organismus, weil er schutzlos wird.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Daher haben wir Schutzz&ouml;lle zum Schutz einer gef&auml;hrdeten Gemeinschaft. &auml;hnlich wie wir Sonnenbrillen und Zeckenimpfungen etc. zu unserem Schutz einsetzen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was Gott getrennt hat, sollen wir nicht mit Gewalt einen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt nat&uuml;rliche Grenzen wie zum Beispiel die Sahara, das Mittelmeer und die Alpen, in deren Schutz sich uralte Kulturen gebildet haben wie die afrikanischen, die mediterranen und die nordeurop&auml;ischen Kulturen. Die Alpen haben eine Schutzfunktion sowohl f&uuml;r den Norden als auch f&uuml;r den S&uuml;den.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein schrankenloser, sinnloser Transitverkehr ist gleichbedeutend mit einem Niederrei&szlig;en und Nivellieren der Alpen, auch wenn der Verkehr untertunnelt wird. &Ouml;sterreich hat genauso wie die Schweiz eine Alpine Schutzw&auml;chterfunktion f&uuml;r Europa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die fieberhafte, unnat&uuml;rliche, konzeptlose Hin- und Herraserei ist Wahnsinn und wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; zum &quot;grenzenlosen Wahnsinn&quot;. An dem Ort, wo wir sind, machen wir alles hin, dann fl&uuml;chten wir vor unserer eigenen Zerst&ouml;rung, um anderswo alles hin zu machen, und auf dem Weg dahin wird auch alles hin. Dieser falsche Trend wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; forciert und unterst&uuml;tzt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou dr&uuml;ckt das so aus: Eine Wirtschaft, die nur auf Kurzzeit-Rentabilit&auml;t ausgerichtet ist, ohne Plan, ohne Vision, ohne Sinn, die arbeitsstellen-fressende Maschinen produziert, die mehr und mehr von der Transport- und Kommunikationsgeschwindigkeit abh&auml;ngig ist und die unter Au&szlig;erachtlassung des &ouml;kologischen Gleichgewichtes die Menschen zu einer ebenso forcierten Beweglichkeit zwingt wie die Waren, die Kapitalien, die Technologien und Informationen unter Missachtung der Menschenw&uuml;rde und des Schutzes der gewohnten Lebensweisen, eine &ouml;konomische Diktatur, die &uuml;ber alle anderen menschlichen T&auml;tigkeiten triumphiert...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn man das, was man zu sch&uuml;tzen hat, vorher umbringt, braucht man keinen Schutz mehr. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen die Bauern und die Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; weg und die Kleinbetriebe und der &quot;nutzlose&quot; Artenreichtum, die &quot;unrentable&quot; Vielfalt. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir uns angleichen an internationales Mittelma&szlig;, an vergiftetes Essen, genmanipulierte und bestrahlte Lebensmittel. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir in vorauseilendem Gehorsam uns selbst nivellieren und uns vernichten, dann kann die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; widerstandslos einmarschieren und durchmarschieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich als ganzes wird ein Vasallenstaat, eine neue Ostmark. Selbstverst&auml;ndlich ist dann &Ouml;sterreichs Position als neutrale, kernkraftfreie, umweltbewusste Nation kaum mehr haltbar. &Ouml;sterreich kann dann nicht mehr selbst entscheiden, was es tut, was und wieviel es produziert und in welche L&auml;nder es exportiert und aus welchen es importiert. &Ouml;sterreichs Geschicke werden von fremden Leuten in Br&uuml;ssel oder anderswo in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; bestimmt, von Schreibtischstrategen, die sich einen Dreck um &Ouml;sterreichs Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit scheren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;tswillen, &uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Umweltbewusstsein wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Kommandozentrale nur gelacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Slogan &quot;einsam oder gemeinsam&quot; ist eine angstmachende, demagogische Aufforderung zur Verunsicherung, zur Unfreiheit und zur Abh&auml;ngigkeit. Es mag paradox klingen, aber allein ist jeder am st&auml;rksten. Aus pers&ouml;nlicher Erfahrung wei&szlig; ich, dass ein Aussenstehender genauso stark ist wie die Gruppe und nicht schw&auml;cher. Der Au&szlig;enstehende ist beweglicher, effektiver in seinem Handeln und im Reagieren als eine schwerf&auml;llige, b&uuml;rokratische, chaotische Organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa ist nur stark dank der Vielfalt seiner Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. Diese kleinteilige Vielfalt muss verst&auml;rkt und gesch&uuml;tzt werden. Diese Vielfalt ist Europa. Schon de Gaulle erkannte, dass Europa nur eine Chance als Europa der selbst&auml;ndigen, freien Vaterl&auml;nder hat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unverst&auml;ndlich, wie verantwortungslos unsere Politiker jetzt unser wertvollstes Gut, unsere Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit und Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit aufgeben und &Ouml;sterreich entm&uuml;ndigen wollen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein Verrat an &Ouml;sterreich. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim letzten Anschluss gab es auch jede Menge Seyss-Inquarts, Guislings, Petains, die in der damaligen Situation wahrscheinlich auch aus &Uuml;berzeugung und Patriotismus glaubten, das Richtige zu tun und ihre Pflicht erf&uuml;llen zu m&uuml;ssen, indem sie ihr Land einer fremden Hegemonie anvertrauten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Heute lehrt uns die Geschichte, dass ihr Tun falsch und sch&auml;dlich war, und sie sind l&auml;ngst als Verr&auml;ter und Kollaborateure gebrandmarkt, bestraft und hingerichtet worden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mitgefangen - mitgehangen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Unter der Dunstglocke der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird von allen unbemerkt der Anschluss an Deutschland vollzogen. Wenn dann diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Schiffbruch erleidet, haben wir noch ein St&uuml;ck mehr unserer Unabh&auml;ngigkeit verloren und bleiben am gro&szlig;en deutschen Bruder kleben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Bei Wahrung aller Unterschiede hat &Ouml;sterreich &Auml;hnliches bereits erlebt, als auch aus wirtschaftlichen Gr&uuml;nden 1937-1938 ein Anschluss an das &quot;Altreich&quot; propagiert wurde. &quot;Heim ins Reich&quot; hie&szlig; damals die Parole. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim Umtausch des Schilling in den Gro&szlig;macht-Euro muss man fatalerweise Analogien mit dem Umtausch des Schilling 1938 in die Reichsmark feststellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man darf nicht vergessen, dass das Versprechen einer finanziellen und wirtschaftlichen Besserstellung der k&uuml;nftigen Ostm&auml;rker Haupttriebfeder vieler &Ouml;sterreicher war, um f&uuml;r den Anschluss zu stimmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auf die bejubelte Einverleibung mit Gro&szlig;deutschland erfolgte die Ern&uuml;chterung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Jetzt ist es &auml;hnlich. Genau das, was man uns in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; vorgaukeln will, verlieren wir in der&lt;strong&gt; EU&lt;/strong&gt;: sozialen Wohlstand, Vollbesch&auml;ftigung, eine intakte Umwelt, unsere hohe Lebensqualit&auml;t, unsere Heimat, unsere Selbstachtung, unsere Natur und unsere uralten Kulturen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europ&auml;er ist man nur dann, wenn man sein unabh&auml;ngiges, eigenst&auml;ndiges Europ&auml;ertum bewahrt und hochh&auml;lt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Schweiz, wohlhabend und demokratisch, auch im Herzen Europas gelegen, soll uns ein leuchtendes Beispiel sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe auch nicht, wieso unser Bundespr&auml;sident uns zur Aufgabe unserer Souver&auml;nit&auml;t auffordert. Er m&uuml;sste doch als oberster Patriot warnen und die Verfassung sch&uuml;tzen. Ist denn Landesverrat kein Vergehen, wenn man &Ouml;sterreich einer ausl&auml;ndischen Zentralgewalt unterwerfen will? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Staatsvertrag brachte &Ouml;sterreich die Befreiung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Vertrag ist eine Kapitulation &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Entm&uuml;ndigung &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Unterwerfung unter eine neue anachronistische Hegemonie - und ein Bruch des Staatsvertrages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unglaublich: Die Politiker bereiten den zweiten Anschluss vor und wollen das &ouml;sterreichische Volk vor vollendete Tatsachen stellen. Sind unsere Politiker von allen guten Geistern verlassen, so dass erst&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; die Geschichte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; sie zurechtweisen muss? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich bin kein Jurist, aber ich bin der festen &Uuml;berzeugung, dass wir von m&auml;chtigen Interessensgruppen au&szlig;erhalb jeder ethischen, geschichtlichen, moralischen, kulturellen und &ouml;kologischen Legalit&auml;t mit einer miesen Demagogie manipuliert werden, so wie seinerzeit bei Zwentendorf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Inbetriebnahme des Atommeilers wurde durch Volksabstimmung verhindert)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten werden nivelliert und anonymisiert und ihrer Identit&auml;t beraubt. In diese Richtung geht es und nicht in die Richtung der Dezentralisation und&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Vertiefung&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Zum Beweis gen&uuml;gt die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne mit den jetzt 12 genau gleichen 5-zackigen Sternchen. Welches dieser Sternchen w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich symbolisieren, etwa das dritte rechts von unten oder das zweite, das genauso aussieht?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der F&uuml;nfstern ist kein Symbol aus der europ&auml;ischen und schon gar nicht aus der &ouml;sterreichischen Geschichte. Er kommt in der Entwicklung der Staaten des Okzidents nicht vor. Das Pentagramm, ein okkultistisches Zeichen der Druden und Freimaurer ist ein Fremdk&ouml;rper in der abendl&auml;ndischen Heraldik. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die 5-zackigen Sterne dienen eher als Merkmal der Unterwerfung, Inbesitznahme und Kolonisierung wie auf der austral-neuseel&auml;ndischen, amerikanischen und auf Kolonialfahnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne ist noch dazu ein Plagiat aus dem Sternenbanner. Auch die Vereinigten Staaten Amerikas waren als 5-zackige Sternchen, wei&szlig; auf blau, zuerst im Kreis angeordnet, genauso wie jetzt die M&ouml;chtegern-&quot;Vereinigten Staaten Europas&quot;. Sp&auml;ter, als sie sich vermehrten, wurden sie in Reih und Glied gebracht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese 5-zackigen Sternchen sind dieselben wie der Sowjetstern, der Stern der jugoslawischen, chinesischen, kubanischen und sonstigen Volksrepubliken. Wahrlich, dieses Symbol ist ein Armutszeugnis f&uuml;r die gewachsenen Identit&auml;ten Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein b&ouml;ses Omen, wenn schon das Zeichen falsch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Sternchenfahne symbolisiert die Selbstaufgabe Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist die Kultur weniger als Nebensache. Die sch&ouml;pferischen Kr&auml;fte werden zu n&uuml;tzlichen Idioten getrimmt. Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung und Verbr&auml;mung und Legitimierung eines merkantilen und industriellen Wachstums, das sich selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kultur ist in Br&uuml;ssel nicht pr&auml;sent. Sie ist in der nur merkantilen und industriellen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; kein Thema. In Br&uuml;ssel kennt man den Preis von allem und den Wert von nichts. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es geht in dieser kulturlosen, sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; nur um Zahlen: Produktionszahlen, Termine und Laufzeiten, &Uuml;bergangsfristen, Einwohner- und Viehzahlen. Bruttosozialprodukte, Anbau-, Wald- und Weidegebiete in Quadratkilometern, Lohnkosten, Sozialleistungen, Nebenkosten. Exportziffern, Tonnenzahlen f&uuml;r Schwertransporte, Milchpreise, Preisanpassungen, Finanzierungszahlen, Ausgleichszahlen, Prozente, Preissenkungen, Zucker-, Milch&shy;- und Fischquoten, Transitbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen, Kontingente, Mitfinanzierungen, Tabellen, Statistiken, Marktzugangsbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen. Laufzeiten, Ecu Umtauschkurse, hohe Arbeitslosenzahlen, niedrige Besch&auml;ftigungszahlen, F&ouml;rderungs- und Subventionszahlen, die Anzahl von &Ouml;kopunkten, Geldzahlungen aller Art, irreale Wirtschaftswachstumszahlen, Umfrageergebnisse in Zahlen und Prozenten, Stimmenanzahlen des Ministerrates und der Sperrminorit&auml;t, Mehrheiten, Minderheiten, Abstimmungsergebnisse, EU-Werbeausgaben. Ja sogar H&ouml;henzahlen f&uuml;r Bergbauern in Metern und Breitegradzahlen f&uuml;r die Landwirtschaft in Finnland. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das nicht symptomatisch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch der Umweltschutz ist in der Br&uuml;sseler Hegemonie abwesend. Nur 0,3 Prozent (30 von 10.000) der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Beamten sind f&uuml;r die &Ouml;kologie t&auml;tig. Vom Grenzen &uuml;berbr&uuml;ckenden Umweltschutz ist nur die Rede. &Ouml;sterreich muss die Kernkraft mitfinanzieren und z. B. Plastikflaschen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-Produkte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und idiotisch-gef&auml;hrliche Richtlinien f&uuml;r Apfelgr&ouml;&szlig;en und Monokultur-Obstsorten &uuml;bernehmen. Das habe ich selbst gesehen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Von Kultur und den Werten des Abendlandes ist in Br&uuml;ssel keine Rede. Um Ausgaben f&uuml;r Kultur muss man erst Br&uuml;ssel bitten. Das Kulturstudium und auch der gesamte Studienbereich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird ausgerichtet auf die N&uuml;tzlichkeit f&uuml;r die Industrie und auf das forcierte Wachstum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Kreativit&auml;t und organisches Wachstum lehren. Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Achtung lehren vor dem Artenreichtum und der unglaublichen Vielfalt, deren Teil wir selbst sind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; aber gehen die Bestrebungen in die genau umgekehrte Richtung: Vernichtung der kleinteiligen sch&ouml;pferischen Werte zugunsten einer v&ouml;llig falschen und &uuml;berholten Automatisierung, Zentralisierung und Rationalisierung, die uns &uuml;ber kurz oder lang zum Untergang bringt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das Gewissen unserer Zivilisation, unsere uralte Bestimmung, h&ouml;here Werte anzustreben, bleibt auf der Strecke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_occasion_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Written in Vienna &ndash; Paris &ndash; Kaurinui, 1988&ndash;1994. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Passages in italics: La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Geschrieben in Wien - Paris - Kaurinui, 1988 - 1994,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; erg&auml;nzt in kursiv in La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1993, p. 65-68 (Text Anschlu&szlig;psychose, 1988) (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;protokolle&lt;/em&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. edited by Otto Breicha. Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Vienna, 1997, pp. 185-193 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1998, p. 83-99 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 1151-1162 (German and English)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Langen M&uuml;ller: Munich, 2004, pp. 55-64 (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1993, S. 65-68 (Text &lt;span style=&quot;background: yellow 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial&quot;&gt;Anschlu&szlig;psychose&lt;/span&gt;, 1988)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;protokolle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. hrsg. von Otto Breicha. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Wien 1997, S. 185-193&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1998, S. 83-99&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. II: F&uuml;r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;st, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 1151-1162 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Langen M&uuml;ller: M&uuml;nchen 2004, S. 55-64&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'', text_translator-'Courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-22 13:46:19.5649###object###text###1.4.5.1###TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.5.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-124&quot;&gt; 124&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-124&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;124 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-125&quot;&gt; 125&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-125&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;125 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-126&quot;&gt; 126&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-126&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;126 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-127&quot;&gt; 127&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-127&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;127 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-128&quot;&gt; 128&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-128&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;128 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', id-130, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-130, txt-'1.4.5.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?', text_title_ge-'', text_keywords-'', text_date-'1994-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_language-en, text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In Sache &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird die &ouml;sterreichische &Ouml;ffentlichkeit von den staatlichen Medien einer dogmatischen Gehirnw&auml;sche ohnegleichen ausgesetzt. Es herrscht im Fernsehen, im Radio und fast in der gesamten Presse eine infame verschleierte Zensur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich w&uuml;rde das auch nicht in einer Demokratie f&uuml;r m&ouml;glich halten, h&auml;tte ich diese Art von Zensur nicht selbst erlebt. Unter allerlei Pr&auml;texten und Vorw&auml;nden wurde ich mehrmals behindert und verhindert,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; &ouml;ffentlich&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; eine Anti-&lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Meinung zu vertreten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Vorw&auml;nde waren: es passe nicht in die Sendung, ich d&uuml;rfe nichts vorlesen, ich w&auml;re daf&uuml;r nicht zust&auml;ndig, ich w&auml;re verr&uuml;ckt oder aber man versucht mit gezielter Diffamation mich unglaubw&uuml;rdig zu machen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dabei sind meine Bedenken und &Auml;ngste in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten selbst l&auml;ngst best&auml;tigt. Warum h&ouml;rt man nicht auf Leopold Kohr (Das Ende der Gro&szlig;en), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (Small is beautiful), Jimmy Goldsmith (Le pi&egrave;ge - et si nous avions suivi la mauvaise route?), Henry Coston (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe des banquiers), Jean Pierre Chevenement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe Seguin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (Cacciamo i mercanti dal tempio dell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europa), Gerard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht-Partei), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (Ex-EU-Kommissar: &quot;k&uuml;nstliche Superkonstruktion nicht lebensf&auml;hig&quot;), Denis de Rougemont (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe doit se faire pour la diversit&eacute;) und unz&auml;hlige andere Warner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich ist von der Geschichte auserw&auml;hlt, Beispiel und Zentrum und Halt in Mitteleuropa zu sein. &Ouml;sterreich ist eine Br&uuml;cke der Hoffnung zum Osten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wir haben seit dem Krieg in m&uuml;hevoller Arbeit ein riesiges Kapital an Wohlstand, innerem Frieden, internationalem Respekt und Glaubw&uuml;rdigkeit aufgebaut als unabh&auml;ngige, liebenswerte, friedliebende Kulturnation im Herzen Europas. Das kann nicht kurzsichtig und verantwortungslos aufs Spiel gesetzt werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt nach dem Zerfall der kommunistischen Diktatur und der &Ouml;ffnung der Grenzen muss sich &Ouml;sterreich seiner Verantwortung in Europa bewusst werden und darf sich nicht selbst eliminieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mit einer uns suggerierten Torschlusspanik wird eine Anschlussneurose erzeugt. Angst vor was oder wem? Welche Feinde hat &Ouml;sterreich? Wer sollte und warum &Ouml;sterreichs Sicherheit gef&auml;hrden? Gerade durch den Anschluss an einen Milit&auml;rblock w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich als &quot;Randgebiet Ostmark&quot; erst zum Aufmarschgebiet und zum Feindbild und Angriffsziel werden (Warnung von Erwin Lanc). Gegen atomare Bedrohung ist kein Kraut gewachsen und bei Regionalkriegen - siehe Bosnien - gibt es keinen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Schutz, nicht einmal in Nordirland, innerhalb der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;t ist gerade jetzt n&ouml;tiger als je zuvor. Man muss die Neutralit&auml;t beim Namen nennen und zu ihr stehen. Neutralit&auml;t ist ein wahrer Wert. Die immerw&auml;hrende Neutralit&auml;t ist das Fundament unseres Staates und darf nicht verraten und ausgeh&ouml;hlt werden. Wenn wir dieses Fundament unterminieren, zerst&ouml;ren wir diesen unseren Staat &Ouml;sterreich, der darauf errichtet ist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ab jetzt bedeutet die Neutralit&auml;t &Ouml;sterreichs Selbst&auml;ndigkeit, Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit, Verantwortung tragen, Beispiel geben, eine aktive Neutralit&auml;t. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch hier ist die Schweiz ein Beispiel und wird auch im Staatsvertrag als Beispiel genannt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es besteht kein Anlass, gerade jetzt einen Graben quer durch Europa zu ziehen. Es ist so als ob &ouml;stlich von Wien Feindesland w&auml;re.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Die Grenzposten werden von Deutschland an den eben beseitigten Eisernen Vorhang verlegt!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp; Diese neue Grenzziehung ist nicht nur quer durch Europa, sondern quer durch &Ouml;sterreich, wo die Donaumonarchie war. Es w&auml;re verantwortungslos und gef&auml;hrlich, durch den Anschluss an eine wirtschaftliche und politische &Uuml;bermacht das Gef&auml;lle zu und die Bedrohung f&uuml;r die L&auml;nder &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; zu vergr&ouml;&szlig;ern. &Ouml;sterreichs kulturelle, wirtschaftliche und geschichtliche Bestimmung, &Ouml;sterreichs Verantwortung und Ausstrahlung liegt im Osten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;(Das besagt auch der Name &Ouml;sterreich.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Fronten haben sich gewandelt. Es sind nicht mehr die politischen Grenzen, sondern die Front verl&auml;uft zwischen der brutalen, nur wirtschaftsinteressierten Wegwerfgesellschaft und der ausgebeuteten Natur und der zerst&ouml;rten Seele des Menschen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt einen neuen Widerstand und schon wieder feige Kollaborateure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die jetzt verantwortlichen Politiker sind Hampelm&auml;nner der Wirtschaftsinteressen und heucheln Umweltbewusstsein und Kulturbewusstsein mit Lippenbekenntnissen. Sie beschlie&szlig;en umweltzerst&ouml;rende und kulturzerst&ouml;rende Ma&szlig;nahmen, die unsere Zukunft in Frage stellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die sogenannte &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; betreibt die brutale Vernichtung unserer Lebensbasis, unserer uralten Kulturen, unserer kleinen, gewachsenen Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten, unseres Artenreichtums und unserer Selbstachtung.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Handelsvertretung des Gro&szlig;unternehmertums, der Gewerkschaften, Genossenschaften, der Gro&szlig;banken, der Giftkonzerne, der Monokultur-Monopolisten und der Atom-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;obby, die uns wie brave Schafe gemeinsam wie das Schlachtvieh in einen Zug in die falsche Richtung verladen will.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dieser riesigen Wirtschaftsmafia geht es nur um Macht und Geld und nicht um das Wohl der Natur und des Menschen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine von verantwortungslosen Schreibtischstrategen ferngesteuerte gigantische Fehlplanung zerst&ouml;rt die Fundamente unseres &uuml;ber uralte Zeiten gewachsenen Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa erlebt die gr&ouml;&szlig;te Vergewaltigung seiner Geschichte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus Br&uuml;ssel kommt keine geistige und kulturelle Erneuerung Europas. Von dort kommen keine Antworten auf die Fragen, die das Gewissen der V&ouml;lker Europas beunruhigen (Alberto Miele). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus dieser neuen Hegemonie kommen keine Botschaften, die die Identit&auml;t, unsere uralten Werte, die Inhalte unserer Zivilisation und die Sehns&uuml;chte der Menschen Europas betreffen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wo sind die Kulturen, die Religionen, die Philosophien, die ein neues europ&auml;isches Zeitalter aus der Taufe heben?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt, wo unsere Gesellschaft die Grenzen des Wachstums erreicht, ist Dezentralisierung unsere einzige &Uuml;berlebenschance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein Anschluss an diese &uuml;berm&auml;chtige Zentralgewalt, die noch immer Wirtschaftswachstum als Zentraldogma gegen alle Evidenz durchziehen will, hat f&uuml;r alle Beteiligten katastrophale Folgen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wohin diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; uns mithineinziehen will, ist ein gnadenloser Konkurrenzkampf, ein Amoklauf in eine gro&szlig;e, gef&auml;hrliche Illusion, in die Sackgasse des Wirtschaftswachstums. Es w&auml;re Wahnsinn, diesem exklusiven Klub der Wegwerfgesellschaft beizutreten, der sich selbst in den M&uuml;ll wirft und ad absurdum f&uuml;hrt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das Produkt &quot;EU&quot; so gut ist, warum muss man derart intensiv daf&uuml;r werben? Und dieser verd&auml;chtige Zeitdruck: Wir m&uuml;ssen uns sofort enteignen, sonst ist es zu sp&auml;t! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Alle guten Dinge geschehen langsam in einem organischen Ablauf von selbst. Einen Baum kann man auch nicht mit Drohungen &uuml;berzeugen und &uuml;berreden, da&szlig; er im tiefen Winter zu bl&uuml;hen hat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe nicht, warum man uns mit Gewalt &uuml;berreden will, die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;, dieses sinkende Schiff zu besteigen, und zwar sofort.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Titanic. Die Analogien zum Untergang der Titanic sind erschreckend. Hier wie dort: Konzeptlosigkeit, Gr&ouml;&szlig;enwahn, Ma&szlig;losigkeit, blinde Technologiegl&auml;ubigkeit und Geschwindigkeitswahn um jeden Preis. Dort das Rennen um das &quot;blaue Band&quot; in die t&ouml;dlichen Eisberge, hier das m&ouml;rderische Wettrennen an die Grenzen des Wachstums der Wegwerfgesellschaft, die unsere Umwelt und uns selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;So einen &quot;europ&auml;ischen Ungl&uuml;cksdampfer&quot; besteigt man nicht und vertraut man unser Leben und unsere Zukunft nicht an. Da ist es besser, man bleibt in einem kleinen, aber man&ouml;vrierbaren Boot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In praktisch der ganzen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; geht es wild zu: Nordirland, Baskenland, Korsika, Mafia, Comorra, Ausl&auml;nderverfolgungen, Rassenhass und Pogrome, Diskriminierung von Gr&ouml;nl&auml;ndern, Macedoniern und Bretonen, brutale Streiks, blutige Ausschreitungen, Studentenrevolten, Drogenkriminalit&auml;t, nukleare St&ouml;rf&auml;lle, verw&uuml;stete Landstriche, Apathie und Katastrophenstimmung, Jugendkriminalit&auml;t, bald 20 Millionen Arbeitslose und eine Staatsspaltung in Flamen und Wallonen, ausgerechnet in Br&uuml;ssel, dem Sitz der &quot;Europ&auml;ischen Union&quot;. Im Vergleich dazu haben das &quot;isolierte &Ouml;sterreich&quot; und die skandinavischen L&auml;nder, die man unbedingt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; treiben will, es &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; noch gut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; mit Menschenschicksalen jongliert als w&auml;ren es Bauern auf dem Schachbrett. Man kann doch freie Bauern nicht mit Geld abspeisen und ins Ausgedinge schicken, das ist erniedrigend, oder sie nur noch als Folklore- und Alibibauern ben&uuml;tzen, zum Herzeigen f&uuml;r den Tourismus. Das geht gegen Ehre und Selbstachtung, das ist &auml;rger als Mord.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man bezahlt die Bauern f&uuml;r ihren Selbstmord. Die EU verlangt von den Bauern, sie sollen ihre eigene uralte Kultur zerst&ouml;ren. Daf&uuml;r bekommen sie Geld. Anders als bei der Katastrophenhilfe wird die Katastrophe erst mutwillig in Gang gesetzt. Umgebrachte gewachsene Strukturen kann man auch mit sehr viel Geld nicht wiedergutmachen. Tote kann man mit Geld nicht zum Leben erwecken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Wunsch einiger m&auml;chtiger und konkurrenzf&auml;higer Gro&szlig;industrieller nach Eintritt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist, noch mehr wirtschaftliche Vorteile zu erlangen. Das geht jedoch auf Kosten der sowieso schon gef&auml;hrdeten Kleinbetriebe und Kleinbauern.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich wei&szlig; aus eigener Erfahrung, dass in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten z.B. in Frankreich nur Agrargenossenschaften &uuml;ber 100 ha eine &Uuml;berlebenschance haben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das schaut dann so aus: entweder brachliegende, ver&ouml;dete Felder, verlassene D&ouml;rfer oder Nivellierung von Terrain, Beseitigung von f&uuml;r Gro&szlig;maschinen st&ouml;rende W&auml;ldchen, B&auml;umen und Felsen, Nivellierung von uralten Geh&ouml;ften, Begradigung von B&auml;chen. Eine perfide Zerst&ouml;rung, die in ihren gigantischen Auswirkungen jeden Krieg &uuml;bersteigt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Vermehrte Verwendung von Kunstd&uuml;nger, Pestiziden, genetischen Manipulationen, Bestrahlungen und Umweltgiften aller Art, nat&uuml;rlich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; erzeugt. Eine sadistische, technokratische Zerst&ouml;rung jeglicher Romantik mit dem Schlagwort: unrentabel. Monokultur, so weit das Auge reicht. Dem Bauern wird befohlen, unsere &Uuml;berlebensgrundlage systematisch zu vergewaltigen, den ihm zu treuen H&auml;nden anvertrauten Grund und Boden, Wald und Fluren zu vergiften und zu zerst&ouml;ren. Die Landwirtschaft wird zur gigantischen Agro-Business-Industrie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Abh&auml;ngigkeit der Bauern und von uns allen von Industrie, Chemie und Monopolwirtschaft, diese neue Leibeigenschaft, wird durch einen Anschluss an die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ins Unertr&auml;gliche gesteigert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ausl&auml;ndische, m&auml;chtigere, brutalere Befehlshaber treten an die Stelle der einheimischen kleineren Firmen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ebenso ergeht es den Kleineren, d. h. allen menschlichen Betrieben, sie werden vernichtet, daf&uuml;r gibt es noch mehr Gro&szlig;kaufh&auml;user, Gro&szlig;banken und Gro&szlig;industrialisierung. Kurzum alles, was unser aller Leben romantisch, liebens- und lebenswert macht, hat kaum mehr &Uuml;berlebensm&ouml;glichkeit. Die stupiden Brutalit&auml;ten siegen, die delikaten Werte kommen um, weil sie sich nicht wehren k&ouml;nnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Agro-Business-Industrie in der EU betreibt fast analog dem &bdquo;Dritten Reich&quot; eine brutale Auslese von reinrassigen gleichgeschalteten &quot;Elite&quot;-Produkten und eine Eliminierung von &quot;minderwertigem&quot; Erbgut oder Saatgut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es beginnt mit den sch&ouml;nen gro&szlig;en &Auml;pfeln, die alle gleich sein m&uuml;ssen, die in Monokultur gez&uuml;chtet sind, in gleicher Rasse, mit gleichem Geschmack, und setzt sich fort in der genetischen &quot;Nutztierveredelung&quot; und den Legehennenbatterien. Alles nicht produktive Leben wird eliminiert. Alle nicht profitable Vielfalt, alle Andersartigkeit, alle Kleinteiligkeit, aller nutzloser Artenreichtum, alle unrentable Sch&ouml;nheit wird vernichtet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dadurch sterben auch das Kleinbauerntum, die Familienbetriebe, die Romantik, kurzum unsere Lebensqualit&auml;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Durch das Sterben der Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen),&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Bauern, der Familien- und Kleinbetriebe, durch das Sterben der kleinen Identit&auml;ten entsteht eine Gleichschaltung und eine Anonymisierung unserer Gesellschaft. Man raubt dem Menschen seine W&uuml;rde. Dies bringt eine neue Abh&auml;ngigkeit, eine neue Versklavung, eine neue Leibeigenschaft noch nie dagewesenen Ausma&szlig;es hervor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das ist das Ende des humanistischen Europas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was dann &uuml;brigbleibt ist keine menschengerechte, sondern eine maschinengerechte und computergerechte Welt. Es ist eine Zerst&ouml;rung von h&ouml;heren Werten, die in ihrer Vielfalt Europa ausmachen. Es ist die Zerst&ouml;rung Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kleinbauern m&uuml;ssen Haus und Hof und Land verkaufen, werden entweder arbeitslos oder Stadtproletariat oder m&uuml;ssen sich Agro-Business-Genossenschaften anschlie&szlig;en, wo sie nur mehr Befehlsempf&auml;nger ohne Entscheidungsfreiheit sind, auf einem Land, das einmal ihnen geh&ouml;rte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; leidet unter einem wachsenden Arbeitslosenheer, das schon jetzt der arbeitenden Bev&ouml;lkerung eines Landes 7- bis 10-mal so gro&szlig; wie &Ouml;sterreich entspricht!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man kann sich vorstellen, welches verheerende Beispiel die &lt;strong&gt;EU &lt;/strong&gt;damit der Welt gibt, wenn die 3 Milliarden Menschen, die in der Dritten Welt auf dem Lande ihr Auskommen finden, diesem &lt;strong&gt;EU B&lt;/strong&gt;eispiel zu folgen gezwungen werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine gigantische Fl&uuml;chtlingswelle von 2 Milliarden Landbev&ouml;lkerung - diesen &quot;exode rural mondial&quot;, wie Jimmy Goldsmith warnt, k&ouml;nne die Welt nicht mehr ertragen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Grenzen sind so wie unsere Haut. Sie sch&uuml;tzen den gewachsenen Organismus, unsere individuelle Andersartigkeit vor Gefahr von Au&szlig;en wie Hitze und K&auml;lte. Wenn man die Haut entfernt, stirbt der Organismus, weil er schutzlos wird.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Daher haben wir Schutzz&ouml;lle zum Schutz einer gef&auml;hrdeten Gemeinschaft. &auml;hnlich wie wir Sonnenbrillen und Zeckenimpfungen etc. zu unserem Schutz einsetzen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was Gott getrennt hat, sollen wir nicht mit Gewalt einen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt nat&uuml;rliche Grenzen wie zum Beispiel die Sahara, das Mittelmeer und die Alpen, in deren Schutz sich uralte Kulturen gebildet haben wie die afrikanischen, die mediterranen und die nordeurop&auml;ischen Kulturen. Die Alpen haben eine Schutzfunktion sowohl f&uuml;r den Norden als auch f&uuml;r den S&uuml;den.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein schrankenloser, sinnloser Transitverkehr ist gleichbedeutend mit einem Niederrei&szlig;en und Nivellieren der Alpen, auch wenn der Verkehr untertunnelt wird. &Ouml;sterreich hat genauso wie die Schweiz eine Alpine Schutzw&auml;chterfunktion f&uuml;r Europa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die fieberhafte, unnat&uuml;rliche, konzeptlose Hin- und Herraserei ist Wahnsinn und wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; zum &quot;grenzenlosen Wahnsinn&quot;. An dem Ort, wo wir sind, machen wir alles hin, dann fl&uuml;chten wir vor unserer eigenen Zerst&ouml;rung, um anderswo alles hin zu machen, und auf dem Weg dahin wird auch alles hin. Dieser falsche Trend wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; forciert und unterst&uuml;tzt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou dr&uuml;ckt das so aus: Eine Wirtschaft, die nur auf Kurzzeit-Rentabilit&auml;t ausgerichtet ist, ohne Plan, ohne Vision, ohne Sinn, die arbeitsstellen-fressende Maschinen produziert, die mehr und mehr von der Transport- und Kommunikationsgeschwindigkeit abh&auml;ngig ist und die unter Au&szlig;erachtlassung des &ouml;kologischen Gleichgewichtes die Menschen zu einer ebenso forcierten Beweglichkeit zwingt wie die Waren, die Kapitalien, die Technologien und Informationen unter Missachtung der Menschenw&uuml;rde und des Schutzes der gewohnten Lebensweisen, eine &ouml;konomische Diktatur, die &uuml;ber alle anderen menschlichen T&auml;tigkeiten triumphiert...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn man das, was man zu sch&uuml;tzen hat, vorher umbringt, braucht man keinen Schutz mehr. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen die Bauern und die Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; weg und die Kleinbetriebe und der &quot;nutzlose&quot; Artenreichtum, die &quot;unrentable&quot; Vielfalt. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir uns angleichen an internationales Mittelma&szlig;, an vergiftetes Essen, genmanipulierte und bestrahlte Lebensmittel. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir in vorauseilendem Gehorsam uns selbst nivellieren und uns vernichten, dann kann die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; widerstandslos einmarschieren und durchmarschieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich als ganzes wird ein Vasallenstaat, eine neue Ostmark. Selbstverst&auml;ndlich ist dann &Ouml;sterreichs Position als neutrale, kernkraftfreie, umweltbewusste Nation kaum mehr haltbar. &Ouml;sterreich kann dann nicht mehr selbst entscheiden, was es tut, was und wieviel es produziert und in welche L&auml;nder es exportiert und aus welchen es importiert. &Ouml;sterreichs Geschicke werden von fremden Leuten in Br&uuml;ssel oder anderswo in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; bestimmt, von Schreibtischstrategen, die sich einen Dreck um &Ouml;sterreichs Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit scheren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;tswillen, &uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Umweltbewusstsein wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Kommandozentrale nur gelacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Slogan &quot;einsam oder gemeinsam&quot; ist eine angstmachende, demagogische Aufforderung zur Verunsicherung, zur Unfreiheit und zur Abh&auml;ngigkeit. Es mag paradox klingen, aber allein ist jeder am st&auml;rksten. Aus pers&ouml;nlicher Erfahrung wei&szlig; ich, dass ein Aussenstehender genauso stark ist wie die Gruppe und nicht schw&auml;cher. Der Au&szlig;enstehende ist beweglicher, effektiver in seinem Handeln und im Reagieren als eine schwerf&auml;llige, b&uuml;rokratische, chaotische Organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa ist nur stark dank der Vielfalt seiner Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. Diese kleinteilige Vielfalt muss verst&auml;rkt und gesch&uuml;tzt werden. Diese Vielfalt ist Europa. Schon de Gaulle erkannte, dass Europa nur eine Chance als Europa der selbst&auml;ndigen, freien Vaterl&auml;nder hat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unverst&auml;ndlich, wie verantwortungslos unsere Politiker jetzt unser wertvollstes Gut, unsere Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit und Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit aufgeben und &Ouml;sterreich entm&uuml;ndigen wollen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein Verrat an &Ouml;sterreich. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim letzten Anschluss gab es auch jede Menge Seyss-Inquarts, Guislings, Petains, die in der damaligen Situation wahrscheinlich auch aus &Uuml;berzeugung und Patriotismus glaubten, das Richtige zu tun und ihre Pflicht erf&uuml;llen zu m&uuml;ssen, indem sie ihr Land einer fremden Hegemonie anvertrauten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Heute lehrt uns die Geschichte, dass ihr Tun falsch und sch&auml;dlich war, und sie sind l&auml;ngst als Verr&auml;ter und Kollaborateure gebrandmarkt, bestraft und hingerichtet worden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mitgefangen - mitgehangen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Unter der Dunstglocke der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird von allen unbemerkt der Anschluss an Deutschland vollzogen. Wenn dann diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Schiffbruch erleidet, haben wir noch ein St&uuml;ck mehr unserer Unabh&auml;ngigkeit verloren und bleiben am gro&szlig;en deutschen Bruder kleben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Bei Wahrung aller Unterschiede hat &Ouml;sterreich &Auml;hnliches bereits erlebt, als auch aus wirtschaftlichen Gr&uuml;nden 1937-1938 ein Anschluss an das &quot;Altreich&quot; propagiert wurde. &quot;Heim ins Reich&quot; hie&szlig; damals die Parole. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim Umtausch des Schilling in den Gro&szlig;macht-Euro muss man fatalerweise Analogien mit dem Umtausch des Schilling 1938 in die Reichsmark feststellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man darf nicht vergessen, dass das Versprechen einer finanziellen und wirtschaftlichen Besserstellung der k&uuml;nftigen Ostm&auml;rker Haupttriebfeder vieler &Ouml;sterreicher war, um f&uuml;r den Anschluss zu stimmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auf die bejubelte Einverleibung mit Gro&szlig;deutschland erfolgte die Ern&uuml;chterung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Jetzt ist es &auml;hnlich. Genau das, was man uns in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; vorgaukeln will, verlieren wir in der&lt;strong&gt; EU&lt;/strong&gt;: sozialen Wohlstand, Vollbesch&auml;ftigung, eine intakte Umwelt, unsere hohe Lebensqualit&auml;t, unsere Heimat, unsere Selbstachtung, unsere Natur und unsere uralten Kulturen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europ&auml;er ist man nur dann, wenn man sein unabh&auml;ngiges, eigenst&auml;ndiges Europ&auml;ertum bewahrt und hochh&auml;lt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Schweiz, wohlhabend und demokratisch, auch im Herzen Europas gelegen, soll uns ein leuchtendes Beispiel sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe auch nicht, wieso unser Bundespr&auml;sident uns zur Aufgabe unserer Souver&auml;nit&auml;t auffordert. Er m&uuml;sste doch als oberster Patriot warnen und die Verfassung sch&uuml;tzen. Ist denn Landesverrat kein Vergehen, wenn man &Ouml;sterreich einer ausl&auml;ndischen Zentralgewalt unterwerfen will? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Staatsvertrag brachte &Ouml;sterreich die Befreiung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Vertrag ist eine Kapitulation &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Entm&uuml;ndigung &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Unterwerfung unter eine neue anachronistische Hegemonie - und ein Bruch des Staatsvertrages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unglaublich: Die Politiker bereiten den zweiten Anschluss vor und wollen das &ouml;sterreichische Volk vor vollendete Tatsachen stellen. Sind unsere Politiker von allen guten Geistern verlassen, so dass erst&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; die Geschichte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; sie zurechtweisen muss? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich bin kein Jurist, aber ich bin der festen &Uuml;berzeugung, dass wir von m&auml;chtigen Interessensgruppen au&szlig;erhalb jeder ethischen, geschichtlichen, moralischen, kulturellen und &ouml;kologischen Legalit&auml;t mit einer miesen Demagogie manipuliert werden, so wie seinerzeit bei Zwentendorf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Inbetriebnahme des Atommeilers wurde durch Volksabstimmung verhindert)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten werden nivelliert und anonymisiert und ihrer Identit&auml;t beraubt. In diese Richtung geht es und nicht in die Richtung der Dezentralisation und&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Vertiefung&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Zum Beweis gen&uuml;gt die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne mit den jetzt 12 genau gleichen 5-zackigen Sternchen. Welches dieser Sternchen w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich symbolisieren, etwa das dritte rechts von unten oder das zweite, das genauso aussieht?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der F&uuml;nfstern ist kein Symbol aus der europ&auml;ischen und schon gar nicht aus der &ouml;sterreichischen Geschichte. Er kommt in der Entwicklung der Staaten des Okzidents nicht vor. Das Pentagramm, ein okkultistisches Zeichen der Druden und Freimaurer ist ein Fremdk&ouml;rper in der abendl&auml;ndischen Heraldik. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die 5-zackigen Sterne dienen eher als Merkmal der Unterwerfung, Inbesitznahme und Kolonisierung wie auf der austral-neuseel&auml;ndischen, amerikanischen und auf Kolonialfahnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne ist noch dazu ein Plagiat aus dem Sternenbanner. Auch die Vereinigten Staaten Amerikas waren als 5-zackige Sternchen, wei&szlig; auf blau, zuerst im Kreis angeordnet, genauso wie jetzt die M&ouml;chtegern-&quot;Vereinigten Staaten Europas&quot;. Sp&auml;ter, als sie sich vermehrten, wurden sie in Reih und Glied gebracht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese 5-zackigen Sternchen sind dieselben wie der Sowjetstern, der Stern der jugoslawischen, chinesischen, kubanischen und sonstigen Volksrepubliken. Wahrlich, dieses Symbol ist ein Armutszeugnis f&uuml;r die gewachsenen Identit&auml;ten Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein b&ouml;ses Omen, wenn schon das Zeichen falsch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Sternchenfahne symbolisiert die Selbstaufgabe Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist die Kultur weniger als Nebensache. Die sch&ouml;pferischen Kr&auml;fte werden zu n&uuml;tzlichen Idioten getrimmt. Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung und Verbr&auml;mung und Legitimierung eines merkantilen und industriellen Wachstums, das sich selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kultur ist in Br&uuml;ssel nicht pr&auml;sent. Sie ist in der nur merkantilen und industriellen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; kein Thema. In Br&uuml;ssel kennt man den Preis von allem und den Wert von nichts. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es geht in dieser kulturlosen, sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; nur um Zahlen: Produktionszahlen, Termine und Laufzeiten, &Uuml;bergangsfristen, Einwohner- und Viehzahlen. Bruttosozialprodukte, Anbau-, Wald- und Weidegebiete in Quadratkilometern, Lohnkosten, Sozialleistungen, Nebenkosten. Exportziffern, Tonnenzahlen f&uuml;r Schwertransporte, Milchpreise, Preisanpassungen, Finanzierungszahlen, Ausgleichszahlen, Prozente, Preissenkungen, Zucker-, Milch&shy;- und Fischquoten, Transitbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen, Kontingente, Mitfinanzierungen, Tabellen, Statistiken, Marktzugangsbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen. Laufzeiten, Ecu Umtauschkurse, hohe Arbeitslosenzahlen, niedrige Besch&auml;ftigungszahlen, F&ouml;rderungs- und Subventionszahlen, die Anzahl von &Ouml;kopunkten, Geldzahlungen aller Art, irreale Wirtschaftswachstumszahlen, Umfrageergebnisse in Zahlen und Prozenten, Stimmenanzahlen des Ministerrates und der Sperrminorit&auml;t, Mehrheiten, Minderheiten, Abstimmungsergebnisse, EU-Werbeausgaben. Ja sogar H&ouml;henzahlen f&uuml;r Bergbauern in Metern und Breitegradzahlen f&uuml;r die Landwirtschaft in Finnland. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das nicht symptomatisch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch der Umweltschutz ist in der Br&uuml;sseler Hegemonie abwesend. Nur 0,3 Prozent (30 von 10.000) der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Beamten sind f&uuml;r die &Ouml;kologie t&auml;tig. Vom Grenzen &uuml;berbr&uuml;ckenden Umweltschutz ist nur die Rede. &Ouml;sterreich muss die Kernkraft mitfinanzieren und z. B. Plastikflaschen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-Produkte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und idiotisch-gef&auml;hrliche Richtlinien f&uuml;r Apfelgr&ouml;&szlig;en und Monokultur-Obstsorten &uuml;bernehmen. Das habe ich selbst gesehen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Von Kultur und den Werten des Abendlandes ist in Br&uuml;ssel keine Rede. Um Ausgaben f&uuml;r Kultur muss man erst Br&uuml;ssel bitten. Das Kulturstudium und auch der gesamte Studienbereich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird ausgerichtet auf die N&uuml;tzlichkeit f&uuml;r die Industrie und auf das forcierte Wachstum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Kreativit&auml;t und organisches Wachstum lehren. Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Achtung lehren vor dem Artenreichtum und der unglaublichen Vielfalt, deren Teil wir selbst sind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; aber gehen die Bestrebungen in die genau umgekehrte Richtung: Vernichtung der kleinteiligen sch&ouml;pferischen Werte zugunsten einer v&ouml;llig falschen und &uuml;berholten Automatisierung, Zentralisierung und Rationalisierung, die uns &uuml;ber kurz oder lang zum Untergang bringt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das Gewissen unserer Zivilisation, unsere uralte Bestimmung, h&ouml;here Werte anzustreben, bleibt auf der Strecke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_occasion_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Written in Vienna &ndash; Paris &ndash; Kaurinui, 1988&ndash;1994. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Passages in italics: La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Geschrieben in Wien - Paris - Kaurinui, 1988 - 1994,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; erg&auml;nzt in kursiv in La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1993, p. 65-68 (Text Anschlu&szlig;psychose, 1988) (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;protokolle&lt;/em&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. edited by Otto Breicha. Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Vienna, 1997, pp. 185-193 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1998, p. 83-99 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 1151-1162 (German and English)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Langen M&uuml;ller: Munich, 2004, pp. 55-64 (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1993, S. 65-68 (Text &lt;span style=&quot;background: yellow 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial&quot;&gt;Anschlu&szlig;psychose&lt;/span&gt;, 1988)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;protokolle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. hrsg. von Otto Breicha. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Wien 1997, S. 185-193&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1998, S. 83-99&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. II: F&uuml;r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;st, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 1151-1162 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Langen M&uuml;ller: M&uuml;nchen 2004, S. 55-64&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'', text_translator-'Courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-22 13:49:5.23449###object###text###1.4.5.1###TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.5.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-124&quot;&gt; 124&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-124&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;124 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-125&quot;&gt; 125&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-125&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;125 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-126&quot;&gt; 126&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-126&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;126 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-127&quot;&gt; 127&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-127&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;127 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-128&quot;&gt; 128&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-128&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;128 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-129&quot;&gt; 129&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-129&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;129 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', id-130, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-130, txt-'1.4.5.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?', text_title_ge-'', text_keywords-'', text_date-'1994-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_language-en, text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In Sache &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird die &ouml;sterreichische &Ouml;ffentlichkeit von den staatlichen Medien einer dogmatischen Gehirnw&auml;sche ohnegleichen ausgesetzt. Es herrscht im Fernsehen, im Radio und fast in der gesamten Presse eine infame verschleierte Zensur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich w&uuml;rde das auch nicht in einer Demokratie f&uuml;r m&ouml;glich halten, h&auml;tte ich diese Art von Zensur nicht selbst erlebt. Unter allerlei Pr&auml;texten und Vorw&auml;nden wurde ich mehrmals behindert und verhindert,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; &ouml;ffentlich&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; eine Anti-&lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Meinung zu vertreten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Vorw&auml;nde waren: es passe nicht in die Sendung, ich d&uuml;rfe nichts vorlesen, ich w&auml;re daf&uuml;r nicht zust&auml;ndig, ich w&auml;re verr&uuml;ckt oder aber man versucht mit gezielter Diffamation mich unglaubw&uuml;rdig zu machen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dabei sind meine Bedenken und &Auml;ngste in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten selbst l&auml;ngst best&auml;tigt. Warum h&ouml;rt man nicht auf Leopold Kohr (Das Ende der Gro&szlig;en), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (Small is beautiful), Jimmy Goldsmith (Le pi&egrave;ge - et si nous avions suivi la mauvaise route?), Henry Coston (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe des banquiers), Jean Pierre Chevenement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe Seguin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (Cacciamo i mercanti dal tempio dell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europa), Gerard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht-Partei), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (Ex-EU-Kommissar: &quot;k&uuml;nstliche Superkonstruktion nicht lebensf&auml;hig&quot;), Denis de Rougemont (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe doit se faire pour la diversit&eacute;) und unz&auml;hlige andere Warner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich ist von der Geschichte auserw&auml;hlt, Beispiel und Zentrum und Halt in Mitteleuropa zu sein. &Ouml;sterreich ist eine Br&uuml;cke der Hoffnung zum Osten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wir haben seit dem Krieg in m&uuml;hevoller Arbeit ein riesiges Kapital an Wohlstand, innerem Frieden, internationalem Respekt und Glaubw&uuml;rdigkeit aufgebaut als unabh&auml;ngige, liebenswerte, friedliebende Kulturnation im Herzen Europas. Das kann nicht kurzsichtig und verantwortungslos aufs Spiel gesetzt werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt nach dem Zerfall der kommunistischen Diktatur und der &Ouml;ffnung der Grenzen muss sich &Ouml;sterreich seiner Verantwortung in Europa bewusst werden und darf sich nicht selbst eliminieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mit einer uns suggerierten Torschlusspanik wird eine Anschlussneurose erzeugt. Angst vor was oder wem? Welche Feinde hat &Ouml;sterreich? Wer sollte und warum &Ouml;sterreichs Sicherheit gef&auml;hrden? Gerade durch den Anschluss an einen Milit&auml;rblock w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich als &quot;Randgebiet Ostmark&quot; erst zum Aufmarschgebiet und zum Feindbild und Angriffsziel werden (Warnung von Erwin Lanc). Gegen atomare Bedrohung ist kein Kraut gewachsen und bei Regionalkriegen - siehe Bosnien - gibt es keinen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Schutz, nicht einmal in Nordirland, innerhalb der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;t ist gerade jetzt n&ouml;tiger als je zuvor. Man muss die Neutralit&auml;t beim Namen nennen und zu ihr stehen. Neutralit&auml;t ist ein wahrer Wert. Die immerw&auml;hrende Neutralit&auml;t ist das Fundament unseres Staates und darf nicht verraten und ausgeh&ouml;hlt werden. Wenn wir dieses Fundament unterminieren, zerst&ouml;ren wir diesen unseren Staat &Ouml;sterreich, der darauf errichtet ist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ab jetzt bedeutet die Neutralit&auml;t &Ouml;sterreichs Selbst&auml;ndigkeit, Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit, Verantwortung tragen, Beispiel geben, eine aktive Neutralit&auml;t. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch hier ist die Schweiz ein Beispiel und wird auch im Staatsvertrag als Beispiel genannt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es besteht kein Anlass, gerade jetzt einen Graben quer durch Europa zu ziehen. Es ist so als ob &ouml;stlich von Wien Feindesland w&auml;re.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Die Grenzposten werden von Deutschland an den eben beseitigten Eisernen Vorhang verlegt!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp; Diese neue Grenzziehung ist nicht nur quer durch Europa, sondern quer durch &Ouml;sterreich, wo die Donaumonarchie war. Es w&auml;re verantwortungslos und gef&auml;hrlich, durch den Anschluss an eine wirtschaftliche und politische &Uuml;bermacht das Gef&auml;lle zu und die Bedrohung f&uuml;r die L&auml;nder &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; zu vergr&ouml;&szlig;ern. &Ouml;sterreichs kulturelle, wirtschaftliche und geschichtliche Bestimmung, &Ouml;sterreichs Verantwortung und Ausstrahlung liegt im Osten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;(Das besagt auch der Name &Ouml;sterreich.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Fronten haben sich gewandelt. Es sind nicht mehr die politischen Grenzen, sondern die Front verl&auml;uft zwischen der brutalen, nur wirtschaftsinteressierten Wegwerfgesellschaft und der ausgebeuteten Natur und der zerst&ouml;rten Seele des Menschen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt einen neuen Widerstand und schon wieder feige Kollaborateure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die jetzt verantwortlichen Politiker sind Hampelm&auml;nner der Wirtschaftsinteressen und heucheln Umweltbewusstsein und Kulturbewusstsein mit Lippenbekenntnissen. Sie beschlie&szlig;en umweltzerst&ouml;rende und kulturzerst&ouml;rende Ma&szlig;nahmen, die unsere Zukunft in Frage stellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die sogenannte &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; betreibt die brutale Vernichtung unserer Lebensbasis, unserer uralten Kulturen, unserer kleinen, gewachsenen Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten, unseres Artenreichtums und unserer Selbstachtung.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Handelsvertretung des Gro&szlig;unternehmertums, der Gewerkschaften, Genossenschaften, der Gro&szlig;banken, der Giftkonzerne, der Monokultur-Monopolisten und der Atom-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;obby, die uns wie brave Schafe gemeinsam wie das Schlachtvieh in einen Zug in die falsche Richtung verladen will.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dieser riesigen Wirtschaftsmafia geht es nur um Macht und Geld und nicht um das Wohl der Natur und des Menschen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine von verantwortungslosen Schreibtischstrategen ferngesteuerte gigantische Fehlplanung zerst&ouml;rt die Fundamente unseres &uuml;ber uralte Zeiten gewachsenen Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa erlebt die gr&ouml;&szlig;te Vergewaltigung seiner Geschichte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus Br&uuml;ssel kommt keine geistige und kulturelle Erneuerung Europas. Von dort kommen keine Antworten auf die Fragen, die das Gewissen der V&ouml;lker Europas beunruhigen (Alberto Miele). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus dieser neuen Hegemonie kommen keine Botschaften, die die Identit&auml;t, unsere uralten Werte, die Inhalte unserer Zivilisation und die Sehns&uuml;chte der Menschen Europas betreffen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wo sind die Kulturen, die Religionen, die Philosophien, die ein neues europ&auml;isches Zeitalter aus der Taufe heben?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt, wo unsere Gesellschaft die Grenzen des Wachstums erreicht, ist Dezentralisierung unsere einzige &Uuml;berlebenschance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein Anschluss an diese &uuml;berm&auml;chtige Zentralgewalt, die noch immer Wirtschaftswachstum als Zentraldogma gegen alle Evidenz durchziehen will, hat f&uuml;r alle Beteiligten katastrophale Folgen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wohin diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; uns mithineinziehen will, ist ein gnadenloser Konkurrenzkampf, ein Amoklauf in eine gro&szlig;e, gef&auml;hrliche Illusion, in die Sackgasse des Wirtschaftswachstums. Es w&auml;re Wahnsinn, diesem exklusiven Klub der Wegwerfgesellschaft beizutreten, der sich selbst in den M&uuml;ll wirft und ad absurdum f&uuml;hrt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das Produkt &quot;EU&quot; so gut ist, warum muss man derart intensiv daf&uuml;r werben? Und dieser verd&auml;chtige Zeitdruck: Wir m&uuml;ssen uns sofort enteignen, sonst ist es zu sp&auml;t! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Alle guten Dinge geschehen langsam in einem organischen Ablauf von selbst. Einen Baum kann man auch nicht mit Drohungen &uuml;berzeugen und &uuml;berreden, da&szlig; er im tiefen Winter zu bl&uuml;hen hat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe nicht, warum man uns mit Gewalt &uuml;berreden will, die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;, dieses sinkende Schiff zu besteigen, und zwar sofort.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Titanic. Die Analogien zum Untergang der Titanic sind erschreckend. Hier wie dort: Konzeptlosigkeit, Gr&ouml;&szlig;enwahn, Ma&szlig;losigkeit, blinde Technologiegl&auml;ubigkeit und Geschwindigkeitswahn um jeden Preis. Dort das Rennen um das &quot;blaue Band&quot; in die t&ouml;dlichen Eisberge, hier das m&ouml;rderische Wettrennen an die Grenzen des Wachstums der Wegwerfgesellschaft, die unsere Umwelt und uns selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;So einen &quot;europ&auml;ischen Ungl&uuml;cksdampfer&quot; besteigt man nicht und vertraut man unser Leben und unsere Zukunft nicht an. Da ist es besser, man bleibt in einem kleinen, aber man&ouml;vrierbaren Boot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In praktisch der ganzen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; geht es wild zu: Nordirland, Baskenland, Korsika, Mafia, Comorra, Ausl&auml;nderverfolgungen, Rassenhass und Pogrome, Diskriminierung von Gr&ouml;nl&auml;ndern, Macedoniern und Bretonen, brutale Streiks, blutige Ausschreitungen, Studentenrevolten, Drogenkriminalit&auml;t, nukleare St&ouml;rf&auml;lle, verw&uuml;stete Landstriche, Apathie und Katastrophenstimmung, Jugendkriminalit&auml;t, bald 20 Millionen Arbeitslose und eine Staatsspaltung in Flamen und Wallonen, ausgerechnet in Br&uuml;ssel, dem Sitz der &quot;Europ&auml;ischen Union&quot;. Im Vergleich dazu haben das &quot;isolierte &Ouml;sterreich&quot; und die skandinavischen L&auml;nder, die man unbedingt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; treiben will, es &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; noch gut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; mit Menschenschicksalen jongliert als w&auml;ren es Bauern auf dem Schachbrett. Man kann doch freie Bauern nicht mit Geld abspeisen und ins Ausgedinge schicken, das ist erniedrigend, oder sie nur noch als Folklore- und Alibibauern ben&uuml;tzen, zum Herzeigen f&uuml;r den Tourismus. Das geht gegen Ehre und Selbstachtung, das ist &auml;rger als Mord.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man bezahlt die Bauern f&uuml;r ihren Selbstmord. Die EU verlangt von den Bauern, sie sollen ihre eigene uralte Kultur zerst&ouml;ren. Daf&uuml;r bekommen sie Geld. Anders als bei der Katastrophenhilfe wird die Katastrophe erst mutwillig in Gang gesetzt. Umgebrachte gewachsene Strukturen kann man auch mit sehr viel Geld nicht wiedergutmachen. Tote kann man mit Geld nicht zum Leben erwecken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Wunsch einiger m&auml;chtiger und konkurrenzf&auml;higer Gro&szlig;industrieller nach Eintritt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist, noch mehr wirtschaftliche Vorteile zu erlangen. Das geht jedoch auf Kosten der sowieso schon gef&auml;hrdeten Kleinbetriebe und Kleinbauern.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich wei&szlig; aus eigener Erfahrung, dass in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten z.B. in Frankreich nur Agrargenossenschaften &uuml;ber 100 ha eine &Uuml;berlebenschance haben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das schaut dann so aus: entweder brachliegende, ver&ouml;dete Felder, verlassene D&ouml;rfer oder Nivellierung von Terrain, Beseitigung von f&uuml;r Gro&szlig;maschinen st&ouml;rende W&auml;ldchen, B&auml;umen und Felsen, Nivellierung von uralten Geh&ouml;ften, Begradigung von B&auml;chen. Eine perfide Zerst&ouml;rung, die in ihren gigantischen Auswirkungen jeden Krieg &uuml;bersteigt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Vermehrte Verwendung von Kunstd&uuml;nger, Pestiziden, genetischen Manipulationen, Bestrahlungen und Umweltgiften aller Art, nat&uuml;rlich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; erzeugt. Eine sadistische, technokratische Zerst&ouml;rung jeglicher Romantik mit dem Schlagwort: unrentabel. Monokultur, so weit das Auge reicht. Dem Bauern wird befohlen, unsere &Uuml;berlebensgrundlage systematisch zu vergewaltigen, den ihm zu treuen H&auml;nden anvertrauten Grund und Boden, Wald und Fluren zu vergiften und zu zerst&ouml;ren. Die Landwirtschaft wird zur gigantischen Agro-Business-Industrie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Abh&auml;ngigkeit der Bauern und von uns allen von Industrie, Chemie und Monopolwirtschaft, diese neue Leibeigenschaft, wird durch einen Anschluss an die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ins Unertr&auml;gliche gesteigert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ausl&auml;ndische, m&auml;chtigere, brutalere Befehlshaber treten an die Stelle der einheimischen kleineren Firmen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ebenso ergeht es den Kleineren, d. h. allen menschlichen Betrieben, sie werden vernichtet, daf&uuml;r gibt es noch mehr Gro&szlig;kaufh&auml;user, Gro&szlig;banken und Gro&szlig;industrialisierung. Kurzum alles, was unser aller Leben romantisch, liebens- und lebenswert macht, hat kaum mehr &Uuml;berlebensm&ouml;glichkeit. Die stupiden Brutalit&auml;ten siegen, die delikaten Werte kommen um, weil sie sich nicht wehren k&ouml;nnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Agro-Business-Industrie in der EU betreibt fast analog dem &bdquo;Dritten Reich&quot; eine brutale Auslese von reinrassigen gleichgeschalteten &quot;Elite&quot;-Produkten und eine Eliminierung von &quot;minderwertigem&quot; Erbgut oder Saatgut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es beginnt mit den sch&ouml;nen gro&szlig;en &Auml;pfeln, die alle gleich sein m&uuml;ssen, die in Monokultur gez&uuml;chtet sind, in gleicher Rasse, mit gleichem Geschmack, und setzt sich fort in der genetischen &quot;Nutztierveredelung&quot; und den Legehennenbatterien. Alles nicht produktive Leben wird eliminiert. Alle nicht profitable Vielfalt, alle Andersartigkeit, alle Kleinteiligkeit, aller nutzloser Artenreichtum, alle unrentable Sch&ouml;nheit wird vernichtet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dadurch sterben auch das Kleinbauerntum, die Familienbetriebe, die Romantik, kurzum unsere Lebensqualit&auml;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Durch das Sterben der Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen),&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Bauern, der Familien- und Kleinbetriebe, durch das Sterben der kleinen Identit&auml;ten entsteht eine Gleichschaltung und eine Anonymisierung unserer Gesellschaft. Man raubt dem Menschen seine W&uuml;rde. Dies bringt eine neue Abh&auml;ngigkeit, eine neue Versklavung, eine neue Leibeigenschaft noch nie dagewesenen Ausma&szlig;es hervor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das ist das Ende des humanistischen Europas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was dann &uuml;brigbleibt ist keine menschengerechte, sondern eine maschinengerechte und computergerechte Welt. Es ist eine Zerst&ouml;rung von h&ouml;heren Werten, die in ihrer Vielfalt Europa ausmachen. Es ist die Zerst&ouml;rung Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kleinbauern m&uuml;ssen Haus und Hof und Land verkaufen, werden entweder arbeitslos oder Stadtproletariat oder m&uuml;ssen sich Agro-Business-Genossenschaften anschlie&szlig;en, wo sie nur mehr Befehlsempf&auml;nger ohne Entscheidungsfreiheit sind, auf einem Land, das einmal ihnen geh&ouml;rte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; leidet unter einem wachsenden Arbeitslosenheer, das schon jetzt der arbeitenden Bev&ouml;lkerung eines Landes 7- bis 10-mal so gro&szlig; wie &Ouml;sterreich entspricht!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man kann sich vorstellen, welches verheerende Beispiel die &lt;strong&gt;EU &lt;/strong&gt;damit der Welt gibt, wenn die 3 Milliarden Menschen, die in der Dritten Welt auf dem Lande ihr Auskommen finden, diesem &lt;strong&gt;EU B&lt;/strong&gt;eispiel zu folgen gezwungen werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine gigantische Fl&uuml;chtlingswelle von 2 Milliarden Landbev&ouml;lkerung - diesen &quot;exode rural mondial&quot;, wie Jimmy Goldsmith warnt, k&ouml;nne die Welt nicht mehr ertragen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Grenzen sind so wie unsere Haut. Sie sch&uuml;tzen den gewachsenen Organismus, unsere individuelle Andersartigkeit vor Gefahr von Au&szlig;en wie Hitze und K&auml;lte. Wenn man die Haut entfernt, stirbt der Organismus, weil er schutzlos wird.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Daher haben wir Schutzz&ouml;lle zum Schutz einer gef&auml;hrdeten Gemeinschaft. &auml;hnlich wie wir Sonnenbrillen und Zeckenimpfungen etc. zu unserem Schutz einsetzen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was Gott getrennt hat, sollen wir nicht mit Gewalt einen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt nat&uuml;rliche Grenzen wie zum Beispiel die Sahara, das Mittelmeer und die Alpen, in deren Schutz sich uralte Kulturen gebildet haben wie die afrikanischen, die mediterranen und die nordeurop&auml;ischen Kulturen. Die Alpen haben eine Schutzfunktion sowohl f&uuml;r den Norden als auch f&uuml;r den S&uuml;den.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein schrankenloser, sinnloser Transitverkehr ist gleichbedeutend mit einem Niederrei&szlig;en und Nivellieren der Alpen, auch wenn der Verkehr untertunnelt wird. &Ouml;sterreich hat genauso wie die Schweiz eine Alpine Schutzw&auml;chterfunktion f&uuml;r Europa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die fieberhafte, unnat&uuml;rliche, konzeptlose Hin- und Herraserei ist Wahnsinn und wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; zum &quot;grenzenlosen Wahnsinn&quot;. An dem Ort, wo wir sind, machen wir alles hin, dann fl&uuml;chten wir vor unserer eigenen Zerst&ouml;rung, um anderswo alles hin zu machen, und auf dem Weg dahin wird auch alles hin. Dieser falsche Trend wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; forciert und unterst&uuml;tzt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou dr&uuml;ckt das so aus: Eine Wirtschaft, die nur auf Kurzzeit-Rentabilit&auml;t ausgerichtet ist, ohne Plan, ohne Vision, ohne Sinn, die arbeitsstellen-fressende Maschinen produziert, die mehr und mehr von der Transport- und Kommunikationsgeschwindigkeit abh&auml;ngig ist und die unter Au&szlig;erachtlassung des &ouml;kologischen Gleichgewichtes die Menschen zu einer ebenso forcierten Beweglichkeit zwingt wie die Waren, die Kapitalien, die Technologien und Informationen unter Missachtung der Menschenw&uuml;rde und des Schutzes der gewohnten Lebensweisen, eine &ouml;konomische Diktatur, die &uuml;ber alle anderen menschlichen T&auml;tigkeiten triumphiert...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn man das, was man zu sch&uuml;tzen hat, vorher umbringt, braucht man keinen Schutz mehr. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen die Bauern und die Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; weg und die Kleinbetriebe und der &quot;nutzlose&quot; Artenreichtum, die &quot;unrentable&quot; Vielfalt. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir uns angleichen an internationales Mittelma&szlig;, an vergiftetes Essen, genmanipulierte und bestrahlte Lebensmittel. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir in vorauseilendem Gehorsam uns selbst nivellieren und uns vernichten, dann kann die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; widerstandslos einmarschieren und durchmarschieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich als ganzes wird ein Vasallenstaat, eine neue Ostmark. Selbstverst&auml;ndlich ist dann &Ouml;sterreichs Position als neutrale, kernkraftfreie, umweltbewusste Nation kaum mehr haltbar. &Ouml;sterreich kann dann nicht mehr selbst entscheiden, was es tut, was und wieviel es produziert und in welche L&auml;nder es exportiert und aus welchen es importiert. &Ouml;sterreichs Geschicke werden von fremden Leuten in Br&uuml;ssel oder anderswo in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; bestimmt, von Schreibtischstrategen, die sich einen Dreck um &Ouml;sterreichs Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit scheren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;tswillen, &uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Umweltbewusstsein wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Kommandozentrale nur gelacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Slogan &quot;einsam oder gemeinsam&quot; ist eine angstmachende, demagogische Aufforderung zur Verunsicherung, zur Unfreiheit und zur Abh&auml;ngigkeit. Es mag paradox klingen, aber allein ist jeder am st&auml;rksten. Aus pers&ouml;nlicher Erfahrung wei&szlig; ich, dass ein Aussenstehender genauso stark ist wie die Gruppe und nicht schw&auml;cher. Der Au&szlig;enstehende ist beweglicher, effektiver in seinem Handeln und im Reagieren als eine schwerf&auml;llige, b&uuml;rokratische, chaotische Organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa ist nur stark dank der Vielfalt seiner Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. Diese kleinteilige Vielfalt muss verst&auml;rkt und gesch&uuml;tzt werden. Diese Vielfalt ist Europa. Schon de Gaulle erkannte, dass Europa nur eine Chance als Europa der selbst&auml;ndigen, freien Vaterl&auml;nder hat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unverst&auml;ndlich, wie verantwortungslos unsere Politiker jetzt unser wertvollstes Gut, unsere Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit und Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit aufgeben und &Ouml;sterreich entm&uuml;ndigen wollen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein Verrat an &Ouml;sterreich. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim letzten Anschluss gab es auch jede Menge Seyss-Inquarts, Guislings, Petains, die in der damaligen Situation wahrscheinlich auch aus &Uuml;berzeugung und Patriotismus glaubten, das Richtige zu tun und ihre Pflicht erf&uuml;llen zu m&uuml;ssen, indem sie ihr Land einer fremden Hegemonie anvertrauten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Heute lehrt uns die Geschichte, dass ihr Tun falsch und sch&auml;dlich war, und sie sind l&auml;ngst als Verr&auml;ter und Kollaborateure gebrandmarkt, bestraft und hingerichtet worden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mitgefangen - mitgehangen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Unter der Dunstglocke der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird von allen unbemerkt der Anschluss an Deutschland vollzogen. Wenn dann diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Schiffbruch erleidet, haben wir noch ein St&uuml;ck mehr unserer Unabh&auml;ngigkeit verloren und bleiben am gro&szlig;en deutschen Bruder kleben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Bei Wahrung aller Unterschiede hat &Ouml;sterreich &Auml;hnliches bereits erlebt, als auch aus wirtschaftlichen Gr&uuml;nden 1937-1938 ein Anschluss an das &quot;Altreich&quot; propagiert wurde. &quot;Heim ins Reich&quot; hie&szlig; damals die Parole. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim Umtausch des Schilling in den Gro&szlig;macht-Euro muss man fatalerweise Analogien mit dem Umtausch des Schilling 1938 in die Reichsmark feststellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man darf nicht vergessen, dass das Versprechen einer finanziellen und wirtschaftlichen Besserstellung der k&uuml;nftigen Ostm&auml;rker Haupttriebfeder vieler &Ouml;sterreicher war, um f&uuml;r den Anschluss zu stimmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auf die bejubelte Einverleibung mit Gro&szlig;deutschland erfolgte die Ern&uuml;chterung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Jetzt ist es &auml;hnlich. Genau das, was man uns in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; vorgaukeln will, verlieren wir in der&lt;strong&gt; EU&lt;/strong&gt;: sozialen Wohlstand, Vollbesch&auml;ftigung, eine intakte Umwelt, unsere hohe Lebensqualit&auml;t, unsere Heimat, unsere Selbstachtung, unsere Natur und unsere uralten Kulturen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europ&auml;er ist man nur dann, wenn man sein unabh&auml;ngiges, eigenst&auml;ndiges Europ&auml;ertum bewahrt und hochh&auml;lt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Schweiz, wohlhabend und demokratisch, auch im Herzen Europas gelegen, soll uns ein leuchtendes Beispiel sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe auch nicht, wieso unser Bundespr&auml;sident uns zur Aufgabe unserer Souver&auml;nit&auml;t auffordert. Er m&uuml;sste doch als oberster Patriot warnen und die Verfassung sch&uuml;tzen. Ist denn Landesverrat kein Vergehen, wenn man &Ouml;sterreich einer ausl&auml;ndischen Zentralgewalt unterwerfen will? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Staatsvertrag brachte &Ouml;sterreich die Befreiung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Vertrag ist eine Kapitulation &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Entm&uuml;ndigung &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Unterwerfung unter eine neue anachronistische Hegemonie - und ein Bruch des Staatsvertrages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unglaublich: Die Politiker bereiten den zweiten Anschluss vor und wollen das &ouml;sterreichische Volk vor vollendete Tatsachen stellen. Sind unsere Politiker von allen guten Geistern verlassen, so dass erst&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; die Geschichte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; sie zurechtweisen muss? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich bin kein Jurist, aber ich bin der festen &Uuml;berzeugung, dass wir von m&auml;chtigen Interessensgruppen au&szlig;erhalb jeder ethischen, geschichtlichen, moralischen, kulturellen und &ouml;kologischen Legalit&auml;t mit einer miesen Demagogie manipuliert werden, so wie seinerzeit bei Zwentendorf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Inbetriebnahme des Atommeilers wurde durch Volksabstimmung verhindert)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten werden nivelliert und anonymisiert und ihrer Identit&auml;t beraubt. In diese Richtung geht es und nicht in die Richtung der Dezentralisation und&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Vertiefung&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Zum Beweis gen&uuml;gt die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne mit den jetzt 12 genau gleichen 5-zackigen Sternchen. Welches dieser Sternchen w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich symbolisieren, etwa das dritte rechts von unten oder das zweite, das genauso aussieht?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der F&uuml;nfstern ist kein Symbol aus der europ&auml;ischen und schon gar nicht aus der &ouml;sterreichischen Geschichte. Er kommt in der Entwicklung der Staaten des Okzidents nicht vor. Das Pentagramm, ein okkultistisches Zeichen der Druden und Freimaurer ist ein Fremdk&ouml;rper in der abendl&auml;ndischen Heraldik. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die 5-zackigen Sterne dienen eher als Merkmal der Unterwerfung, Inbesitznahme und Kolonisierung wie auf der austral-neuseel&auml;ndischen, amerikanischen und auf Kolonialfahnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne ist noch dazu ein Plagiat aus dem Sternenbanner. Auch die Vereinigten Staaten Amerikas waren als 5-zackige Sternchen, wei&szlig; auf blau, zuerst im Kreis angeordnet, genauso wie jetzt die M&ouml;chtegern-&quot;Vereinigten Staaten Europas&quot;. Sp&auml;ter, als sie sich vermehrten, wurden sie in Reih und Glied gebracht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese 5-zackigen Sternchen sind dieselben wie der Sowjetstern, der Stern der jugoslawischen, chinesischen, kubanischen und sonstigen Volksrepubliken. Wahrlich, dieses Symbol ist ein Armutszeugnis f&uuml;r die gewachsenen Identit&auml;ten Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein b&ouml;ses Omen, wenn schon das Zeichen falsch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Sternchenfahne symbolisiert die Selbstaufgabe Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist die Kultur weniger als Nebensache. Die sch&ouml;pferischen Kr&auml;fte werden zu n&uuml;tzlichen Idioten getrimmt. Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung und Verbr&auml;mung und Legitimierung eines merkantilen und industriellen Wachstums, das sich selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kultur ist in Br&uuml;ssel nicht pr&auml;sent. Sie ist in der nur merkantilen und industriellen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; kein Thema. In Br&uuml;ssel kennt man den Preis von allem und den Wert von nichts. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es geht in dieser kulturlosen, sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; nur um Zahlen: Produktionszahlen, Termine und Laufzeiten, &Uuml;bergangsfristen, Einwohner- und Viehzahlen. Bruttosozialprodukte, Anbau-, Wald- und Weidegebiete in Quadratkilometern, Lohnkosten, Sozialleistungen, Nebenkosten. Exportziffern, Tonnenzahlen f&uuml;r Schwertransporte, Milchpreise, Preisanpassungen, Finanzierungszahlen, Ausgleichszahlen, Prozente, Preissenkungen, Zucker-, Milch&shy;- und Fischquoten, Transitbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen, Kontingente, Mitfinanzierungen, Tabellen, Statistiken, Marktzugangsbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen. Laufzeiten, Ecu Umtauschkurse, hohe Arbeitslosenzahlen, niedrige Besch&auml;ftigungszahlen, F&ouml;rderungs- und Subventionszahlen, die Anzahl von &Ouml;kopunkten, Geldzahlungen aller Art, irreale Wirtschaftswachstumszahlen, Umfrageergebnisse in Zahlen und Prozenten, Stimmenanzahlen des Ministerrates und der Sperrminorit&auml;t, Mehrheiten, Minderheiten, Abstimmungsergebnisse, EU-Werbeausgaben. Ja sogar H&ouml;henzahlen f&uuml;r Bergbauern in Metern und Breitegradzahlen f&uuml;r die Landwirtschaft in Finnland. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das nicht symptomatisch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch der Umweltschutz ist in der Br&uuml;sseler Hegemonie abwesend. Nur 0,3 Prozent (30 von 10.000) der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Beamten sind f&uuml;r die &Ouml;kologie t&auml;tig. Vom Grenzen &uuml;berbr&uuml;ckenden Umweltschutz ist nur die Rede. &Ouml;sterreich muss die Kernkraft mitfinanzieren und z. B. Plastikflaschen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-Produkte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und idiotisch-gef&auml;hrliche Richtlinien f&uuml;r Apfelgr&ouml;&szlig;en und Monokultur-Obstsorten &uuml;bernehmen. Das habe ich selbst gesehen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Von Kultur und den Werten des Abendlandes ist in Br&uuml;ssel keine Rede. Um Ausgaben f&uuml;r Kultur muss man erst Br&uuml;ssel bitten. Das Kulturstudium und auch der gesamte Studienbereich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird ausgerichtet auf die N&uuml;tzlichkeit f&uuml;r die Industrie und auf das forcierte Wachstum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Kreativit&auml;t und organisches Wachstum lehren. Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Achtung lehren vor dem Artenreichtum und der unglaublichen Vielfalt, deren Teil wir selbst sind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; aber gehen die Bestrebungen in die genau umgekehrte Richtung: Vernichtung der kleinteiligen sch&ouml;pferischen Werte zugunsten einer v&ouml;llig falschen und &uuml;berholten Automatisierung, Zentralisierung und Rationalisierung, die uns &uuml;ber kurz oder lang zum Untergang bringt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das Gewissen unserer Zivilisation, unsere uralte Bestimmung, h&ouml;here Werte anzustreben, bleibt auf der Strecke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_occasion_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Written in Vienna &ndash; Paris &ndash; Kaurinui, 1988&ndash;1994. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Passages in italics: La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Geschrieben in Wien - Paris - Kaurinui, 1988 - 1994,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; erg&auml;nzt in kursiv in La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1993, p. 65-68 (Text Anschlu&szlig;psychose, 1988) (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;protokolle&lt;/em&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. edited by Otto Breicha. Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Vienna, 1997, pp. 185-193 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1998, p. 83-99 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 1151-1162 (German and English)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Langen M&uuml;ller: Munich, 2004, pp. 55-64 (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1993, S. 65-68 (Text &lt;span style=&quot;background: yellow 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial&quot;&gt;Anschlu&szlig;psychose&lt;/span&gt;, 1988)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;protokolle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. hrsg. von Otto Breicha. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Wien 1997, S. 185-193&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1998, S. 83-99&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. II: F&uuml;r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;st, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 1151-1162 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Langen M&uuml;ller: M&uuml;nchen 2004, S. 55-64&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'', text_translator-'Courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-22 13:49:45.0624###object###text###1.4.5.1###TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.5.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-124&quot;&gt; 124&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-124&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;124 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-125&quot;&gt; 125&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-125&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;125 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-126&quot;&gt; 126&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-126&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;126 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-127&quot;&gt; 127&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-127&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;127 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-128&quot;&gt; 128&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-128&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;128 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-129&quot;&gt; 129&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-129&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;129 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-130&quot;&gt; 130&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-130&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;130 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', id-130, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-130, txt-'1.4.5.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?', text_title_ge-'', text_keywords-'', text_date-'1994-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_language-en, text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In Sache &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird die &ouml;sterreichische &Ouml;ffentlichkeit von den staatlichen Medien einer dogmatischen Gehirnw&auml;sche ohnegleichen ausgesetzt. Es herrscht im Fernsehen, im Radio und fast in der gesamten Presse eine infame verschleierte Zensur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich w&uuml;rde das auch nicht in einer Demokratie f&uuml;r m&ouml;glich halten, h&auml;tte ich diese Art von Zensur nicht selbst erlebt. Unter allerlei Pr&auml;texten und Vorw&auml;nden wurde ich mehrmals behindert und verhindert,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; &ouml;ffentlich&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; eine Anti-&lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Meinung zu vertreten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Vorw&auml;nde waren: es passe nicht in die Sendung, ich d&uuml;rfe nichts vorlesen, ich w&auml;re daf&uuml;r nicht zust&auml;ndig, ich w&auml;re verr&uuml;ckt oder aber man versucht mit gezielter Diffamation mich unglaubw&uuml;rdig zu machen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dabei sind meine Bedenken und &Auml;ngste in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten selbst l&auml;ngst best&auml;tigt. Warum h&ouml;rt man nicht auf Leopold Kohr (Das Ende der Gro&szlig;en), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (Small is beautiful), Jimmy Goldsmith (Le pi&egrave;ge - et si nous avions suivi la mauvaise route?), Henry Coston (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe des banquiers), Jean Pierre Chevenement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe Seguin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (Cacciamo i mercanti dal tempio dell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europa), Gerard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht-Partei), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (Ex-EU-Kommissar: &quot;k&uuml;nstliche Superkonstruktion nicht lebensf&auml;hig&quot;), Denis de Rougemont (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe doit se faire pour la diversit&eacute;) und unz&auml;hlige andere Warner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich ist von der Geschichte auserw&auml;hlt, Beispiel und Zentrum und Halt in Mitteleuropa zu sein. &Ouml;sterreich ist eine Br&uuml;cke der Hoffnung zum Osten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wir haben seit dem Krieg in m&uuml;hevoller Arbeit ein riesiges Kapital an Wohlstand, innerem Frieden, internationalem Respekt und Glaubw&uuml;rdigkeit aufgebaut als unabh&auml;ngige, liebenswerte, friedliebende Kulturnation im Herzen Europas. Das kann nicht kurzsichtig und verantwortungslos aufs Spiel gesetzt werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt nach dem Zerfall der kommunistischen Diktatur und der &Ouml;ffnung der Grenzen muss sich &Ouml;sterreich seiner Verantwortung in Europa bewusst werden und darf sich nicht selbst eliminieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mit einer uns suggerierten Torschlusspanik wird eine Anschlussneurose erzeugt. Angst vor was oder wem? Welche Feinde hat &Ouml;sterreich? Wer sollte und warum &Ouml;sterreichs Sicherheit gef&auml;hrden? Gerade durch den Anschluss an einen Milit&auml;rblock w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich als &quot;Randgebiet Ostmark&quot; erst zum Aufmarschgebiet und zum Feindbild und Angriffsziel werden (Warnung von Erwin Lanc). Gegen atomare Bedrohung ist kein Kraut gewachsen und bei Regionalkriegen - siehe Bosnien - gibt es keinen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Schutz, nicht einmal in Nordirland, innerhalb der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;t ist gerade jetzt n&ouml;tiger als je zuvor. Man muss die Neutralit&auml;t beim Namen nennen und zu ihr stehen. Neutralit&auml;t ist ein wahrer Wert. Die immerw&auml;hrende Neutralit&auml;t ist das Fundament unseres Staates und darf nicht verraten und ausgeh&ouml;hlt werden. Wenn wir dieses Fundament unterminieren, zerst&ouml;ren wir diesen unseren Staat &Ouml;sterreich, der darauf errichtet ist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ab jetzt bedeutet die Neutralit&auml;t &Ouml;sterreichs Selbst&auml;ndigkeit, Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit, Verantwortung tragen, Beispiel geben, eine aktive Neutralit&auml;t. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch hier ist die Schweiz ein Beispiel und wird auch im Staatsvertrag als Beispiel genannt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es besteht kein Anlass, gerade jetzt einen Graben quer durch Europa zu ziehen. Es ist so als ob &ouml;stlich von Wien Feindesland w&auml;re.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Die Grenzposten werden von Deutschland an den eben beseitigten Eisernen Vorhang verlegt!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp; Diese neue Grenzziehung ist nicht nur quer durch Europa, sondern quer durch &Ouml;sterreich, wo die Donaumonarchie war. Es w&auml;re verantwortungslos und gef&auml;hrlich, durch den Anschluss an eine wirtschaftliche und politische &Uuml;bermacht das Gef&auml;lle zu und die Bedrohung f&uuml;r die L&auml;nder &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; zu vergr&ouml;&szlig;ern. &Ouml;sterreichs kulturelle, wirtschaftliche und geschichtliche Bestimmung, &Ouml;sterreichs Verantwortung und Ausstrahlung liegt im Osten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;(Das besagt auch der Name &Ouml;sterreich.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Fronten haben sich gewandelt. Es sind nicht mehr die politischen Grenzen, sondern die Front verl&auml;uft zwischen der brutalen, nur wirtschaftsinteressierten Wegwerfgesellschaft und der ausgebeuteten Natur und der zerst&ouml;rten Seele des Menschen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt einen neuen Widerstand und schon wieder feige Kollaborateure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die jetzt verantwortlichen Politiker sind Hampelm&auml;nner der Wirtschaftsinteressen und heucheln Umweltbewusstsein und Kulturbewusstsein mit Lippenbekenntnissen. Sie beschlie&szlig;en umweltzerst&ouml;rende und kulturzerst&ouml;rende Ma&szlig;nahmen, die unsere Zukunft in Frage stellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die sogenannte &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; betreibt die brutale Vernichtung unserer Lebensbasis, unserer uralten Kulturen, unserer kleinen, gewachsenen Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten, unseres Artenreichtums und unserer Selbstachtung.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Handelsvertretung des Gro&szlig;unternehmertums, der Gewerkschaften, Genossenschaften, der Gro&szlig;banken, der Giftkonzerne, der Monokultur-Monopolisten und der Atom-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;obby, die uns wie brave Schafe gemeinsam wie das Schlachtvieh in einen Zug in die falsche Richtung verladen will.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dieser riesigen Wirtschaftsmafia geht es nur um Macht und Geld und nicht um das Wohl der Natur und des Menschen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine von verantwortungslosen Schreibtischstrategen ferngesteuerte gigantische Fehlplanung zerst&ouml;rt die Fundamente unseres &uuml;ber uralte Zeiten gewachsenen Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa erlebt die gr&ouml;&szlig;te Vergewaltigung seiner Geschichte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus Br&uuml;ssel kommt keine geistige und kulturelle Erneuerung Europas. Von dort kommen keine Antworten auf die Fragen, die das Gewissen der V&ouml;lker Europas beunruhigen (Alberto Miele). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus dieser neuen Hegemonie kommen keine Botschaften, die die Identit&auml;t, unsere uralten Werte, die Inhalte unserer Zivilisation und die Sehns&uuml;chte der Menschen Europas betreffen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wo sind die Kulturen, die Religionen, die Philosophien, die ein neues europ&auml;isches Zeitalter aus der Taufe heben?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt, wo unsere Gesellschaft die Grenzen des Wachstums erreicht, ist Dezentralisierung unsere einzige &Uuml;berlebenschance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein Anschluss an diese &uuml;berm&auml;chtige Zentralgewalt, die noch immer Wirtschaftswachstum als Zentraldogma gegen alle Evidenz durchziehen will, hat f&uuml;r alle Beteiligten katastrophale Folgen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wohin diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; uns mithineinziehen will, ist ein gnadenloser Konkurrenzkampf, ein Amoklauf in eine gro&szlig;e, gef&auml;hrliche Illusion, in die Sackgasse des Wirtschaftswachstums. Es w&auml;re Wahnsinn, diesem exklusiven Klub der Wegwerfgesellschaft beizutreten, der sich selbst in den M&uuml;ll wirft und ad absurdum f&uuml;hrt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das Produkt &quot;EU&quot; so gut ist, warum muss man derart intensiv daf&uuml;r werben? Und dieser verd&auml;chtige Zeitdruck: Wir m&uuml;ssen uns sofort enteignen, sonst ist es zu sp&auml;t! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Alle guten Dinge geschehen langsam in einem organischen Ablauf von selbst. Einen Baum kann man auch nicht mit Drohungen &uuml;berzeugen und &uuml;berreden, da&szlig; er im tiefen Winter zu bl&uuml;hen hat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe nicht, warum man uns mit Gewalt &uuml;berreden will, die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;, dieses sinkende Schiff zu besteigen, und zwar sofort.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Titanic. Die Analogien zum Untergang der Titanic sind erschreckend. Hier wie dort: Konzeptlosigkeit, Gr&ouml;&szlig;enwahn, Ma&szlig;losigkeit, blinde Technologiegl&auml;ubigkeit und Geschwindigkeitswahn um jeden Preis. Dort das Rennen um das &quot;blaue Band&quot; in die t&ouml;dlichen Eisberge, hier das m&ouml;rderische Wettrennen an die Grenzen des Wachstums der Wegwerfgesellschaft, die unsere Umwelt und uns selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;So einen &quot;europ&auml;ischen Ungl&uuml;cksdampfer&quot; besteigt man nicht und vertraut man unser Leben und unsere Zukunft nicht an. Da ist es besser, man bleibt in einem kleinen, aber man&ouml;vrierbaren Boot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In praktisch der ganzen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; geht es wild zu: Nordirland, Baskenland, Korsika, Mafia, Comorra, Ausl&auml;nderverfolgungen, Rassenhass und Pogrome, Diskriminierung von Gr&ouml;nl&auml;ndern, Macedoniern und Bretonen, brutale Streiks, blutige Ausschreitungen, Studentenrevolten, Drogenkriminalit&auml;t, nukleare St&ouml;rf&auml;lle, verw&uuml;stete Landstriche, Apathie und Katastrophenstimmung, Jugendkriminalit&auml;t, bald 20 Millionen Arbeitslose und eine Staatsspaltung in Flamen und Wallonen, ausgerechnet in Br&uuml;ssel, dem Sitz der &quot;Europ&auml;ischen Union&quot;. Im Vergleich dazu haben das &quot;isolierte &Ouml;sterreich&quot; und die skandinavischen L&auml;nder, die man unbedingt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; treiben will, es &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; noch gut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; mit Menschenschicksalen jongliert als w&auml;ren es Bauern auf dem Schachbrett. Man kann doch freie Bauern nicht mit Geld abspeisen und ins Ausgedinge schicken, das ist erniedrigend, oder sie nur noch als Folklore- und Alibibauern ben&uuml;tzen, zum Herzeigen f&uuml;r den Tourismus. Das geht gegen Ehre und Selbstachtung, das ist &auml;rger als Mord.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man bezahlt die Bauern f&uuml;r ihren Selbstmord. Die EU verlangt von den Bauern, sie sollen ihre eigene uralte Kultur zerst&ouml;ren. Daf&uuml;r bekommen sie Geld. Anders als bei der Katastrophenhilfe wird die Katastrophe erst mutwillig in Gang gesetzt. Umgebrachte gewachsene Strukturen kann man auch mit sehr viel Geld nicht wiedergutmachen. Tote kann man mit Geld nicht zum Leben erwecken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Wunsch einiger m&auml;chtiger und konkurrenzf&auml;higer Gro&szlig;industrieller nach Eintritt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist, noch mehr wirtschaftliche Vorteile zu erlangen. Das geht jedoch auf Kosten der sowieso schon gef&auml;hrdeten Kleinbetriebe und Kleinbauern.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich wei&szlig; aus eigener Erfahrung, dass in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten z.B. in Frankreich nur Agrargenossenschaften &uuml;ber 100 ha eine &Uuml;berlebenschance haben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das schaut dann so aus: entweder brachliegende, ver&ouml;dete Felder, verlassene D&ouml;rfer oder Nivellierung von Terrain, Beseitigung von f&uuml;r Gro&szlig;maschinen st&ouml;rende W&auml;ldchen, B&auml;umen und Felsen, Nivellierung von uralten Geh&ouml;ften, Begradigung von B&auml;chen. Eine perfide Zerst&ouml;rung, die in ihren gigantischen Auswirkungen jeden Krieg &uuml;bersteigt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Vermehrte Verwendung von Kunstd&uuml;nger, Pestiziden, genetischen Manipulationen, Bestrahlungen und Umweltgiften aller Art, nat&uuml;rlich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; erzeugt. Eine sadistische, technokratische Zerst&ouml;rung jeglicher Romantik mit dem Schlagwort: unrentabel. Monokultur, so weit das Auge reicht. Dem Bauern wird befohlen, unsere &Uuml;berlebensgrundlage systematisch zu vergewaltigen, den ihm zu treuen H&auml;nden anvertrauten Grund und Boden, Wald und Fluren zu vergiften und zu zerst&ouml;ren. Die Landwirtschaft wird zur gigantischen Agro-Business-Industrie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Abh&auml;ngigkeit der Bauern und von uns allen von Industrie, Chemie und Monopolwirtschaft, diese neue Leibeigenschaft, wird durch einen Anschluss an die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ins Unertr&auml;gliche gesteigert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ausl&auml;ndische, m&auml;chtigere, brutalere Befehlshaber treten an die Stelle der einheimischen kleineren Firmen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ebenso ergeht es den Kleineren, d. h. allen menschlichen Betrieben, sie werden vernichtet, daf&uuml;r gibt es noch mehr Gro&szlig;kaufh&auml;user, Gro&szlig;banken und Gro&szlig;industrialisierung. Kurzum alles, was unser aller Leben romantisch, liebens- und lebenswert macht, hat kaum mehr &Uuml;berlebensm&ouml;glichkeit. Die stupiden Brutalit&auml;ten siegen, die delikaten Werte kommen um, weil sie sich nicht wehren k&ouml;nnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Agro-Business-Industrie in der EU betreibt fast analog dem &bdquo;Dritten Reich&quot; eine brutale Auslese von reinrassigen gleichgeschalteten &quot;Elite&quot;-Produkten und eine Eliminierung von &quot;minderwertigem&quot; Erbgut oder Saatgut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es beginnt mit den sch&ouml;nen gro&szlig;en &Auml;pfeln, die alle gleich sein m&uuml;ssen, die in Monokultur gez&uuml;chtet sind, in gleicher Rasse, mit gleichem Geschmack, und setzt sich fort in der genetischen &quot;Nutztierveredelung&quot; und den Legehennenbatterien. Alles nicht produktive Leben wird eliminiert. Alle nicht profitable Vielfalt, alle Andersartigkeit, alle Kleinteiligkeit, aller nutzloser Artenreichtum, alle unrentable Sch&ouml;nheit wird vernichtet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dadurch sterben auch das Kleinbauerntum, die Familienbetriebe, die Romantik, kurzum unsere Lebensqualit&auml;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Durch das Sterben der Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen),&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Bauern, der Familien- und Kleinbetriebe, durch das Sterben der kleinen Identit&auml;ten entsteht eine Gleichschaltung und eine Anonymisierung unserer Gesellschaft. Man raubt dem Menschen seine W&uuml;rde. Dies bringt eine neue Abh&auml;ngigkeit, eine neue Versklavung, eine neue Leibeigenschaft noch nie dagewesenen Ausma&szlig;es hervor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das ist das Ende des humanistischen Europas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was dann &uuml;brigbleibt ist keine menschengerechte, sondern eine maschinengerechte und computergerechte Welt. Es ist eine Zerst&ouml;rung von h&ouml;heren Werten, die in ihrer Vielfalt Europa ausmachen. Es ist die Zerst&ouml;rung Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kleinbauern m&uuml;ssen Haus und Hof und Land verkaufen, werden entweder arbeitslos oder Stadtproletariat oder m&uuml;ssen sich Agro-Business-Genossenschaften anschlie&szlig;en, wo sie nur mehr Befehlsempf&auml;nger ohne Entscheidungsfreiheit sind, auf einem Land, das einmal ihnen geh&ouml;rte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; leidet unter einem wachsenden Arbeitslosenheer, das schon jetzt der arbeitenden Bev&ouml;lkerung eines Landes 7- bis 10-mal so gro&szlig; wie &Ouml;sterreich entspricht!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man kann sich vorstellen, welches verheerende Beispiel die &lt;strong&gt;EU &lt;/strong&gt;damit der Welt gibt, wenn die 3 Milliarden Menschen, die in der Dritten Welt auf dem Lande ihr Auskommen finden, diesem &lt;strong&gt;EU B&lt;/strong&gt;eispiel zu folgen gezwungen werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine gigantische Fl&uuml;chtlingswelle von 2 Milliarden Landbev&ouml;lkerung - diesen &quot;exode rural mondial&quot;, wie Jimmy Goldsmith warnt, k&ouml;nne die Welt nicht mehr ertragen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Grenzen sind so wie unsere Haut. Sie sch&uuml;tzen den gewachsenen Organismus, unsere individuelle Andersartigkeit vor Gefahr von Au&szlig;en wie Hitze und K&auml;lte. Wenn man die Haut entfernt, stirbt der Organismus, weil er schutzlos wird.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Daher haben wir Schutzz&ouml;lle zum Schutz einer gef&auml;hrdeten Gemeinschaft. &auml;hnlich wie wir Sonnenbrillen und Zeckenimpfungen etc. zu unserem Schutz einsetzen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was Gott getrennt hat, sollen wir nicht mit Gewalt einen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt nat&uuml;rliche Grenzen wie zum Beispiel die Sahara, das Mittelmeer und die Alpen, in deren Schutz sich uralte Kulturen gebildet haben wie die afrikanischen, die mediterranen und die nordeurop&auml;ischen Kulturen. Die Alpen haben eine Schutzfunktion sowohl f&uuml;r den Norden als auch f&uuml;r den S&uuml;den.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein schrankenloser, sinnloser Transitverkehr ist gleichbedeutend mit einem Niederrei&szlig;en und Nivellieren der Alpen, auch wenn der Verkehr untertunnelt wird. &Ouml;sterreich hat genauso wie die Schweiz eine Alpine Schutzw&auml;chterfunktion f&uuml;r Europa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die fieberhafte, unnat&uuml;rliche, konzeptlose Hin- und Herraserei ist Wahnsinn und wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; zum &quot;grenzenlosen Wahnsinn&quot;. An dem Ort, wo wir sind, machen wir alles hin, dann fl&uuml;chten wir vor unserer eigenen Zerst&ouml;rung, um anderswo alles hin zu machen, und auf dem Weg dahin wird auch alles hin. Dieser falsche Trend wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; forciert und unterst&uuml;tzt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou dr&uuml;ckt das so aus: Eine Wirtschaft, die nur auf Kurzzeit-Rentabilit&auml;t ausgerichtet ist, ohne Plan, ohne Vision, ohne Sinn, die arbeitsstellen-fressende Maschinen produziert, die mehr und mehr von der Transport- und Kommunikationsgeschwindigkeit abh&auml;ngig ist und die unter Au&szlig;erachtlassung des &ouml;kologischen Gleichgewichtes die Menschen zu einer ebenso forcierten Beweglichkeit zwingt wie die Waren, die Kapitalien, die Technologien und Informationen unter Missachtung der Menschenw&uuml;rde und des Schutzes der gewohnten Lebensweisen, eine &ouml;konomische Diktatur, die &uuml;ber alle anderen menschlichen T&auml;tigkeiten triumphiert...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn man das, was man zu sch&uuml;tzen hat, vorher umbringt, braucht man keinen Schutz mehr. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen die Bauern und die Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; weg und die Kleinbetriebe und der &quot;nutzlose&quot; Artenreichtum, die &quot;unrentable&quot; Vielfalt. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir uns angleichen an internationales Mittelma&szlig;, an vergiftetes Essen, genmanipulierte und bestrahlte Lebensmittel. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir in vorauseilendem Gehorsam uns selbst nivellieren und uns vernichten, dann kann die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; widerstandslos einmarschieren und durchmarschieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich als ganzes wird ein Vasallenstaat, eine neue Ostmark. Selbstverst&auml;ndlich ist dann &Ouml;sterreichs Position als neutrale, kernkraftfreie, umweltbewusste Nation kaum mehr haltbar. &Ouml;sterreich kann dann nicht mehr selbst entscheiden, was es tut, was und wieviel es produziert und in welche L&auml;nder es exportiert und aus welchen es importiert. &Ouml;sterreichs Geschicke werden von fremden Leuten in Br&uuml;ssel oder anderswo in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; bestimmt, von Schreibtischstrategen, die sich einen Dreck um &Ouml;sterreichs Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit scheren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;tswillen, &uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Umweltbewusstsein wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Kommandozentrale nur gelacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Slogan &quot;einsam oder gemeinsam&quot; ist eine angstmachende, demagogische Aufforderung zur Verunsicherung, zur Unfreiheit und zur Abh&auml;ngigkeit. Es mag paradox klingen, aber allein ist jeder am st&auml;rksten. Aus pers&ouml;nlicher Erfahrung wei&szlig; ich, dass ein Aussenstehender genauso stark ist wie die Gruppe und nicht schw&auml;cher. Der Au&szlig;enstehende ist beweglicher, effektiver in seinem Handeln und im Reagieren als eine schwerf&auml;llige, b&uuml;rokratische, chaotische Organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa ist nur stark dank der Vielfalt seiner Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. Diese kleinteilige Vielfalt muss verst&auml;rkt und gesch&uuml;tzt werden. Diese Vielfalt ist Europa. Schon de Gaulle erkannte, dass Europa nur eine Chance als Europa der selbst&auml;ndigen, freien Vaterl&auml;nder hat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unverst&auml;ndlich, wie verantwortungslos unsere Politiker jetzt unser wertvollstes Gut, unsere Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit und Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit aufgeben und &Ouml;sterreich entm&uuml;ndigen wollen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein Verrat an &Ouml;sterreich. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim letzten Anschluss gab es auch jede Menge Seyss-Inquarts, Guislings, Petains, die in der damaligen Situation wahrscheinlich auch aus &Uuml;berzeugung und Patriotismus glaubten, das Richtige zu tun und ihre Pflicht erf&uuml;llen zu m&uuml;ssen, indem sie ihr Land einer fremden Hegemonie anvertrauten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Heute lehrt uns die Geschichte, dass ihr Tun falsch und sch&auml;dlich war, und sie sind l&auml;ngst als Verr&auml;ter und Kollaborateure gebrandmarkt, bestraft und hingerichtet worden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mitgefangen - mitgehangen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Unter der Dunstglocke der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird von allen unbemerkt der Anschluss an Deutschland vollzogen. Wenn dann diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Schiffbruch erleidet, haben wir noch ein St&uuml;ck mehr unserer Unabh&auml;ngigkeit verloren und bleiben am gro&szlig;en deutschen Bruder kleben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Bei Wahrung aller Unterschiede hat &Ouml;sterreich &Auml;hnliches bereits erlebt, als auch aus wirtschaftlichen Gr&uuml;nden 1937-1938 ein Anschluss an das &quot;Altreich&quot; propagiert wurde. &quot;Heim ins Reich&quot; hie&szlig; damals die Parole. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim Umtausch des Schilling in den Gro&szlig;macht-Euro muss man fatalerweise Analogien mit dem Umtausch des Schilling 1938 in die Reichsmark feststellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man darf nicht vergessen, dass das Versprechen einer finanziellen und wirtschaftlichen Besserstellung der k&uuml;nftigen Ostm&auml;rker Haupttriebfeder vieler &Ouml;sterreicher war, um f&uuml;r den Anschluss zu stimmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auf die bejubelte Einverleibung mit Gro&szlig;deutschland erfolgte die Ern&uuml;chterung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Jetzt ist es &auml;hnlich. Genau das, was man uns in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; vorgaukeln will, verlieren wir in der&lt;strong&gt; EU&lt;/strong&gt;: sozialen Wohlstand, Vollbesch&auml;ftigung, eine intakte Umwelt, unsere hohe Lebensqualit&auml;t, unsere Heimat, unsere Selbstachtung, unsere Natur und unsere uralten Kulturen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europ&auml;er ist man nur dann, wenn man sein unabh&auml;ngiges, eigenst&auml;ndiges Europ&auml;ertum bewahrt und hochh&auml;lt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Schweiz, wohlhabend und demokratisch, auch im Herzen Europas gelegen, soll uns ein leuchtendes Beispiel sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe auch nicht, wieso unser Bundespr&auml;sident uns zur Aufgabe unserer Souver&auml;nit&auml;t auffordert. Er m&uuml;sste doch als oberster Patriot warnen und die Verfassung sch&uuml;tzen. Ist denn Landesverrat kein Vergehen, wenn man &Ouml;sterreich einer ausl&auml;ndischen Zentralgewalt unterwerfen will? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Staatsvertrag brachte &Ouml;sterreich die Befreiung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Vertrag ist eine Kapitulation &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Entm&uuml;ndigung &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Unterwerfung unter eine neue anachronistische Hegemonie - und ein Bruch des Staatsvertrages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unglaublich: Die Politiker bereiten den zweiten Anschluss vor und wollen das &ouml;sterreichische Volk vor vollendete Tatsachen stellen. Sind unsere Politiker von allen guten Geistern verlassen, so dass erst&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; die Geschichte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; sie zurechtweisen muss? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich bin kein Jurist, aber ich bin der festen &Uuml;berzeugung, dass wir von m&auml;chtigen Interessensgruppen au&szlig;erhalb jeder ethischen, geschichtlichen, moralischen, kulturellen und &ouml;kologischen Legalit&auml;t mit einer miesen Demagogie manipuliert werden, so wie seinerzeit bei Zwentendorf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Inbetriebnahme des Atommeilers wurde durch Volksabstimmung verhindert)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten werden nivelliert und anonymisiert und ihrer Identit&auml;t beraubt. In diese Richtung geht es und nicht in die Richtung der Dezentralisation und&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Vertiefung&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Zum Beweis gen&uuml;gt die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne mit den jetzt 12 genau gleichen 5-zackigen Sternchen. Welches dieser Sternchen w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich symbolisieren, etwa das dritte rechts von unten oder das zweite, das genauso aussieht?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der F&uuml;nfstern ist kein Symbol aus der europ&auml;ischen und schon gar nicht aus der &ouml;sterreichischen Geschichte. Er kommt in der Entwicklung der Staaten des Okzidents nicht vor. Das Pentagramm, ein okkultistisches Zeichen der Druden und Freimaurer ist ein Fremdk&ouml;rper in der abendl&auml;ndischen Heraldik. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die 5-zackigen Sterne dienen eher als Merkmal der Unterwerfung, Inbesitznahme und Kolonisierung wie auf der austral-neuseel&auml;ndischen, amerikanischen und auf Kolonialfahnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne ist noch dazu ein Plagiat aus dem Sternenbanner. Auch die Vereinigten Staaten Amerikas waren als 5-zackige Sternchen, wei&szlig; auf blau, zuerst im Kreis angeordnet, genauso wie jetzt die M&ouml;chtegern-&quot;Vereinigten Staaten Europas&quot;. Sp&auml;ter, als sie sich vermehrten, wurden sie in Reih und Glied gebracht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese 5-zackigen Sternchen sind dieselben wie der Sowjetstern, der Stern der jugoslawischen, chinesischen, kubanischen und sonstigen Volksrepubliken. Wahrlich, dieses Symbol ist ein Armutszeugnis f&uuml;r die gewachsenen Identit&auml;ten Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein b&ouml;ses Omen, wenn schon das Zeichen falsch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Sternchenfahne symbolisiert die Selbstaufgabe Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist die Kultur weniger als Nebensache. Die sch&ouml;pferischen Kr&auml;fte werden zu n&uuml;tzlichen Idioten getrimmt. Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung und Verbr&auml;mung und Legitimierung eines merkantilen und industriellen Wachstums, das sich selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kultur ist in Br&uuml;ssel nicht pr&auml;sent. Sie ist in der nur merkantilen und industriellen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; kein Thema. In Br&uuml;ssel kennt man den Preis von allem und den Wert von nichts. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es geht in dieser kulturlosen, sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; nur um Zahlen: Produktionszahlen, Termine und Laufzeiten, &Uuml;bergangsfristen, Einwohner- und Viehzahlen. Bruttosozialprodukte, Anbau-, Wald- und Weidegebiete in Quadratkilometern, Lohnkosten, Sozialleistungen, Nebenkosten. Exportziffern, Tonnenzahlen f&uuml;r Schwertransporte, Milchpreise, Preisanpassungen, Finanzierungszahlen, Ausgleichszahlen, Prozente, Preissenkungen, Zucker-, Milch&shy;- und Fischquoten, Transitbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen, Kontingente, Mitfinanzierungen, Tabellen, Statistiken, Marktzugangsbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen. Laufzeiten, Ecu Umtauschkurse, hohe Arbeitslosenzahlen, niedrige Besch&auml;ftigungszahlen, F&ouml;rderungs- und Subventionszahlen, die Anzahl von &Ouml;kopunkten, Geldzahlungen aller Art, irreale Wirtschaftswachstumszahlen, Umfrageergebnisse in Zahlen und Prozenten, Stimmenanzahlen des Ministerrates und der Sperrminorit&auml;t, Mehrheiten, Minderheiten, Abstimmungsergebnisse, EU-Werbeausgaben. Ja sogar H&ouml;henzahlen f&uuml;r Bergbauern in Metern und Breitegradzahlen f&uuml;r die Landwirtschaft in Finnland. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das nicht symptomatisch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch der Umweltschutz ist in der Br&uuml;sseler Hegemonie abwesend. Nur 0,3 Prozent (30 von 10.000) der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Beamten sind f&uuml;r die &Ouml;kologie t&auml;tig. Vom Grenzen &uuml;berbr&uuml;ckenden Umweltschutz ist nur die Rede. &Ouml;sterreich muss die Kernkraft mitfinanzieren und z. B. Plastikflaschen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-Produkte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und idiotisch-gef&auml;hrliche Richtlinien f&uuml;r Apfelgr&ouml;&szlig;en und Monokultur-Obstsorten &uuml;bernehmen. Das habe ich selbst gesehen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Von Kultur und den Werten des Abendlandes ist in Br&uuml;ssel keine Rede. Um Ausgaben f&uuml;r Kultur muss man erst Br&uuml;ssel bitten. Das Kulturstudium und auch der gesamte Studienbereich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird ausgerichtet auf die N&uuml;tzlichkeit f&uuml;r die Industrie und auf das forcierte Wachstum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Kreativit&auml;t und organisches Wachstum lehren. Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Achtung lehren vor dem Artenreichtum und der unglaublichen Vielfalt, deren Teil wir selbst sind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; aber gehen die Bestrebungen in die genau umgekehrte Richtung: Vernichtung der kleinteiligen sch&ouml;pferischen Werte zugunsten einer v&ouml;llig falschen und &uuml;berholten Automatisierung, Zentralisierung und Rationalisierung, die uns &uuml;ber kurz oder lang zum Untergang bringt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das Gewissen unserer Zivilisation, unsere uralte Bestimmung, h&ouml;here Werte anzustreben, bleibt auf der Strecke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_occasion_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Written in Vienna &ndash; Paris &ndash; Kaurinui, 1988&ndash;1994. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Passages in italics: La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Geschrieben in Wien - Paris - Kaurinui, 1988 - 1994,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; erg&auml;nzt in kursiv in La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1993, p. 65-68 (Text Anschlu&szlig;psychose, 1988) (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;protokolle&lt;/em&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. edited by Otto Breicha. Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Vienna, 1997, pp. 185-193 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1998, p. 83-99 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 1151-1162 (German and English)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Langen M&uuml;ller: Munich, 2004, pp. 55-64 (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1993, S. 65-68 (Text &lt;span style=&quot;background: yellow 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial&quot;&gt;Anschlu&szlig;psychose&lt;/span&gt;, 1988)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;protokolle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. hrsg. von Otto Breicha. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Wien 1997, S. 185-193&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1998, S. 83-99&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. II: F&uuml;r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;st, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 1151-1162 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Langen M&uuml;ller: M&uuml;nchen 2004, S. 55-64&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'', text_translator-'Courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-22 13:51:51.6642###object###text###1.4.5.1###TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.5.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-124&quot;&gt; 124&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-124&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;124 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-125&quot;&gt; 125&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-125&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;125 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-126&quot;&gt; 126&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-126&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;126 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-127&quot;&gt; 127&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-127&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;127 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-128&quot;&gt; 128&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-128&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;128 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-129&quot;&gt; 129&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-129&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;129 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-130&quot;&gt; 130&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-130&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;130 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-131&quot;&gt; 131&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-131&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;131 &lt;/span&gt; De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', id-130, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-130, txt-'1.4.5.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'TO JOIN THE E.U. IS TO BETRAY AUSTRIA AND BETRAY EUROPE. WHY?', text_title_ge-'', text_keywords-'', text_date-'1994-00-00', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_language-en, text_contents-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. question the Austrian public is being subjected to a dogmatic brain washing by the state-controlled media the likes &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;of which has never been seen. Television, radio and almost the entire press are in the grip of a disgraceful veiled censorship.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I would also not think it possible in a democracy, if I hadn&rsquo;t experienced this kind of censorship myself. More than once all manner of pretexts and excuses were made to obstruct and prevent me from stating an anti-E.U. opinion publicly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The excuses were: it has no relevance to the broadcast; I may not deliver a prepared text; it was not my responsibility; I was crazy; or they resorted to deliberate diffamation to destroy my credibility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;And at that, my misgivings and fears have long since been corroborated in the E.U. states themselves. Why don&rsquo;t people listen to Leopold Kohr (&ldquo;The Breakdown of Nations&rdquo;), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (&ldquo;Small is Beautiful&rdquo;), Jimmy Goldsmith (&ldquo;The Trap &ndash; and What If We Have Taken a Bad Road?&rdquo;), Henry Coston (&ldquo;The Europe of the Bankers&rdquo;), Jean-Pierre Chev&egrave;nement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe S&eacute;guin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Drive the Merchants Out of the Temple of Europe&rdquo;), G&eacute;rard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht Party), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (ex-E.U. commissioner: &ldquo;Artificial super-construction not viable&rdquo;), Denis de Rougemont (&ldquo;Europe must strive for diversity&rdquo;) and untold other warning voices?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria has been chosen by history to be an example and centre and mainstay in Central Europe. Austria is a bridge of hope towards the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Since the war we have built up with laborious toil a huge capital of prosperity, domestic peace, international respect and credibility as an independent, attractive, peace-loving, cultivated nation in the heart of Europe. That cannot be shortsightedly and irresponsibly put at risk.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;At this very moment, after the collapse of the communist dictatorship and the opening of boundaries, Austria must be mindful of its responsibility in Europe and may not eliminate itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;With a suggested last-minute panic, an &ldquo;Anschluss&rdquo; neurosis is being generated. Fear of what or whom? What enemies does Austria have? Who would jeopardise Austria&rsquo;s security, and why? Precisely by joining a military block, Austria would, as a &ldquo;fringe region East Mark&rdquo;, first be an area for marshalling forces and then become an enemy and target of attack (warning by Erwin Lanc). There is no cure for the threat of nuclear attack, and in regional wars &ndash; see Bosnia &ndash; there is no E.U. protection, not even in Northern Ireland, inside the E.U. itself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s neutrality is at this precise moment more necessary than ever before. One must call neutrality by its real name and stand up for it. Neutrality is a true value. Permanent neutrality is the foundation of our state and must not be betrayed and eroded. If we undermine this foundation, we will destroy this our state, Austria, which has been erected upon it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As of now Austria&rsquo;s neutrality means autonomy, independence, freedom, assuming responsibility, setting an example &ndash; an active neutrality.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Here, too, Switzerland is an example and is also cited as an example in the [Austrian] State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is no reason for cutting a divide right across Europe at this of all moments. It is as if to the east of Vienna were enemy territory. &lt;em&gt;Border patrols are being deployed by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Germany&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; right where the Iron Curtain has just been removed!&lt;/em&gt; This new line of demarcation runs not only right through Europe, but right through Austria, where the Danube monarchy was. It would be irresponsible and dangerous to increase the difference with and the threat to the countries &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo; by an Anschluss with an economically and politically superior power. Austria&rsquo;s cultural, economic and historic destiny, Austria&rsquo;s responsibility and its appeal lie to the East.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is also what the name Austria &ndash; &Ouml;sterreich in German &ndash; really means: realm to the east.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The fronts have undergone a change. It is no longer the political boundaries, the front is now drawn between the brutal throw-away society, which is only interested in business, and exploited nature and the destroyed soul of man.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There is a new resistance, and already there are once again cowardly collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The politicians who now bear the responsibility are puppets of business interests and pay hypocritical lip service to environmental awareness and cultural consciousness. They adopt measures which destroy the environment and culture and make our future doubtful.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The so-called E.U. is contriving to destroy our life base, our ageold cultures, our small, evolved idiosyncrasies, our species diversity and our self-esteem.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic sales outlet of big business, the labour unions, the trade associations, the major banks, the poison corporations, the monoculture monopolists and the nuclear and genetic lobbies, which are about to load us like meek sheep onto a train going in the wrong direction, together with the cattle for slaughter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This huge business mafia is interested solely in power and money and not in the well-being of nature and man. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Remote-controlled, gigantic misguided planning by irresponsible strategists sitting at their desks is destroying the foundations of our Europe, which have taken ages to grow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is undergoing the grossest rape in its history.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From Brussels no spiritual and cultural renewal of Europe will come. From there come no answers to the questions occupying the conscience of the peoples of Europe (Alberto Miele).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;From this new hegemony no messages come regarding the identity, our age-old values, the substance of our civilisation and the longings of the people of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Where are the cultures, the religions, the philosophies to launch a new European epoch?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Precisely now, when our society is reaching the limits of growth, decentralisation is our only chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;An Anschluss with this overpowering central authority, which, despite all evidence to the contrary, still intends to push economic growth through as its central dogma, will have catastrophic consequences for all concerned.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What this E.U. is trying to draw us into is a merciless competitive struggle, to make us run amok in a great, dangerous illusion, in the cul-de-sac of economic growth. It would be madness to join this exclusive club of throw-away society which is throwing itself into the dustbin and reducing itself to absurdity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If the E.U. is such a good product, why do they have to promote it so intensively? And this suspicious pressure: we must dispossess ourselves immediately or it will be too late! All good things happen slowly, in an organic process, of themselves. A tree cannot be convinced and persuaded even by threats to blossom in the middle of winter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I do not understand why they want at all costs to persuade us to board the E.U., this sinking ship, right away.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. is a gigantic Titanic. The analogies to the sinking of the Titanic are horrifying. In both cases lack of planning, megalomania, immoderation, blind faith in technology and the mania of speed at all costs. If the former raced for the Blue Ribbon through the deadly icebergs, the latter is in a murderous race to the limits of growth of the throw-away society which is destroying our environment and us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One should not board such a &ldquo;doomed steamer Europe&rdquo; and entrust it with our life and future. Better to stay in a small but maneuverable boat.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Just about everywhere in the E.U. things are out of control: Northern Ireland, the Basque region, Corsica, the Mafia, Camorra, persecution of foreigners, racial hatred and pogroms, discrimination against Greenlanders, Macedonians and the Bretons, brutal strikes, bloody excesses, student revolts, drug crime, nuclear-plant mishaps, devastated tracts of land, apathy and a feeling of looming disaster, juvenile crime, soon 20 million out of work and a split-up of the country into Flemish and Walloons, in Brussels, of all places, the seat of the European Union. Compared to this, &ldquo;isolated Austria&rdquo; and the Scandinavian countries, whom they want to herd into the E.U. at all costs, are pretty well off &ldquo;on the outside&rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U. human fates are juggled like pawns [called &ldquo;farmers&rdquo; in German] on a chessboard. But you can&rsquo;t fob off free farmers with money and send them off to their allotted property, that is humiliating, or use them as folklore and alibi farmers, to be trotted out for the tourists; that goes against honour and self-respect; that is worse than murder.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;They are paying the farmers for their suicide. The E.U. is demanding that the farmers destroy their age-old culture. For this they will receive money. In contrast to disaster relief, the disaster is first made to happen on purpose. Evolved structures cannot be compensated for even with a great deal of money once they have been done away with. You can&rsquo;t raise the dead with money.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A few powerful and competitive industrial magnates favour membership in the E.U. in order to gain even more economic advantage. But that will happen at the cost of small business and small farmers, which are jeopardised as it is.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I know from my own experience that in the E.U. countries, in France, for example, only agrarian co-operatives with over 100 hectares have a chance of survival.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This is then how it will look: either barren fields lying fallow, deserted villages or the levelling of terrain, the removal of copses, trees and rocks which get in the way of large machines, the razing of ancient farmsteads, the regulation of brooks. Perfidious destruction, with gigantic repercussions in excess of any war.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The increased use of artificial fertilizer, pesticides, genetic manipulation, radiation and environmental toxins of all kinds, of course manufactured in the E.U. A sadistic, technocratic destruction of any kind of romanticism with the catchword &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo;. Monoculture as far as the eye can see. The farmer is advised to systematically violate the basis of our survival, to poison and destroy the soil, forests and meadows entrusted to his care. Agriculture will then become a gigantic agribusiness industry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dependence of farmers and of all of us on industry, chemistry and monopolistic businesses, this new serfdom, will be increased to an intolerable level by joining the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Foreign, more powerful, more brutal commanders take the place of the smaller domestic companies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This will also be the fate of the smaller, i. e., all human business operations: they will be destroyed; instead, there will be more large department stores, large banks and large-scale industrialisation. In short, everything which makes our life romantic, attractive and worth living will scarcely have a way of surviving. Stupid brutality will be victorious; the delicate values will perish because they can&rsquo;t defend themselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Agribusiness in the E.U. practises, in a close analogy to the Third Reich, a brutal selection process of pure-blooded, conformist &ldquo;elite&rdquo; products and the elimination of &ldquo;inferior&rdquo; genotypes or seeds.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This begins with the nice big apples which all have to be alike, which are bred in monocultures, of the same &ldquo;race&rdquo;, with the same taste, and is continued with genetic &ldquo;improvement of economic animals&rdquo; and the batteries of laying hens. Any unproductive life is eliminated. All unprofitable diversity, everything which is different, everything small-scale, all useless species diversity, all unprofitable beauty, are destroyed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This makes the small farm die, too, the family farms, romanticism: in short, our quality of life.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The dying-out of the mom-and-pop stores, the farmers, family farms and small businesses, the death of small entities brings about a conformism and anonymisation of our society. Man is robbed of his dignity. This creates a new dependence, a new enslavement, a new serfdom on an unheard-of scale.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is the end of humanistic Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What then remains is a world not fitting to man, but a machine-compatible, computer-compatible one. It is a destruction of higher values which in their diversity are what make Europe what it is. It is the destruction of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The small farmers must sell their houses, their barnyards, their land; they are then either unemployed or join the urban proletariat or must join agribusiness co-operatives, where they merely take orders, with no freedom to decide for themselves, on land which once belonged to them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. is plagued by a growing army of unemployed, which even now amounts to the working population of a country 7 to 10 times as big as Austria!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One can imagine what a devastating example the E.U. is setting for the world if the three thousand million people who are eking out an existence on the land in the Third World are forced to follow this E.U. example.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;A gigantic deluge of refugees, two thousand million people from rural areas &ndash; this &ldquo;global rural exodus&rdquo;, as Jimmy Goldsmith warns &ndash; would be more than the world can cope with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Boundaries are like our skin. They protect the grown organism, our individual differentness, from danger from the outside, such as heat and cold. If the skin is removed, the organism dies because it has no protection. &lt;em&gt;That is why we have protective tariffs to protect an endangered polity. Like the way we use sunglasses and vaccinations against Lyme&rsquo;s disease etc., for our protection.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;What God has separated we should not unite by force.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;There are natural boundaries, e.g., the Sahara, the Mediterranean and the Alps, under whose protection age-old cultures have evolved, such as the African, the Mediterranean and the Northern European cultures. The Alps have a protective function for the North as well as the South.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Unencumbered, senseless transit traffic is tantamount to tearing down and levelling off the Alps, even if the traffic is routed through tunnels. Austria has a function as an Alpine protective sentry for Europe, just like Switzerland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This feverish, unnatural, mindless racing back and forth is madness and becomes in the E.U. &ldquo;madness unlimited&rdquo;. Wherever we happen to be, we ruin everything; then we flee from our own destruction, only to ruin everything somewhere else, and on the way there everything is destroyed, too. This false trend is encouraged and supported in the E.U.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou puts it this way: an economy which is only geared to short-term profitability, without planning, without vision, without meaning, which produces labour-devouring machines, which is more and more dependent on the speed of communication and which with no regard to ecological balance forces people to an equally forced mobility, like its goods, capital, technologies and information, in contempt of human dignity and protection of the accustomed way of living, [is] an economic dictatorship which triumphs over all human activity &hellip;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If you kill what you are supposed to protect beforehand, you don&rsquo;t need to protect it anymore. First the farmers and mom-and-pop shops have to go and the small businesses and &ldquo;useless&rdquo; species diversity, &ldquo;unprofitable&rdquo; variety. First we must adapt to international mediocrity, to poisoned food, genetically engineered and irradiated foodstuffs. First, in our haste to obey, we must reduce ourselves to the lowest common denominator and annihilate ourselves; then the E.U. can march in unresisted and march right through.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria as a whole will become a vassal state, a new Ostmark. Needless to say, Austria&rsquo;s position as a neutral, environmentally conscious nation free of nuclear power will scarcely be tenable any longer. Then Austria will no longer be able to decide what it wants to do for itself, what and how much it produces and to which countries it will export and from which it will import goods. Austria&rsquo;s fortunes will be decided by strangers in Brussels or elsewhere in the E.U., by strategists sitting at their desks who don&rsquo;t care a fig about Austria&rsquo;s autonomy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Austria&rsquo;s wish for neutrality, Austria&rsquo;s environmental awareness will only be a source of mirth in the E.U. command centre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The slogan &ldquo;alone or together&rdquo; is an alarmist, demagogical appeal to insecurity, to servitude and dependence. It may sound paradoxical, but anyone is strongest when he is alone. I know from personal experience that a person standing alone is just as strong as the group; he is not weaker. The man on the outside is more mobile, more effective in his action and reaction than a cumbersome, bureaucratic, chaotic organisation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Europe is only strong thanks to the diversity of its autonomies. This small-scale diversity must be bolstered and protected. This diversity is Europe. De Gaulle already realised that Europe only has a chance as a Europe of independent, free fatherlands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incomprehensible how irresponsibly our politicians now intend to relinquish our most valuable asset, our independence, freedom and autonomy and declare Austria legally incapacitated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;That is a betrayal of Austria.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The last time there was an Anschluss there were any number of Seyss-Inquarts, Quislings, P&eacute;tains, too, who in their situation at the time probably also thought that their convictions and patriotism were making them do the right thing, that they were doing their duty by entrusting their country to foreign hegemony.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Today history teaches us that their actions were wrong and harmful, and they have long since been branded, punished and executed as traitors and collaborators.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Cling together &ndash; swing together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Beneath the smokescreen of the E.U. the Anschluss is taking place, unnoticed by everyone. When this E.U. then founders, we will have lost one more piece of our independence and will be stuck to our German big brother.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;While bearing all the differences in mind, Austria already experienced a similar fate when, in 1937&ndash;1938, an Anschluss to the &ldquo;Old Reich&rdquo; was propageted, also for economic reasons. &ldquo;Back home to the Reich&rdquo; was the slogan then.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The exchange of the schilling to the superpower-Euro brings ominous analogies with the exchange of the schilling to the Reichmark in 1938 to mind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It must not be forgotten that the promise of financial and economic improvement for the future population of the East Mark was the main reason that many Austrians intended to vote for the Anschluss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The acclaimed integration with Greater Germany was followed by disenchantment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Now it is similar. Precisely what they are touting in the E.U. is what we will lose in the E.U.: social prosperity, full employment, an intact environment, our high quality of life, our homeland, our self-esteem, our nature and our age-old cultures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;One is only a European if one retains and values one&rsquo;s independent, autonomous European-ness. Switzerland, prosperous and democratic, also located in the heart of Europe, should be a shining example to us.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I also don&rsquo;t understand why our Federal President is urging us to give up our sovereignty. After all, he, our highest-ranking patriot, should be issuing a warning and protecting our constitution. Is treason not a crime, the intention to subject Austria to a foreign central authority?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The State Treaty brought liberation to Austria. The E.U. Treaty is a capitulation by Austria, a legal incapacitation of Austria, a subjugation to a new, anachronistic hegemony &ndash; and a breach of the State Treaty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is incredible: the politicians are preparing for a second Anschluss and want to present a fait accompli to the Austrian people. Are our politicians out of their minds, so that only history can show them the error of their ways?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;I am not a lawyer, but I am firmly convinced that we are being manipulated by powerful interest groups which are outside the pale of any ethical, historical, moral, cultural and ecological legality with a despicable demagogy, just like with Zwentendorf back then &lt;em&gt;(the beginning of operations at the nuclear power plant was prevented by a plebiscite)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The E.U. countries are being reduced to the lowest common denominator, rendered anonymous and robbed of their identity. That is the direction this is moving in and not in the direction of decentralisation &lt;em&gt;and the deepening&lt;/em&gt; of autonomies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;As proof, just take the E.U. flag with, as of now, 12 five-pointed little stars exactly alike. Which of these stars would stand for Austria, the one third on the right from the bottom, maybe, or the second, which looks exactly the same?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star is not a symbol from European history, and certainly not from Austria&rsquo;s. In the evolution of the states of the Occident it does not occur. The pentagram, an occult symbol of the Druids and Free Masons, is a foreign body to western heraldry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The five-pointed star serves rather as a sign of subjugation, conquest and colonisation, as on the flags of Australia, New Zealand, America and diverse colonial regimes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;This E.U. flag is in addition a plagiarised version of the Stars and Stripes. The United States of America were also arranged as five-pointed stars, white on blue, at first in a circle, just like the would-be &ldquo;United States of Europe&rdquo;. Later, when there were more of them, they were brought into rank and file.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;These little five-pointed stars are just like the Soviet star, the star of the Yugoslavian, Chinese, Cuban and the other people&rsquo;s epublics. Indeed, this symbol is pathetic proof of the evolved identities of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;It is a bad omen when even the symbol is wrong. This E.U. flag of stars symbolises Europe&rsquo;s self-sacrifice.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the so-called E.U. culture is less than a secondary matter. Creative talents are being trimmed down to useful idiots. To support and window-dress and legitimise a mercantile and industrial growth which is self-destructive.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Culture is not present in Brussels. It is not relevant in the solely mercantile and industrial E.U. In Brussels they know the price of everything and the value of nothing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In this culture-devoid so-called E.U. only numbers count: production figures, deadlines and terms, transition times, population and cattle statistics. Gross national product, agricultural, forest and pastures in square kilometers, labour costs, social benefits, ancillary costs. Export figures, tonnage of heavy transport, milk prices, price adjustments, financing figures, compensatory figures, percents, price reductions, sugar, milk and fish quotas, transit restrictions in numbers, contingents, co-financing, tables, statistics, market-access restrictions in figures. Terms of validity, ecu exchange rates, high unemployment figures, low employment figures, subsidy figures, the number of eco-points, monetary remittances of all kinds, irreal figures on economic growth, poll results in numbers and percents, number of votes in the Council of Ministers and of the blocking minority, majorities, minorities, voting results, E.U. advertising expenditures. Even altitude statistics for alpine famers in meters and latitudes for agriculture in Finland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;If that is not symptomatic!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Environmental protection is also absent in the Brussels hegemony. Only 0.3 percent of the E.U. officials (30 out of 10,000) are concerned with ecology. Talk of environmental protection across borders is just that. Austria must share in the financing of nuclear energy and admit, e.g., plastic bottles and &lt;em&gt;genetically engineered products&lt;/em&gt; and idiotically dangerous regulations on the size of apples and monoculture fruit varieties. I have seen this myself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In Brussels nobody speaks of culture and Western values. Brussels only makes expenditures for culture when asked to. Cultural studies, indeed all study courses, are oriented in the E.U. to their usefulness for industry and to exaggerated growth goals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Only creation can teach us creativity and organic growth. Only creation can teach us to respect species diversity and its incredibly rich variety, of which we are a part ourselves.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;In the E.U., however, efforts are being made in precisely the opposite direction: destruction of the small-scale, creative values in favour of a completely false and outdated automatisation, centralisation and rationalisation, which will be our ruin sooner or later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;The conscience of our civilisation, our age-old destiny to strive for higher values, is being left behind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In Sache &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird die &ouml;sterreichische &Ouml;ffentlichkeit von den staatlichen Medien einer dogmatischen Gehirnw&auml;sche ohnegleichen ausgesetzt. Es herrscht im Fernsehen, im Radio und fast in der gesamten Presse eine infame verschleierte Zensur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich w&uuml;rde das auch nicht in einer Demokratie f&uuml;r m&ouml;glich halten, h&auml;tte ich diese Art von Zensur nicht selbst erlebt. Unter allerlei Pr&auml;texten und Vorw&auml;nden wurde ich mehrmals behindert und verhindert,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; &ouml;ffentlich&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; eine Anti-&lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Meinung zu vertreten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Vorw&auml;nde waren: es passe nicht in die Sendung, ich d&uuml;rfe nichts vorlesen, ich w&auml;re daf&uuml;r nicht zust&auml;ndig, ich w&auml;re verr&uuml;ckt oder aber man versucht mit gezielter Diffamation mich unglaubw&uuml;rdig zu machen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dabei sind meine Bedenken und &Auml;ngste in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten selbst l&auml;ngst best&auml;tigt. Warum h&ouml;rt man nicht auf Leopold Kohr (Das Ende der Gro&szlig;en), Ernst Friedrich Schumacher (Small is beautiful), Jimmy Goldsmith (Le pi&egrave;ge - et si nous avions suivi la mauvaise route?), Henry Coston (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe des banquiers), Jean Pierre Chevenement, Margaret Thatcher, Philippe Seguin, Marie-France Garaud, Elisabeth Guigou, Alberto Miele (Cacciamo i mercanti dal tempio dell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europa), Gerard de Selys, Dr. Manfred Brunner (Anti-Maastricht-Partei), Sir Ralf Dahrendorf (Ex-EU-Kommissar: &quot;k&uuml;nstliche Superkonstruktion nicht lebensf&auml;hig&quot;), Denis de Rougemont (L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;europe doit se faire pour la diversit&eacute;) und unz&auml;hlige andere Warner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich ist von der Geschichte auserw&auml;hlt, Beispiel und Zentrum und Halt in Mitteleuropa zu sein. &Ouml;sterreich ist eine Br&uuml;cke der Hoffnung zum Osten.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wir haben seit dem Krieg in m&uuml;hevoller Arbeit ein riesiges Kapital an Wohlstand, innerem Frieden, internationalem Respekt und Glaubw&uuml;rdigkeit aufgebaut als unabh&auml;ngige, liebenswerte, friedliebende Kulturnation im Herzen Europas. Das kann nicht kurzsichtig und verantwortungslos aufs Spiel gesetzt werden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt nach dem Zerfall der kommunistischen Diktatur und der &Ouml;ffnung der Grenzen muss sich &Ouml;sterreich seiner Verantwortung in Europa bewusst werden und darf sich nicht selbst eliminieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mit einer uns suggerierten Torschlusspanik wird eine Anschlussneurose erzeugt. Angst vor was oder wem? Welche Feinde hat &Ouml;sterreich? Wer sollte und warum &Ouml;sterreichs Sicherheit gef&auml;hrden? Gerade durch den Anschluss an einen Milit&auml;rblock w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich als &quot;Randgebiet Ostmark&quot; erst zum Aufmarschgebiet und zum Feindbild und Angriffsziel werden (Warnung von Erwin Lanc). Gegen atomare Bedrohung ist kein Kraut gewachsen und bei Regionalkriegen - siehe Bosnien - gibt es keinen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Schutz, nicht einmal in Nordirland, innerhalb der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; selbst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;t ist gerade jetzt n&ouml;tiger als je zuvor. Man muss die Neutralit&auml;t beim Namen nennen und zu ihr stehen. Neutralit&auml;t ist ein wahrer Wert. Die immerw&auml;hrende Neutralit&auml;t ist das Fundament unseres Staates und darf nicht verraten und ausgeh&ouml;hlt werden. Wenn wir dieses Fundament unterminieren, zerst&ouml;ren wir diesen unseren Staat &Ouml;sterreich, der darauf errichtet ist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ab jetzt bedeutet die Neutralit&auml;t &Ouml;sterreichs Selbst&auml;ndigkeit, Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit, Verantwortung tragen, Beispiel geben, eine aktive Neutralit&auml;t. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch hier ist die Schweiz ein Beispiel und wird auch im Staatsvertrag als Beispiel genannt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es besteht kein Anlass, gerade jetzt einen Graben quer durch Europa zu ziehen. Es ist so als ob &ouml;stlich von Wien Feindesland w&auml;re.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Die Grenzposten werden von Deutschland an den eben beseitigten Eisernen Vorhang verlegt!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&nbsp; Diese neue Grenzziehung ist nicht nur quer durch Europa, sondern quer durch &Ouml;sterreich, wo die Donaumonarchie war. Es w&auml;re verantwortungslos und gef&auml;hrlich, durch den Anschluss an eine wirtschaftliche und politische &Uuml;bermacht das Gef&auml;lle zu und die Bedrohung f&uuml;r die L&auml;nder &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; zu vergr&ouml;&szlig;ern. &Ouml;sterreichs kulturelle, wirtschaftliche und geschichtliche Bestimmung, &Ouml;sterreichs Verantwortung und Ausstrahlung liegt im Osten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;(Das besagt auch der Name &Ouml;sterreich.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Fronten haben sich gewandelt. Es sind nicht mehr die politischen Grenzen, sondern die Front verl&auml;uft zwischen der brutalen, nur wirtschaftsinteressierten Wegwerfgesellschaft und der ausgebeuteten Natur und der zerst&ouml;rten Seele des Menschen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt einen neuen Widerstand und schon wieder feige Kollaborateure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die jetzt verantwortlichen Politiker sind Hampelm&auml;nner der Wirtschaftsinteressen und heucheln Umweltbewusstsein und Kulturbewusstsein mit Lippenbekenntnissen. Sie beschlie&szlig;en umweltzerst&ouml;rende und kulturzerst&ouml;rende Ma&szlig;nahmen, die unsere Zukunft in Frage stellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die sogenannte &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; betreibt die brutale Vernichtung unserer Lebensbasis, unserer uralten Kulturen, unserer kleinen, gewachsenen Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten, unseres Artenreichtums und unserer Selbstachtung.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Handelsvertretung des Gro&szlig;unternehmertums, der Gewerkschaften, Genossenschaften, der Gro&szlig;banken, der Giftkonzerne, der Monokultur-Monopolisten und der Atom-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;L&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;obby, die uns wie brave Schafe gemeinsam wie das Schlachtvieh in einen Zug in die falsche Richtung verladen will.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dieser riesigen Wirtschaftsmafia geht es nur um Macht und Geld und nicht um das Wohl der Natur und des Menschen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine von verantwortungslosen Schreibtischstrategen ferngesteuerte gigantische Fehlplanung zerst&ouml;rt die Fundamente unseres &uuml;ber uralte Zeiten gewachsenen Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa erlebt die gr&ouml;&szlig;te Vergewaltigung seiner Geschichte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus Br&uuml;ssel kommt keine geistige und kulturelle Erneuerung Europas. Von dort kommen keine Antworten auf die Fragen, die das Gewissen der V&ouml;lker Europas beunruhigen (Alberto Miele). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Aus dieser neuen Hegemonie kommen keine Botschaften, die die Identit&auml;t, unsere uralten Werte, die Inhalte unserer Zivilisation und die Sehns&uuml;chte der Menschen Europas betreffen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wo sind die Kulturen, die Religionen, die Philosophien, die ein neues europ&auml;isches Zeitalter aus der Taufe heben?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Gerade jetzt, wo unsere Gesellschaft die Grenzen des Wachstums erreicht, ist Dezentralisierung unsere einzige &Uuml;berlebenschance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein Anschluss an diese &uuml;berm&auml;chtige Zentralgewalt, die noch immer Wirtschaftswachstum als Zentraldogma gegen alle Evidenz durchziehen will, hat f&uuml;r alle Beteiligten katastrophale Folgen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wohin diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; uns mithineinziehen will, ist ein gnadenloser Konkurrenzkampf, ein Amoklauf in eine gro&szlig;e, gef&auml;hrliche Illusion, in die Sackgasse des Wirtschaftswachstums. Es w&auml;re Wahnsinn, diesem exklusiven Klub der Wegwerfgesellschaft beizutreten, der sich selbst in den M&uuml;ll wirft und ad absurdum f&uuml;hrt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das Produkt &quot;EU&quot; so gut ist, warum muss man derart intensiv daf&uuml;r werben? Und dieser verd&auml;chtige Zeitdruck: Wir m&uuml;ssen uns sofort enteignen, sonst ist es zu sp&auml;t! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Alle guten Dinge geschehen langsam in einem organischen Ablauf von selbst. Einen Baum kann man auch nicht mit Drohungen &uuml;berzeugen und &uuml;berreden, da&szlig; er im tiefen Winter zu bl&uuml;hen hat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe nicht, warum man uns mit Gewalt &uuml;berreden will, die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;, dieses sinkende Schiff zu besteigen, und zwar sofort.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist eine riesige Titanic. Die Analogien zum Untergang der Titanic sind erschreckend. Hier wie dort: Konzeptlosigkeit, Gr&ouml;&szlig;enwahn, Ma&szlig;losigkeit, blinde Technologiegl&auml;ubigkeit und Geschwindigkeitswahn um jeden Preis. Dort das Rennen um das &quot;blaue Band&quot; in die t&ouml;dlichen Eisberge, hier das m&ouml;rderische Wettrennen an die Grenzen des Wachstums der Wegwerfgesellschaft, die unsere Umwelt und uns selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;So einen &quot;europ&auml;ischen Ungl&uuml;cksdampfer&quot; besteigt man nicht und vertraut man unser Leben und unsere Zukunft nicht an. Da ist es besser, man bleibt in einem kleinen, aber man&ouml;vrierbaren Boot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In praktisch der ganzen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; geht es wild zu: Nordirland, Baskenland, Korsika, Mafia, Comorra, Ausl&auml;nderverfolgungen, Rassenhass und Pogrome, Diskriminierung von Gr&ouml;nl&auml;ndern, Macedoniern und Bretonen, brutale Streiks, blutige Ausschreitungen, Studentenrevolten, Drogenkriminalit&auml;t, nukleare St&ouml;rf&auml;lle, verw&uuml;stete Landstriche, Apathie und Katastrophenstimmung, Jugendkriminalit&auml;t, bald 20 Millionen Arbeitslose und eine Staatsspaltung in Flamen und Wallonen, ausgerechnet in Br&uuml;ssel, dem Sitz der &quot;Europ&auml;ischen Union&quot;. Im Vergleich dazu haben das &quot;isolierte &Ouml;sterreich&quot; und die skandinavischen L&auml;nder, die man unbedingt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; treiben will, es &quot;drau&szlig;en&quot; noch gut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; mit Menschenschicksalen jongliert als w&auml;ren es Bauern auf dem Schachbrett. Man kann doch freie Bauern nicht mit Geld abspeisen und ins Ausgedinge schicken, das ist erniedrigend, oder sie nur noch als Folklore- und Alibibauern ben&uuml;tzen, zum Herzeigen f&uuml;r den Tourismus. Das geht gegen Ehre und Selbstachtung, das ist &auml;rger als Mord.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man bezahlt die Bauern f&uuml;r ihren Selbstmord. Die EU verlangt von den Bauern, sie sollen ihre eigene uralte Kultur zerst&ouml;ren. Daf&uuml;r bekommen sie Geld. Anders als bei der Katastrophenhilfe wird die Katastrophe erst mutwillig in Gang gesetzt. Umgebrachte gewachsene Strukturen kann man auch mit sehr viel Geld nicht wiedergutmachen. Tote kann man mit Geld nicht zum Leben erwecken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Wunsch einiger m&auml;chtiger und konkurrenzf&auml;higer Gro&szlig;industrieller nach Eintritt in die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist, noch mehr wirtschaftliche Vorteile zu erlangen. Das geht jedoch auf Kosten der sowieso schon gef&auml;hrdeten Kleinbetriebe und Kleinbauern.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich wei&szlig; aus eigener Erfahrung, dass in den &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten z.B. in Frankreich nur Agrargenossenschaften &uuml;ber 100 ha eine &Uuml;berlebenschance haben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das schaut dann so aus: entweder brachliegende, ver&ouml;dete Felder, verlassene D&ouml;rfer oder Nivellierung von Terrain, Beseitigung von f&uuml;r Gro&szlig;maschinen st&ouml;rende W&auml;ldchen, B&auml;umen und Felsen, Nivellierung von uralten Geh&ouml;ften, Begradigung von B&auml;chen. Eine perfide Zerst&ouml;rung, die in ihren gigantischen Auswirkungen jeden Krieg &uuml;bersteigt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Vermehrte Verwendung von Kunstd&uuml;nger, Pestiziden, genetischen Manipulationen, Bestrahlungen und Umweltgiften aller Art, nat&uuml;rlich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; erzeugt. Eine sadistische, technokratische Zerst&ouml;rung jeglicher Romantik mit dem Schlagwort: unrentabel. Monokultur, so weit das Auge reicht. Dem Bauern wird befohlen, unsere &Uuml;berlebensgrundlage systematisch zu vergewaltigen, den ihm zu treuen H&auml;nden anvertrauten Grund und Boden, Wald und Fluren zu vergiften und zu zerst&ouml;ren. Die Landwirtschaft wird zur gigantischen Agro-Business-Industrie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Abh&auml;ngigkeit der Bauern und von uns allen von Industrie, Chemie und Monopolwirtschaft, diese neue Leibeigenschaft, wird durch einen Anschluss an die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ins Unertr&auml;gliche gesteigert.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ausl&auml;ndische, m&auml;chtigere, brutalere Befehlshaber treten an die Stelle der einheimischen kleineren Firmen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ebenso ergeht es den Kleineren, d. h. allen menschlichen Betrieben, sie werden vernichtet, daf&uuml;r gibt es noch mehr Gro&szlig;kaufh&auml;user, Gro&szlig;banken und Gro&szlig;industrialisierung. Kurzum alles, was unser aller Leben romantisch, liebens- und lebenswert macht, hat kaum mehr &Uuml;berlebensm&ouml;glichkeit. Die stupiden Brutalit&auml;ten siegen, die delikaten Werte kommen um, weil sie sich nicht wehren k&ouml;nnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Agro-Business-Industrie in der EU betreibt fast analog dem &bdquo;Dritten Reich&quot; eine brutale Auslese von reinrassigen gleichgeschalteten &quot;Elite&quot;-Produkten und eine Eliminierung von &quot;minderwertigem&quot; Erbgut oder Saatgut.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es beginnt mit den sch&ouml;nen gro&szlig;en &Auml;pfeln, die alle gleich sein m&uuml;ssen, die in Monokultur gez&uuml;chtet sind, in gleicher Rasse, mit gleichem Geschmack, und setzt sich fort in der genetischen &quot;Nutztierveredelung&quot; und den Legehennenbatterien. Alles nicht produktive Leben wird eliminiert. Alle nicht profitable Vielfalt, alle Andersartigkeit, alle Kleinteiligkeit, aller nutzloser Artenreichtum, alle unrentable Sch&ouml;nheit wird vernichtet. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Dadurch sterben auch das Kleinbauerntum, die Familienbetriebe, die Romantik, kurzum unsere Lebensqualit&auml;t.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Durch das Sterben der Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen),&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Bauern, der Familien- und Kleinbetriebe, durch das Sterben der kleinen Identit&auml;ten entsteht eine Gleichschaltung und eine Anonymisierung unserer Gesellschaft. Man raubt dem Menschen seine W&uuml;rde. Dies bringt eine neue Abh&auml;ngigkeit, eine neue Versklavung, eine neue Leibeigenschaft noch nie dagewesenen Ausma&szlig;es hervor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das ist das Ende des humanistischen Europas. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was dann &uuml;brigbleibt ist keine menschengerechte, sondern eine maschinengerechte und computergerechte Welt. Es ist eine Zerst&ouml;rung von h&ouml;heren Werten, die in ihrer Vielfalt Europa ausmachen. Es ist die Zerst&ouml;rung Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kleinbauern m&uuml;ssen Haus und Hof und Land verkaufen, werden entweder arbeitslos oder Stadtproletariat oder m&uuml;ssen sich Agro-Business-Genossenschaften anschlie&szlig;en, wo sie nur mehr Befehlsempf&auml;nger ohne Entscheidungsfreiheit sind, auf einem Land, das einmal ihnen geh&ouml;rte.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; leidet unter einem wachsenden Arbeitslosenheer, das schon jetzt der arbeitenden Bev&ouml;lkerung eines Landes 7- bis 10-mal so gro&szlig; wie &Ouml;sterreich entspricht!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man kann sich vorstellen, welches verheerende Beispiel die &lt;strong&gt;EU &lt;/strong&gt;damit der Welt gibt, wenn die 3 Milliarden Menschen, die in der Dritten Welt auf dem Lande ihr Auskommen finden, diesem &lt;strong&gt;EU B&lt;/strong&gt;eispiel zu folgen gezwungen werden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Eine gigantische Fl&uuml;chtlingswelle von 2 Milliarden Landbev&ouml;lkerung - diesen &quot;exode rural mondial&quot;, wie Jimmy Goldsmith warnt, k&ouml;nne die Welt nicht mehr ertragen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Grenzen sind so wie unsere Haut. Sie sch&uuml;tzen den gewachsenen Organismus, unsere individuelle Andersartigkeit vor Gefahr von Au&szlig;en wie Hitze und K&auml;lte. Wenn man die Haut entfernt, stirbt der Organismus, weil er schutzlos wird.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Daher haben wir Schutzz&ouml;lle zum Schutz einer gef&auml;hrdeten Gemeinschaft. &auml;hnlich wie wir Sonnenbrillen und Zeckenimpfungen etc. zu unserem Schutz einsetzen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Was Gott getrennt hat, sollen wir nicht mit Gewalt einen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es gibt nat&uuml;rliche Grenzen wie zum Beispiel die Sahara, das Mittelmeer und die Alpen, in deren Schutz sich uralte Kulturen gebildet haben wie die afrikanischen, die mediterranen und die nordeurop&auml;ischen Kulturen. Die Alpen haben eine Schutzfunktion sowohl f&uuml;r den Norden als auch f&uuml;r den S&uuml;den.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ein schrankenloser, sinnloser Transitverkehr ist gleichbedeutend mit einem Niederrei&szlig;en und Nivellieren der Alpen, auch wenn der Verkehr untertunnelt wird. &Ouml;sterreich hat genauso wie die Schweiz eine Alpine Schutzw&auml;chterfunktion f&uuml;r Europa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die fieberhafte, unnat&uuml;rliche, konzeptlose Hin- und Herraserei ist Wahnsinn und wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; zum &quot;grenzenlosen Wahnsinn&quot;. An dem Ort, wo wir sind, machen wir alles hin, dann fl&uuml;chten wir vor unserer eigenen Zerst&ouml;rung, um anderswo alles hin zu machen, und auf dem Weg dahin wird auch alles hin. Dieser falsche Trend wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; forciert und unterst&uuml;tzt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Elisabeth Guigou dr&uuml;ckt das so aus: Eine Wirtschaft, die nur auf Kurzzeit-Rentabilit&auml;t ausgerichtet ist, ohne Plan, ohne Vision, ohne Sinn, die arbeitsstellen-fressende Maschinen produziert, die mehr und mehr von der Transport- und Kommunikationsgeschwindigkeit abh&auml;ngig ist und die unter Au&szlig;erachtlassung des &ouml;kologischen Gleichgewichtes die Menschen zu einer ebenso forcierten Beweglichkeit zwingt wie die Waren, die Kapitalien, die Technologien und Informationen unter Missachtung der Menschenw&uuml;rde und des Schutzes der gewohnten Lebensweisen, eine &ouml;konomische Diktatur, die &uuml;ber alle anderen menschlichen T&auml;tigkeiten triumphiert...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn man das, was man zu sch&uuml;tzen hat, vorher umbringt, braucht man keinen Schutz mehr. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen die Bauern und die Grei&szlig;ler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Gemischtwarenhandlungen)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; weg und die Kleinbetriebe und der &quot;nutzlose&quot; Artenreichtum, die &quot;unrentable&quot; Vielfalt. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir uns angleichen an internationales Mittelma&szlig;, an vergiftetes Essen, genmanipulierte und bestrahlte Lebensmittel. Zuerst m&uuml;ssen wir in vorauseilendem Gehorsam uns selbst nivellieren und uns vernichten, dann kann die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; widerstandslos einmarschieren und durchmarschieren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Ouml;sterreich als ganzes wird ein Vasallenstaat, eine neue Ostmark. Selbstverst&auml;ndlich ist dann &Ouml;sterreichs Position als neutrale, kernkraftfreie, umweltbewusste Nation kaum mehr haltbar. &Ouml;sterreich kann dann nicht mehr selbst entscheiden, was es tut, was und wieviel es produziert und in welche L&auml;nder es exportiert und aus welchen es importiert. &Ouml;sterreichs Geschicke werden von fremden Leuten in Br&uuml;ssel oder anderswo in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; bestimmt, von Schreibtischstrategen, die sich einen Dreck um &Ouml;sterreichs Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit scheren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&Uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Neutralit&auml;tswillen, &uuml;ber &Ouml;sterreichs Umweltbewusstsein wird in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Kommandozentrale nur gelacht.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Slogan &quot;einsam oder gemeinsam&quot; ist eine angstmachende, demagogische Aufforderung zur Verunsicherung, zur Unfreiheit und zur Abh&auml;ngigkeit. Es mag paradox klingen, aber allein ist jeder am st&auml;rksten. Aus pers&ouml;nlicher Erfahrung wei&szlig; ich, dass ein Aussenstehender genauso stark ist wie die Gruppe und nicht schw&auml;cher. Der Au&szlig;enstehende ist beweglicher, effektiver in seinem Handeln und im Reagieren als eine schwerf&auml;llige, b&uuml;rokratische, chaotische Organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europa ist nur stark dank der Vielfalt seiner Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. Diese kleinteilige Vielfalt muss verst&auml;rkt und gesch&uuml;tzt werden. Diese Vielfalt ist Europa. Schon de Gaulle erkannte, dass Europa nur eine Chance als Europa der selbst&auml;ndigen, freien Vaterl&auml;nder hat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unverst&auml;ndlich, wie verantwortungslos unsere Politiker jetzt unser wertvollstes Gut, unsere Unabh&auml;ngigkeit, Freiheit und Eigenst&auml;ndigkeit aufgeben und &Ouml;sterreich entm&uuml;ndigen wollen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein Verrat an &Ouml;sterreich. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim letzten Anschluss gab es auch jede Menge Seyss-Inquarts, Guislings, Petains, die in der damaligen Situation wahrscheinlich auch aus &Uuml;berzeugung und Patriotismus glaubten, das Richtige zu tun und ihre Pflicht erf&uuml;llen zu m&uuml;ssen, indem sie ihr Land einer fremden Hegemonie anvertrauten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Heute lehrt uns die Geschichte, dass ihr Tun falsch und sch&auml;dlich war, und sie sind l&auml;ngst als Verr&auml;ter und Kollaborateure gebrandmarkt, bestraft und hingerichtet worden. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Mitgefangen - mitgehangen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Unter der Dunstglocke der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird von allen unbemerkt der Anschluss an Deutschland vollzogen. Wenn dann diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Schiffbruch erleidet, haben wir noch ein St&uuml;ck mehr unserer Unabh&auml;ngigkeit verloren und bleiben am gro&szlig;en deutschen Bruder kleben.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Bei Wahrung aller Unterschiede hat &Ouml;sterreich &Auml;hnliches bereits erlebt, als auch aus wirtschaftlichen Gr&uuml;nden 1937-1938 ein Anschluss an das &quot;Altreich&quot; propagiert wurde. &quot;Heim ins Reich&quot; hie&szlig; damals die Parole. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Beim Umtausch des Schilling in den Gro&szlig;macht-Euro muss man fatalerweise Analogien mit dem Umtausch des Schilling 1938 in die Reichsmark feststellen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Man darf nicht vergessen, dass das Versprechen einer finanziellen und wirtschaftlichen Besserstellung der k&uuml;nftigen Ostm&auml;rker Haupttriebfeder vieler &Ouml;sterreicher war, um f&uuml;r den Anschluss zu stimmen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auf die bejubelte Einverleibung mit Gro&szlig;deutschland erfolgte die Ern&uuml;chterung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Jetzt ist es &auml;hnlich. Genau das, was man uns in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; vorgaukeln will, verlieren wir in der&lt;strong&gt; EU&lt;/strong&gt;: sozialen Wohlstand, Vollbesch&auml;ftigung, eine intakte Umwelt, unsere hohe Lebensqualit&auml;t, unsere Heimat, unsere Selbstachtung, unsere Natur und unsere uralten Kulturen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Europ&auml;er ist man nur dann, wenn man sein unabh&auml;ngiges, eigenst&auml;ndiges Europ&auml;ertum bewahrt und hochh&auml;lt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Schweiz, wohlhabend und demokratisch, auch im Herzen Europas gelegen, soll uns ein leuchtendes Beispiel sein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich verstehe auch nicht, wieso unser Bundespr&auml;sident uns zur Aufgabe unserer Souver&auml;nit&auml;t auffordert. Er m&uuml;sste doch als oberster Patriot warnen und die Verfassung sch&uuml;tzen. Ist denn Landesverrat kein Vergehen, wenn man &Ouml;sterreich einer ausl&auml;ndischen Zentralgewalt unterwerfen will? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der Staatsvertrag brachte &Ouml;sterreich die Befreiung. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; Vertrag ist eine Kapitulation &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Entm&uuml;ndigung &Ouml;sterreichs, eine Unterwerfung unter eine neue anachronistische Hegemonie - und ein Bruch des Staatsvertrages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist unglaublich: Die Politiker bereiten den zweiten Anschluss vor und wollen das &ouml;sterreichische Volk vor vollendete Tatsachen stellen. Sind unsere Politiker von allen guten Geistern verlassen, so dass erst&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; die Geschichte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; sie zurechtweisen muss? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Ich bin kein Jurist, aber ich bin der festen &Uuml;berzeugung, dass wir von m&auml;chtigen Interessensgruppen au&szlig;erhalb jeder ethischen, geschichtlichen, moralischen, kulturellen und &ouml;kologischen Legalit&auml;t mit einer miesen Demagogie manipuliert werden, so wie seinerzeit bei Zwentendorf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; (Inbetriebnahme des Atommeilers wurde durch Volksabstimmung verhindert)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Staaten werden nivelliert und anonymisiert und ihrer Identit&auml;t beraubt. In diese Richtung geht es und nicht in die Richtung der Dezentralisation und&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; Vertiefung&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; der Eigenst&auml;ndigkeiten. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Zum Beweis gen&uuml;gt die &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne mit den jetzt 12 genau gleichen 5-zackigen Sternchen. Welches dieser Sternchen w&uuml;rde &Ouml;sterreich symbolisieren, etwa das dritte rechts von unten oder das zweite, das genauso aussieht?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Der F&uuml;nfstern ist kein Symbol aus der europ&auml;ischen und schon gar nicht aus der &ouml;sterreichischen Geschichte. Er kommt in der Entwicklung der Staaten des Okzidents nicht vor. Das Pentagramm, ein okkultistisches Zeichen der Druden und Freimaurer ist ein Fremdk&ouml;rper in der abendl&auml;ndischen Heraldik. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die 5-zackigen Sterne dienen eher als Merkmal der Unterwerfung, Inbesitznahme und Kolonisierung wie auf der austral-neuseel&auml;ndischen, amerikanischen und auf Kolonialfahnen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Fahne ist noch dazu ein Plagiat aus dem Sternenbanner. Auch die Vereinigten Staaten Amerikas waren als 5-zackige Sternchen, wei&szlig; auf blau, zuerst im Kreis angeordnet, genauso wie jetzt die M&ouml;chtegern-&quot;Vereinigten Staaten Europas&quot;. Sp&auml;ter, als sie sich vermehrten, wurden sie in Reih und Glied gebracht. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese 5-zackigen Sternchen sind dieselben wie der Sowjetstern, der Stern der jugoslawischen, chinesischen, kubanischen und sonstigen Volksrepubliken. Wahrlich, dieses Symbol ist ein Armutszeugnis f&uuml;r die gewachsenen Identit&auml;ten Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es ist ein b&ouml;ses Omen, wenn schon das Zeichen falsch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Diese &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Sternchenfahne symbolisiert die Selbstaufgabe Europas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; ist die Kultur weniger als Nebensache. Die sch&ouml;pferischen Kr&auml;fte werden zu n&uuml;tzlichen Idioten getrimmt. Zur Unterst&uuml;tzung und Verbr&auml;mung und Legitimierung eines merkantilen und industriellen Wachstums, das sich selbst zerst&ouml;rt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Die Kultur ist in Br&uuml;ssel nicht pr&auml;sent. Sie ist in der nur merkantilen und industriellen &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; kein Thema. In Br&uuml;ssel kennt man den Preis von allem und den Wert von nichts. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Es geht in dieser kulturlosen, sogenannten &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; nur um Zahlen: Produktionszahlen, Termine und Laufzeiten, &Uuml;bergangsfristen, Einwohner- und Viehzahlen. Bruttosozialprodukte, Anbau-, Wald- und Weidegebiete in Quadratkilometern, Lohnkosten, Sozialleistungen, Nebenkosten. Exportziffern, Tonnenzahlen f&uuml;r Schwertransporte, Milchpreise, Preisanpassungen, Finanzierungszahlen, Ausgleichszahlen, Prozente, Preissenkungen, Zucker-, Milch&shy;- und Fischquoten, Transitbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen, Kontingente, Mitfinanzierungen, Tabellen, Statistiken, Marktzugangsbeschr&auml;nkungen in Zahlen. Laufzeiten, Ecu Umtauschkurse, hohe Arbeitslosenzahlen, niedrige Besch&auml;ftigungszahlen, F&ouml;rderungs- und Subventionszahlen, die Anzahl von &Ouml;kopunkten, Geldzahlungen aller Art, irreale Wirtschaftswachstumszahlen, Umfrageergebnisse in Zahlen und Prozenten, Stimmenanzahlen des Ministerrates und der Sperrminorit&auml;t, Mehrheiten, Minderheiten, Abstimmungsergebnisse, EU-Werbeausgaben. Ja sogar H&ouml;henzahlen f&uuml;r Bergbauern in Metern und Breitegradzahlen f&uuml;r die Landwirtschaft in Finnland. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Wenn das nicht symptomatisch ist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Auch der Umweltschutz ist in der Br&uuml;sseler Hegemonie abwesend. Nur 0,3 Prozent (30 von 10.000) der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt;-Beamten sind f&uuml;r die &Ouml;kologie t&auml;tig. Vom Grenzen &uuml;berbr&uuml;ckenden Umweltschutz ist nur die Rede. &Ouml;sterreich muss die Kernkraft mitfinanzieren und z. B. Plastikflaschen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und Gen-Produkte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; und idiotisch-gef&auml;hrliche Richtlinien f&uuml;r Apfelgr&ouml;&szlig;en und Monokultur-Obstsorten &uuml;bernehmen. Das habe ich selbst gesehen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Von Kultur und den Werten des Abendlandes ist in Br&uuml;ssel keine Rede. Um Ausgaben f&uuml;r Kultur muss man erst Br&uuml;ssel bitten. Das Kulturstudium und auch der gesamte Studienbereich in der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; wird ausgerichtet auf die N&uuml;tzlichkeit f&uuml;r die Industrie und auf das forcierte Wachstum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Kreativit&auml;t und organisches Wachstum lehren. Nur die Sch&ouml;pfung kann uns Achtung lehren vor dem Artenreichtum und der unglaublichen Vielfalt, deren Teil wir selbst sind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;In der &lt;strong&gt;EU&lt;/strong&gt; aber gehen die Bestrebungen in die genau umgekehrte Richtung: Vernichtung der kleinteiligen sch&ouml;pferischen Werte zugunsten einer v&ouml;llig falschen und &uuml;berholten Automatisierung, Zentralisierung und Rationalisierung, die uns &uuml;ber kurz oder lang zum Untergang bringt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Das Gewissen unserer Zivilisation, unsere uralte Bestimmung, h&ouml;here Werte anzustreben, bleibt auf der Strecke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_occasion_en-'&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Written in Vienna &ndash; Paris &ndash; Kaurinui, 1988&ndash;1994. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Passages in italics: La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;Geschrieben in Wien - Paris - Kaurinui, 1988 - 1994,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%&quot;&gt; erg&auml;nzt in kursiv in La Picaudi&egrave;re, 1997.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1993, p. 65-68 (Text Anschlu&szlig;psychose, 1988) (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;protokolle&lt;/em&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. edited by Otto Breicha. Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Vienna, 1997, pp. 185-193 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (ed.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. UNIPRESS: Salzburg, 1998, p. 83-99 (German)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (ed.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Vol. II: F&uuml;rst, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute;. Taschen: Cologne, 2002, pp. 1151-1162 (German and English)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot; size=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (ed.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. (Beautiful Paths &ndash; Thoughts on Art and Life) Langen M&uuml;ller: Munich, 2004, pp. 55-64 (German)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Verraten und Verkauft - Das EG-Lesebuch. UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1993, S. 65-68 (Text &lt;span style=&quot;background: yellow 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial&quot;&gt;Anschlu&szlig;psychose&lt;/span&gt;, 1988)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;protokolle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;. Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Literatur und Kunst. hrsg. von Otto Breicha. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Verlagsb&uuml;ro Lehner: Wien 1997, S. 185-193&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Witzany, G&uuml;nther (Hg.): Zukunft &Ouml;sterreich - EU Anschlu&szlig; und die Folgen. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;UNIPRESS: Salzburg 1998, S. 83-99&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schmied, Wieland (Hg.): Hundertwasser 1928&ndash;2000, Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Vol. II: F&uuml;r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;st, Andrea Christa: Catalogue Raisonn&eacute; / Werkverzeichnis. Taschen: K&ouml;ln 2002, S. 1151-1162 (Deutsch und Englisch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &ndash; Sch&ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. Langen M&uuml;ller: M&uuml;nchen 2004, S. 55-64&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 150%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'', text_translator-'Courtesy TASCHEN, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-23 8:16:29.958###object###text###1.4.6.4###THE ANTIPODAL TIMEPIECE
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.4.6.4&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-132&quot;&gt; 132&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;We live in an absurd anti-time. Values are topsy-turvy. &lt;br&gt;Uglyness is considered honest and worthwhile. Beauty is branded populist kitsch. &lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-132&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;132 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Time, the clock, has become the symbol of pressing deadlines. &lt;br&gt;More than ever before we need to hark back to the course of eternal events in harmony with nature and creation. &lt;br&gt;Timelessness - lasting values, awareness of the cosmos, where there is no up and down, no right and left, no clockwise or counter-clockwise. That is why the antipodal timepiece does not actually indicate time in the sense of our business mentality, but rather an anti-time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Time is not the important thing, but the organic course of events in organic, beautiful form. Time should create new life, slowly, spiraloidally, vegetatively and surely and creatively. Time should not destroy the time before and cause panic about the time of tomorrow, which will be dead the day after tomorrow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;That is why the antipodal timepiece has hands which move to the left as well as the right not in a circular, but in an organically dented housing, which can also be situated vertically in several positions. Lasting values are represented, such as ecology and creativity. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The measurement of time is a human, bogus idea and invention, as is the straight line, but eternity and the eternal course of events are all there is. &lt;br&gt;So this antipodal timepiece is intended as a simile of these higher laws.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', txt-'1.4.6.4', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'THE ANTIPODAL TIMEPIECE', text_title_ge-'DER ANTIPODISCHE ZEITTIMER', text_contents_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Wir leben in einer absurden Anti-Zeit. Werte werden auf den Kopf gestellt.&lt;br /&gt;H&amp;auml;&amp;szlig;liches wird als ehrlich und erstrebenswert dargestellt. Sch&amp;ouml;nes als populistischer Kitsch gebrandmarkt. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Die Zeit, die Uhr werden zum Symbol der rasenden Termine.&lt;br /&gt;Eine Besinnung auf ewige Abl&amp;auml;ufe in Harmonie mit der Natur und der Sch&amp;ouml;pfung ist mehr vonn&amp;ouml;ten als je zuvor. &lt;br /&gt;Zeitlosigkeit - best&amp;auml;ndige Werte, das Wissen um den Kosmos, wo es kein Oben und Unten, kein Rechts und kein Links, keinen Uhrzeigersinn gibt. Deswegen zeigt der antipodische Zeittimer eigentlich keine Zeit im Sinne unserer Business-Mentalit&amp;auml;t an, sondern eine Anti-Zeit.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Nicht die Zeit ist wichtig, sondern der organische Ablauf von Geschehen in organischer, sch&amp;ouml;ner Form. Die Zeit soll neues Leben schaffen, langsam, spiraloid, vegetativ und sicher und kreativ. Die Zeit soll nicht zerst&amp;ouml;ren die vorige Zeit und panische Angst erzeugen vor der morgigen Zeit, die &amp;uuml;bermorgen schon tot ist.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Daher hat der antipodische Zeittimer nach rechts wie auch nach links laufende Zeiger in einem nicht kreisrunden, sondern organisch eingebuchteten Geh&amp;auml;use, das man auch senkrecht in mehreren Positionen aufstellen kann. Bleibende Werte sind ebenso vertreten wie &amp;Ouml;kologie und Kreativit&amp;auml;t. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Zeiteinteilung ist eine menschliche, irrige Idee und Erfindung, so wie die gerade Linie, es gibt aber nur Ewigkeit und organische Abl&amp;auml;ufe. &lt;br /&gt;Daher soll dieser antipodische Zeittimer diesen &amp;uuml;bergeordneten Gesetzen ein Gleichnis sein.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_keywords-'Zeit, time, Kitsch, kitsch, antipodal time piece, antipodischer Zeittimer, Uhr, clock', text_date-'1990-11-01', text_summary_en-'', text_summary_ge-'', text_occasion_en-'&lt;div&gt;written November 1, 1990, for a brochure for the object &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;908&amp;nbsp; IRREGULAR&amp;nbsp; DOUBLE-FACED WATCH-OBJECT&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Verfa&amp;szlig;t 1. November 1990 f&amp;uuml;r eine Brosch&amp;uuml;zre zum Werk&lt;br /&gt;908 UNREGELM&amp;Auml;SSIGES DOPPELSEITIGES UHR-OBJEKT&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;div&gt;Brosch&amp;uuml;re, M&amp;auml;nnedorf/Glarus 1992&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A. C. F&amp;uuml;rst, Hundertwasser 1928-2000, Catalogue Raisonn&amp;eacute;, Cologne: Taschen, 2002, Vol. II, p. 1080&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Der unbekannte Hundertwasser, KunstHausWien, Munich: Prestel Verlag, 2008, p. 206&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;div&gt;Broschure, M&amp;auml;nnedorf/Glarus 1992&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A. C. F&amp;uuml;rst, Hundertwasser 1928-2000, Catalogue Raisonn&amp;eacute;, K&amp;ouml;ln: Taschen, 2002, Vol. II, S.&amp;nbsp; 1080&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Der unbekannte Hundertwasser, KunstHausWien, M&amp;uuml;nchen: Prestel Verlag, 2008, p. 206&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'courtesy Taschen, Cologne', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-23 10:37:13.0384###object###text###1.5.6.1###EINE NEUE FRIEDHOFSORDNUNG - WIEDERGEBURT ZU HAUSE
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.5.6.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-133&quot;&gt; 133&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;As Utopian as it may sound, burying the dead at home, in the humus layers of the wooded terraces, is actually quite feasible.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-133&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;133 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For instance, when a building has 50 apartments and 500 metric tons of soil are on the roofs, these 500,000 kilos of soil would have no problem whatsoever absorbing the body of one dead person weighing 50 kilos each year, particularly since it turns into humus anyhow. It would be 1% of 1%, or one-thousandth, of the soil volume that would be reduced to one-hundred-thousandth within a year, from 50 kilos down to 5 kilos.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There would be no hygiene problem, as the process of decomposition would be aerobic, preventing the growth of dangerous anaerobic putrefactive bacteria. The interment should take place without a coffin, wrapped in a shroud, in a layer of earth at least 60 centimeters thick. A tree should be planted on top of the grave to guarantee that the deceased will live on symbolically as well as in reality.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When people move out, there are two options. The remains may continue to be respected by the new occupants in the form of&amp;nbsp; a sacred site 2 by 1 meters, which the old occupants may visit, or the remains may safely be exhumed and interred elsewhere after about one year, when their weight is reduced to approximately 5 kilos.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Nowadays, people are buried in a way that is completely non-ecological and anti-religious, against all the laws of nature, of the universe, of the cycle of life, of reincarnation and resurrection: in coffins that are sealed airtight, 4 meters below ground, where they do not turn into humus, but rather rot as if stricken with the plague, far removed from the underground life of vegetation and tree roots.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To make resurrection impossible, the path to Creation is additionally blocked by concrete slabs, uniform tombstones, synthetic grass and artificial flowers. Any form of silent prayer at this site of the twice-murdered dead, who are denied reincarnation, is impossible. A dead person is entitled to reincarnation in the form of, for example, a tree that grows on top of him and through him. The result would be a sacred forest of living dead. A garden of the happy dead, which we have such a real need for. Reincarnation would even be demonstrable in chemical terms, as substances from the deceased are found in the tree on top of the grave. The gravesite of today becomes a site of worship and silent prayer, of joy and life regained.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;And not somewhere far away in a cemetery tended to by strangers, but right at home.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Family and friends don&rsquo;t die. The circle expands and the good spirits return.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', id-253, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-253, txt-'1.5.6.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'NEW FUNERARY REGULATIONS - REINCARNATION AT HOME', text_title_ge-'EINE NEUE FRIEDHOFSORDNUNG - WIEDERGEBURT ZU HAUSE', text_keywords-'Friedhofsordnung, Wiedergeburt, reincarnation, funerary regulations,&lt;br /&gt;Bestattung', text_date-'1950-00-00', text_summary_en-'Hundertwasser first expressed the idea of an ecological burial - his wish to be buried naked and without a coffin under a tree - in 1979 in the book Ao Tea Roa &ndash; Insel der verlorenen W&uuml;nsche (Island of Lost Desire.&lt;br /&gt;In 1984 Hundertwasser obtained permission from the Minister of Health of New Zealand, Anthony G. Malcolm, to be buried on his property in the Bay of Islands. Hundertwasser died on February 19, 2000, in the Pacific Ocean on board the Queen Elizabeth 2, and he was buried on his land in New Zealand, in the &ldquo;Garden of the Happy Dead,&rdquo; in harmony with nature under a tulip tree, just as he had wanted.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;', text_summary_ge-'Hundertwasser formulierte den Gedanken einer &ouml;kologischen Bestattung, seinen Wunsch, nackt und ohne Sarg unter einem Baum begraben zu werden, zum ersten Mal 1979 in dem Buch Ao Tea Roa &ndash; Insel der verlorenen W&uuml;nsche: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Im Jahr 1984 hat Hundertwasser vom Gesundheitsminister Neuseelands, Anthony G. Malcolm, eine Genehmigung erwirkt, auf seinem Grundst&uuml;ck in der Bay of Islands bestattet  zu werden. &lt;br /&gt;Nach dem Tod Hundertwassers am Samstag, dem 19. Februar 2000, im Pazifischen Ozean an Bord der Queen Elizabeth 2, wurde er, wie von ihm gew&uuml;nscht, auf seinem Land in Neuseeland, im &bdquo;Garten der gl&uuml;cklichen Toten&ldquo;, in Harmonie mit der Natur unter einem Tulpenbaum begraben.&lt;br /&gt;', text_language-ge, text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Utopisch klingt, aber durchf&uuml;hrbar ist die Totenbestattung im eigenen Haus, in den Humusschichten der bewaldeten Terrassen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Wenn das Haus z.B. 50 Wohngemeinschaften hat, auf den D&auml;chern 500 Tonnen Erdreich liegen, so k&ouml;nnen 500.000 kg Erde spielend pro Jahr einen 50 kg schweren Toten in sich aufnehmen, besonders weil er ja sowieso zu Humus wird. Das w&auml;ren 1 % von 1 % oder ein Zehntausendstel des Erdvolumens, das sich innerhalb eines Jahres auf ein Hunderttausendstel verringern w&uuml;rde, von 50 kg auf 5 kg.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Die Hygiene w&auml;re gegeben, weil die Humisierung aerobisch vor sich geht, wodurch anaerobisch gef&auml;hrliche F&auml;ulnisbakterien nicht entstehen k&ouml;nnen. Die Bestattung mu&szlig; ohne Sarg, mit einem Leichentuch, in mindestens 60 cm dicker Erdschicht vorgenommen werden. Ein Baum soll auf dem Grab gepflanzt werden, der symbolisch, aber auch faktisch das Weiterleben des Toten gew&auml;hrleistet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Bei einer Umsiedlung sind zwei M&ouml;glichkeiten offen. Entweder die Gebeine bleiben als eine heilige St&auml;tte im Ausma&szlig; 2 x 1 m von den neuen Bewohnern respektiert und die alten Bewohner kommen die heilige St&auml;tte ab und zu besuchen, oder aber die Gebeine k&ouml;nnen nach etwa einem Jahr gefahrlos exhumiert und woanders beigesetzt werden, da die Reste nur etwa 5 kg wiegen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Der Mensch wird jetzt total un&ouml;kologisch und antireligi&ouml;s bestattet, gegen alle Gesetze der Natur, des Kosmos, des Kreislaufes und der Wiedergeburt und der Wiederauferstehung: in luftdicht abgeschlossenen S&auml;rgen, in 4 Meter Tiefe, wo er nicht zu Humus werden, sondern nur pestilenzartig verfaulen kann, weit weg vom Untergrundleben der Vegetation und der Baumwurzeln.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Um die Auferstehung unm&ouml;glich zu machen, versperrt man den Weg zur Sch&ouml;pfung noch zus&auml;tzlich mit Betonplatten, uniformen Grabsteinen, Plastikrasen und Plastikblumen. Eine Andacht an dieser St&auml;tte des nochmals gemordeten Toten, dem man die Wiedergeburt verwehrt, ist unm&ouml;glich. Ein Toter hat das Recht auf Wiedergeburt in Form z.B. eines Baumes, der auf ihm und durch ihn w&auml;chst. Es entst&uuml;nde ein heiliger Wald von lebenden Toten. Ein Garten der gl&uuml;cklichen Toten, den wir so sehr ben&ouml;tigen. Sogar chemisch ist die Wiedergeburt nachzuweisen, weil sich Substanzen des Toten im Baum auf dem Grab wiederfinden. Die bisherige Totenst&auml;tte wird zum Ort der Andacht, zum Ort der Freude und des wiedergewonnenen Lebens.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Und das bei sich zu Hause, nicht auf einem fernen, von Fremden verwalteten Friedhof.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Die Familie und die Freunde sterben nicht. Der Kreis wird gr&ouml;&szlig;er und die guten Geister kehren zur&uuml;ck.&lt;/p&gt;', text_contents_ge-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Utopisch klingt, aber durchf&amp;uuml;hrbar ist die Totenbestattung im eigenen Haus, in den Humusschichten der bewaldeten Terrassen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Wenn das Haus z.B. 50 Wohngemeinschaften hat, auf den D&amp;auml;chern 500 Tonnen Erdreich liegen, so k&amp;ouml;nnen 500.000 kg Erde spielend pro Jahr einen 50 kg schweren Toten in sich aufnehmen, besonders weil er ja sowieso zu Humus wird. Das w&amp;auml;ren 1 % von 1 % oder ein Zehntausendstel des Erdvolumens, das sich innerhalb eines Jahres auf ein Hunderttausendstel verringern w&amp;uuml;rde, von 50 kg auf 5 kg.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Die Hygiene w&amp;auml;re gegeben, weil die Humisierung aerobisch vor sich geht, wodurch anaerobisch gef&amp;auml;hrliche F&amp;auml;ulnisbakterien nicht entstehen k&amp;ouml;nnen. Die Bestattung mu&amp;szlig; ohne Sarg, mit einem Leichentuch, in mindestens 60 cm dicker Erdschicht vorgenommen werden. Ein Baum soll auf dem Grab gepflanzt werden, der symbolisch, aber auch faktisch das Weiterleben des Toten gew&amp;auml;hrleistet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Bei einer Umsiedlung sind zwei M&amp;ouml;glichkeiten offen. Entweder die Gebeine bleiben als eine heilige St&amp;auml;tte im Ausma&amp;szlig; 2 x 1 m von den neuen Bewohnern respektiert und die alten Bewohner kommen die heilige St&amp;auml;tte ab und zu besuchen, oder aber die Gebeine k&amp;ouml;nnen nach etwa einem Jahr gefahrlos exhumiert und woanders beigesetzt werden, da die Reste nur etwa 5 kg wiegen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Der Mensch wird jetzt total un&amp;ouml;kologisch und antireligi&amp;ouml;s bestattet, gegen alle Gesetze der Natur, des Kosmos, des Kreislaufes und der Wiedergeburt und der Wiederauferstehung: in luftdicht abgeschlossenen S&amp;auml;rgen, in 4 Meter Tiefe, wo er nicht zu Humus werden, sondern nur pestilenzartig verfaulen kann, weit weg vom Untergrundleben der Vegetation und der Baumwurzeln.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Um die Auferstehung unm&amp;ouml;glich zu machen, versperrt man den Weg zur Sch&amp;ouml;pfung noch zus&amp;auml;tzlich mit Betonplatten, uniformen Grabsteinen, Plastikrasen und Plastikblumen. Eine Andacht an dieser St&amp;auml;tte des nochmals gemordeten Toten, dem man die Wiedergeburt verwehrt, ist unm&amp;ouml;glich. Ein Toter hat das Recht auf Wiedergeburt in Form z.B. eines Baumes, der auf ihm und durch ihn w&amp;auml;chst. Es entst&amp;uuml;nde ein heiliger Wald von lebenden Toten. Ein Garten der gl&amp;uuml;cklichen Toten, den wir so sehr ben&amp;ouml;tigen. Sogar chemisch ist die Wiedergeburt nachzuweisen, weil sich Substanzen des Toten im Baum auf dem Grab wiederfinden. Die bisherige Totenst&amp;auml;tte wird zum Ort der Andacht, zum Ort der Freude und des wiedergewonnenen Lebens.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Und das bei sich zu Hause, nicht auf einem fernen, von Fremden verwalteten Friedhof.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Die Familie und die Freunde sterben nicht. Der Kreis wird gr&amp;ouml;&amp;szlig;er und die guten Geister kehren zur&amp;uuml;ck.&lt;/p&gt;', text_occasion_en-'&lt;div&gt;written 1985 for the book &amp;quot;Das Hundertwasser Haus&amp;quot;&lt;/div&gt;', text_occasion_ge-'&lt;div&gt;verfa&amp;szlig;t 1985 f&amp;uuml;r das Buch &amp;quot;Das Hundertwasser Haus&amp;quot;&lt;/div&gt;', text_published_en-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus, Vienna: &amp;Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag/Compress Verlag, 1985, p. 318 (German)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &amp;ndash; Sch&amp;ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &amp;uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. [Beautiful Paths - Thoughts on Art and Life]. Munich: Langen M&amp;uuml;ller Verlag, 2004, pp. 278-279 (German)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The Unknown Hundertwasser, KunstHausWien, Munich: Prestel Verlag, 2008, p. 240&lt;/p&gt;', text_published_ge-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Das Hundertwasser Haus, Wien: &amp;Ouml;sterreichischer Bundesverlag/Compress Verlag, 1985, S. 318&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Schurian, Walter (Hg.): Hundertwasser &amp;ndash; Sch&amp;ouml;ne Wege, Gedanken &amp;uuml;ber Kunst und Leben. M&amp;uuml;nchen: Langen M&amp;uuml;ller Verlag, 2004, S. 278-279&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Der unbekannte Hundertwasser, KunstHausWien, M&amp;uuml;nchen: Prestel Verlag, 2008, S. 241&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', text_author-'Hundertwasser', text_orig_lang-'German', text_translator-'courtesy Prestel Verlag, Munich, 2008', text_source_en-'', text_source_ge-'', text_excerpt-'', text_origin-'']

%1###2009-12-23 10:38:24.8826###object###text###1.5.6.1###EINE NEUE FRIEDHOFSORDNUNG - WIEDERGEBURT ZU HAUSE
[text_contents_en-'&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onclick=&quot;return showBox(this);&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;/kb/edit?id=1.5.6.1&amp;amp;type=text&quot; class=&quot;thumb_image&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-133&quot;&gt; 133&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;As Utopian as it may sound, burying the dead at home, in the humus layers of the wooded terraces, is actually quite feasible.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-133&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;133 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For instance, when a building has 50 apartments and 500 metric tons of soil are on the roofs, these 500,000 kilos of soil would have no problem whatsoever absorbing the body of one dead person weighing 50 kilos each year, particularly since it turns into humus anyhow. It would be 1% of 1%, or one-thousandth, of the soil volume that would be reduced to one-hundred-thousandth within a year, from 50 kilos down to 5 kilos.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There would be no hygiene problem, as the process of decomposition would be aerobic, preventing the growth of dangerous anaerobic putrefactive bacteria. The interment should take place without a coffin, wrapped in a shroud, in a layer of earth at least 60 centimeters thick. &lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlS-134&quot;&gt; 134&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;A tree should be planted on top of the grave to guarantee that the deceased will live on symbolically as well as in reality.&lt;span style=&quot;cursor: pointer;&quot; class=&quot;hw-highlight&quot; id=&quot;hlE-134&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;134 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When people move out, there are two options. The remains may continue to be respected by the new occupants in the form of&amp;nbsp; a sacred site 2 by 1 meters, which the old occupants may visit, or the remains may safely be exhumed and interred elsewhere after about one year, when their weight is reduced to approximately 5 kilos.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Nowadays, people are buried in a way that is completely non-ecological and anti-religious, against all the laws of nature, of the universe, of the cycle of life, of reincarnation and resurrection: in coffins that are sealed airtight, 4 meters below ground, where they do not turn into humus, but rather rot as if stricken with the plague, far removed from the underground life of vegetation and tree roots.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To make resurrection impossible, the path to Creation is additionally blocked by concrete slabs, uniform tombstones, synthetic grass and artificial flowers. Any form of silent prayer at this site of the twice-murdered dead, who are denied reincarnation, is impossible. A dead person is entitled to reincarnation in the form of, for example, a tree that grows on top of him and through him. The result would be a sacred forest of living dead. A garden of the happy dead, which we have such a real need for. Reincarnation would even be demonstrable in chemical terms, as substances from the deceased are found in the tree on top of the grave. The gravesite of today becomes a site of worship and silent prayer, of joy and life regained.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;And not somewhere far away in a cemetery tended to by strangers, but right at home.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Family and friends don&rsquo;t die. The circle expands and the good spirits return.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;', id-253, typeOfObject-'TEXT', text_id-253, txt-'1.5.6.1', text_type-'', text_category-'', text_title_en-'NEW FUNERARY REGULATIONS - REINCARNATION AT HOME', text_title_ge-'EINE NEUE FRIEDHOFSORDNUNG - WIEDERGEBURT ZU HAUSE', text_keywords-'Friedhofsordnung, Wiedergeburt, reincarnation, funerary regulations,&lt;br /&gt;Bestattung', text_date-'1950-00-00', text_summary_en-'Hundertwasser first expressed the idea of an ecological burial - his wish to be buried naked and without a coffin under a tree - in 1979 in the book Ao Tea Roa &ndash; Insel der verlorenen W&uuml;nsche (Island of Lost Desire.&lt;br /&gt;In 1984 Hundertwasser obtained permission from the Minister of Health of New Zealand, Anthony G. Malcolm, to be buried on his property in the Bay of Islands. Hundertwasser died on February 19, 2000, in the Pacific Ocean on board the Queen Elizabeth 2, and he was buried on his land in New Zealand, in the &ldquo;Garden of the Happy Dead,&rdquo; in harmony with nature under a tulip tree, just as he had wanted.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;', text_summary_ge-'Hundertwasser formulierte den Gedanken einer &ouml;kologischen Bestattung, seinen Wunsch, nackt und ohne Sarg unter einem Baum begraben zu werden, zum ersten Mal 1979 in dem Buch Ao Tea Roa &ndash; Insel der verlorenen W&uuml;nsche: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Im Jahr 1984 hat Hundertwasser vom Gesundheitsminister Neuseelands, Anthony G. Malcolm, eine Genehmigung erwirkt, auf seinem Grundst&uuml;ck in der Bay of Islands bestattet  zu werden. &lt;br /&gt;Nach dem Tod Hundertwassers am Samstag, dem 19. Februar 2000, im Pazifischen Ozean an Bord der Queen Elizabeth 2, wurde er, wie von ihm gew&uuml;nscht, auf seinem Land in Neuseeland, im &bdquo;Garten der gl&uuml;cklichen Toten&ldquo;, in Harmonie mit der Natur unter einem Tulpenbaum begraben.&lt;br /&gt;', text_language-ge, text_contents-'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Utopisch klingt, aber durchf&uuml;hrbar ist die Totenbestattung im eigenen Haus, in den Humusschichten der bewaldeten Terrassen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Wenn das Haus z.B. 50 Wohngemeinschaften hat, auf den D&auml;chern 500 Tonnen Erdreich liegen, so k&ouml;nnen 500.000 kg Erde spielend pro Jahr einen 50 kg schweren Toten in sich aufnehmen, besonders weil er ja sowieso zu Humus wird. Das w&auml;ren 1 % von 1 % oder ein Zehntausendstel des Erdvolumens, das sich innerhalb eines Jahres auf ein Hunderttausendstel verringern w